INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c561a220-5da9-43b6-bb56-a67c453c7a4a', 'Halve the potatoes, unpeeled, and cut them into 1-inch wedges. In a large roasting pan heat 1/3 cup of the oil in the middle of a preheated 425°F. oven for 5 minutes, add the potatoes, tossing them to coat them with the oil, and roast them, stirring them every 10 minutes, for 30 minutes, or until they are tender. Let the potatoes cool in the pan. In a blender purée the garlic, the vinegar, the rosemary leaves, and salt to taste, with the motor running add the remaining 1/3 cup oil in a stream, and blend the dressing until it is emulsified. In a small bowl of ice and cold water let the onion soak for 5 minutes, drain it well, and pat it dry. In a kettle of boiling salted water boil the green beans for 5 minutes, or until they are crisp-tender, and drain them in a colander. Refresh the beans under cold water and pat them dry. In a very large bowl combine the potatoes, the onion, the green beans, and the olives, add the dressing, and toss the salad gently. Serve the salad, garnished with the rosemary sprigs, at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.91', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.638');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82f89a07-ce6f-4080-b6b1-bac8a0d8acc5', 'Cut off and discard 1 inch from stem ends of broccoli rabe. Cook broccoli rabe, uncovered, in 2 batches in a 6- to 8-quart pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 3 minutes, transferring with a slotted spoon to a large bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. Drain well in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.927', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.642');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c36ec68c-7789-48ae-a4a2-ee284da7bf57', 'Cook garlic in oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until garlic is golden, about 5 minutes. Add broccoli rabe and cook, tossing to coat with oil, until heated through, 3 to 5 minutes. Toss broccoli rabe with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.932', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.642');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a9734cb8-fd94-45f2-8f45-ee07017fabdb', 'Cut peel and white pith from grapefruits and oranges. Cut between membranes to release segments. Combine fruit in large shallow bowl. (Fruit can be segmented 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.937', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a73059b9-323c-4db0-abaa-a29841147b63', 'Place mint and sugar in processor. Using on/off turns, blend until mint is finely chopped, occasionally scraping down sides of bowl. Sprinkle mint sugar and pomegranate seeds over fruit; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.942', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a886d86-6a6b-49c2-b4cb-8c5dd7893985', 'Preheat oven to 475°F. Pierce eggplants with fork. Place on baking sheet. Roast until skins are blackened and eggplants are soft, turning occasionally, about 1 hour. Cut eggplants in half. Spoon flesh into strainer set over bowl; drain 15 minutes. Maintain oven temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.947', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2b6b6445-12bd-435c-b499-7cf1d30ff3f6', 'Meanwhile, brush pita rounds lightly with oil. Sprinkle pita rounds with salt and pepper. Cut each pita round into 6 wedges. Arrange wedges on clean baking sheet. Bake until crisp, about 4 minutes; cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.951', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d576ce11-85e8-4f7e-8bf3-7b82e7a8d488', 'Transfer drained eggplant to medium bowl. Mix in olives, garlic, vinegar, cumin and 1 tablespoon oil. Season spread with salt and pepper. Mound in small bowl. Serve with chips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.955', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.644');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d01bdbe4-c06a-445f-af3c-d2648eb12e70', 'Grind the parsley, sage, rosemary, and thyme into a fine powder. I use a coffee grinder for this.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.959', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.644');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4521fdbe-f299-4dfd-9db3-bb6539ddf874', 'In a mixing bowl, crumble the tofu and mix well with the spice mixture so that the herbs are well infused with the tofu. Let sit for the flavors to meld.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.645');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c1c0f05-fd50-493c-b630-9ffbb8ad21b7', 'In a microwave-safe bowl, mix together the TVP granules and the broth, cover tightly with plastic wrap, and microwave for 5 to 6 minutes. Alternatively, bring the broth to a boil, pour over the TVP, cover, and let sit for 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.645');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9cce7b2c-db97-442e-8357-0d3bf3069e3d', 'When cool enough to handle, add the TVP to the tofu mixture, then add the minced garlic, flaxseed mixture, sunflower seeds, pumpkin seeds, and salt and pepper to taste. Mix with your hands until all the ingredients are very well incorporated. The mixture will be nice and smooth, and should form lovely burgers. Shape into 6 patties. Refrigerate until ready to cook, although refrigeration isn''t necessary if you plan on cooking them right away.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.971', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.645');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6115442b-5ff7-46c6-9c88-024b6fd22418', 'I recommend baking these rather than frying. It just seems that this burger is too healthy to fry. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C, or gas mark 4) and line a baking sheet with parchment or a silicone baking mat. Bake, covered with a foil tent, for 15 minutes per side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.975', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('41c0dcc4-b3dc-446b-8a5e-9177db973307', 'With a knife cut cabbage into very thin slices and coarsely chop arugula. In a large bowl toss together all ingredients with salt and pepper to taste until greens are coated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.978', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('700ea93a-4c85-4f3d-be2b-34d0ede071b6', 'Trim root end of each onion and cut an X in it. Blanch in boiling water 1 minute, then drain in a colander. Cool slightly, then peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.983', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fda0580-70ff-43a4-89db-6e5d22b722a2', 'Bring juice, sugar, vinegar, and spices to a boil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Add onions and quinces and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender but not falling apart, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.987', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38910987-307b-48d1-bd08-9d9365328d73', 'Add cranberries and simmer until tender but not falling apart, 5 to 8 minutes. Discard cloves. Transfer fruit and onions to a bowl using a slotted spoon, then boil syrup, if necessary, until reduced to 1/2 cup. Pour syrup over compote and cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.991', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22f12d8d-8288-4e7d-9f59-f778de292d4b', 'In a heavy saucepan cook the onion and the garlic in the oil over moderate heat, stirring, until they are golden, add the tomatoes with the juice, the sugar , the red pepper flakes, and salt to taste, and simmer the sauce, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes, or until it is thickened. (The tomato sauce may be made 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.994', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8f649b4-6ce8-4733-be5c-42af852e7272', 'Using a long-handled fork char the peppers over an open flame, turning them, for 2 to 3 minutes, or until the skins are blackened. (Or broil the peppers on the rack of a broiler pan under a preheated broiler about 2 inches from the heat, turning them every 5 minutes, for 15 to 25 minutes, or until the skins are blistered and charred.) Transfer the peppers to a bowl and let them steam, covered, until they are cool enough to handle. Peel them starting at the blossom end, cut off the tops, and discard the seeds and ribs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:20.999', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c91e09fb-75aa-4658-bebf-7e5ec8785a10', 'In a kettle cook the chard stems in about 1/2 cup water, covered, over high heat for 5 minutes, add the chard leaves, and cook the chard, covered, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Drain the chard well and in a bowl toss it with the roasted pepper, the oil, and salt and pepper to taste. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the chard mixture, covered and chilled,, for making the cod cannelloni.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.003', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c06424d0-210a-4485-a4c9-01031258295b', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Oil 2 large rimmed baking sheets. Combine all ingredients in very large bowl; toss to coat. Divide vegetables between prepared baking sheets; spread evenly. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Roast vegetables until tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour 15 minutes. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Rewarm in 350°F oven 15 minutes.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.007', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7c3b019-096e-4292-afa5-504cb8411f94', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over high heat. Add ginger and garlic; sauté 20 seconds. Add bell pepper and mushrooms; sauté until pepper is crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add green onions and bok choy and sauté until just wilted, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.01', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('947cd9d3-272d-4a0a-a41f-91b4c237ca66', 'Cook beans in a 4- to 5-quart pot of boiling salted water , uncovered, until just tender, about 5 minutes. Drain beans in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.015', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2e8c0ac-a553-4b26-8cae-b3f2d0039c6e', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then fry shallots in 3 batches, stirring frequently, until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes per batch (watch carefully; shallots burn easily). Transfer shallots quickly as browned with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Shallots will become crisp as they cool.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.018', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4449645e-a873-49f2-8d37-34ef490f36a0', 'Discard all but about 1 tablespoon oil from skillet, then cook chile over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 2 minutes. Add beans and salt and toss with tongs until heated through. Remove from heat and add fried shallots and mint, tossing to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.022', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c0ac8e30-b095-433c-90d3-0b1e3c253750', 'Trim stalks and cut fennel bulb lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick strips, discarding core. Cut carrots into 1/4-inch-thick sticks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.025', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b193ca6-09ba-4616-881e-804992d5a0d8', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté fennel and carrots with salt to taste, stirring occasionally, until they begin to brown. Add wine, water, and sugar and simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Boil, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until liquid is evaporated and vegetables are tender. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('58d07fd9-b6d8-4482-ac4d-4bdc414f1abb', 'Mix tomatoes and sugar in a large wide shallow pot. Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, occasionally stirring gently. Boil, stirring often, for 15 minutes. Stir in salt, pepper, and paprika. Cook until thickened and reduced to 2 cups, about 10 minutes. Ladle into a clean, hot 1-pint jar. Wipe rim, seal, and process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.035', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b32a0f7d-f77f-4b68-a9d5-665e209bbff7', 'Cook linguine in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain, reserving 1 cup pasta cooking liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.04', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd8f79e5-8c44-44b4-ad47-312e2133641b', 'Meanwhile, heat extra-virgin olive oil in large skillet over medium heat. Add garlic; sauté until golden, about 1 minute. Add grated lemon peel to skillet and cook 20 seconds. Remove skillet from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('542f1e7e-a1db-4d9a-b0a7-23d8bae948c0', 'Add linguine to skillet with garlic and lemon peel. Return skillet to medium heat; mix in parsley. Add 1/2 cup pasta cooking liquid and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Toss until heated through, adding more cooking liquid to moisten if dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.049', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.651');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bb51e211-7ed0-40b1-b735-97276e777d5f', 'Mash 1/2 cup blackberries with fork in small bowl. Puree remaining berries in processor. Pour puree into strainer set over bowl, pressing on solids to extract as much liquid as possible. Discard solids in strainer. Whisk preserves and mashed berries into puree. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.053', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.651');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f68d20fb-d6a8-48b6-a094-480fa446803f', 'In a bowl combine the frisée, the radicchio, and the pears. In a small bowl whisk together the vinegar, the mustard, and salt and pepper to taste, add the oils in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified. Toss the salad with the dressing, divide it among 8 salad plates, and sprinkle each serving with some of the hazelnuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.057', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.651');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b4b7867-3067-447a-849e-90b101673e0e', 'Toast the hazelnuts in one layer in a baking pan in a preheated 350°F. oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until they are colored lightly and the skins blister. Wrap the nuts in a kitchen towel and let them steam for 1 minute. Rub the nuts in the towel to remove the skins and let them cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.064', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.652');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b06a7228-fb92-4176-a0c6-72d7143b43dc', '1. Heat a wok over high heat for 30 seconds. Add the peanut oil and onions, and cook for 7 minutes, stirring and turning the onions often to prevent burning and to ensure even browning. Reduce the heat to medium and cook, stirring often, for 15 minutes more, or until the onions turn light brown.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.069', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.652');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('022eb4a4-8318-4cb3-add7-0896e6e6ec36', 'Turn off the heat. Strain the oil through a fine-mesh strainer into a heatproof bowl, pressing the onions with a ladle as they drain. Allow the oil to cool to room temperature. Set the fried onions aside to cool. Pour the cooled oil into a sterilized glass jar and close tightly. The oil will keep at room temperature for 1 week or refrigerated for up to 3 months. Transfer the fried onions to a plastic container, cover, and refrigerate. They will keep for up to 3 months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.073', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.652');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c097f3dd-70bc-4640-9000-d176f11153ae', 'Divide the berries equally among four bowls. Place the remaining ingredients in another bowl, and toss to combine. Sprinkle the mixture over each of the four bowls and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.077', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.653');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7422e13d-3f8b-45a7-89dd-95b6d41eb39d', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Brush eggplant on all sides with oil, season with salt and pepper, and roast, cut side down, on a rimmed baking sheet until lightly browned and softened, 30–40 minutes. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.083', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.653');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('66e5ae3c-33e6-4b80-a158-9221af1ec56a', 'Meanwhile, heat a dry medium cast-iron skillet over high. Cook broccoli florets, tossing occasionally, until surfaces are blackened, 10–15 minutes. Transfer to a large plate; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.087', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.653');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ecd8997-5913-4238-9412-15e93f986755', 'Toss chiles, sugar, and 1 tsp. salt in a small bowl. Let sit until juices release, 12–15 minutes. Add white wine vinegar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.092', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.654');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee045887-c4d8-4415-a740-ae313adcbf61', 'Meanwhile, toast coriander seeds in a dry small skillet, tossing often, until fragrant, about 4 minutes; let cool. Finely grind in a spice mill or with a mortar and pestle. Transfer to a small bowl and whisk in rice vinegar, 1/4 cup oil, 1 Tbsp. lemon juice, and 2 Tbsp. water; season vinaigrette with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.654');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c5e642c5-5440-4531-b32e-a3f8acd2d812', 'Scoop eggplant flesh into a food processor; discard skin. Add malt vinegar, agave, tahini, and remaining 2 Tbsp. lemon juice. With motor running, stream in remaining 1/4 cup oil; process until smooth. Season eggplant purée with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.102', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.654');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c4a49edc-7706-4926-8956-043a63677e20', 'Toss charred broccoli, broccoli stems, and vinaigrette in a large bowl. Serve over eggplant purée topped with cashews, cilantro, and drained chiles.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.106', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.655');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d00f6f97-7b12-4239-b782-e59ba18e97bc', 'Preheat the oven to 400°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.111', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.655');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38209b43-27a8-42ee-80dd-77be4cb309ca', 'Pierce the softest eye of the coconut with a metal skewer or small screwdriver and drain any liquid into a small bowl to sample—you should have about 1/2 cup liquid. (If the liquid tastes sweet, the coconut is fresh; if it tastes oily, the coconut is rancid and should be discarded.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.116', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.656');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a73c9267-1739-4eda-b716-38715720ee01', 'Bake the coconut for 15 minutes then transfer to a folded towel on a work surface. Using the back of a knife or a cleaver, crack the shell open. Break the shell into large pieces and use a strong knife to carefully remove the flesh from the shell. Using a vegetable peeler, remove the brown skin then shave the coconut into thin strips—you should have about 4 cups shaved coconut. Reserve 2 cups for the ambrosia salad; wrap and freeze the remainder for another use. DO AHEAD: Coconut shavings can stored, in an airtight container, in the refrigerator up to 1 week or frozen up to 3 months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.656');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('023dea5a-5a76-4117-8471-061a10051813', 'Using a serrated knife, cut the peel off the grapefruits and oranges. Cut the fruit crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick rounds then cut the rounds into bite-size pieces. Transfer to a large bowl; add the pineapple, kumquats, pomegranate seeds, 2 cups coconut shavings, 1/2 cup coconut juice, and the apple juice, and toss gently to combine. Serve at room temperature or chilled. DO AHEAD: Florida Ambrosia Salad can be prepared ahead and stored, covered, in the refrigerator up to 8 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.657');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('578b7c1c-2d28-4431-90ef-c6b4e74c75b4', 'Preheat oven to 500°F. Spray large baking sheet with vegetable oil spray. Toss sweet potatoes with oil in large bowl. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Spread sweet potatoes in single layer on prepared baking sheet. Bake until sweet potatoes are tender and golden brown, turning occasionally, about 30 minutes. Transfer sweet potatoes to platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.132', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.657');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f65074d9-5192-4e91-b97e-c180fb368d7d', 'Mix parsley, thyme and garlic in small bowl. Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.136', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.657');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('775ab8e4-136f-47e4-97c2-4059abc0997a', 'Cut peel and pith from oranges. Working over medium bowl, cut between membranes to release segments. Add cilantro, red onion, olive oil, red wine vinegar, and habanero chile; toss well. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.173', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.658');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9331aa01-cc0c-4be9-bc0f-c43b9427796b', 'Drain salsa just before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.176', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.658');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('286e3714-aba2-47aa-b76b-eb3a9091da67', 'Rub outsides of peppers with oil, then arrange peppers, cut sides down, in 1 layer in a large shallow baking pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.181', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.659');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('edc46f08-1e13-45c8-9b2a-a45b21a5f28d', 'Preheat broiler', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.185', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.66');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f8bfc63-30d4-4935-8def-3a7d520a808e', 'Broil peppers 4 to 5 inches from heat until well charred (peppers will not char evenly, especially at ends), 20 to 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.189', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.66');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aac3cd20-97de-468b-adaa-bd1e12dabd2a', 'Transfer to a bowl and cover tightly with plastic wrap, then let stand about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.193', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.661');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('90a5e110-c957-43ff-a81d-6c83bbc86f60', 'When peppers are cool enough to handle, peel off skin. Chop peppers and reserve 1/4 cup for saffron rouille (if making) or for another use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.196', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.661');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('916dde9d-8b03-44b7-b8f4-78ee82a79664', 'Bring water to boil in small saucepan. Stir in salt and rice; bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 17 minutes. Remove pan from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.201', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.661');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b61112ab-c51c-4780-93c9-dafb690a090c', 'With a vegetable peeler or paring knife peel squash. Cut squash and onion into 1/4-inch dice and cut broccoli rabe into 1/2-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.205', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.662');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be1471f7-d6d0-4caa-a748-36dd27a71db6', 'In a 12-inch nonstick skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and add vegetables and salt to taste, stirring to coat with oil. Add water and cook vegetables, covered, over moderate heat 5 minutes, or until tender. Remove lid and cook vegetables over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until liquid is evaporated and vegetables begin to brown, about 3 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.209', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.662');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09918d1a-d05e-467a-89f9-f70670616142', 'Pur&eaacute;e tomatillos, half of tomatoes, and half of onion with chile, garlic, vinegar, and 1 1/4 teaspoons salt in a blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.214', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.663');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ccc1ad73-0c88-49f5-82b6-7063b744e8ba', 'Force through a medium-mesh sieve into a bowl, discarding solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.217', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.663');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a97f88e0-e13e-433b-93f4-b43fab9a35aa', 'Stir in remaining tomatoes and onion, water, oil, and cilantro. Chill until cold, at least 1 hour and up to 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.221', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.664');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6324e7f5-a226-4f10-8441-40e4338b35fa', 'Pass first 5 ingredients through a juicer. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl. Stir in lemon juice. Pour into glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.224', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.664');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42bcc702-206c-4f69-b761-7eafc70a2582', 'Place rice in strainer. Rinse under cold water until water runs clear. Drain well. Transfer rice to heavy medium saucepan. Add 3 cups cold water. Stir in ginger. Bring water to boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook until rice is tender, about 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Sprinkle peas over rice (do not stir into rice). Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir peas into rice. Season rice lightly with salt. Transfer to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.228', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.664');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eeae1754-a0f4-45c2-98d9-9f1e6bed94ab', 'In the bowl of a food processor, combine the mangoes, orange zest, sugar, lime juice, and 1 cup water. Process until the mixture is smooth. Pour through a fine-mesh sieve set over a large bowl then press gently on and discard any solids (there will be about 3 cups syrup). Transfer to a freezer-safe dish, cover with plastic, and freeze until the mixture is firm 2 inches in from the sides, about 2 hours. Scrape into a food processor and process until the mixture is slushy. Repeat the freezing and processing 2 more times, then freeze for at least 1 hour before serving. DO AHEAD: The ice can be made ahead and stored in the freezer, well wrapped, up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.232', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.665');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1bdadd54-51b8-4f27-b895-19e5ccf00aca', 'Place onion slices in a medium bowl. Pour vinegar and 1/2 cup warm water over onion. Stir in sugar and season with salt; let stand until slightly pickled, about 30 minutes. Drain. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Let cool slightly. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.236', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.665');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4abd9750-aed2-4666-a03a-92ce77d75cf6', 'Cut the cauliflower into medium florets. Put into a large pan, cover with cold water, add some salt, and bring up to a rolling boil. This will partly cook the cauliflower. Take off the heat right away, drain well, and keep warm in the pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.239', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.666');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0cc50e44-881e-4dc4-872c-58f14d49e1bd', 'Heat the oil in a second large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onions, garlic, and ginger and sauté for about 10 minutes, stirring often.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.243', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.666');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22b9f7ec-2ffd-4073-9c4b-86a431f4ba92', 'Add the ground coriander, cumin, chile flakes, star anise, and some salt and pepper and cook for a further 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.247', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.666');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2730636b-afea-4619-a329-aa3a23c166a4', 'Add the tomatoes with their juice and the chickpeas. Stir well, then add the parcooked cauliflower. Pour in enough cold water to almost but not quite cover everything (1/3 to 3/4 cup/100 to 200ml) and bring to a simmer. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until the cauliflower is tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.25', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.667');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7825f2dc-e305-446a-bec7-e2e29974e934', 'Stir in the garam masala and half of the chopped cilantro, then check the seasoning. Serve scattered with the remaining cilantro and accompanied by rice, flat breads, or naan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.253', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.667');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e090ff04-5337-4db7-b194-ed5018d035b8', 'Combine 1 cup water, Port, sugar, cinnamon sticks, and ginger in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to boil over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add fruit. Reduce heat to medium. Simmer until fruit is tender and syrup thickens slightly, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Transfer compote to bowl. Cover and chill at least 4 hours and up to 1 day.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.256', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.667');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6c7017b-5990-48df-a97a-c06787711153', 'Combine peppers, chiles, sugar, red pepper flakes and salt in a heavy wide pot over medium heat and bring to a simmer, stirring to dissolve sugar. Stir in pectin and lemon juice. Reduce heat and simmer gently for 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.259', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.668');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e7871dd-da16-46ce-a848-c880cdcef84e', 'Stir in cranberries and simmer gently until they burst and juices thicken, about 10 minutes longer. Transfer jelly to a jar, let cool, and cover. Will keep for up to 3 weeks in the refrigerator.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.263', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.668');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dae1e6e7-5de4-48b8-81b7-0c8dc4211d42', 'Boil vinegar in heavy small saucepan over medium heat until reduced by half, about 3 minutes. Pour vinegar into large bowl. Whisk in oil, mustard, marjoram and garlic. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.265', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.668');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79599b16-c839-4476-84bb-fc0a439c0c60', 'Cook asparagus in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again. Add asparagus and bell pepper to dressing; toss to blend well. Sprinkle with pecans and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.268', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.669');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4349cc8f-751b-4314-abd4-da735ccfddd5', 'Combine the warm water and saffron in a small bowl. Heat the olive oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add the shallot and sauté until translucent, about 3 minutes. Add the rice and saffron and cook, stirring constantly, until the rice is evenly coated with the oil. Stir in the water, salt, and ginger. Increase the heat, cover, and bring to a boil. Decrease the heat to low and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, until the water is absorbed. Check after 20 minutes; if there are steam holes on the top, it''s ready. Remove ginger. Add the lemon juice, lemon zest, and parsley and fluff with a fork to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.272', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.669');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4a1ee46-8ea4-4f15-b6e2-26eb88b0faf1', 'Squeeze 2 lemon halves into a large bowl of cold water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.669');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b03a756-0701-4bf0-bd61-74c919fddea2', 'Cut off top inch of 1 artichoke and bend back outer leaves until they snap off close to base (keep stem attached). Discard several more layers of leaves in same manner until you reach pale yellow leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.277', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.67');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('06adad63-f8e1-44ab-a6e8-2ff84e4045b8', 'Cut off remaining leaves 1/2 inch above top of artichoke base using a sharp knife, then pull out purple leaves and scoop out fuzzy choke with a melon-ball cutter. Trim dark green fibrous parts from base and side of artichoke.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.28', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.67');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91d79918-0a8b-498d-b8d0-48c11257d884', 'Trim a thin slice from stem end, then trim side of stem down to pale green inner core. Rub cut surfaces with lemon halves, then put artichokes in lemon water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.283', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.671');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7aaf22de-3ffd-482b-833a-1e82cacb8b38', 'Trim remaining artichokes in same manner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.285', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.671');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('72a5027d-8e00-4485-8589-4ac54ec3ebd0', 'Combine lemon juice, water (3 cups), oil, 3 tablespoons mint, garlic, and 1 teaspoon salt in a 4-to 5-quarts heavy pot (wide enough to hold artichokes in 1 layer with stems pointing upward) and bring to a simmer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.288', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.672');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fb9b5c2-d39c-4190-b28b-c0cec928bd8e', 'Stand artichokes, stem ends up, in liquid and cover with a round of parchment paper. Simmer, covered with parchment and lid, until just tender when artichoke bottom is pierced with a knife, 25 to 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.291', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.674');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02e92e54-4b7a-4bc3-8fb5-295d262677e4', 'Transfer artichokes with a slotted spoon to a shallow serving dish. Boil cooking liquid until reduced to about 1/2 cup, about 20 minutes. During last 2 minutes of boiling, whisk liquid until it emulsifies. Pour over artichokes and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.293', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.674');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9f7a33f3-d594-4c95-ab9c-07e99faa38ce', 'Yarden Galilee
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('20b4cf23-dd9b-4a27-b226-c1091ad279b0', 'Simmer wine, water, sugar, and ginger, stirring occasionally, until reduced to about 3/4 cup, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.298', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.676');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78806182-04e8-41da-9908-e856775aa9dd', 'While syrup is simmering, slice peaches and toss with lemon juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.677');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('101c2330-ce46-4591-9d9a-4fddeaa0d904', 'Pour hot syrup through a fine sieve onto peaches, then stir.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.304', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.677');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d965f91c-b3fe-45ca-b615-d9237df3c959', 'Let stand 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.307', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.678');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('41ddc78e-d29f-4b17-92db-48510922b501', 'Quarter cabbage lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 2-to 3-inch pieces. Toss with 3 tablespoons salt in a large bowl and let stand, tossing occasionally, 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.679');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ded3be4a-5c63-4385-a4f6-c276e5c2a529', 'Rinse cabbage well, then drain. Squeeze out excess water with your hands and transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.313', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.681');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55351842-4238-4751-bfb4-d73330777114', 'Purée garlic and ginger with fish sauce and vinegar in a blender until smooth, then pour over cabbage. Add scallions, sesame seeds, and red-pepper flakes and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.316', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d41ee7e-4784-4515-adbd-77962e8b529c', 'Peel pear, then grate on large holes of a box grater (avoid core and seeds). Add to cabbage mixture and toss well. Marinate at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.318', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f8bdc2d-46db-4fb0-b7b9-a34fa69b0c5c', 'Falafel can be made 5 days ahead; store in an airtight container and chill, or freeze up to 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.413', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.7');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb836bdc-67a5-4522-a367-ab8c517fbbf6', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Combine leeks, turnips, and sweet potatoes in large roasting pan. Top with bay leaves and drizzle with 2 tablespoons oil. Sprinkle with thyme, salt, and freshly ground black pepper, and toss to coat thoroughly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.321', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.683');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea3f56c3-6c91-4ee8-9724-a2bb169a8071', 'Place garlic, cut side up, on a piece of foil and drizzle with remaining tablespoon oil. Wrap garlic in foil and place on oven shelf. Place roasting pan next to garlic in oven, and roast until vegetables are just tender and slightly browned, about 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.324', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.684');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5e5e4b8-12f9-47eb-9550-a5aa79cc25e4', 'Unwrap garlic. Squeeze cloves from their skins, slice cloves, and toss with roasted vegetables. Serve with Slow-Braised Lamb Shanks with Guajillo-Pineapple Sauce .', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.328', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.684');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('93cf91a9-be29-4ef2-9182-c8ebae8f4fa2', 'In a blender purée all ingredients except bread until smooth. In a small heavy saucepan simmer sofrito, stirring, 3 minutes and season with salt and pepper. Sofrito may be made 2 days ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.685');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('456c3143-0065-4c1c-9ece-db08f0a32344', 'Prepare grill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.335', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.686');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c040be8-a6b7-48b7-8d9c-e26a2d84e1f3', 'If desired halve bread slices. Spread some sofrito on 1 side of each bread slice (reserving any remaining sofrito for another use) and grill, sofrito side down, on an oiled rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals until golden brown, about 2 minutes. (Alternatively, bread may be grilled in a hot well-seasoned ridged grill pan over moderately high heat.) Transfer sofrito bread as grilled with tongs to a bread basket.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.339', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.687');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d98f6c85-474c-4dd5-a13c-4bb39fecfa2a', 'Place garlic and rosemary in a food processor and finely chop. Add lemon juice and blend. Add beans and artichoke hearts and puree until smooth, stopping the machine a few times to scrape down the sides. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with carrot and celery sticks and/or pita bread (not potato chips!). Dip will keep refrigerated for 2 to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.342', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.687');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ebfd7f65-7ba5-4ee3-9780-c6df47fa5ba3', 'Trim roots and ends from spring onions or scallions, leaving about 8 inches of stalk. Onions or scallions may be prepared up to this point 6 hours ahead and chilled in a sealed plastic bag.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.346', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.689');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2338c972-a1e0-49af-bd3d-f271ce6c32a3', 'In a sealable plastic bag or large bowl toss onions or scallions with oil and salt. Grill onions or scallions on a rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals, turning them with tongs 3 or 4 times, 5 to 7 minutes, or until softened and lightly charred. (Alternatively, onions or scallions may be broiled on rack of a broiler pan about 3 inches from heat, turning them with tongs 2 or 3 times, 10 to 12 minutes.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.349', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.689');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a458911-dd7f-46e3-844d-81c1fc30d761', 'Transfer onions or scallions to a platter and squeeze 4 lime wedges over them. Garnish platter with additional lime wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.353', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.69');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35ed827c-9154-4f3a-951e-e1726180f7b0', 'Stir together all ingredients in a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.357', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.69');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3bed60a1-2a46-4540-bba0-f10cf25f1b01', 'In a large, heavy nonstick dry skillet, cook the pineapple slices (in batches, if necessary) over low heat until caramelized, 6 to 7 minutes per side. (It is important to cook the pineapples on low heat so the sugars in the fruit develop deep flavor, without any burning.) Remove from the heat and cut the pineapple into 1/8-inch dice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.36', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.691');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ef3550c-d169-4a03-b6ba-d46e240d0990', 'In a large bowl, mix the diced pineapple with the chile, bell pepper, cilantro, and lime juice. Serve immediately for the freshest flavor, but you can make this salsa 1 to 3 hours ahead.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.364', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.691');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('678bfc58-833b-4072-95b3-328edd9e2791', 'In a small, dry frying pan over low heat, toast the cumin, stirring often, until aromatic, about 30 seconds. Pour onto a plate and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.368', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.692');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('768ae96a-c9a4-49df-9bc6-d345bd238650', 'In a small container with a tight-fitting lid, stir together the cumin, paprika, sugar, coriander, cayenne pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper. Cover and shake vigorously to mix. Use right away, or store in a cool, dark place for up to 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.372', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.693');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff98a18e-0a0f-4bd9-b6ed-8deefe5605fd', 'Stir first 3 ingredients in medium bowl until sugar dissolves. Fold in berries and apricots. Let stand up to 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.693');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('99e4080a-36b2-4be9-9131-1791de7c6874', 'Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray. Stir sugar and water in heavy small saucepan over medium-low heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat; boil until deep amber color, occasionally brushing down sides of pan with wet pastry brush and swirling pan, about 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.378', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.694');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e84dbc69-f60d-4156-80b1-81b805ddf1e8', 'Stir nuts into caramel and immediately pour onto prepared sheet. Working quickly and carefully (caramel is very hot and hardens fast), press tip of small knife into edges of caramel and gently stretch in all directions to form very thin sheet, approximately 12 by 10 inches. Cool brittle completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.382', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.694');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c62abf9f-c218-41c0-a3f1-69bce05e336d', 'Break brittle into irregular pieces. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.386', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.695');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f8372dc-a3eb-43d6-b07e-67c355aaa954', 'Whisk together vinegar, sugar, and salt in a large bowl until sugar and salt are dissolved, then whisk in oil, caraway, and pepper. Add cabbages and toss well. Let stand, uncovered, at room temperature, tossing occasionally, until wilted, about 1 hour. Core apple, then cut into thin matchsticks and toss with slaw.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.389', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.695');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f2eecee4-61bb-4829-bff1-96602f5bc247', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Thinly slice one-third of onion. Toss slices with 1/4 cup orange juice, 1/4 cup vinegar, and 1/2 tsp. salt in a small bowl; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.696');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2cf8fec4-312a-4358-b178-b586ae64f595', 'Pulse chickpeas, garlic, coriander, cumin, 3/4 cup parsley, 1 tsp. salt, and remanining onion in a food processor until very coarsely chopped, about 30 seconds. Add flour and baking powder and pulse a few more times to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.396', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.696');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef296f9e-ad74-4154-83c5-f7416b4a4c1e', 'Lightly oil a rimmed baking sheet. Using a 1/4-cup measuring cup, portion out 12 ping pong-sized balls and place on sheet, spacing 1" apart. Gently press down on tops to flatten slightly. Brush tops with 1 Tbsp. oil. Bake falafel, turning balls halfway through, until golden brown and crispy, 20–25 minutes. Wrap pitas in foil and warm in oven during last 5 minutes of baking.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.4', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.697');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9271a2c-eef9-40ca-963e-1be44fdfe867', 'Meanwhile, whisk 1/4 cup oil and remaining 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon orange juice, 2 tsp. vinegar, and 1 tsp. salt in a medium bowl. Whisk in tahini and 1/4 cup water until a smooth sauce forms.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.403', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.698');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b8fc471-d55a-42c4-89d7-e84610f0bd9e', 'Whisk 2 Tbsp. pickling liquid from reserved onions with remaining 3 Tbsp. oil in another medium bowl. Add cabbage, tomatoes, and onions and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.406', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.699');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2923e9f4-5b48-49f6-ba2c-1bd49c8e98e4', 'Cut each pita into 4 pieces. Drizzle falafel with 2 Tbsp. tahini sauce and top with remaining 1/4 cup parsley. Serve with pita, hummus, salad, and remaining tahini sauce alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.409', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.699');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f100cfe-cc11-4adc-a8b3-5318e786994f', 'Rinse the spinach well and remove the stems. Place in a large sauté pan with only the rinsing water clinging to the leaves. Cook over medium heat, turning as needed until wilted, just a few minutes. Drain well and set aside. Add the olive oil to the now-empty pan and place over medium heat. Add the onions and sauté until tender, about 8 minutes. Add the spinach, raisins, and pine nuts and sauté briefly to warm through. Season with salt and pepper and serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.416', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.701');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8f260eb-5d51-43fb-88ea-59124495bb05', 'In a dry heavy saucepan (about 3-quart capacity) cook sugar over moderate heat, stirring with a fork until melted and then swirling pan, until sugar is a golden caramel. Remove pan from heat and carefully add 3 cups water down side of pan (it will bubble up and steam). Return pan to heat and simmer, stirring, until caramel is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.42', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.701');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d56921b-6255-493a-b28f-3684a8e23648', 'Add apricots and simmer, covered, until soft, about 10 minutes. Cool mixture 10 minutes and in a blender purée with remaining 1 cup water and vanilla until very smooth. Sauce may be made 3 days ahead and chilled, covered. Reheat sauce to warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.423', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.702');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe334104-b177-4841-8ca6-fb1dfa908282', 'Combine the apricots, raisins and vinegar in a 5-litre (5-quart) saucepan. Soak overnight to plump the fruit. Alternatively, if time is tight, simply cover, bring to the boil and set aside for about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.427', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.703');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0075b0bf-4a94-449e-a2a2-bf4e03bad5b4', 'Add the remaining ingredients, and cook uncovered over medium heat, stirring occasionally at first, then constantly towards the end of the cooking time, until the chutney has reduced to about one-third, and is beautifully thick. It should take 1 1/2-2 hours. To know when it is ready for bottling, test the consistency by putting a little in the freezer to cool. Pour into hot, sterilized jars, seal and store in a cool, dark cupboard.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.431', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.705');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('75ffced9-cb77-463b-b01a-041ea26fe6df', 'Heat olive oil in small saucepan over low heat. Add garlic and simmer until garlic is very tender, about 10 minutes (do not brown). Remove from heat; stir in dried crushed red pepper. (Melted garlic can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewarm before continuing.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.434', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.705');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15c3541f-f440-4edf-8f82-47086dfcff44', 'Cook broccoli rabe in very large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 5 minutes. Drain well. Toss with melted garlic and oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.437', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.706');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc401af7-35f9-485e-bb0a-1777afd984c1', 'Pour eau-de-vie into a Champagne flute and swirl around to coat inside of glass. Top off with Champagne.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.44', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.707');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94092e31-a5ae-4033-8c62-276fefd83dce', 'Set aside 2 tablespoons chickpeas for serving. Process tahini, lemon juice, red pepper paste, pomegranate molasses (if using), and remaining chickpeas in a food processor, adding water as needed, until hummus is very smooth; season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.443', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.708');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81333cdf-083c-4a6a-8290-51573993d21f', 'Serve hummus drizzled with oil and topped with Aleppo pepper and reserved chickpeas, with pita bread alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.447', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.71');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cdd04b7-84fe-40ba-98ab-58af8644d039', '1. In the wok, heat the oil and sauté the onion and garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.451', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.711');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c0d9f3e5-452f-49a9-bdf1-104721c330c3', '2. Add the sweet potatoes, beans, red peppers, soy chunks, tomatoes and all the spices except for the saffron and cook at a high temperature for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.454', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.712');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36aa6898-625b-4788-a2d4-21e670b51e91', '3. Add the vegetable stock, prunes, apricots and the liquid from the artichokes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.458', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.712');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c437ec59-9319-4bbb-bae5-bb7e2fde032a', '4. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.462', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.714');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c75eee7-436d-4966-ba41-7b824fb4ab72', '5. Stir in the artichokes, olives, brown sugar and saffron. Simmer for another 5 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.465', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.714');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4631afe-69c4-43c8-bdee-7fba191b5517', '6. While you are waiting, toast the almonds in a dry frying pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.468', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.715');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cd2f036f-b642-442e-bc71-44a9ced8d938', '7. In a separate stainless steel bowl, pour 3 1/2 cups (875 ml) of boiling water over the couscous and let it stand for 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.472', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.716');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7aae6289-7b89-4431-a8c3-c90296b73454', '8. Fluff the couscous with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.476', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.716');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('033974ec-a7db-4a2f-bb95-65881d43892b', '9. Serve the stew over the couscous and garnish with toasted almonds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.479', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.717');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6dc8907c-e2e6-4bda-bf52-ab940791c72a', 'Preheat oven to 400°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.482', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.718');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49d1d34c-3ade-4044-b8f9-c6be60d0773f', 'Brush 2 large baking sheets well with some oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.718');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f79d4dfb-2fb2-468c-8079-713a0481da83', 'Peel potatoes and with a mandoline or other hand-held slicing device cut length-wise into 1/8-inch-thick slices. Immediately arrange potatoes in one layer on baking sheets and brush with remaining oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.493', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.721');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2560c46c-774e-419d-ba56-0fd99584ee6f', 'Bake potatoes in middle of oven until golden, 12 to 15 minutes, and while still warm transfer with a metal spatula to racks. Sprinkle with thyme and salt to taste. Chips may be made 3 days ahead. Cool chips completely and keep in an airtight container at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.722');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ab1fb9ff-17ca-4bd2-8cde-02b6cf72f095', 'Whisk together flour and beer in a bowl until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.501', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.722');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd76053b-b0f4-4238-90c5-19a95a6300e1', 'Heat 2 inches oil in a 4-quart heavy pot over moderate heat until it registers 365°F on thermometer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.613', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.722');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95a3c623-4413-432d-a68c-d7529369b219', 'Working in batches of about 15, toss sugar snaps in batter until coated. Lift sugar snaps out of batter 1 at a time, letting excess batter drip off, and transfer to oil. Fry sugar snaps, turning with a slotted spoon, until golden, about 1 1/2 minutes. Transfer with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Return oil to 365°F between batches.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.723');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a845a2f8-743a-417c-a396-928def4a1d74', 'Serve sugar snaps warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.67', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.724');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3cae74a3-ef1a-4728-803b-302f39343249', 'Preheat oven to 425°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.677', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.726');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cb6af16-d421-49a3-acb0-f6af8a217e9e', 'Halve, peel, and seed squash and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Finely chop shallot and in a shallow baking pan toss with squash, oil, curry powder, and salt and pepper to taste until combined well. Bake squash mixture in middle of oven until almost tender, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.685', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.726');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('267d29c9-4343-4d48-aff0-87098302b535', 'Chop walnuts and sprinkle over squash. Bake squash mixture 10 minutes more, or until walnuts are lightly toasted and squash is tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.693', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.73');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f071f9be-46a6-4ed4-8bf8-b911d94b777f', 'While squash is baking, in a saucepan of boiling water cook lentils until just tender but not falling apart, about 20 minutes. Drain lentils in a sieve and transfer to a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.702', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.731');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8251c31-141c-49c6-8b37-9932bd0e6c0e', 'To lentils add squash mixture, cilantro, lime juice, and salt and pepper to taste and toss until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.709', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.731');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1ac4143e-2180-4e42-bdab-c0b98e30df79', 'tranfer to serving bowl and top with red onion, thinly sliced.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.312', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.817');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70f4a211-9375-4570-a0f8-d8c33c5cde65', 'Combine 2 small dried chiles, 1 seeded thinly sliced jalapeño, 1/4 thinly sliced medium red onion, 2 cups corn kernels (from about 2 ears), 1/4 cup fresh cilantro leaves with tender stems, 1/4 cup fresh lime juice, and 1/4 teaspoon coarsely ground black pepper in a heatproof 1-quart jar. Bring 1/2 cup white wine vinegar or apple cider vinegar, 2 teaspoons kosher salt, 1 teaspoon sugar, and 3/4 cup water to a boil; pour over corn. (Add water to cover, if needed.) Seal jar. Let cool; chill. Will keep up to 1 month unopened.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.716', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.732');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bfe19d33-3cd0-45bf-aded-bc3c9a8e75d1', 'Toss together arugula, lemon juice, and salt in a bowl. Drizzle with oil and toss to combine well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.723', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.733');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d5d38ad-4357-4de4-a3ce-1cccf1381c4a', 'Stir all ingredients together and season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.733');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3c93ad5-381c-41a1-997d-c501cd6fa6e8', 'Bring all ingredients to boil in heavy medium saucepan, stirring often. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until most of cranberries burst, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Transfer sauce to medium bowl. Cool, cover, and refrigerate cranberry sauce. DO AHEAD Basic Cranberry Sauce can be prepared 1 week ahead. Keep refrigerated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.733', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.734');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0112ec59-a903-4dfb-bb24-3c07bcaa92dd', 'Prick kumquats 2 or 3 times with a sharp fork. Cover kumquats generously with cold water in a heavy medium saucepan and bring to a boil. Drain and rinse with cold water, then repeat 2 more times (to remove bitterness).', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.737', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.734');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('480053b5-abaa-48da-bcce-a3ca2a06a1e0', 'Bring kumquats, sugar, and water (3/4 cup) to a boil in rinsed saucepan (liquid will not cover kumquats) over high heat, stirring until sugar has dissolved, then reduce heat and gently simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Remove from heat and cool kumquats in syrup, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.739', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.736');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5d6f791-1097-45d3-838d-0f60a383f8b7', 'Transfer kumquats with a slotted spoon to a bowl, reserving syrup in saucepan. Add cranberries and 1/4 teaspoon salt to syrup and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until berries burst, 8 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.742', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.737');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8fefcf12-f173-4e88-ac78-12faf0a1c74c', 'While cranberries cook, quarter kumquats lengthwise, discarding any seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.745', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.737');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0413d5e8-19a0-401d-b633-7db128496b47', 'Stir kumquats into cranberry mixture and transfer to a bowl. Cool completely, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.747', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.738');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a715466-1f80-444c-87b2-f7def0a08407', 'Cook onion in oil in a 3 1/2- to 4-quart heavy pot over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until edges are golden, about 6 minutes. Add ginger and garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add cumin, coriander, turmeric, salt, and chile and cook, stirring, 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.75', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.739');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c49e1aae-09cb-4850-acd6-56fc91215218', 'Stir in water, lentils, and coconut milk, then simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Stir in zucchini and simmer, covered, until lentils and zucchini are tender, about 15 minutes. Season with salt and serve with cilantro sprigs scattered on top.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.753', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.74');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ca39871-bd8d-41d7-bc96-0c1ab2f9ccb5', 'Make the caponata: In a heavy skillet heat 2 tablespoons of the oil over moderately high heat until it hot but not smoking, in it cook the eggplant, stirring, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until it is tender, and transfer it to a bowl. To the skillet add the remaining 2 tablespoons oil and in it cook the onion and the celery over moderate heat, stirring, for 5 minutes. Add the olives, the capers, the vinegar, the sugar, the raisins, the pine nuts, and the tomatoes and cook the mixture, covered, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes, or until it is cooked through and the celery is tender, and transfer it to the bowl. Stir in the parsley, let the caponata cool, and chill it, covered,overnight. Season the caponata with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.756', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.74');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('377fccd9-8cad-48ad-8c06-b40af9f7c90b', 'Make the bruschetta: Grill the bread on an oiled rack set about 4 inches over glowing coals for 1 minute on each side, brush the toasts on one side with the oil, and sprinkle them with salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.758', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.741');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eeecb954-9908-4a9e-b701-eeef7bc90d5f', 'Top each toast generously with some of the caponata, arrange 2 or 3 toasts on each of 4 plates, and garnish each serving with the parsley sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.761', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.741');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('75128232-3fd7-49e6-9b6f-a155a2ee9fb0', 'In a saucepan over medium heat, combine the 1/2 cup brown sugar with the water and stir until dissolved. Turn off the heat and add the lime juice and basil leaves. Let stand for at least 15 minutes or up to 1 hour, then discard the basil leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f953157-30c0-4140-91b1-25ce77452d4e', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan over medium heat; lightly oil the grates.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.766', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5a1350de-7eba-4cc2-a5b7-3893162bbaad', 'Lightly sprinkle the peaches with brown sugar and grill cut side down until dark brown grill marks form, about 2 minutes per cut side. Transfer the peaches to bowls and season with a little black pepper. Spoon some of the syrup on top, sprinkle with basil leaves and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.769', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.743');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1184af31-15f3-4682-aa66-8807f39b73a0', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Whisk juice, 1 tablespoon oil, and vinegar in small bowl to blend; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.772', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.743');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4dac3547-35b9-4555-a3c4-6cd1a1032a09', 'Stir remaining 1 tablespoon oil, crushed red pepper, and salt in medium bowl. Add carrots and toss to coat. Scrape carrot mixture onto large rimmed baking sheet. Arrange carrots in single layer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.774', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.744');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0952ca3b-661b-4eb4-87ea-f944d73593c5', 'Roast carrots until almost tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes (depending on size). Add juice mixture and toss to blend. Roast until juices are reduced to glaze and coat carrots, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes longer. Season to taste with more salt, if desired. Transfer carrots to large bowl; add mint and orange peel and toss to blend. Transfer to serving bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.777', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.745');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cd160087-54bf-4a91-a29e-3fdade9f4aae', 'Divide fruit juice between 2 Champagne flutes. Slowly pour Champagne into flutes, dividing equally. Add 1 tablespoon Grand Marnier to each flute; stir gently. Garnish with orange peel twists, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.78', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.745');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a5031f6-5cf2-4f06-8e49-ca1a7eb5e333', 'Sauté onions, bell pepper, garlic, and jalapeño in oil in a 4-quart heavy pot over moderately high heat, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add chili powder, cumin, and salt and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add tomatoes with juice and zucchini and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Stir in beans and chocolate and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Stir in cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.783', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.746');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e6a7b24-4fee-42ff-aa16-0d8bbb80e140', 'Puree the watermelon cubes in a food processor. Measure 4 cups of the puree and place in a bowl. Add the Simple Sugar Syrup and lemon juice and stir well. Freeze in an ice cream maker according to the manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.786', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.747');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3dabe5ab-da9b-40cc-9871-8ab07c8784fa', 'Whisk ginger, miso paste, 3 Tbsp. mirin, 3 Tbsp. vinegar, 1 Tbsp. soy sauce, and 1/4 tsp. salt in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.789', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.749');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('969041cf-1f4f-4ab9-a846-59629a58df19', 'Cook soba noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles, rinse with cold water, then add to ginger mixture. Season with more mirin, vinegar, soy sauce, and salt, if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.792', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.75');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('149b6034-a6ab-45e5-bc15-296da0b264f1', 'Transfer noodles to a serving bowl or platter and top with radishes, scallions, and tofu. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.795', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.751');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8840e775-f951-4ecd-8c7d-9a5779a98749', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and simmer until mushrooms are tender, about 5 minutes. Add tofu, spinach and green onions and simmer until spinach wilts and tofu is heated through, about 2 minutes. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper. Ladle soup into bowls and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.798', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.753');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6123e256-f6f2-4376-b2c8-59777011b770', 'To make the dressing, in a small jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the olive oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt, and pepper to taste. Cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend. Taste and adjust the seasoning. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.802', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.753');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79da5a14-05a8-43db-8385-713969afed4a', 'Place the onions in a medium bowl and cover with cold water. Let stand for 30 minutes. This crisps the onion and takes away the raw onion taste. Drain well and pat dry on paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.805', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.753');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a29b7a5-714e-4ab1-aa0c-51ddb6932b8c', 'In a small bowl, toss the cranberries with 2 tablespoons of the dressing to soften them. Set aside for at least 20 minutes or until ready to serve the salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.809', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.754');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('371f5c59-fff9-4a69-8345-f6810bb56f96', 'To assemble the salad, place the spinach, onions, and pears in a large bowl. Give the remaining dressing a last-minute shake and pour over the salad. Toss to coat evenly. Arrange the salad in a large serving bowl or divide it evenly among 8 salad plates. Scatter the cranberries and hazelnuts over the top(s). Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.812', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.754');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29b85b3f-5799-49bf-b149-398d9b34366c', 'Try to buy shelled hazelnuts (also called filberts) with the brown, papery skins removed as well. To toast, spread the hazelnuts in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet and place in a preheated 375°F oven. Toast for about 12 minutes until lightly browned. If the nuts still have the skins on, transfer them while they''re hot to a clean kitchen towel. (Use a clean towel that is old or you don''t mind washing with bleach, because the skins tend to discolor the fabric.) Rub the nuts to remove most of the skins (they never come completely off).', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.815', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.755');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('241cc183-31da-4513-9be3-f293e8e32d03', 'You can substitute unsalted cashews for the hazelnuts. Toast cashews, as directed above for hazelnuts, for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.819', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.755');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('01d30f18-6712-48f1-8f2b-7871b64b0d04', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Add olive oil and toss to coat. Spread vegetables out on large rimmed baking sheet. Roast vegetables until almost tender, stirring occasionally, about 50 minutes. Mix green onions and stock into vegetables. Bake until vegetables are just tender, about 15 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.823', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.756');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('44584d1b-db87-4fcb-bd4d-fe926c949c1d', 'Mix all the ingredients together in a small bowl. Set aside', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.826', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.756');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ab52354b-3fed-42b4-8dc9-716250b0a1f4', 'Put the tomato paste and 7 quarts (6.6 kilograms) cold water in a large nonreactive stockpot over high heat. Whisk occasionally as the water comes to a boil, then reduce the heat to maintain a gentle boil and cook for about 1 hour, or until it has reduced by about one-quarter. (Remove from the heat if the onions aren''t ready.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.83', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.757');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00447bc0-660d-4822-9130-bd87eb0c5407', 'Meanwhile, rinse the cilantro and parsley well and set aside. Cut the onions into large chunks. Put the chunks in a food processor and pulse until they are becoming a mush. Add as much of the herbs as fit into the food processor. Pulse the machine, adding small amounts of cold water if necessary to allow the blade to spin. As the herbs decrease in volume, add the remaining herbs and the celery leaves and continue to pulse. Stop from time to time to scrape the sides with a rubber spatula and mix the herbs to redistribute them. Run the machine for up to 10 minutes, until the mixture is almost liquefied.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.834', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.757');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2a75b012-65e6-4249-9ef9-b47f6be1e54d', 'Transfer the mixture to a large saucepan and stir in the spice mix.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.838', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.757');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48b9f2f1-6e29-4878-b9dc-6bbc56655b69', 'Add the remaining 5 cups (1.2 kilograms) cold water to the onions and bring to a gentle boil over high heat, then reduce the heat and boil gently for about 1 hour or until the liquid is reduced by half.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.841', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.758');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c413ca8-e7bf-44f3-b17a-9c4fbe4beb4d', 'Stir the onion mixture into the stockpot, return to a simmer, and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, skimming any impurities that rise to the top, until the soup has reduced by about one-third to just over 4 quarts (4 kilograms).', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.758');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24db13da-9d74-4b24-bf08-89b0fe4707eb', 'Cut a lengthwise slit down one side of each date, open it as you would a book, and remove the pit. Cut the dates lengthwise in half, then cut each half lengthwise into 4 strips. Using your fingertips, shape each strip into a rough ball. If you keep the skin side facing out, the ball will be less sticky and will hold together better.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.848', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.758');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e92cc660-e32b-480a-9620-312c653c55e2', 'Pour a shallow pool of olive oil into a small bowl. Rub a little of the oil on the center of one palm, put a date ball on it, and use the index finger of your other hand to roll the date into a smooth ball. Put the ball in the bowl of oil, and repeat with the rest of the dates, adding more oil to the bowl as needed to keep the date balls covered. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.851', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.759');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa195d04-4d48-4ffa-9929-dc3e729a61d9', 'Put the lentils in a saucepan, add 6 cups (1.4 kilograms) cold water, and bring to a simmer over medium heat. Cook the lentils for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring them from time to time.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.854', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.759');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b49410b8-4474-43d0-83dc-a0147ae79450', 'Meanwhile, fill a large bowl with cold water. Taste a lentil. When they have started to soften but are still firm in the center, drain them in a fine-mesh strainer, rinse them with cold water, and submerge them in the bowl of cold water until ready to use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.857', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.759');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('83f4b828-59af-4998-9493-3e972b0c1fc0', 'Remove the tough outer celery stalks and reserve them for another use. Pinch off the leaves from the inner stalks and place the leaves in a bowl of ice water. Cut the stalks into 1/8-inch dice; you need 1 cup (120 grams). Put the diced celery in a small bowl, toss with the olive oil and parsley, and season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.86', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.76');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f97f3f1-0b71-482b-9026-44b59c8be3b4', 'Once the soup has reduced, add the lentils; keep warm over low heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.863', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.76');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39f020b2-d9ac-461a-a055-96a94c0e3d2f', 'Whisk together the flour, water, and yeast in a small bowl and let sit at room temperature until foamy and bubbling, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.866', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.76');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9199fbe-2432-4011-950c-7198954a2bd1', 'In a shallow baking pan toast nuts in middle of oven until golden, about 5 minutes. Cut escarole into 1-inch pieces and chop garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.041', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.802');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff23bfa7-c847-4d06-9e12-bb1cc36e1c47', 'Whisking constantly, add the flour mixture to the soup, then stir with a flat-bottomed wooden spoon, scraping the bottom of the pot, as you bring the soup to a simmer over medium heat. (High heat could cause the flour to stick to the bottom of the pot.) Simmer the soup gently, stirring often, for 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt, remove the soup from the heat, and stir in the lemon juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.869', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.761');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce40309c-5e63-43c6-80c1-c9e82d4bf3ce', 'Drain and dry the celery leaves. Using 2 soupspoons, form the celery salad into a quenelle or football shape and place toward the rim of each soup bowl. Stack about 8 date balls alongside each quenelle. (If you end up with extra date balls, keep them in the refrigerator and add them to salads.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.872', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.761');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c483123c-81f5-490d-9802-5d733d89c1cf', 'Carefully ladle the soup around the garnishes so that a bit of the celery salad and the date balls remain visible. Drizzle some of the olive oil that remains in the bowl of celery salad over the soup and garnish with the celery leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.876', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.762');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df67ad4e-92ef-402c-bbe4-8a1d11d1f22c', 'Divide sliced onion between two 1-quart wide-mouth glass jars. Pack cucumber slices horizontally in jars. Top each jar with dill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.88', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.762');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22b47e64-8c5c-45da-84ee-8838d20155ea', 'Using mortar and pestle or resealable plastic bag and mallet, crush mustard seeds and peppercorns together. Place crushed spices in medium saucepan. Add vinegar, 1 cup water, sugar, coarse salt, and dill seeds. Bring mixture to boil over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.884', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.763');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e198c49e-67bb-4fe8-ae45-3a4b29f49168', 'Ladle mixture evenly over cucumbers. Leave jars uncovered and chill 24 hours. Cover glass pickle jars tightly with lids. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep refrigerated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.889', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.763');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fce80ba-c9e7-4e58-98b1-bc1df585cd2e', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Combine squash, rutabagas, and sweet potatoes in large bowl. Add oil and cayenne and toss to coat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread vegetable mixture on prepared baking sheet. Roast until vegetables are tender, stirring and turning occasionally, about 1 hour. (Vegetables can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Let stand on baking sheet at room temperature. Rewarm in 350°F oven until heated through, about 15 minutes.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.892', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.766');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b2bf9102-57cb-48f2-a2a0-6529872e42f7', 'Transfer vegetable mixture to bowl. Add red onion, chives, and vinegar; toss to blend. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.896', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.768');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c09274ae-cefe-45fd-8a38-38d5bbe84afe', 'Whisk all ingredients into small bowl to blend. DO AHEAD: Spice blend can be made 2 weeks ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.9', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.768');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4f6c4cf-bf7f-4cf3-ac64-e6cf14d270d0', 'Whisk oil and vinegar in medium bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, watercress, and chervil; toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.905', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.769');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97464043-3849-416b-8ce7-325f2a6a5028', 'Process 8 garlic cloves, 2 dried guindilla or New Mexico chiles, 2 teaspoons smoked paprika, 1 teaspoon ground cumin, and 1 teaspoon kosher salt in a food processor, occasionally scraping down sides of bowl, until a smooth paste forms. With machine running, drizzle in 1 cup extra-virgin olive oil and process until well blended. Add 1 teaspoon Sherry vinegar and 1 teaspoon water and process to blend. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.908', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.769');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24fcd920-67b5-4d39-a797-7bf187315844', 'Cook potatoes in large saucepan of boiling salted water until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain, reserving 1 cup cooking liquid. Place in large microwave-safe bowl. Add 3 tablespoons oil. Mash until potatoes are smooth, adding remaining 1 tablespoon oil, if desired, and reserved cooking liquid by 1/4 cupfuls to moisten to desired consistency. Mix in horseradish. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Potatoes can be made up to 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Rewarm potatoes in microwave before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.912', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.77');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('139b6b3e-6cc2-4a7f-86c1-dab2ab5817e6', 'Transfer potatoes to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.771');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8787920e-67cf-41a1-b7df-afda0800af30', 'Bring 5 1/2 cups water with salt to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan. Add carrot, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.919', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.775');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c027c39e-cf46-4e15-9bf4-d195a20b0895', 'Whisk together shiro miso and remaining 1/2 cup water in a small bowl until smooth, then whisk into carrot mixture. Add tofu and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.924', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.778');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7267e090-a926-49a6-85ec-9d868d7ae273', 'Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic; sauté until deep brown, about 3 minutes. Discard garlic. Add onion to saucepan and sauté until tender, about 5 minutes. Add rice; stir 5 minutes. Add 3 cups hot water, parsley, and salt (mixture will sputter). Bring to boil, stirring. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until almost all liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes. Stir rice, then re-cover and continue to simmer until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat; let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Discard parsley; fluff rice with fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.928', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.778');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('422db355-949e-48e3-aea4-1a75102c6879', 'In a bowl soak noodles in very hot water to cover 15 minutes and drain well in a colander. Reserve half of noodles for another use. With scissors cut remaining noodles into 3- to 4-inch lengths and in a small bowl toss with vinegar and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.779');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da37fade-e836-4db8-8a4f-5172c98c403c', 'Cut out and discard ribs from lettuce leaves, halving each leaf.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.935', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.779');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('977a374c-ab31-4bbe-801e-5ecd64118a52', 'In a shallow baking pan or cake pan soak 2 rounds rice paper in hot water to cover until very pliable, 45 seconds to 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.938', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.78');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23534b60-0b76-4e64-8c89-f758e8c607c0', 'Carefully spread 1 soaked round on a paper towel, leaving remaining round in water, and blot with paper towels. Arrange 1 piece of lettuce leaf on bottom half of sheet, leaving a 1-inch border along edge. Top lettuce with about one fourth of peanuts and about one fourth of noodles, arranging them in a line across lettuce. Top noodles with one fourth each of scallion, carrot, cabbage, and herbs. Roll up filling tightly in rice paper, folding insides after first roll to completely enclose filling, and continue rolling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.942', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.781');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed643287-89b8-4e34-87b5-2bbba36b95da', 'Spread remaining soaked rice paper round on paper towel and blot with another paper towel. Wrap rice paper around spring roll in same manner. (Double wrapping covers any tears and makes roll more stable and easier to eat.) Wrap spring roll in rinsed and squeezed paper towel and put in a resealable plastic bag. Make 3 more rolls with remaining ingredients in same manner. Rolls may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, wrapped in wet paper towels in sealed plastic bag. Before serving, bring rolls to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.946', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.781');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af8ee1f6-e5dd-46a1-9951-cb2f401fd912', 'Discard paper towels. Halve rolls diagonally and serve with peanut sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.95', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.783');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9f6ea8f-a5c0-4337-8170-a909aae77c01', 'Preheat the oven to 400°F/200°C/gas 6. Peel and cut the vegetables into equal sized pieces, about 1-in/2.5-cm chunks. Toss vegetables and onions in olive oil in a large bowl and season generously with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.954', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.785');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c92025cc-088a-4a30-acea-ee5bdfa879e3', 'Spread the pieces out in a single layer on one or two roasting pans/trays so that the vegetables don''t touch. Roast until the veggies are lightly browned and just tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on the vegetable. Remove and toss with additional olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and garnish with parsley before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.957', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.786');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fbddde11-a305-4a8b-b8ab-c655f248b091', 'If you are using dried chipotle or pasilla de Oaxaca chiles, soak them in warm water for minutes to soften, then drain, seed, and finely chop them. If using canned chipotles, rinse, seed, and finely chop them. If using jalapeño chiles, seed and finely chop them. Ready the poblano chiles. Set all the chiles aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.961', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.786');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ca11e0e-0b23-4ebf-9228-f8124e734b70', 'Halve the mango lengthwise, remove the pit, scoop out the flesh from each half with a spoon, and cut into 1/2-inch dice. Twist the stem off the pineapple half and stand the pineapple upright. Cut downward on all sides to remove the peel. Then, with a paring knife, remove the "eyes" by making diagonal cuts across the flesh just deep enough to lift them out. Cut the pineapple lengthwise into quarters, and cut away the strip of core that runs along each wedge. Cut the quarters crosswise into wedges about 1/4 inch wide, and cut the wedges into 1/4-inch dice. Peel the papaya, cut it in half lengthwise, and spoon out the seeds. Cut the halves lengthwise into wedges about 1/2 inch wide, and cut the wedges into 1/2-inch dice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.787');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9ca5b43-1024-4406-a559-33c563b41d56', 'In a bowl, combine the chiles, mango, pineapple, papaya, onion, cilantro, and lime juice. Toss together to mix well and then season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.967', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.787');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a91fcd2a-ead0-4bf4-9f67-409e0a1b7126', 'Bring ginger, garlic, vinegar, sugar, salt, coriander seeds, and 2 cups water to a boil in a medium pot over high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.971', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.788');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c86347c4-d5dc-4fb3-8626-af8a70c296bb', 'Place cucumbers and dill in a heatproof resealable container or jar (divide among several containers if necessary). Pour hot brining liquid over cucumbers and dill. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.974', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.788');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0011d650-b7f5-47ed-aadf-4f006ec31f45', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Toss peppers with 1/4 cup olive oil in bowl. Transfer peppers to large rimmed baking sheet. Roast peppers until partially charred, turning every 10 minutes, about 50 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.977', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.789');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0ef9531-1895-4bda-8687-56140b59a9b3', 'Transfer peppers to reserved bowl; cover tightly with plastic wrap. Cool 15 minutes. Peel and seed peppers over bowl. Tear each pepper lengthwise into 6 strips. Transfer pepper strips to heavy large skillet. Strain liquid from bowl into skillet. Add garlic, vinegar, and 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil to skillet. Simmer over medium heat until liquid becomes syrupy, stirring frequently, about 25 minutes. Cool. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover; let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.981', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.789');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('73b160be-ca83-4b74-8b7d-20ba337671ee', 'Transfer pepper mixture to platter. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.984', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.79');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('80f49ba0-7614-47be-b432-81e2ee120012', 'Cut the tofu into 1 1/2 by 3/4-inch pieces and place on a cloth to dry. Put enough oil in a wok to deep-fry the tofu and heat to 350°F, or until a cube of bread dropped in the oil browns in 15 seconds. Deep-fry the tofu for about 5 minutes, or until it is golden and very crisp. Once all of the tofu is cooked, remove the oil from the wok and reserve for later use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.988', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.79');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac086c3e-8074-4138-a28a-7c711bd42161', 'Place 2 teaspoons of oil back into the wok and place over high heat. Add the scallions, chile, and garlic, stir-fry for 30 seconds, then return the tofu to the wok. Toss to combine the flavors and season with the salt and pepper seasoning mix. Serve with salt, pepper, and lemon dipping sauce or vegetarian dipping sauce .', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.991', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.791');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe09a411-6ba7-4f05-bfa0-e56849de57b6', 'In a small saucepan combine the sugar and 3-1/2 cups water and bring the mixture to a boil, stirring. In a blender purée the ginger with the syrup, the wine, and the food coloring, chill the mixture until is cold, and stir it. Transfer the mixture to 2 metal ice-cube trays without the dividers or to a shallow metal pan and freeze it, stirring and crushing the lumps with a fork every 30 minutes, for 2 to 3 hours, or until it is firm but not frozen solid. The granita may be made 2 days in advance and kept covered and frozen. Scrape the granita with a fork to lighten the texture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:21.995', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.791');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('715f126b-ce7d-4f44-9796-33bf7c690f9f', 'On each of 4 plates arrange 2 of the honeydew slices and top 1 of the slices on each plate with a scoop of the honeydew and sake granita. Top the other slices with a scoop of the pickled ginger and plum-wine granita.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.793');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a0670054-a3ac-43ac-be1c-96bbfa588670', 'Using vegetable peeler, remove peel (colored part only) from fruit in 1 1/2- to 2-inch-long pieces. Cut peel into very thin strips (about 1/16 inch wide). Bring small saucepan of water to boil. Add strips and boil 5 minutes. Drain. Repeat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.004', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.794');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94d5a54f-ad5e-4801-af44-8810ae5a81e6', 'Bring sugar and 1/4 cup water to simmer in small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add blanched citrus peel, cover, and simmer 3 minutes. Transfer syrup with peel to small bowl. Cover and chill overnight. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.008', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.795');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('131ca963-c2de-4724-bf30-cb9060d6467c', 'Using slotted spoon, transfer citrus peel to paper towels to drain before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.012', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.796');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a9d0e782-c01d-42df-85d7-6310889eae6a', 'Whisk all ingredients to blend in small bowl. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.016', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.797');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a038987-117e-4a2b-993e-80762d51cf17', 'Steam sweet potatoes in batches until potatoes are just tender, about 10 minutes per batch. Transfer sweet potatoes to large bowl. Cool to room temperature. Add green onions, parsley, pecans, and all raisins. Pour dressing over; toss gently to blend. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.021', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.799');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b19ba01-316c-46a0-a35a-74c193c2e442', 'Peel and coarsely grate 1 pound fresh horseradish root. Combine grated horseradish, 2 tablespoons white wine vinegar, and 2 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt in a food processor; pulse 4 or 5 times, or until the horseradish begins to break down. Add 6 tablespoons more vinegar, a tablespoonful at a time, until mixture forms a coarse paste. Transfer mixture to a jar and refrigerate for up to 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.024', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.8');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3898265b-7149-46de-a3ce-89ca2177af20', 'In a bowl combine bulgur and water. Soak bulgur 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bulgur may be prepared 1 day ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.028', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.8');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f50777eb-65f3-427b-a298-6dc1fd691e5d', 'Mince enough onion to measure 1 cup and in a bowl stir together with salt, allspice, and cinnamon. Let onion mixture stand 30 minutes. Finely chop parsley and mint. Finely chop enough scallion greens to measure 2/3 cup. Quarter and seed cucumber and tomatoes and thinly slice. In a bowl toss together all salad ingredients with salt and pepper to taste. Salad may be made 1 hour ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.032', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.801');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2b862f97-2b80-438e-b0a1-aa6130e87795', 'Preheat oven to 350°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.037', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.801');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64628d16-4342-4f57-99ad-0d8744681030', 'In a 12-inch nonstick skillet sauté garlic in oil over moderately high heat, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add escarole in 3 batches, tossing each batch with tongs until wilted before adding next. Stir in currants, capers, and salt and pepper to taste and cook, covered, over moderately low heat until escarole is tender, about 3 minutes. Remove lid and cook over moderately high heat until most liquid is evaporated, about 2 minutes more. Stir in nuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.046', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.802');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a388cf1c-ca6e-4e62-8d7c-c6f61976054e', 'Place the water and the sugar in a small saucepan over medium-high heat and bring to a boil, stirring all the while. When the sugar has dissolved, add the apricots, return to the boil, and reduce the heat so the liquid is simmering gently. Simmer the apricots just until they begin to turn tender, about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.051', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.803');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4176c688-0565-4920-8000-c2263c22646a', 'Puree the apricots and their poaching liquid in a food processor until smooth. Strain the mixture if you like, though it isn''t necessary. Chill the mixture in an airtight container in the refrigerator for at least one hour and up to 24 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.055', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.803');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02ace841-d39c-4a90-8b6c-648bd1473d75', 'Just before freezing, whisk in the lemon juice. Freeze according to the ice cream freezer manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.06', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.803');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7770f7c4-ee27-4a59-80d2-50fbf6be0b70', 'Heat a dry small heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot and toast coriander seeds, stirring, until fragrant and a little darker, about 2 minutes. With a mortar and pestle or in a spice grinder or cleaned electric coffee grinder, grind coriander to a coarse powder. In a bowl, whisk together coriander and remaining dressing ingredients.Dressing may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.064', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.804');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57c20559-2707-4d16-b70d-4d1b6f3e18a8', 'With a Japanese rotary slicer or other thin-slicing device, slice onion crosswise into thin spirals or rings. In a bowl of ice and cold water, soak onion (separate rings if necessary) 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.068', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.804');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('871cb175-ff21-4bda-a7b5-bbbad6ee9026', 'Trim stalks from fennel and with slicing device, thinly slice fennel bulb crosswise.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.072', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.805');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6bcf2db9-dfea-45a5-abbd-b524e4dae686', 'With a sharp knife, cut a slice from top and bottom of each orange to expose flesh and arrange cut side down on a cutting board. cutting from top to bottom, remove peel and pith. Cut oranges crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.078', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.805');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec9171ee-10c4-4fc7-8a30-3680a3f4bb8d', 'Drain onion well and pat dry between paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.084', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.805');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bdcddd7-50ac-418a-97ab-cdf862b6c5f0', 'Arrange fennel, onion and orange decoratively on a platter and scatter with mint. Whisk dressing and drizzle over salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.088', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8ea587a1-a6df-4809-a868-63a4650f62f9', 'Blend all ingredients except beans with salt and pepper to taste in a blender until a coarse purée.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.092', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eef8397a-9d5a-4bd6-8af3-eb7a91975181', 'Cook beans in boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking, then drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('081383c1-926d-4739-b25c-137c347d8ec9', 'Toss beans with half of pesto, or to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.103', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('706e55fd-018b-4a18-877f-446a285f476f', 'In a large heavy saucepan combine the soaked beans with enough cold water to cover them by 1 inch and simmer them, uncovered, for 15 minutes, or until they are tender but not falling apart. While the beans are cooking, in a heavy skillet cook the onion, the carrots, and the garlic in 2 tablespoons of the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until the carrots are softened and stir in the bell pepper. Reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid, drain the beans, and in a bowl combine them with the vegetable mixture, the reserved cooking liquid, the remaining 6 tablespoons oil, the parsley, the lemon juice, and salt and pepper to taste. Let the salad stand, covered and chilled, for 3 hours to allow the flavors to develop. The salad may be made 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled. Serve the salad at room temperature with the pita wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.107', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7cf4e450-c530-47b3-9ffc-0529cb201bd0', 'Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Cover and let stand 1 to 3 hours. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.111', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78dc9e36-b4df-4d83-9da8-3d1aadc72193', 'In a sauté pan over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil. Add the onion and peppers and cook until the onion is softened, about 5 minutes. Add the remaining oil, then add the potatoes, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper to taste. Lower the heat and continue to cook, stirring often, until the potatoes are nicely browned, 20 to 25 minutes. Serve at once.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.116', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e644ca1-b50d-463c-a628-209d734c20c8', 'Cook onion and sun-dried tomatoes in 1/4 cup oil with 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a 5- to 6-qt pot over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Add garlic and paprika and cook, stirring, 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.12', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e14f4cb-597e-4941-97a5-f8159e000cd8', 'Stir in beans, water, spinach, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until spinach is wilted, about 5 minutes. Season with pepper and drizzle with remaining 2 tablespoon oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.124', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ce0c412-cab4-4631-89f8-2f37985a2bb6', 'Halve cucumber lengthwise, then slice crosswise 3/4 inch thick.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.127', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.808');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e31f62c-cf46-4eb3-8bf2-0b2196486935', 'Bring vinegar, water, sugar, and salt to a boil in a saucepan, then cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.132', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.808');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('06695df0-a7d5-4ff6-bcbc-75eb26522714', 'Combine cucumber, radish, and vinegar in a bowl and chill, covered, until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.136', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.808');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82bc676e-de85-41d9-93ac-05883d016d1d', 'Drain vegetables before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.139', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.809');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd4f57d5-79e7-459d-8649-3e681a8c1605', 'Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Add sugar snap peas; cook 1 minute. Using slotted spoon, transfer peas to strainer. Rinse with cold water and drain. Add orzo to same pot. Boil until tender but still firm to bite, about 8 minutes. Drain and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.142', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.809');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('738ee80c-670f-4688-95ea-944e52691902', 'Place orzo in large bowl. Mix in sugar snap peas, tomatoes, cucumber, green onions, parsley. mint and lemon peel. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.146', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.809');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71c56d27-60ac-4e8b-8647-80663927c853', 'Combine lemon juice, lemon peel and garlic in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in olive oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.149', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.81');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7af896d-a2be-4b48-9a10-a9fcb1559d76', 'Pour half of dressing over salad; toss to coat. (Can be Made 6 hours ahead. Cover salad and remaining dressing separately and chill. Bring to room temperature before continuing.) Toss salad with enough remaining dressing to coat generously. Season with salt and pepper. Line shallow serving bowl with lettuce. Mount salad in bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.154', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.81');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42e27b26-e5fb-4ffb-8084-f292f3567994', 'Cut enough onion into 1/4-inch dice to measure 1 cup and thinly slice garlic. Trim fennel stalks flush with bulb, discarding stalks. Halve bulb and core. Cut enough fennel bulb into 1/4-inch dice to measure 1 1/4 cups. Cut enough zucchini into 1/4-inch dice to measure 1 1/2 cups. Cut enough carrot into 1/4-inch dice to measure 2/3 cup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.158', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.81');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e70d006c-faba-4048-8872-e5385f3bebdb', 'Peel tomato (see below), reserving boiling water and ice water, and seed. Cut enough tomato into 1/4-inch dice to measure 3/4 cup. Add carrot to boiling water and cook 1 minute. Drain carrot in a colander. Transfer carrot to ice water to stop cooking and drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.81');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3457fb91-dd42-4a3e-b5c3-af431bfef9f2', 'In a large heavy skillet cook onion and garlic in oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until softened. Add fennel, zucchini, and carrot and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, about 5 minutes. Add spices and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Stir in tomato and pepper and salt to taste and cook, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally, until fennel and carrot are just tender, 10 to 12 minutes. Keep vegetables warm, partially covered. Vegetables may be prepared 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Reheat vegetables with 1 to 2 tablespoons water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.165', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.811');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27cf696f-01a8-4769-87b9-b96c2684323f', 'Have ready a bowl of ice and cold water. Cut an X in blossom end of each tomato. In a saucepan of boiling water blanch tomatoes 10 seconds. Transfer tomatoes with a slotted spoon to ice water to stop cooking. Peel tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.168', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.811');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e8ed05b-4fa7-40d4-afb2-c49cef127bee', 'Mash together all ingredients in a bowl with a fork until smooth, using enough water for desired consistency. For a smoother dip, puréei n a blender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.172', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.811');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8da5ed65-2954-4eb5-80da-ef30f94bcdc6', 'Blend oil, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt, and 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper in blender until almost smooth. Using fork or wooden skewer, pierce zucchini all over. Place in medium bowl. Pour garlic oil over zucchini and let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes and up to 1 hour, tossing occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.175', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.812');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('592fffe4-a4d2-4a37-bec6-4ee89d05ae98', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Grill zucchini until tender and golden in spots, turning occasionally, about 6 minutes. Transfer to plate, sprinkle with additional salt, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.179', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.812');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4145389-2175-404a-9262-ce666ee963bb', 'In a food processor, combine all the ingredients and process until smooth. The mixture will have the consistency of a ganache. Use immediately, or store in a covered container in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.813');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57e3b311-6942-46c5-91f5-ad28f0b73320', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Combine potatoes, oil, garlic, herbs and pepper in large bowl and toss to coat. Spread potatoes in single layer in baking pan. Bake until brown and cooked through, turning once, about 1 hour. Season potatoes to taste with salt and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.815');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fbd9af83-5420-4c99-83bf-d6dc16e845f4', 'In a saucepan with a tight-fitting lid bring water to a boil with salt. Stir in rice and cook, covered, over low heat 20 minutes, or until water is absorbed and rice is tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.196', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.815');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('16629f60-082b-4670-8ba6-f0f89327f42f', 'While rice is cooking, lightly toast walnuts and chop coarse. Chop dill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.216', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.816');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9ccb359-c4f5-4aeb-ba8c-08fce19ad9ce', 'Fluff rice with a fork and stir in walnuts, dill, raisins, zest, vinegar, oil, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.224', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.816');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3dd0e584-37b7-4abe-a1ef-10b64029edc2', 'Whisk oil, cranberry juice concentrate and vinegar in small bowl to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.232', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.816');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb7098ea-a36e-4c5b-bdad-9d82971dd34f', 'Combine endive and apples in medium bowl. Pour dressing over; toss to coat. Sprinkle cranberries, green onions and walnuts over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.244', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.817');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7fa4289d-7743-4349-8d0e-b388ca856e92', 'Combine first four ingredients in bowl. Stir until sugar dissolves. Refrigerate plum mixture at least 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.252', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.818');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36250dc5-c41e-4eb3-b862-8fe5dc59d9e6', 'Spoon sorbet into balloon glasses. Top with plums and marinating liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.26', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.818');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ca17d6a-5303-4b12-b3e5-faf1f53af16a', '1. To make the sweet potato filling, bring a medium pot of salted water to a boil over high heat. Boil the sweet potato chunks just until tender, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.265', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.819');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcdd1e46-eb25-4be8-8e4c-08b7a26c0141', '2. Drain the potatoes, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.27', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.819');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('694cb859-5bee-4926-b5f5-9dc6cb42221d', '3. Transfer the hot potatoes and reserved cooking water, the brown sugar, vegan butter, vanilla, and salt to a medium bowl. Beat with a hand mixer until totally smooth, then set aside to fully cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.276', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.82');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65698187-be26-4a86-b8ce-55ae40279430', '4. Meanwhile, make the sweet kraut. Heat the oil in a medium sauté pan over medium heat. Add the cabbage and allow it to start to sear for about 3 minutes, then add the brown sugar and spices. Let the sugar start to melt with the cabbage juice for another 3 minutes, then add the Riesling. Allow the cabbage to cook down and steam itself for another 8 to 10 minutes. The cabbage will now be dark pink instead of purple. Remove the pan from the heat and let it cool fully.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.281', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.82');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30311c18-9243-4001-a5bf-df0745659994', '5. While the potatoes and kraut are cooling, make the turnover crust. Pulse together the flour, vegan butter, and vegan shortening until it looks chunky and sandy. Add the sugar, olive oil, cinnamon, salt, and allspice and pulse again. While pulsing, slowly drizzle in 2 to 3 tablespoons cold water, little by little-just until a loose dough ball is formed and spins around the bowl of the food processor. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 10 minutes or up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.285', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.821');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('304a0f11-18c7-46b3-be1a-f1203a538727', '6. Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.289', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.821');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ba4c9ff7-e35c-440f-9139-23699b7fab4c', '7. On a work surface dusted with flour, roll out the dough to 1/4 inch thick. Use a 4-inch-wide circle cutter to stamp out the turnover shells. Place 1 heaping tablespoon of the sweet potato filling in the center of each dough circle. Bring the edges of the circle together, forming a half circle, and pinch them together tightly. Use a fork to crimp the edges of the seal. Arrange the turnovers on the prepared sheet pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.293', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.822');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d4c1a80-7bd5-448e-bd6e-c70f0ea351ff', '8. Bake the turnovers until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly. Arrange on serving dishes with the sweet kraut and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.297', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.822');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('695aaf03-82e3-4ecc-a583-572902a6495a', 'Mince garlic and mash to a paste with a pinch of salt, then transfer to a large bowl. Whisk in oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, and sugar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.823');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dace6ed4-4c38-43ca-bb00-412862cba982', 'Roast bell peppers on racks of gas burners over high heat, turning with tongs, until skins are blackened, 12 to 15 minutes. (Or broil peppers on a broiler pan about 5 inches from heat, turning occasionally, about 15 minutes.) Transfer to a bowl and cover tightly with plastic wrap, then let stand 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.305', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.823');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88453eee-de2a-4c23-8b78-295302fa6c0d', 'When cool enough to handle, peel peppers, discarding stems and seeds. Cut peppers lengthwise into 1-inch-wide strips, then cut strips crosswise into 1/4-inch-wide pieces. Add peppers to dressing along with onion and arugula and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.824');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e3b8758-f763-4b21-aea9-bd5741dff5f2', 'Place chiles in medium saucepan filled with water; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until chiles are tender, adding more water if needed to keep chiles submerged, 1 to 11/2 hours, depending on dryness of chiles. Drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.314', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.824');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cd1fd075-7534-495b-8c94-e7a0e7c6a5a3', 'Combine softened chipotles, cranberries, sugar, and lemon juice in heavy medium saucepan and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Continue cooking until cranberries begin to pop, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Stir in garlic, cinnamon, and cumin. Simmer until sauce thickens slightly and flavors meld, stirring often, about 5 minutes. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.317', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.825');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68bcb0e8-088c-481a-ba54-aef2a31a38df', 'Remove chipotles. Stem and seed. Mince chiles and return to cranberry sauce; stir to distribute. Cover and chill. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.321', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.825');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b784e88-24ca-447f-b3eb-c01a0c66e922', 'Can be found at specialty foods stores, natural foods stores, and Latin markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.826');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('917bcdf1-e89b-47ab-8f97-926c89829c24', 'Cook green beans in a large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 3 minutes. Drain; transfer to a bowl of ice water and let cool. Drain. Place in a large heatproof jar or bowl with fennel and lemon slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.326', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.827');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cdaf2d6b-4567-47d2-8b6e-685eb639ddbf', 'Bring chiles, vinegar, sugar, peppercorns, 2 tablespoons salt, and 2 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan; pour over green beans. Let cool. Cover and chill at least 12 hours and up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.329', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.827');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4e08425-550b-4b86-b804-e2b37a95190e', 'In large heavy sauté pan over moderate heat, heat 3 tablespoons oil until hot but not smoking. Add 1/2 of garlic and sauté until softened, about 2 minutes. Add mushrooms, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and sauté until mushrooms begin to give off liquid, about 5 minutes. Transfer to colander and let drain until ready to use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.828');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39f4394b-076c-48ed-a860-ec9ae4153440', 'In medium saucepan over low heat, bring stock to simmer. Cover and keep simmering.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.335', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.829');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be05e61d-ef24-4e0d-9f8b-c10ca2773acf', 'In large heavy pot over moderate heat, heat 1/4 cup oil until hot but not smoking. Add onion and remaining garlic and sauté until softened, about 4 minutes. Add rice and sauté 4 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.338', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('16572ae5-f5b9-4aaf-9e27-810c5e3892fe', 'Add wine and cook, stirring constantly, until absorbed, about 2 minutes. Stir 1/2 cup simmering stock into rice and cook, stirring constantly, until absorbed. Continue cooking and adding stock, about 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly and letting each addition be absorbed before adding next, until rice is tender and creamy-looking but still al dente, about 18 minutes. (You will have about 1 cup stock left over.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.341', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25bf1d0f-a4a2-43ec-9854-420b1a264bee', 'Remove from heat and stir in drained mushrooms, thyme, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate, covered, until cold, about 4 hours. (Risotto can be made ahead and refrigerated, covered, up to 24 hours.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.343', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.833');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f504d000-d276-465c-bbf4-458e53721d12', 'Preheat oven to 250°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.346', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.833');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0284a77c-ad33-41cd-afc6-847baaf870d2', 'Transfer 1 cup flour, eggs, and bread crumbs to 3 separate shallow bowls. Stir 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper into flour. Stir remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper into bread crumbs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.35', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.834');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fcc35d3-0347-4fc2-ac10-25eb046a328d', 'Stir remaining 2 tablespoons flour into risotto, then, using wet hands, shape into 12 (1/2-inch-thick) patties.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.352', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.834');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97c24274-93f1-4015-8068-23f4ab2dc321', 'In heavy large sauté pan over moderate heat, heat 1/4 cup oil until hot but not smoking. Working in batches of 4 and adding 2 tablespoons oil after each batch, dredge cakes in flour (tapping off excess), then egg (letting excess drip off), then bread crumbs, and fry until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side. Keep warm in oven while frying remaining batches.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.355', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.835');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa3e4f3e-80fa-48c0-9f8c-1952c6b01ee3', 'Serve warm with salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.357', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.835');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b54a9a4-cad4-41f8-9351-cfed7177e1ca', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Spread mushrooms and next 6 ingredients in single layer on prepared sheet. Drizzle with oil; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons rosemary, salt, and pepper. Roast until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.36', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.836');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5eb47d13-8c2a-4f5d-ac6b-e87b854ad7dd', 'Add zucchini, 2 cups broth, and tomatoes with juices to vegetables; stir to blend well. Continue to roast until zucchini are tender and juices thicken slightly, stirring occasionally and adding more broth if liquid evaporates too quickly, about 30 minutes longer. Transfer ragù to bowl. Mix basil, parsley, and 1 teaspoon rosemary into ragù. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.362', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.836');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee4df7b4-2dbd-4bd8-85e9-7e7c4f4bf96a', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Divide first 5 ingredients between 2 heavy large baking sheets. Brush vegetables with 3 tablespoons oil and balsamic vinegar. Sprinkle herbs over. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until tender, turning occasionally, about 45 minutes. Cool. Remove and discard peels from garlic. Coarsely chop garlic. Cut roasted vegetables into 3/4-inch pieces. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.366', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.837');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fdb28ff-46df-4734-bfb6-53e9717fa6c2', 'Bring 2 1/2 cups water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 tablespoon oil to boil in medium saucepan. Stir in couscous. Remove from heat. Cover; let stand until water is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Fluff couscous with fork. Transfer to large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.369', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.837');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18e3d569-ab14-4c49-a7a9-31c6b7f505e7', 'Gently mix roasted garlic and vegetables, 1/4 cup oil, olives, lemon juice, capers and basil into couscous. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.372', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('912237cd-c43c-4842-98cf-73740c3b7df5', 'Place the fennel and parsley in a serving bowl and toss to combine. Place the orange juice, oil, mustard, salt, and pepper in a bowl and whisk to combine. Pour over the salad and serve with the simple leek and ricotta tarts .', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.374', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc89233c-b273-4a5b-bd3f-7099a6ad068d', 'Cook potatoes and beets in separate medium pots of boiling salted water until tender, about 30 minutes for potatoes and 35 minutes for beets. Drain; cool slightly. Peel vegetables and thinly slice into rounds. Whisk vinegar, oil and coriander in medium bowl. Season generously with salt and pepper. Add vegetables; toss gently to coat. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.377', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b9c91472-cf69-4961-9f33-3dc3edca4be4', 'Stir together all ingredients in a bowl, then let stand at least 30 minutes for flavors to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.38', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de026595-b817-42af-b698-601b4abdbcfc', 'Toss all ingredients in small bowl to blend. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.383', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('67c4ca8e-9738-4dba-88f9-acbc86a16af6', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.386', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.84');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b63cec8-1334-47dd-8968-a069ebe049be', 'Spoon fruit and some syrup into large stemmed goblets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:33.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.604');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47bc6f1c-a10c-4f8c-bacd-1dbd18cdbde2', 'Cook spaghetti in large pot of rapidly boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite. Drain. Rinse under cold water to cool. Drain well. Add to vinegar mixture in bowl. Sprinkle with green onions and cilantro and toss well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.389', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.84');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10eed0f9-fce5-45d0-8914-48f93d0857dc', 'Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Let stand at least 30 minutes and up to 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.841');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e741ab3c-6a1c-4d41-8f75-5e9a6c700593', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Add apricots and cherries; simmer until fruit is tender, about 5 minutes. Transfer to bowl. Chill until cold, about 2 hours. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep chilled.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.395', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.841');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('117b87c9-00f7-4dd9-a34d-41d72608afbc', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Toast walnuts on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing once, until slightly darkened in color and fragrant, 8–10 minutes. Let cool; coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.398', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.842');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2546f55a-5b2f-4235-889f-4c5912334888', 'Whisk vinegar, lemon juice, shallot, and mustard in a medium bowl. Whisking constantly, gradually add oil. Whisk until emulsified; season vinaigrette with kosher salt and pepper. Stir in thyme.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.402', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.842');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60d99317-2f9a-4d3c-b609-eaed90684591', 'Toss watercress, radicchio, carrots, turnips, oranges, kumquats (if using), and toasted walnuts in a large bowl. Drizzle with vinaigrette, season with sea salt and pepper, and toss again to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.405', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.843');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bcd8d88b-066e-407e-8bf7-152cc26fdde2', 'Combine Port and small shallots in heavy medium saucepan. Simmer over medium heat until shallots are tender and Port glazes shallots, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes. Set aside. (Can be prepared 8 hours ahead. Keep at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.407', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.843');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a5425a8-9d1c-4db5-84d1-c0ce124297c6', 'Finely chop large shallot. Combine chopped shallot, drained lentils and 3 cups water in heavy large saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover sauce-pan and simmer until lentils are just tender, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.411', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.844');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dffebfd4-af70-4f70-aeef-275c8b92ad70', 'Rewarm Port mixture over medium-low heat. Stir oil and Port mixture into lentils. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer lentils to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.414', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.846');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0a6cb82-f842-4dee-a873-cda4008ee70d', '1. To roast the peppers: Cut off the stems, then cut the peppers in half lengthwise. Core, seed and carefully trim off all of the inner white connective tissue. Lay the pepper halves skin-side up in a single layer on a baking sheet. Broil about 3 inches from the heat until the skins are charred black, 12 to 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.418', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.847');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38ba2066-831c-47d8-a611-f5bef6d90e8b', '2. Remove the peppers from the broiler and place them in a paper or plastic bag; seal tightly and let the peppers steam inside the bag for about 15 minutes. Then slip off the charred skins and proceed with the recipe.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.421', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.847');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eb47eee3-d253-423c-a95d-c8e6ec34036a', '3. Arrange the peppers decoratively on a platter. Drizzle with the oil; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.424', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.847');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33657a91-b88f-49ea-9e84-766cf3d91132', '4. Place garlic slivers attractively around the peppers. Scatter with the capers and sprinkle generously with the oregano leaves. Serve the toasted peasant bread alongside the peppers in a napkin-lined basket.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.428', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.848');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('202357e0-5376-4b00-a641-4eada1d9b987', 'Cook two 10-ounce bags fresh spinach (not baby) in a large pot of boiling salted water just until wilted, 1-2 minutes. Drain, then transfer to a bowl of ice water; let cool. Drain and squeeze out excess water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.432', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.848');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe460bc3-660c-4915-9fe0-264c2325ef9d', 'Heat 2 tablespoons toasted sesame oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add 2 chopped garlic cloves and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute. Add spinach, 2 tablespoons reduced-sodium soy sauce, and 1 teaspoon distilled white vinegar. Stir to combine; season with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.436', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.848');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f452da1-c645-4369-82af-a2d778c31347', '1. Wash spinach leaves thoroughly under cold running water, drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.439', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.849');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b3487004-225c-49c3-8b29-856969baeb5f', '2. Heat the oil in a wok or skillet. Using a medium-high flame, cook the bamboo shoots in the oil approximately 45 seconds, stirring constantly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.442', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.849');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a84b8379-4449-4d73-b486-755f771f3efc', '3. Add spinach and stir until wilted.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.445', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.849');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1862e277-4b6e-4636-8fde-3f0dc9ddffac', '4. Add salt and sugar, and cook, stirring, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.449', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9aa3dc03-058e-42c4-ab42-cc821ae9ec3f', '5. Transfer to a hot platter, but do not add the liquid from the pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.452', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d613295e-cae5-429d-b302-d0a4bd956172', 'Spoon sauce into bowl or pitcher and serve with platter of sliced fresh fruit, such as:', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.455', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('01175b65-8643-42b7-9f9c-8232654047e7', 'Oranges', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.458', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57db1f41-e11a-4d3e-95d5-f3644aee92b8', 'Cantaloupe', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.462', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.851');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15ea5382-bf81-4ad2-9a99-0730725d0118', 'Kiwi', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.465', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.851');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b05df263-da4d-4740-880b-8896aa1cfd68', 'Strawberries', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.469', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.852');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7117b6c-507d-4567-b0aa-5432220aaa29', 'Bananas', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.472', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.852');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d25c0b75-3686-4d59-898c-72a5af0ffcb0', 'Serve with:', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.475', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.852');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3129c591-4f47-4f48-88b9-fafecee0305d', 'Quartered limes', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.479', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c2e4997-87cb-4e34-941e-0d2ab39e2db7', 'Yogurt', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.484', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27fdde43-af39-40ef-aa96-464b709d729f', 'Granola', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.487', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fa18f74-c231-4a61-ac99-888839fa2af1', 'Whisk together lemon juice, sugar, salt, cumin, and cayenne in a large bowl until sugar and salt are dissolved. Add carrots and figs and toss well. Let stand, uncovered, at room temperature, tossing occasionally, until carrots are wilted, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.491', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('828b7507-6362-41fa-b5fd-aa1674182340', '1. Cut McIntosh apples into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces. Cut Granny Smith apples into smaller dice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.494', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c65680f-4c33-4cb3-8b93-eef33ff2d2db', '2. Combine apples and cider in a very large stainless steel or enamel saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat and boil gently for 20 minutes or until mixture is reduced by half.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0c30e0e-52c1-40db-8d08-6d5c48dd1692', '3. Stir in sugar and lemon juice. Return to a boil, reduce heat, and boil gently for about 25 minutes or until mixture is very thick. There should still be some tender apple chunks remaining. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.501', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e0e41f7-5e79-40bc-9aa6-4ea81e7457d8', '4. Ladle into sterilized jars and process as directed for Shorter Time Processing Procedure .', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.504', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3dbbc48-5d42-4a0d-b5f8-15edf61eebdf', 'Add 2 tsp (10 mL) ground cinnamon and 1/2 tsp (2 mL) each ground cloves and allspice with the sugar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.507', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be678101-610a-4cc2-b6ac-e9d22b54aecd', 'Bring vinegar, salt, and 1 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in onion. Let cool. Drain before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.76', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e850f3b2-61ae-4a08-891c-90ff55da21b4', '1. Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add the shallot and cook until soft, about 2 minutes. Add the vinegar, juniper berries, caraway seeds, mustard seeds, thyme, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to a boil and cook until the sugar and salt are dissolved, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Let sit for 15 minutes then strain into a small bowl, discarding the solids. Slowly whisk in the remaining 1/2 cup oil until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1c5f52e4-1664-44c8-a027-1af493ee0699', '2. Heat your grill to high for direct grilling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.514', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dbe441b1-5e4c-4126-9e8d-03fc00b4eda2', '3. Brush the cut sides of the radicchio with oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill, cut side down, until golden brown and slightly charred, 2 to 3 minutes. Brush the tops with oil, flip over the radicchio, and continue grilling until just heated through, 2 to 3 minutes longer. Remove from the grill. Thinly slice the radicchio and put it in a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.518', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39470584-6a71-4d9f-b97f-1084cdaccb8e', '4. Remove the kale from the water and shake gently to get some of the water off. Season with salt and pepper and place on the grill. Cook until slightly wilted and charred on all sides, about 30 seconds per side. Remove from the grill. Thinly slice and add to the radicchio.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.521', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eadf2912-b065-4ae0-8641-9f8995ca7889', '5. Add the dressing to the radicchio and kale and toss to coat. Let sit at room temperature for 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.524', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('efb8bd71-b514-4e48-88f4-03a5032e4174', 'Boil apple concentrate in small saucepan over medium heat until reduced to 1/4 cup, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Whisk in vinegar, oil, mustard, and mustard seeds. Season vinaigrette with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewarm before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.527', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.856');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e1104c0-6981-4829-8445-9edc50ced497', 'Cook beans in medium pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes; drain well. Transfer beans to large bowl; cool slightly. Add greens, onion, radishes, and pickles. Toss with enough vinaigrette to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.531', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.856');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('295cb142-1629-44b5-a65e-f5461266d799', 'Mash onion and chiles with 3/4 teaspoon salt in a molcajete or with a mortar and pestle, or mince and mash with a heavy knife. Transfer to a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.534', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.856');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f80cf494-0476-4fcb-a68a-3bafbe4746fd', 'Pit and peel avocados and mash in bowl with chile mixture. Stir in cilantro and lime juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.538', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.856');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0ca8a4a-fa26-4c22-8f26-da07b2e82224', 'Whisk together vinegar, sugar, and salt in a small bowl until sugar is dissolved, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified. Toss together cucumber, jicama, ginger, and dressing in a bowl until combined well, then let stand, covered and chilled, 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.541', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.857');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb8b2d61-292d-4fdc-9898-1609a7c8142c', 'Stir first 8 ingredients in medium bowl to blend. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Let stand 30 minutes to blend flavors.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.544', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.857');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70210ca4-b205-4744-aee7-46ccd2a8c53f', 'Cook green beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer beans to cold water to cool. Drain well. Pat dry with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.547', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.857');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf40d1d4-2b52-4115-8314-50e28ad41164', 'Return water to boil. Add pasta and cook until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring often, about 2 minutes. Drain. Rinse pasta under cold water. Drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.551', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.859');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('003a54f1-37dc-48ea-b4d6-88507b4eb7d4', 'Combine green beans, pasta, carrots, green onions and dressing in large bowl. Toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.859');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c1ec385-8daf-48d2-b73b-4c2cb47271e4', 'Preheat the oven to 425°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.557', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.86');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('324322ae-e5c7-47ac-92f2-d503c1e50a47', 'Toss carrots with oil and salt and pepper to taste in a shallow (1-inch-deep) baking pan. Roast in middle of oven, stirring once, until barely tender, about 20 minutes. Leave oven on.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.56', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.861');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6ee7ee32-766b-4279-bbbf-87082b7d4523', 'Stir together vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Drizzle over carrots, shaking pan to coat, then roast until carrots are tender and vinegar is evaporated, 5 to 8 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.564', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.861');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8906c37a-cff0-4b31-beb7-7d984884d331', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the vinegar, mustard, and salt, and season with black pepper. Whisk in the olive oil in a steady stream to make a smooth, emulsified dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.568', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.861');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00a34de3-277e-476a-af81-4b266d1134b0', 'Toss the endive, apples, and walnuts together in a large serving bowl. Drizzle with the dressing, toss well, and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.571', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.862');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24aee5d2-01f7-4657-a83c-f8fb72a9b5dd', 'Stir first 5 ingredients in small saucepan over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer until liquid is syrupy and slightly reduced, about 8 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.574', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.863');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a44b95a-c533-4dc2-87ce-7d18e655cd25', 'Arrange orange and kiwi slices in shallow bowl. Pour hot syrup and spices over fruit. Chill at least 1 hour and up to 4 hours. Sprinkle almonds over; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.577', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.865');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c9973a7-bec2-4268-a534-f4f6e55546e8', 'Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in large nonstick skillet or wok over high heat. Add tofu; stir gently until starting to brown around edges, about 4 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer to bowl. Add 3 tablespoons oil, ginger and garlic to skillet; stir 1 minute. Add mushrooms; stir-fry until tender and golden around edges, about 5 minutes. Add broccoli, bell peppers and green onions; stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Return tofu to skillet; stir to mix. Stir in sake, soy sauce and sesame oil; simmer 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to large bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.581', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.865');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('300c5fb3-f706-4970-b043-7fe077baf626', 'Bring 1/2 cup water and sugar to boil in small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Simmer 5 minutes. Cool syrup completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.584', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.866');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11902372-8318-4300-93aa-43728ab051e0', 'Combine Champagne, rum, and pomegranate juice in punch bowl. Add enough syrup to sweeten to taste. Mix in lemon slices, pomegranate seeds, and mint leaves. Add ice block to bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.587', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.866');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de1addcd-48f4-4bc8-984d-c3f818b4ae21', 'Mince and mash garlic to a paste with 1 teaspoon salt. Purée remaining ingredients with garlic paste in food processor until almost smooth. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.59', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.867');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f323f985-6512-42a3-8417-fd7b229810b3', 'Cut orange into 1/4-inch-thick rounds; cut rounds into 1/4-inch cubes. Place in heavy medium saucepan; add 3 cups water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Drain, rinse, and drain well. Boil again with 3 cups water; rinse and drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.593', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.867');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00fda5f2-0e3c-4046-8385-d1d1ebace9d8', 'Return orange cubes to same pan. Add 3/4 cup water, 1/2 cup sugar, and 1 cinnamon stick. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil gently until all liquid evaporates, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.597', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.868');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4bf427ac-5e63-4217-be11-09993621f3ec', 'Add basil, 2 tablespoons oil and minced garlic to peppers. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.41', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.318');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('040317ab-3c18-42dd-a68d-eb313b38eed9', 'Bring brown sugar, rum, vinegar, allspice, 1/4 cup water, and 1 cinnamon stick to boil in saucepan. Mix in cranberries. Cook until thick syrup forms, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Mix in orange; cook 1 minute. Transfer chutney to small bowl; cool. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.6', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.868');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46a30fce-5f8a-450b-8174-bbb9e3a1981d', 'Cut out stems and center ribs from chard, discarding any tough parts (see Cooks'' notes), then chop. Wash leaves well, then cut in half crosswise (leave whole if on the smaller side).', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.603', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.869');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('250eaeee-b311-4b2c-b1a2-0ece41a929e0', 'Heat oil in a wide heavy pot (5- to 7-quart capacity) over medium heat until shimmering, then cook onion, stirring occasionally, until it begins to soften, about 5 minutes. Add chard stems and ribs, the water, and 1/2 teaspoon salt, and cook, covered, until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.607', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.869');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5113a0d7-d837-4524-87be-f77766dde683', 'Increase heat to medium-high. Add leaves in handfuls, turning with tongs and adding more as previous batches wilt, until all leaves have been added to pot. Cover with lid, then reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring once or twice, until just tender (do not overcook), 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in horseradish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.61', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.87');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('053c5a15-a2fd-4069-a333-da6221b53875', 'Bring first 3 ingredients to boil in large saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves and brushing down sides of pan with wet pastry brush. Attach candy thermometer to sides of pan and boil syrup until thermometer registers 225°F, about 6 minutes. Mix in strawberries. Return mixture to boil, reduce heat, and simmer until jam thickens and thermometer registers 216°F, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour. Transfer jam to small bowl and cool. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.87');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70c0781d-638c-441d-b4a8-f72c496e7253', 'Purée chiles, garlic, lemongrass, oil, ginger, cumin, sugar, and 1 tsp. salt in a blender or food processor until smooth. Score cut sides of eggplant in a cross-hatch pattern with the tip of a sharp knife. Coat each eggplant liberally with curry paste; set aside any remaining paste. Let eggplants sit at least 10 minutes and up to 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.618', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.871');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d8dd7b9-507f-4dc9-80d5-65d41ca7a207', 'Prepare a grill for medium-high heat. Lightly season eggplants with salt and grill, turning occasionally, until browned and tender, about 5 minutes per side. Serve with reserved curry paste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.621', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.871');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e46feb9-7461-44b2-a996-741b30e57ec2', 'Marinade can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.625', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.872');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77b912b1-f0f4-4900-a70b-fd2ab176f42d', 'Trim stem ends from broccoli rabe and discard. Cut remainder crosswise into 1 1/2-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.628', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.872');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('208e39f1-8a06-45f9-98bf-18b79944e4ae', 'Cook broccoli rabe and peas in a 4- to 6-quart pot of boiling salted water until broccoli rabe is wilted and stems are crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain well in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.631', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.873');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dad7797d-6a02-4489-aaf8-a4d0b4c4ef60', 'Heat oil with garlic in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat, turning garlic frequently, until garlic is golden, 1 to 2 minutes, then discard garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.635', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.874');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3294ef98-1fb3-4d19-a5ff-d0c021551f58', 'Add broccoli rabe, peas, salt, and pepper to skillet and sauté, stirring, until well coated with garlic oil, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.638', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.875');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('431ca061-6779-44b2-a000-a7a5b362ebc9', 'Combine all the ingredients and mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.64', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.877');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a30b5b5f-33e7-4d9c-be5f-1b6f3a4c62fa', 'In a large saucepan cover potatoes with salted cold water by 1 inch and simmer, covered, until just tender, about 15 to 30 minutes, depending on size of potatoes. In a colander drain potatoes and rinse under cold water to cool. With a sharp knife peel potatoes and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.644', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.878');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8deccd3f-13e8-4834-b92f-fff2a0ef4a1c', 'While potatoes are boiling, prepare grill. In a small bowl whisk together oil, salt, and cumin and brush some onto both sides of potato slices, reserving remaining cumin oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.647', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.879');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ccabe9e5-b827-4fb4-a5b9-5b2c035ef76f', 'Grill slices on an oiled rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals until golden brown, about 1 minute on each side, and transfer with tongs to a platter. Thinly slice scallion diagonally and sprinkle over potatoes. Whisk lime juice into remaining cumin oil with salt and pepper to taste and drizzle over potatoes. Serve potato salad with lime wedges and sprinkled with coriander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.651', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.88');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('673d12a0-f430-40c4-9f45-59de1ba665b4', 'Preheat a heavy-bottomed skillet, preferably cast iron, over low heat. Add the oil and the onions and toss the onions to coat. Cover and cook for 20 minutes, leaving a little gap for steam to escape. Stir occasionally, every 5 minutes or so. Onions should turn amber, but not burn, although a couple of darker spots are fine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.655', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.881');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5400f99a-f9a5-4c15-9fbf-e8caec8ccf40', 'Remove the cover and turn the heat up just a bit, to a medium setting. Stir often for 10 more minutes. Onions should become a darker amber, and some of the moisture should evaporate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.659', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.882');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d7bbf6b-659a-46ec-8af4-f571e030f2d6', 'In a medium-size pot, cover potatoes in water. Place a lid on the pot and bring to a boil. Once boiling, cook for about 20 more minutes or until potatoes are easily pierced with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.882');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f607384-f0fe-4def-8dd1-638eff26f071', 'Meanwhile, in a large pan, sauté the onions in oil over medium heat for about 7 minutes. Turn the heat off but continue to stir occasionally because they could still burn from the hot pan. When the potatoes are done boiling, drain them well and add them to the pan with the onions. Just mash them right in there with a potato masher; that way you are sure to get all the oil, plus you save a dish. Add the salt and pepper. Make sure potatoes are mashed well and fluffy. Set aside to cool a bit.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.666', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.883');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('26876c83-e6ce-4bc2-8e8d-1d93f7e83138', 'You know I don''t usually advise cooking with margarine, but I really love it with the mushrooms here, I think because growing up the mushrooms I ate were really buttery. Anyway, this filling is really simple. In a large skillet, melt the margarine over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and sauté for about 7 minutes, until the mushrooms are soft.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.669', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.883');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a67739d-a90c-42c3-b5aa-cba560516650', 'Before adding the sauerkraut to the pan, give it a squeeze over the sink to get out as much water as you can. It''s important to do this so that your pierogi don''t get all wet. You''ll need to add the sauerkraut to the pan a cup at a time. Add to the pan and cook for about 10 minutes, cooking out any excess water. Season with the pepper. The filling shouldn''t look dry (a small amount of water is okay), but you shouldn''t be able to slosh around in it in rain boots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f9585b7-0d4b-4e60-aaa7-8e68af22fa43', 'Using on/off turns, mince garlic and ginger in processor. Add beans, reserved bean liquid, cashew butter, rice vinegar, soy sauce, chili-garlic sauce, and ground star anise. Process mixture to coarse puree. Add cilantro and green onion; process to combine. Transfer to bowl; garnish with whole star anise, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.754', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.9');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3314e9d7-effb-43b5-bb10-bf16d556e7c0', 'Preheat oven to 400° F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:33.593', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.604');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4020636b-e7fd-4bce-ac6d-9bcf13a7cbe8', 'This is really the brunt of the work in this recipe. If you''re like me, you have limited counter space and so rolling out dough can be a hassle. I make the dough last because the mess becomes much more manageable when you don''t have to prep on the counter afterwards. It also gives your filling some time to cool. So make sure you clean up after your filling making and get someone to do the dishes for you. I find that a serene counter makes all the difference in dough making.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('680da4a2-b02f-4d33-b7a9-1cca7137b633', 'Pour the water and oil into a large bowl. Add 2 cups of the flour and the salt, keeping one cup aside. Use a fork to stir the flour in, and as it starts to come together, use your hands to knead until a loose dough forms (about 3 minutes).', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.679', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.885');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e614955-d0d9-4fba-b6f5-e2a603c48d3f', 'Sprinkle your counter with flour, then turn the dough out onto it and knead. Add the reserved cup of flour a little bit at a time, working it into the dough, until it is very smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. If it''s too sticky, you can add a little bit more fl our and knead it in, sometimes up to 1/4 cup extra. Conversely, if you get a good-feeling, smooth, elastic dough with less than the extra cup of fl our, then that''s okay, too.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.683', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.885');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d93c6ed-8894-47fc-ab7b-bb55e6185d86', 'Now we roll the dough out, and also bring a salted pot of water to boil—the largest pot you''ve got—for boiling the pierogi.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.686', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.886');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68d73845-96db-4663-810f-cb73664ade4f', 'Divide the dough in half and make sure your counter is clean and sprinkled with a dusting of flour to prevent sticking. Roll half the dough out to about 1/16 of an inch thick, which is to say, very thin but not see-through. I roll it into an 18 x 10-inch rectangle, but as long as you have the thinness going, the shape doesn''t matter so much. Sprinkle the top with a light dusting of flour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.689', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.887');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12a4b067-2ded-4ba8-bdc1-f939f34d887a', 'Now we''re going to make circles. I use the top of a glass that is 3 1/2 inches in diameter, but somewhere between 3 1/2 and 4 inches is perfect. Use a glass or a cookie cutter. Have ready a lightly floured plate to place the finished circles on, and go ahead and fi rmly press your glass or cookie cutter into the dough, as close together as you can. Pull together the excess dough and set aside. Place circles on the floured plate and transfer to the fridge while you repeat with the other half of the dough. Combine the excess dough and see if you can get a few more wrappers out of the deal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.693', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.887');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9685795c-2325-4a2e-9b34-cf4cf9963fc0', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and sauté until tender, about 5 minutes. Add rice and allspice and stir 30 seconds. Add 1 1/2 cups water and currants and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.697', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('231fa810-fbfa-4c87-8c3f-3716d880da0d', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy small skillet over medium-low heat. Add pine nuts and sauté until golden brown, about 6 minutes. Mix nut mixture into rice. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.7', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a1e74ef-04c3-4468-844f-b9656af754d6', 'Bring large pot of water to boil. Add grape leaves and stir to separate. Turn off heat; let stand 1 minute. Drain. Rinse with cold water to cool; drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.704', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c07a8fc0-1f99-4df5-bfc7-66bc0d609f2a', 'Cover bottom of heavy large skillet or Dutch oven with about 10 grape leaves, pressing about 1 inch up sides of skillet. Arrange 1 leaf, vein side up, on work surface. Place 1 rounded tablespoon rice filling near stem. Fold in sides, then roll up jelly roll fashion. Repeat with remaining filling and leaves. Arrange stuffed leaves, seam side down, close together in leaf-lined skillet. Drizzle 3 tablespoons oil over. Add 1/4 cup water and fresh lemon juice. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook 50 minutes. Cool completely. (Grape leaves can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.707', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0bf72e60-f415-4c81-b13d-a51b2f7a351f', 'Arrange stuffed grape leaves on platter. Garnish with lemon and parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.71', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.89');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e747d6e-d91d-459a-b63c-700333e1ebf8', 'Halve, pit, and peel avocados. Coarsely mash in a bowl. Stir in onion, chiles, 1/4 cup lime juice, and 1 1/4 teaspoons salt, then fold in pomegranate seeds, mango, and cilantro. Season with salt and additional lime juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.713', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.892');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('222dd65e-5a4a-42c2-bad0-825a2c140056', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray large baking sheet with nonstick spray. Toss onion and next 5 ingredients together on prepared baking sheet; spread in single layer. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake vegetables until tender and brown around edges, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.717', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.892');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ebbe510-2a8e-4a5b-97af-a9ca684734b2', 'Cut large chiles into 1/4 inch rings. Pierce small chiles 3-4 times with a skewer. Pack all chiles in a clean 1-quart jar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.72', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.893');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0454e3fa-9e88-4aeb-bb13-355abaa9a126', 'Bring vinegar, all remaining ingredients, and 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour hot brine over peppers; seal jar. Let cool, then refrigerate. Serve within 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.724', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.893');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b55620e5-0df3-4341-acae-2a7c78d0a7d4', 'Finely grind coriander and fenugreek seeds with a mortar and pestle or an electric coffee/spice grinder.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.726', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.894');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('573f21b1-07b9-48f7-8ba2-5068e82b4c1d', 'Finely chop cilantro, basil, and garlic together in a food processor. Add bell pepper and jalape‱os and pulse until finely chopped.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.897');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ebdfbd00-034b-465a-bee3-bb32bab39501', 'Add vinegar, coriander mixture, and salt and blend until just combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.734', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.898');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c69198d7-9d79-42a9-afc4-720421ce901b', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion; sauté until golden, about 5 minutes. Add cumin and garlic; stir 1 minute. Add tomatoes with their juices; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until most liquid has cooked away, about 5 minutes. Stir in edamame, corn and broth. Simmer until most broth is absorbed, about 6 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl. Sprinkle with cilantro and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.898');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf76b0a7-f058-4d1d-bcc9-7926fbcfc40b', 'Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil in a 1-quart heavy nonreactive saucepan over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer until slightly syrupy and reduced to about 1/2 cup, about 15 minutes. Pour into a heatproof bowl and cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.745', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.899');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de4d7828-9ffc-4d7d-a65c-72dbeef8614d', 'Thinly slice cabbage and onion separately. In a small bowl stir together water, vinegar, and sugar until sugar is dissolved. In a 10- to 12-inch heavy skillet cook onion in oil over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until softened. Add cabbage and sauté over moderately high heat, stirring, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in vinegar mixture and pepper until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.75', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.899');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad853040-2dc6-4224-940a-3774f41cb2d3', '*Available in the Asian foods section of many supermarkets and at Asian markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.757', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c83671e-02f6-4838-a9af-101143d35329', 'Rub oiled side of each bread slice with cut side of garlice halves. Divide peppers among bread slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.415', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.319');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d5d021ee-89ab-4787-90e7-6f2563b0768f', 'Whisk together lime juice, soy sauce, ginger, sugar, and oil in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('823b926a-e1fc-4d12-bdf6-652c9b8e5e80', 'Using pestle or blunt end of wooden spoon, mash all ingredients and 1 tablespoon freshly ground black pepper in mortar or small bowl 2 to 3 minutes. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.767', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9619a3cb-5c87-47bf-86de-98dbfe477f5e', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Place garlic on foil; drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil. Wrap garlic in foil; roast until soft, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.77', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.902');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22bc0786-c62b-4870-b399-ac19daf57a5b', 'Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in large pot over medium-high heat. Add spinach and garlic with oil from foil packet. Sauté until spinach is wilted, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer spinach to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.774', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.902');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e130d3a-f4f9-48ce-b216-70610407fc6e', 'Combine the tomatillos, jalapeño, cilantro, garlic, green onions, salt, water, and half of the avocado in a blender or food processor. Purée until smooth. Check for seasoning and adjust if necessary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.777', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.902');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1d15ac46-62b7-4183-a8e3-bd9d27d20c8f', 'In a 12-inch skillet bring water and soy sauce with garlic to a boil. Add broccoli rabe and cook, covered, over moderately high heat 2 minutes. Remove cover and cook until water is evaporated and broccoli rabe is tender. Season broccoli rabe with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.781', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0680b05c-3526-4b25-a60b-06fcc5701cc7', 'Heat oven to 350°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.784', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6e2debe-6a41-47ce-b5c4-917f470a1413', 'Spread pine nuts in a small baking sheet and bake until pale golden, about 8 minutes. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.787', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97d688e5-638a-4f97-887b-a3129d7b5609', 'Using mandoline, thinly slice fennel bulb crosswise, beginning at base, into a large bowl, stopping about halfway up bulb (reserve remaining bulb for another use). Toss fennel with radicchio, frisée, and mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.79', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f676b99c-d078-4714-b3ea-8c1485bfa7fa', 'Whisk together oil, vinegar, shallot, Dijon mustard, and 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.793', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e890bff1-7b72-432a-96ab-31e5d10b4138', 'Toss salad well with vinaigrette and pine nuts. Season to taste, if necessary, with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.797', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64e1e112-3af4-4f77-8dcf-5f217b1065d2', 'Using back of large spoon, mash first 3 ingredients in bowl. Let stand 5 minutes. Strain mixture through fine sieve set over bowl, pressing on solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.801', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa1c14b9-8e63-410c-8efc-247f4cd1de18', 'Pour 2 tablespoons kumquat syrup into each of four 6-ounce Champagne flutes. Fill each with 2/3 cup Champagne.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.804', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2a631807-54c2-49de-af37-9143130a5866', 'Thinly slice onion and mince garlic. Peel gingerroot and mince. In a sieve rinse lentils and drain. In a 2-quart heavy saucepan cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil over moderate heat, stirring, until golden. Add gingerroot and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add lentils and water and gently boil, uncovered, until lentils fall apart, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.806', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1b7b2e6-d61c-468d-a6ac-a8dfccacecb8', 'While lentils are boiling, rinse tofu and trim ends. Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes and gently press between paper towels to remove excess moisture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.809', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.905');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('410c4ca6-fbc1-4f27-b890-941e86932a3e', 'In a small heavy skillet heat remaining tablespoon oil over moderate heat until hot but not smoking and cook cumin seeds, stirring, until a shade darker, about 1 minute. Add garam masala, salt, and cayenne and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 15 to 30 seconds. Stir hot spice oil into lentils and gently stir in tofu cubes. Let curry stand, covered, 5 minutes to allow flavors to develop. Stir in cilantro and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.813', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.905');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81ef5191-ba88-4705-aeb9-e16c0c39c368', 'Serve curry over rice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.817', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.905');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9bd36f61-6fe0-4e59-aa78-1c5401ad7abb', 'In a bowl toss together the radishes, the cabbage, the carrots, the onion, the lemon juice, the sugar, the oil, the coriander, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.82', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.905');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d5be050d-d095-49bf-a095-a811586605bf', 'Heat the oil in a medium skillet. Toss in the garlic, sautéing until just fragrant, then add the chard and cook for a few minutes. Sprinkle on a little salt, the paprika, cumin, and harissa, and cook for another minute, stirring. Pour the vinegar or lemon juice into the pan, and cook for another minute, or until it has begun to evaporate. Season with salt and freshly ground pepper to taste. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.823', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.906');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77734ef8-87b2-45bc-99d9-f6e538bdadc4', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray heavy large baking sheet with nonstick spray. Arrange bell peppers, mushrooms, and zucchini on prepared sheet; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until peppers and zucchini are brown in spots, turning twice, about 35 minutes. Sprinkle with thyme, mint, and orange peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.826', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.907');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24bbd0f6-1594-4404-b2ce-7ff5f6d2fd12', 'Whisk oil, vinegar, and fennel seeds to blend in small bowl. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper. Mix beans, fennel, onion, and all but 1 tablespoon dressing in medium bowl. Season salad with salt and pepper. Spoon salad into center of large platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.829', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.908');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e44e83b-77ca-46a7-a556-298b8e927b15', 'Toss greens with remaining 1 tablespoon dressing in large bowl; arrange greens around bean salad. Place peppers, mushrooms, and zucchini atop greens. Garnish with tomato wedges and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.832', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.908');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37b44bf1-d8bc-4965-95aa-161a802c2f83', 'Put rice in a bowl and wash in several changes of cold water until water is clear. Drain in a sieve 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.836', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.908');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cdb48c26-eb40-4bed-bbcd-a0241c36976f', 'Soak rice in water (3 cups) in a 4-quart heavy pot 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.839', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.909');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('73b560e1-9ea5-4316-9c8d-480289a43446', 'Cover pot with lid and bring rice just to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until water is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes (avoid lifting lid). Remove from heat; let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Stir gently with a heatproof rubber spatula, folding from top to bottom of pot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.842', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.909');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1d04742f-7795-4140-8e19-8ae5b1fe0da8', 'Cook beans in a large saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain in a colander and transfer to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. Drain beans well and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.846', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.91');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1df1168-50a2-422b-979e-7aceb91b0b0b', 'Heat oil in a heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook shallots, stirring, until just softened. Add garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add bell peppers and chile and sauté over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until peppers are softened, about 3 minutes. Add vinegar and sugar and cook, stirring, until liquid is evaporated, about 2 minutes. Cool relish and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.85', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.91');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('528327e7-b22f-4325-8324-972a4678a3f4', 'Serve beans topped with relish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.853', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.912');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7619044-eb86-4af7-a2d9-22214c6dbf51', '• 1 to 2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.516', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.334');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc0201aa-8601-4f07-b288-94f543614844', 'Combine 1 cup water and sugar in medium saucepan. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Transfer to bowl and chill until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.856', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.913');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0d7b2ad5-ec7b-4b4d-b4d0-27c37a8f9241', 'Puree quartered strawberries in processor until smooth. Add lime juice and sugar syrup; process until blended. Chill mixture until cold, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.859', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.914');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('db9fbf76-b8cb-4d41-b819-d456b2a06c8d', 'Transfer strawberry mixture to ice cream maker and process according to manufacturer''s instructions. Spoon sorbet into container; cover and freeze until firm, about 4 hours. DO AHEAD Can be made 3 days ahead. Keep frozen.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.92');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f10ff98a-78ff-4dcb-9b38-52d436bd8150', 'Scoop sorbet into individual glasses or bowls; garnish with strawberries. Serve Shortbread Cookies alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.865', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.923');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bd66196-d0cc-4a65-9c11-cf4846bed6a9', 'Combine the vinegar, mustard, and salt. Whisk in the oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.868', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.924');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8185c055-b525-4d88-8743-bbb820655521', 'Brush large bowl with oil. Mix warm water and sugar in processor. Sprinkle yeast over; stir to dissolve. Let stand until mixture bubbles, about 10 minutes. Add flour, 4 1/2 tablespoons oil, and salt. Process 1 minute. Transfer dough to floured surface; knead until smooth, about 5 minutes. Transfer to prepared bowl, turning to coat with oil. Cover bowl with plastic wrap. Let dough rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in volume, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.872', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.925');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('043ac8b5-23b8-40fa-bf0f-ddf1024663d1', 'Sprinkle cornmeal over rimmed baking sheet. Divide dough into 6 equal portions; roll each into ball. Space dough balls evenly on baking sheet. Lightly spray large sheet of plastic wrap with nonstick spray; place over dough, sprayed side down. Refrigerate 1 hour before rolling and baking.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.875', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.931');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad9b9d28-d8e4-41f1-a535-54acc2485669', 'Shred carrots with a mandoline or other manual slicer or in a food processor fitted with shredding disk. Julienne radishes. Whisk together zest, juice, oil, and salt and pepper to taste and toss with vegetables.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.878', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.933');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3eda87fd-bcf8-4641-a5fe-d31ee69fbfe8', 'Blend miso with garlic, ginger, 1 cup cool water and 1 tablespoon vinegar in a food processor until smooth. Transfer miso broth to a bowl; stir in 2 cups cool water. Divide broth, tofu, snow peas, radishes and scallions among 4 bowls. Toss pea shoots with remaining 1/2 tablespoon vinegar and oil; garnish each bowl before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.881', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.933');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f209d2ef-d9cf-42fd-9011-5b37f778e632', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Cut tops and root ends off beets. Wrap beets in aluminum foil and bake until tender, about 50 minutes. Cool slightly. Peel beets. Slice beets into rounds; stack rounds and cut into strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.885', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.935');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46e568a7-7259-4d96-8c7e-cfe49312ade1', 'Combine fresh lemon juice and honey in small bowl. Gradually mix in olive oil. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper. (Dressing can be prepared 1 day ahead. Wrap beets tightly and refrigerate. Cover dressing and let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.888', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.937');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c7d2bc6-cb48-41a6-9051-476e5752464d', 'Place watercress in bowl and toss with enough dressing to coat. Arrange on platter. Top with fennel and then beets. Drizzle remaining dressing over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.892', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.94');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0a69279-3b8f-4389-8a47-11b577c207db', 'Peel gingerroot and slice thin. Cut slices into thin strips and in a saucepan simmer in 1 quart water 10 minutes. Drain gingerroot and discard water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.895', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.94');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b2b64922-332b-4caa-9591-a142a252f452', 'In a saucepan just large enough to hold pears lying on their sides bring 3 cups water to boil with gingerroot, sugar, Port, and lemon juice, stirring until sugar is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.898', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.941');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('58b44e7a-f4d7-4a88-a85e-5a7d84cef077', 'Peel pears, leaving stems intact, and cut a thin slice from bottom of each if necessary to enable pears to stand upright when served. Arrange pears on their sides in poaching liquid, adding enough of remaining water as necessary to just cover. Simmer pears, turning them occasionally, until tender, 20 to 40 minutes depending on ripeness. Carefully transfer pears with a slotted spoon to a bowl and boil poaching liquid until reduced to about 3/4 cup and slightly syrupy. Pour sauce over pears. Pears may be made 1 day ahead and cooled in sauce before being chilled, covered. Serve pears warm or chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.902', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.941');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7f0b7ee-2b23-4ed8-8a9b-b8050cb2b641', 'In a large heavy saucepan heat oil over moderate heat until hot but not smoking and cook cuminseed, cinnamon stick, and bay leaf, stirring, until mixture is fragrant and cuminseed is several shades darker (be careful not to burn it).', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.905', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.942');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a7415dad-50cb-4533-a38c-9f8e590e5b49', 'Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened. Add rice and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add water, currants, saffron, and salt and bring to a boil, covered. Reduce heat to very low and simmer rice, covered, 20 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.908', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.943');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9d3fc7d4-34f7-40b4-a4a3-e339e2568e3f', 'Let rice stand 5 minutes. Discard cinnamon stick and bay leaf and stir in pine nuts and mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.911', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.953');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e864c930-a822-4821-b822-fa3aa3a7c4db', 'Position 1 rack in top third and 1 rack in bottom third of oven and preheat to 450°F. Brush 2 large rimmed baking sheets with 1 tablespoon olive oil each. Place potatoes on 1 prepared sheet; drizzle 3 tablespoons olive oil over and toss to coat. Spread potatoes in single layer; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place potatoes on top rack of oven and roast 10 minutes. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons shallots and garlic over. Transfer potatoes to bottom rack of oven and continue to roast until tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes longer. Remove from oven.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.954');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c644f39d-1956-4bfd-8c3f-8d3d3b66ebf3', 'Meanwhile, toss mushrooms on second prepared baking sheet with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread in single layer and roast mushrooms on top rack of oven until golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.919', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.955');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a96dd2ca-7e86-448b-b765-978e693dba5c', 'Add mushrooms to potatoes; stir to combine. do ahead Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Rewarm in 450°F oven until heated through, about 5 minutes, before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.922', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.957');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0beaa9c3-b9d0-486c-aa74-b2083d45fb19', 'Add parsley to potato-mushroom mixture and toss; season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.925', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.959');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e4621b4-abd0-4bc8-abf9-004254afd53c', 'Halve apricots lengthwise and pit. Cut each apricot half into 4 wedges and transfer to a heatproof bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.929', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ac73eb3-c059-4853-a078-12c00712d4f6', 'In a small saucepan bring water and sugar to a boil over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Stir in zest and wine and simmer 5 minutes. Pour syrup over apricots and stir in blackberries. Chill mixture 20 minutes. Serve compote with macaroons.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.932', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('987bdea4-0aeb-4c94-98e4-a60f799832df', 'Soften saffron in 1 tablespoon hot water and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.936', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8854b839-d0a1-427d-845e-cab2dc056742', 'Mix salsa with avocado, lime juice, olive oil, and chopped cilantro. Season with salt and pepper; chill until ready to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.703', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.083');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('52b97413-de56-42e7-a1c9-060e48f58e99', 'Cook onion in oil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 6 minutes. Add orzo and toast, stirring frequently, until fragrant, 2 to 4 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.939', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f762ffe0-58d7-49b5-9397-921ffef0225f', 'Stir in saffron mixture, remaining 2 cups water, and 1 teaspoon salt and simmer, covered, until orzo is just tender and liquid is absorbed, about 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.942', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7f11960-cfaf-48da-85ea-be21570da347', 'Sprinkle fennel bulb over orzo and let stand, covered, off heat 5 minutes. Stir fennel bulb into orzo, then serve sprinkled with fennel fronds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.945', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('877be898-81ff-47fc-8519-2334cbae2621', 'Cook green beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add radishes and cook 30 seconds longer. Drain beans and radishes. Rinse with cold water; drain well. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and toss to coat. Let marinate 1 hour at room temperature, tossing occasionally. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('747d1b56-48e6-4b28-8d0d-5be4e10cc263', 'Finely grind flaxseeds in coffee/spice grinder, then stir together with oats, almonds, pumpkin seeds, sunflower seeds, salt, oil, and syrup in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.962');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3cdc215d-931e-4fab-a4a3-4722a46a61a0', 'Spread mixture evenly in 2 large shallow baking pans (1 inch deep) and bake in upper and lower thirds of oven, stirring and switching position of pans halfway through baking, until golden brown, about 30 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.955', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.962');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb8bc2ce-8db1-4215-8547-6ed13faf6f72', 'Cool granola completely in pans on racks, then stir in ginger (if using) and apricots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.958', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.963');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('230dcefc-551e-4cc4-8a83-52cac6d88997', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Trim greens from beets. Cut off and discard stems. Coarsely chop leaves and reserve. Wrap each beet in foil. Place beets directly on oven rack and roast until tender when pierced with fork, about 1 hour 30 minutes. Cool. Peel beets, then cut each into 8 wedges. Place beets in medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.96', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.963');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0221e07e-17e4-4a00-8837-212f74fbf555', 'Cook beet greens in large saucepan of boiling water just until tender, about 2 minutes. Drain. Cool. Squeeze greens to remove excess moisture. Add greens to bowl with beets. Cut peel and white pith from oranges. Working over another bowl and using small sharp knife, cut between membranes to release segments. Add orange segments and onion to bowl with beet mixture. Whisk vinegar, oil, garlic, and orange peel in small bowl to blend; add to beet mixture and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour. Serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.964');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('629e40de-633b-4e60-9ca6-c1ed8613fbe3', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium; simmer until berries begin to burst, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Transfer to small bowl. Stir in parsley. Cover and chill until cold. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 days ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.964');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bfe59895-a394-4b4f-a9b6-712a999464c5', 'Stir together juice, liqueur, and sugar in a 2-quart pitcher until sugar is dissolved. Chill until cold, about 1 hour. Slowly pour in Prosecco, stirring to combine. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.971', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.965');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('953da8c6-3db9-47f3-b495-59098c8bc10f', 'Pour boiling water over bulgur in a bowl, then cover bowl tightly and let stand 30 minutes. Drain in a sieve if watery.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.974', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.965');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cd587013-03b0-4572-afa6-c32f9dbb0f56', 'Meanwhile, puré mint with oil in a blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.977', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.966');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ac3b51d-9ab5-4dd6-a28a-de8ab4265393', 'Toss bulgur with mint oil, lime juice, honeydew, onion, and salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.982', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.966');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec5ab114-06ce-43f3-846b-07bccf814add', 'Using a small slicer or a mandoline, slice the garlic very thin.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.985', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fdf19983-c0d2-437f-bb01-e35ad432a9ef', 'Heat the olive oil in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat until very hot. Line a plate with two paper towels. To test the temperature of the oil, add a slice of garlic. If it sizzles, add the rest of the garlic and cook until just crisp and light golden brown, a matter of seconds. Use a flat slotted skimmer to keep the slices from sticking together as they cook, and transfer them to the paper towels to drain the moment they turn color. (The oil can be strained and used for another batch or reserved for another use.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.989', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76dc784f-0d62-4bbf-874a-7554a22d3533', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add onions and garlic; sauté until tender and golden, about 9 minutes. Add squash; stir 2 minutes. Stir in chili powder and cumin. Stir in beans, broth, and tomatoes with juices; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until squash is tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in chard; simmer until chard is tender but still bright green, about 4 minutes longer. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Ladle chili into bowls and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.992', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('93fdab93-6690-48cb-90e3-de65e192f182', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a small jar; season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper. Shake to blend. DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill. Shake before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:22.996', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.968');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b5b787e-a990-4685-bf0b-8743bd4c36f0', 'Bring cranberries, horseradish, sugar, and water to a simmer in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring with a wooden spoon until sugar is dissolved. Simmer, uncovered, stirring and mashing berries frequently with spoon, until berries break down, 5 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.001', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.968');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('528bcc45-b73c-48ac-ab0e-4ba4c453626f', 'Serve sauce warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.004', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.968');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0924b5b-4dcc-4d97-89e1-bae9c25ff26e', 'Whisk first 5 ingredients in small bowl to blend; gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing generously with salt and pepper. Toss salad mix in large bowl with 1/4 cup dressing. Divide salad among 4 plates. Tuck mango and avocado into salad; drizzle some of remaining dressing over mango and avocado.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.008', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.969');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc457273-2c39-4281-82d3-03d739968a35', 'Very thinly slice cucumbers crosswise with slicer; toss with 1 teaspoon salt and drain in a colander 15 minutes. Rinse cucumbers under cold water, then squeeze handfuls to remove excess water; pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.011', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.97');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0af7bdd-acca-46d9-aa26-459a495f707b', 'Stir together wasabi powder and water in a bowl and let stand 5 minutes. Add vinegar, sugar, and soy sauce, whisking until sugar has dissolved. Add cucumbers and toss well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.016', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.971');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d68f5ac1-d59d-46d5-b484-4790dc7a11a7', '1. Cook the noodles in plenty of rapidly boiling water until al dente.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.02', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.971');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4bf2777c-7c4b-4787-a72d-ebd1da419cc5', '2. Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet or stir-fry pan. Add the onion and sauté over medium heat until golden.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.023', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.972');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ff80c72-5a47-4f93-8dff-5febed082992', '3. Add all the mushrooms and the wine to the pan. Cover and simmer over low heat until the mushrooms are tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in the tofu and lemon juice and heat gently just until heated through, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.026', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.972');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fdee322a-0a1b-49a4-bf8c-3d4396dce0ac', '4. Drain the noodles and transfer to a serving dish. Stir in the margarine and season with salt, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.974');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea593d2a-1295-4fe9-821b-d697f342f921', '5. To serve, place a bed of noodles on each plate, then top with some of the mushroom mixture. Garnish each serving with a sprinkling of parsley, if desired, plus a dusting of paprika.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.034', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.974');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6741b565-ded4-4496-9fe4-3a23442e68c4', 'Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water until tender when pierced with fork, about 15 minutes. Drain. Cool potatoes until lukewarm. Cut potatoes in half. Place in large bowl. Sprinkle wine over potatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.038', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.975');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('753ff03d-89d5-4d6b-bdf9-67e2d3507dfb', 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onions and sauté until tender, about 5 minutes. Add vinegar, mustard and sugar to skillet and stir to blend. Pour over potatoes and toss to coat. Add radishes, green onions, parsley and remaining 1 teaspoon olive oil and toss to blend. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.042', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.975');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78836468-f4cb-4531-9073-c43ffb9c42a2', 'Mound salad on platter. Surround with cucumber slices and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.046', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64bdd420-a467-4a2d-bcf2-124928e95d60', 'Scrape seeds from vanilla bean into heavy medium saucepan. Add bean, Sherry, cinnamon sticks, and star anise. Bring to simmer over medium heat. Add all dried fruits; return to simmer, stirring occasionally. Simmer until Sherry is almost evaporated, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Mix in enough pineapple juice by tablespoonfuls to moisten chutney. Transfer to bowl, cover, and refrigerate until cold, at least 3 hours. (Chutney can be made 1 day ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.051', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88ddb64a-0860-469e-85ad-573d64957250', 'Remove vanilla bean, cinnamon sticks, and star anise from chutney. Mix in mint and cilantro and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.055', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5282dcdc-8b6b-4d39-b461-5434510aed01', '*Brown star-shaped seedpods; available in the spice section of some supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and Asian markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.059', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.977');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('66cb8c99-591a-4c79-9367-1219f503d050', 'Fill a bowl with ice cubes and water. Blanch the chives in boiling water for 30 seconds, then drain immediately and put the chives in the ice water. Drain, wrap in paper towels, and squeeze out the excess water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.063', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.977');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe791772-43c2-4d58-8bda-495440c6fd93', 'Put the chives in a blender with the remaining ingredients and blend for 2 minutes; strain through a fine sieve. Transfer the oil to a plastic squeeze bottle if you like. The oil can be refrigerated for up to a month; bring to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.066', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.977');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9399e6a8-5431-4a02-96f4-501876e329b8', 'Wrap garlic cloves in aluminum foil. Prick eggplant all over. On a baking sheet roast garlic and eggplant in middle of oven 30 minutes, or until garlic is tender. Transfer garlic to a plate and continue to roast eggplant until blackened and collapsed, about 45 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.071', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.978');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('52bb1b8e-e753-44a3-9db9-5524febf7134', 'While eggplant is roasting, in a small skillet dry-roast seeds over moderate heat, shaking the skillet, until fragrant, being careful not to burn them, and in a mortar with a pestle, an electric spice grinder, or a cleaned coffee grinder grind fine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.075', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.98');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1d98ae5b-0f94-46a4-9b4f-10a446e30571', 'With a large spoon scrape eggplant flesh from skin, discarding skin, and chop coarse. Peel garlic cloves and with flat side of a knife mash to paste. In a bowl stir together eggplant, garlic paste, spice mixture, tomatoes, fresh coriander, lemon juice, oil, gingerroot, paprika, salt, and 2 tablespoons mint until combined well. Salad may be made 2 days ahead and kept chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.079', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.98');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9683b979-ef09-4ffd-b845-79e7d8a379af', 'Sprinkle salad with remaining 2 tablespoons mint and serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.083', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.981');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74b4bdc0-7e16-43b1-b478-7a1eaec0ff53', 'Heat 2 inches oil to 375°F in a wide 5- to 7-quart heavy pot (at least 4 inches deep) over medium heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.087', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.981');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82cb8131-8b17-4be2-a34a-e9f49073eab0', 'Meanwhile, peel potatoes and cut lengthwise with slicer to make 1/8-inch-thick julienne strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.09', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.981');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5df40d0e-b7db-4d28-bcd7-b1c6984f9883', 'Fry potatoes in 5 or 6 small batches, stirring, until golden brown, about 2 minutes per batch. (Return oil to 375°F between batches.) Drain potatoes on paper towels and season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.093', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.982');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c6f30d4c-5fe5-4d13-813a-4cf318e291a3', 'Remove zest from limes in strips with a vegetable peeler and cut away any white pith from zest (pith imparts a bitter flavor). Chop zest (about 1/2 cup), then grind in a food processor with sugar until mixture is pale green with bits of zest still visible.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.982');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6bf36f66-0980-4322-9e3d-ecf0266b52bf', 'In the bowl of a food processor, combine the tahini, garlic, lemon juice and salt and process on low speed for 2 minutes or until thoroughly incorporated. Turn the speed to high and blend until the tahini mixture begins to whiten. Gradually add up to 1/2 cup water until the mixture reaches the desired consistency.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.101', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.983');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4dbec4e-0202-4345-8bde-b1d78972cdb9', 'Transfer the sauce to a serving bowl and garnish with the parsley. Leftover tahini sauce can be stored, tightly covered in the refrigerator, for up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.105', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.983');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6753b0d-a9d1-45e3-b4e9-87d136dae93f', 'Whisk together vinaigrette ingredients.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.108', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.983');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('016054a2-07d5-4b33-827e-890c24e37453', 'Blanch and peel tomatoes . Seed and cut into 1-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.111', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.984');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29a3c6ac-a7a3-48cf-9e10-a9656ca57c18', 'Wrap shallots in a kitchen towel, then twist and squeeze to remove as much liquid as possible.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.114', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.984');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1300705e-67bc-43a6-9e9d-e87a26ff76cd', 'Cook broccoli, cauliflower, celery root, turnips, and haricots verts in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes, then drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.117', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.984');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('92082426-6b74-4c77-889d-a81ecbc744a0', 'Toss warm vegetables with tomatoes, shallots, chives, cilantro, and vinaigrette.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.985');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('584764b7-2e4c-4a53-b369-e32f9986d738', 'Whisk first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl. Add celery and celery leaves, thinly sliced fennel and chopped fennel fronds, and apple; toss to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.124', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.987');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('17625f88-aed7-442e-a9fa-25f0760fc07e', 'Puree all ingredients in processor. Strain into medium bowl, pressing on solids to extract as much liquid as possible. Cover and refrigerate until cold. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.127', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.987');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('405d10db-d027-4edb-bcd7-e72dc4f2d21a', 'In a blender or small food processor purée 1/4 cup parsley with 1/4 cup oil. Pour mixture through a fine sieve set over a bowl, pressing hard on solids, and discard solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.131', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.987');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37a439b1-2bb1-4749-bece-5946d5e5426b', 'In a small baking pan toast pine nuts and cumin seeds, stirring occasionally, until nuts are golden, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.134', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.988');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('636c5936-465f-4bbe-8fe7-221ed0b17a14', 'Combine 5 cups water, sugar and ginger in heavy large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Strain liquid into large bowl; discard solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.328', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.031');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6af0e72a-e837-4ca2-8736-eba89c2b3b7a', 'Sprinkle vegetables with parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.443', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.177');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79853df6-1837-43d5-a9b9-871d289b1f7c', 'In a colander rinse and drain chick-peas and in a food processor purée 1/2 cup with garlic until garlic is finely minced. Add tahini, water, lemon juice, salt, remaining chick-peas, and remaining 1/2 cup olive oil and purée until smooth. Recipe may be prepared up to this point 3 days ahead. Keep hummus and parsley oil chilled, covered, and pine nuts and cumin seeds in an airtight container at room temperature. Bring parsley oil to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.137', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.988');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('163ff32b-2506-4182-b33b-5a870d2df961', 'Strip leaves from additional parsley sprigs. Divide hummus between 2 shallow dishes and smooth tops. Drizzle hummus with parsley oil and sprinkle with parsley, pine nuts, and cumin seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.14', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.988');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ab7c55e6-4511-4868-96c2-558c7599c2c7', 'Serve hummus with pita toasts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.143', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.989');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eeee2d0a-f817-47a5-884e-424e3f2338ff', 'Add lemon halves to a large bowl of cold water, squeezing to release juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.146', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.991');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2de14bbd-2262-46f0-b409-46443efa0be2', 'Cut off top inch of 1 artichoke and bend back outer leaves until they snap off close to base (keep stem attached). Discard several more layers in same manner until you reach pale yellow leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.149', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.991');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b24fea29-2aef-4941-8b53-641c3dcf40b1', 'Cut remaining leaves flush with top of artichoke bottom using a sharp knife. Trim dark green fibrous parts from base and sides of artichoke.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.153', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.991');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a49855ff-d3e2-4fde-8299-d39a05661363', 'Peel sides of stem down to pale inner core. Put in lemon water while preparing remaining artichokes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:18.992');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2b9087bd-995c-4bcb-8c60-0afd079be26a', 'Cook shallots, carrot, garlic, and seeds in 1/4 cup oil in a 4-to 5-quart heavy pot (pot should be wide enough to hold artichokes in 1 layer with stems pointing upward) over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes. Add water, zest, and 3 tablespoons lemon juice and bring to a simmer. Stand artichokes in pot and season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover artichokes with wax paper, then a lid, and simmer over medium-low heat until bases are just tender when pierced with a knife, 20 to 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.16', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.001');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2f2bd9f-519a-4fdc-971b-3dc42d790b03', 'Transfer artichokes to a dish and reserve cooking liquid. When artichokes are cool enough to handle, halve lengthwise. Scoop out and discard inner choke (fuzzy center and any sharp leaves).', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.163', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.002');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da8989d7-c4d6-4388-bf1e-00aafb265ece', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then brown cut sides of artichokes in 2 batches, about 2 minutes per batch, transferring to a serving dish. Add reserved cooking liquid to skillet along with remaining tablespoon lemon juice and remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Boil vigorously 3 minutes, then stir in parsley and pour over artichokes. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.166', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.004');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec520286-ea63-4ce8-b2b7-77daf8c7c645', 'Thinly slice 2 garlic cloves. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy small skillet over low heat. Add sliced garlic and sauté until tender, about 10 minutes. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.171', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.004');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39234262-b833-4e89-8ef9-d4dd340a44e0', 'Cook potatoes and remaining 8 garlic cloves in large saucepan of boiling salted water until potatoes are tender, about 35 minutes. Drain, reserving 1 1/4 cups cooking liquid. Combine boiled potatoes and garlic, sautéed garlic mixture and remaining 3 tablespoons oil in same saucepan. Mash until smooth, adding enough reserved cooking liquid to form creamy consistency. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer potatoes to bowl. (Can be prepared 8 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Rewarm potatoes in microwave until heated through.) Sprinkle with parsley and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.175', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.005');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c07ca836-5ee9-4c9d-98fe-26c34524b395', 'Whisk 1 1/2 cups water, polenta, and salt in heavy large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to simmer. Gradually whisk in remaining 4 1/2 cups water. Bring to boil, whisking polenta often. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook until polenta is thick, soft, and creamy, stirring often, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.005');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d64b9ec-28e9-4f59-872e-30e57acc2b7e', 'Available at Italian markets, natural foods stores, and some supermarkets. If polenta is unavailable, substitute 1 1/2 cups regular yellow cornmeal and cook mixture for about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.006');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b1ec73a3-a01d-4140-87a2-b9b8fa5ad2f9', '1. Heat the oil in a large pot over medium heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.006');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('919c9458-d825-4937-91ee-faf20f4c72d3', '2. Add the onions and garlic and cook for 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.19', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.007');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b35ae5ea-f944-4456-8112-2cf50594f1c0', '3. Add the celery, carrots, paprika, cinnamon, cumin, ginger and salt. Cook an additional 5 minutes, until the veggies are soft and the spices are fragrant.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.194', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.008');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70e2feac-41cd-42d3-9d0a-be077b6de610', '4. Add the tomatoes, butternut squash, cauliflower, and vegetable broth, and stir to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.198', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.008');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e37ea66-53fb-4a4b-804b-6c554c53355b', '5. Cover, reduce the heat to low, and simmer for 15–20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.201', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.009');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('304ab7bf-eba3-4f0a-9d22-ef641d38a4c7', '6. Stir in the chickpeas and raisins and cook an additional 10–15 minutes or until the vegetables are soft.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.205', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.012');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb5c2ea7-8006-42c2-957f-aa207677e7a6', '7. Serve over couscous with sliced almonds and green or black olives, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.208', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.012');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('96918c74-b3ec-4a99-b469-c3f0fcedde37', 'Keeping grapes on stems, poke each grape several times with a wooden pick and put in a large heatproof bowl. In a saucepan stir together remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour hot syrup over grapes. Macerate grapes at room temperature, gently turning occasionally, 1 hour. Chill grapes, covered, at least 2 hours and up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.212', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.012');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f6de992-8f68-4010-aa41-5d7747b2d2da', 'Puree tomatoes, onion, and garlic in blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.216', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.014');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59fd34c2-1a3d-47d8-b5f8-6e354514e05d', 'Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add rice; stir until rice is pale golden, about 1 minute. Stir in tomato puree, then 1 cup hot water, carrot, peas, corn, cilantro sprigs, chiles, and salt. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook until almost all liquid is absorbed, about 12 minutes. Uncover and cook until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes longer. Remove from heat, cover, and let stand 5 minutes. Discard cilantro and chiles. Fluff rice with fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.22', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.014');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8ce222bc-70f7-45da-a15c-14c42f17220d', '1. In a heavy-bottomed medium saucepan (no larger than 2 quarts, or the mixture will reduce too rapidly and burn before it reaches the correct temperature) over high heat, bring the sugar, water, and chocolate to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Attach a candy thermometer to the pan. Reduce the heat to medium and cook, uncovered, stirring, until the mixture reaches 234°F., about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.224', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.015');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b993dff-cf5b-4648-9adb-ab05691fa9cf', '2. Remove from the heat and stir to cool and thicken slightly, about 1 minute. Use immediately. When pouring, do not scrape the pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.228', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.016');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed74aa88-f060-42e5-8f36-0cdd4b8847df', 'Use 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water, and 4 ounces bittersweet chocolate. Make the glaze in a small saucepan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.231', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.017');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea87e025-ed5c-4ca2-994b-df5b2cc94085', 'Cook onion with 1/4 teaspoon salt in 2 tablespoons oil in a 5- to 6-quart heavy pot over medium heat, stirring, until softened. Sprinkle with paprika and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add chard in batches, stirring frequently, until wilted, then add raisins and water. Cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until chard is tender, about 7 minutes. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.235', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.018');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61df63fa-d552-4c9f-a29b-be3d37b0dfe0', 'Cook almonds in remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil in a small heavy skillet over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until golden, 3 to 5 minutes. Sprinkle almonds over chard.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.239', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.019');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ddcadb21-658f-472e-80a3-b9a2a7e0bb15', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add leek and bay leaf. Sauté until leek wilts, about 3 minutes. Add split peas and stir to coat. Add 5 1/4 cups broth; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer until split peas are just tender, about 35 minutes. Remove from heat. Transfer 1 cup soup solids, bay leaf, and remaining 1/2 cup broth to blender. Add petite peas and 4 tablespoons dill. Puree until smooth. Return puree to soup. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Ladle into bowls. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon dill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.243', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.019');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a76644d6-60d3-4f90-95b0-dc661483cc3f', 'Toss cabbage with salt in a large bowl and let stand, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.248', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.02');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bb15b8b1-b0a4-4e93-89c8-bb2d952bbe2f', 'Meanwhile, whisk together oil, vinegar, honey mustard, and pepper in a small bowl until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.252', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.02');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b1212283-05ec-4b5c-be44-e339d00a11b0', 'Rinse cabbage with cold water in a colander, then firmly squeeze handfuls to remove excess water and transfer cabbage to cleaned bowl. Add radishes and dressing to cabbage, tossing to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.256', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.021');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('86bbbf98-1b65-419f-ac36-3683dfd8640c', 'Mix first 11 ingredients and 8 cups water in a large pot. Bring to a boil and stir until sugar and salt dissolve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.26', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.021');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c059edb3-c6c2-439e-b2f8-ef8dcfed48cc', 'Add sweet potatoes, brussels sprouts, carrots, and turnips; cook until just barely crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Add fennel; cook for 1 minute. Add peppers, pressing to submerge; remove pot from heat and let cool to room temperature. Cover and chill vegetables until cold. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep chilled. Drain vegetables before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.264', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.021');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e298896-b7b3-45d5-839c-8541aa35be37', 'Combine cilantro sprigs, ginger, garlic, and chiles in a resealable plastic freezer bag; seal. Lightly pound with a skillet or rolling pin until ginger and garlic are well mashed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.268', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.022');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f09c2bc-3f47-4fea-a2e2-2a3814542dfa', 'Add cucumbers, 1 teaspoon salt, and sugar. Seal bag; shake to mix. Squeeze bag firmly to slightly mash cucumbers, 1-2 minutes. Place bag in a large bowl; let macerate at room temperature, turning halfway through, until juices form, about 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.271', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.023');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b95b264-8402-41ba-b082-bbbfbc65de9e', 'Empty contents of bag into bowl; turn bag inside out and scrape out any small bits. Discard cilantro sprigs. Mix in celery, juice, and oil. Season with more salt, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.275', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.023');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea8254c7-053e-439b-a2fd-5e4089ed010c', 'Divide avocado among plates; spoon salad over. Garnish with chopped cilantro and basil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.278', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.024');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('557f4dba-eef5-49f8-b458-79abd306b944', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat) or preheat broiler. Brush zucchini with olive oil. Sprinkle both sides of zucchini with oregano, garlic and rosemary. Season zucchini slices generously with salt and pepper. Grill or broil until zucchini is tender, about 4 minutes per side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.281', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.024');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47138d43-70ef-43d8-a72f-a5aba19ef3f5', 'On a cutting board mince and mash the garlic to a paste with the salt. In a food processor purée the chick-peas with the garlic paste, the tahini, the lemon juice, 1/4 cup of the oil, and 1/2 cup water, scraping down the sides, until the hummus is smooth and add salt to taste. Add water, if necessary, to thin the hummus to the desired consistency and transfer the hummus to a bowl. In the food processor, cleaned, purée the remaining 1/4 cup oil with the parsley until the oil is bright green and the parsley is minced transfer the parsley oil to a small jar. The hummus and the parsley oil may be made 3 days in advance and kept covered and chilled. Divide the hummus between shallow serving dishes and smooth the tops. Drizzle the hummus with the parsley oil and sprinkle it with the pine nuts. Serve the hummus with the pita.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.285', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.025');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6becb22c-a3ca-4609-8876-40065ade270e', 'Combine strawberries, blueberries, and blackberries with sugar and cardamom in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring regularly, for 5-7 minutes, until berries are soft but not falling apart. Remove from heat and stir in coconut milk. Carefully pour warm berry mixture into a pitcher. Pour mix into molds, helping some of the berries along with a spoon so they''re evenly distributed. Freeze at least 4 hours (insert sticks when partially frozen) and up to 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.289', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.025');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f06537c-8081-4290-9dd3-015e2745de1d', 'Using vegetable peeler, remove peel from 1 grapefruit; place in bowl. Cut both grapefruits in half; squeeze enough juice to measure 3/4 cup. Mix juice and sugar in bowl with peel. Let stand 5 minutes. Strain into small bowl, pressing on solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.294', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.026');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca7b0dc0-db83-4342-9c92-04c57bcaa17e', 'Pour 2 tablespoons syrup into each of four 6-ounce flutes. Fill each with 2/3 cup Champagne.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.297', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.027');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8726e12f-c979-48b3-9f7f-11cf9ec1abea', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Fill medium bowl with cold water. Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Working with 1 artichoke at a time, pull off tough outer leaves (about 3 rows). Cut tip and stem off artichoke. Cut artichoke in half. Scoop out any choke. Place in lemon water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.302', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.027');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c19ecd4-606f-4505-8517-8a07b27bdda9', 'Spray large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Drain artichokes; pat dry. Return to bowl. Add 3 tablespoons oil and toss. Transfer to prepared sheet; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until tender when pierced, stirring once, about 20 minutes. Cool on sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.306', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.028');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e10d51e-087a-4ed1-bbb7-26b226c90ffb', 'Whisk 6 tablespoons lemon juice, 1/2 cup oil, shallots, fennel seeds, and lemon peel in large bowl. Stir in sliced fennel, parsley, artichokes, and edamame. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.) Garnish with reserved fennel fronds and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.028');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('883e699c-55ae-4252-af91-a765d0f1dd87', '*Edamame (soybeans) are available at many supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.315', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.029');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89648ec5-d2a6-4bee-b5d5-2b5ecca80b14', 'Preheat broiler. Line rimmed baking sheet with foil. Place tomatillos on prepared baking sheet. Broil until tomatillos are just blackened in spots and tender, about 8 minutes per side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.319', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.029');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('572c3e0f-d4c3-411c-9530-7a6fb90b10c5', 'Combine onion, cilantro, chiles, and lime juice in large bowl. Add roasted tomatillos and any juices from baking sheet to onion mixture. Using fork, mash coarsely. Add avocados and mash with fork until mixture is very coarsely pureed and some chunks remain. Season guacamole to taste with salt. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.03');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed03574a-f5fb-4c78-93b4-a11210a51cd2', '2. Preheat the oven to 450°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.61', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.072');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fff31ffd-d2e2-4321-ab76-f579ee365667', 'Return liquid to same saucepan. Add lemon and lime peels. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Whisk in lemon and lime juices. Cool completely. Pour mixture into 13x9x2-inch glass baking dish. Cover and freeze until solid, about 6 hours or overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.031');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('145c0ffc-67d6-417c-8f08-d2779478069c', 'Transfer mixture to processor and puree until smooth. Return to same glass dish; cover and freeze until solid, at least 3 hours or overnight. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Keep frozen.) Scoop sorbet into glasses or bowls. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.337', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.032');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a224c49b-2f90-475b-a3f7-762c69f83743', 'Heat oven to 425°. Cut 3 medium peeled sweet potatoes into 1/4-inch-thick fries. In a bowl, combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon jalapeño salt; add fries and toss. Arrange fries on two baking sheets coated with vegetable oil cooking spray; coat with more cooking spray. Bake until fries begin to brown, 10 minutes. Remove from oven and flip; spritz with cooking spray and sprinkle with 1 sliced jalapeño. Bake until golden, 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.342', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.034');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c5c6e18-e2db-4d86-817f-5b263cdd82c0', 'Rinse rice in several changes of cold water in a large bowl until water runs clear. Drain in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.345', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.034');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ac66600-374e-4ded-9faf-e8f31eac205a', 'Transfer rice to a 4-quart heavy saucepan, then add water (3 1/3 cups) and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until steam holes appear on surface and water is absorbed, about 13 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, tightly covered and undisturbed, 5 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork and spread in a large shallow baking pan to cool quickly, about 45 minutes. Chill, covered with plastic wrap, at least 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.349', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.035');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f73ac995-e65d-4e42-b983-ca3b1c00b9ec', 'Heat a wok or 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until a drop of water vaporizes instantly. Pour oil around side of wok, then tilt wok to swirl oil, coating side. When oil just begins to smoke, stir-fry ginger, white and pale green parts of scallions, and salt until fragrant, about 1 minute. Crumble rice into wok and stir-fry until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat, then add scallion greens, pineapple, and sesame oil, tossing to combine. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.353', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.035');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ba949a0c-e746-4893-864f-73397dd824fd', 'In a food processor blend together all filling ingredients except water until an almost smooth, jamlike consistency. If date mixture is very dry blend in water, 1 tablespoon at a time. Filling may be made 2 days ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.357', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.036');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55df03b3-432d-47f5-b160-6b7408554361', 'Using processor fitted with shredder attachment, shred horseradish. Transfer horseradish to medium bowl. Fit processor with metal blade. Return horseradish to work bowl. Add next 3 ingredients. Process until almost smooth, scraping down sides of bowl occasionally, about 5 minutes. Mix in salt. Place horseradish in glass jar. Cover tightly; chill at least 1 day and up to 10 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.361', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.036');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd6e9d3d-f6e4-4560-9f6f-3a99e5c7fa85', 'Stir soy sauce and sugar in small bowl until sugar dissolves. Heat oil in heavy large skillet. Add garlic and stir 15 seconds. Add asparagus and stir-fry until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Add soy mixture and toss until asparagus is coated, about 1 minute longer. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl; sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.366', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.037');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ae9a2184-2ee0-4b93-a8e4-144ee319902e', 'Preheat oven to 325°F. Spray large sheet of foil with nonstick spray. Place pecans on small rimmed baking sheet. Whisk maple syrup, 1/2 teaspoon coarse salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in small bowl. Add to nuts and toss to coat; spread in single layer. Bake nuts 5 minutes. Stir. Continue to bake nuts until toasted and glaze is bubbling thickly, about 6 minutes. Immediately transfer nuts to prepared foil and separate. Cool completely. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Store airtight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.369', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.038');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('664af245-4510-4b60-a05e-4370fc4a71cc', 'Whisk mustard, vinegar, lemon juice, and sugar in small bowl; whisk in oil. Season with coarse salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.373', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.039');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb9036ee-4bd3-46c9-9267-fa2b2028ff9c', 'Bring large pot of water to boil. Add 1 tablespoon coarse salt. Add brussels sprouts. Cook until crisp-tender and still bright green, about 5 minutes. Drain; rinse with cold water. Cool on paper towels. Using processor fitted with 1/8- to 1/4-inch slicing disk, slice brussels sprouts. Transfer to large bowl. DO AHEAD: Dressing and brussels sprouts can be made 1 day ahead. Cover separately; chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.376', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.039');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c63d09e4-624c-4c21-9b54-b9d2be54981f', 'Toss brussels sprouts with enough dressing to coat. Let marinate 30 to 60 minutes. Mix in some pecans. Place slaw in serving bowl. Top with remaining pecans.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.38', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.04');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a8359c0-78c8-4948-bf39-c0b0b11075e9', 'Combine garbanzo beans and lemon juice in large bowl. Add 3 tablespoons oil; press in garlic and stir to combine. Let marinate at least 15 minutes and up to 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.384', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.04');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c5123d84-0e66-41a8-a1be-d41cacfffd6a', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add cumin seeds, 1/2 teaspoon turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon paprika; stir until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add 2 cups water, quinoa, and coarse salt; bring to simmer, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 16 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.388', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4baf409-fb12-4f8a-8096-b4edbb2f1b0e', 'Meanwhile, prepare barbecue (medium high heat). Place zucchini on rimmed baking sheet. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil. Sprinkle with ground cumin, 1/2 teaspoon turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon paprika. Toss to coat evenly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a34ea923-c41e-4fd5-91df-f9066708dd0b', 'Place zucchini on grill; sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Grill until tender and browned on all sides, 10 to 12 minutes. Transfer to work surface. Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Add zucchini, green onions, and parsley, then garbanzo bean mixture to quinoa. Toss to blend. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.397', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d74df56-91ba-4175-995d-b005d79c3202', '*Sometimes labeled Pimentón Dulce or Pimentón de La Vera Dulce; available at some supermarkets, at specialty foods stores, and from tienda.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.4', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.042');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bb7c2167-ce0e-4ab0-bcc6-350124dec172', '**A grain with a flavor and texture similar to couscous; available at natural foods stores.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.405', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.042');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fee7e5b8-52fa-401e-924b-9e4478376aa0', 'Wash escarole well in a sinkful of cold water, agitating it, then lift out and drain in a colander. Cook escarole in a 5- to 6-quart heavy pot of boiling salted water, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes, then drain well in colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.409', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.043');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('014204d1-f42a-44b6-99b4-e52bf1f37d58', 'Dry pot, then add oil and heat over moderate heat until hot but not smoking. Add pine nuts to hot oil and cook, stirring, until pale golden, about 1 minute. Add garlic and red-pepper flakes and cook, stirring, until garlic and pine nuts are golden, 1 to 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.414', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.043');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c12b81b-5bd3-4285-b371-8b71689d1d9f', 'Add escarole, stirring to coat with oil, then increase heat to moderately high and cook, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid is evaporated, 3 to 5 minutes. Season escarole with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.417', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.044');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('667d7f02-62a1-45f8-a67a-37b9cd100d18', 'Stir sugar and water in small saucepan over medium-low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Transfer to large bowl. Puree strawberries in processor. Add to syrup. Mix in orange juice and cava. Refrigerate strawberry mixture until well chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.422', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.044');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a48a14e-1cb8-4b59-8874-5e622f845b0d', 'Process strawberry mixture in ice cream maker according to manufacturer''s instructions. Transfer sorbet to covered container and freeze until ready to serve. (Can be prepared 4 days ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.426', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.045');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ec373fd-7e65-4fcd-abc4-b0eeed674602', 'Scoop sorbet into glasses. Top with fresh berries and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.43', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.045');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e34b84c-9a42-4999-952a-4b66441cc300', 'Store 12 cups mixed hearty greens (such as escarole, mustard greens, and kale; if using mustard greens or kale, fold leaves over and cut off tough center rib and stems) and 1 cup kumquats, cut into thin rounds, seeded, in 2 separate resealable plastic bags. Chill greens and kumquats overnight. Before serving, empty bags with greens and kumquats into a large bowl. Add 1/2 cup Granny Smith Apple Cider Vinaigrette to salad and toss to evenly coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.435', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.046');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f019068-b7e7-4b2e-a818-81718080c911', 'Add more vinaigrette, if desired. Season to taste with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. Transfer to a serving bowl and scatter 1/4 cup 1" pieces chives and, for a little crunch, 3 tablespoons roasted salted shelled pumpkin seeds (pepitas) over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.44', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.046');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6078a412-ddaa-49a8-9203-f2dad488cf18', 'Stir together anisette and sugar in a large bowl. Using melon-ball cutter, scoop watermelon balls into bowl. Add mint and toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.443', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.047');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('19d9d2a3-0420-4097-a53c-d3a6b43d4e4e', 'Serve sorbetto with watermelon mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.448', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.047');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a87b6b1-42a3-4cf0-a96f-084f3a9a8146', 'Stir 2 cups water and sugar in heavy medium saucepan over high heat until sugar dissolves. Boil 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.453', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.049');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('817e6cff-93d4-426f-84a5-8e7cafd00fcb', 'Working in batches, puree strawberries in food processor until smooth. Add strawberry puree and orange and lemon juices to sugar syrup; stir to blend. Cover and refrigerate until cold, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.457', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.05');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f311fdd-3751-492e-8cb8-bef95b966d2b', 'Process strawberry mixture in ice cream maker according to manufacturer''s instructions or place mixture in shallow container and freeze, stirring every hour until set, about 6 hours. (Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and freeze in airtight container. If sorbet is frozen solid, place in refrigerator for 15 minutes to soften.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.461', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.051');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f6fa9ca9-6a82-4a04-b162-952f0f7eab63', 'Cut 4 scrubbed large carrots into 3" lengths; place in a steamer basket set in a large saucepan filled with 2" simmering water. Cover and steam until tender, 10–15 minutes; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.464', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.051');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d57fe879-bec9-4131-ba90-6f8178918f8c', 'Cut 4 flat surfaces at 90°F angles lengthwise around each carrot. Heat a dry medium skillet, preferably cast iron, over high and cook carrots, turning, until blackened, 10–12 minutes. Let cool. Cut carrots crosswise into thin slices without cutting all the way through and fan out. Drizzle with olive oil and fresh lemon juice, and sprinkle with flaky sea salt and sliced chives.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.467', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.052');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13b05c29-b072-46e6-baa1-f0ba394c5cca', 'For the sauce, place all the ingredients in a saucepan. Whisk until well combined. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 5 minutes. Taste and add more chili powder, if desired. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.471', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.052');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7b7ccf2-3400-49cb-991b-763c7ec24c85', 'Place the beans in a large bowl. Add the onions, corn, olives, and green chilies (if using). Mix gently until well combined. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.474', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.053');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8fb28eb2-35f5-4733-824f-3054c382f007', 'Preheat the oven to 350°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.478', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.053');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('319d419f-f7bb-44ac-8ac6-8f341b0ad883', 'Place 1 1/2 cups of the sauce in the bottom of a nonstick 9x13-inch baking dish. Place 4 corn tortillas over the bottom of the baking dish; they can overlap or be cut to fit. Spread half of the bean mixture over the tortillas. Place another 4 tortillas over the bean mixture and then spread the remaining bean mixture on top of those tortillas. Cover with 4 more tortillas and then pour the remaining sauce over the tortillas. Cover with parchment paper and then with aluminum foil, crimping the edges over the baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes. Remove from the oven and let rest for about 15 minutes before cutting. Serve with salsa and tofu sour cream, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.481', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3881bd4e-1d85-49b5-a23c-0a5e3b0dc2c7', '6 SERVINGS Cut cucumbers in half lengthwise; scrape out seeds. Cut halves diagonally into 1/2-inch-wide pieces. Place in large bowl. Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour; toss occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.485', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53c6fbf6-9d16-4d0f-b537-e9a3cd8614cb', 'Add tomatoes, red onion, mint and oil to cucumbers and toss to blend. Season salad with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7554a077-47a7-4c8c-97d0-bcc31196c124', 'In a small bowl whisk together the sugar, the salt, the lemon juice, and the oil. Transfer the vinaigrette to a skillet, bring it to a boil, and add the zucchini, stirring to coat it with the dressing. Simmer the zucchini for 3 minutes, or until it is crisp-tender, stir in the mint, and let the zucchini cool in the dressing. Serve the zucchini at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.493', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a8a52819-f8e9-407b-a779-293eb0eb8ed6', 'In a serving bowl whisk together vinegar and salt and pepper to taste and whisk in oil until emulsified. Peel, pit, and chop avocado. Add avocado, romaine, arugula, and onion to vinaigrette and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7e3c16a-d542-4b17-88f0-a6de3e8884ed', 'Stir all ingredients in a small bowl to blend. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 month ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.502', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce29b1ee-afde-492c-a13a-92a2e658a373', 'In a large bowl stir together the garlic paste, the tomatoes, the arugula, the olives, the oil, the vinegar, and salt and pepper to taste and let the mixture marinate for 20 minutes. In a large saucepan of boiling salted water cook the linguine for 10 minutes, or until it is al dente, drain it, and while it is still hot, toss it with the sauce. Serve the pasta warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.506', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c2a74fd2-6a07-4f54-85c6-79e65a13e374', 'Cut the bell peppers into 1-inch pieces and in a food processor chop them vety fine. Transfer the chopped peppers to a deep kettle, add the sugar, the vinegar, and the red pepper flakes, and bring the mixture to a boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Stir in the pectin and boil the mixture over moderately high heat, stirring, until it reaches the jelly stage (222°F. on a candy thermometer). Transfer the jelly to sterilizes Mason-type jars (sterilizing procedure below), filling the jars to within 1/4 inch of the tops, wipe the rims with a dampened towel, and seal the jars. The jelly keeps, sealed, in a cool dark place indefinitely. Serve the jelly as a condiment with grilled meats or with cream cheese on crackers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55e844ec-53eb-4284-a6ae-8d570a9120d5', '3. Whisk together the olive oil, vinegar, remaining salt, and pepper, and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.073');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48896d55-729d-41c6-a654-965a37f1d82a', '• 1/2 to 1 teaspoon Tabasco or other hot sauce', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.519', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.334');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('41ec8850-0741-4f04-b276-7905dfb9ba5c', 'Wash the jars in hot suds and rinse them in scalding water. Put the jars in a kettle and cover them with hot water. Bring the water to a boil, covered, and boil the jars for 15 minutes from the time that steam emerges from the kettle. Turn off the heat and let the jars stand in the hot water. Just before they are to be filled invert the jars onto a kitchen towel to dry. (The jars should be filled while they are still hot.) Sterilize the jar lids for 5 minutes, or according to the manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.514', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2bab49a8-d4ce-4643-8667-697cec3ee0aa', 'To make the muffins, mix together the almond meal, flax meal, and salt in a mixing bowl. Add the agave syrup, vanilla, and coconut oil and mix well. Add the water and mix to a batter consistency. Fold in the blueberries.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.518', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fa893bc-0771-467b-b7fd-24bd55da02d7', 'Place 6 cupcake liners into a muffin pan and spoon about 1/2 cup dough into each. Place the pan in the dehydrator and dehydrate at 104°F for 4 to 6 hours, until the batter is dry and to desired consistency.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.521', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35de7f46-4038-4436-9ee7-5f156fd369a7', 'To make the glaze, combine the cashews, blackberry juice, lemon juice, agave syrup, and water in the Personal Blender with the 1-cup container and blend until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.525', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('900d836f-07bb-4afe-b743-c72a30250340', 'To serve, frost each muffin with the glaze.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.529', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ddace19-7b45-4116-81e4-b5fc01f3f49a', 'Will keep for several days refrigerated. Can be frozen for several weeks and thawed. Warm muffins in the dehydrator at 104°F for an hour or two before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.533', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0fbd3012-f97d-4463-b3ee-81d439c3edde', 'In a bowl whisk together vinegar, mustard, and salt and pepper to taste and whisk in oil until dressing is emulsified. Add watercress, celery, and parsley and toss to combine well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.537', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('efe43e76-1429-483e-a623-79f5575132a3', 'Stir wine and sugar in heavy large saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add cherries. Bring to boil. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer cherries to medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.541', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4436109-9242-4e09-b634-492799a3502b', 'Boil cooking liquid until reduced to 2 cups, about 25 minutes. Mix in orange peel, almond extract and nutmeg. Cool. Pour syrup over cherries; toss. Cover; chill until cold. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep chilled.) Spoon cherry mixture into bowls and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.545', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.061');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95821e1d-2e84-435d-bbee-3b7b4a5c9de7', 'Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. DO AHEAD: can be made up to 2 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.549', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.061');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5dc2038-3c39-4d26-9d73-e8a05e3a051a', 'Heat a large skillet over medium and toast walnuts, shaking pan often, until fragrant, about 5 minutes. Transfer nuts to a plate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.553', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.062');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15b9dde8-2499-4d3d-a855-66b68f96bd6a', 'Heat same skillet over medium and add oil and butter, stirring to combine. Once butter melts, add onion, 1/4 tsp. salt, and 1/4 tsp. pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and translucent, about 5 minutes. Add Swiss chard stems and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 2 minutes more. Add garlic and red pepper flakes and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, 1 minute. Add Swiss chard greens, beet greens, vinegar, remaining 1 tsp. salt, and remaining 1/4 tsp. pepper. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally with tongs, until tender, about 3–4 minutes. Uncover and cook 1 minute more. Serve topped with toasted walnuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.557', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.063');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9234752-a73c-4bc8-b6f0-f328d9df4672', 'Pulse 1 1/2 cups tomato, 1/4 cup cucumber, orange zest and juice, garlic, onion, bell pepper, gochujang, dill, parsley, lemon juice, vinegar, ginger, and salt in a blender until coarsely chopped. Drizzle in oil while pulsing until mixture is combined but not totally smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.561', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.066');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcf455d6-41e1-4c2c-a08a-9c4cde8c0c0a', 'Divide gazpacho between 2 bowls and garnish with remaining tomato and cucumber. Top with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.565', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.066');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe9406e7-8780-4feb-95f8-c330601fc7d6', 'Gazpacho can be made up to 2 days in advance and refrigerated. Wait to garnish until ready to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.57', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.067');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('033dc8cc-b7f2-43e1-8e6e-b0028e336cd5', 'Put oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms, sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt, and cook, stirring occasionally, until they release their water and the pan begins to dry out again, 10-15 minutes. Add leeks and cook, stirring, until they soften a bit, 2-3 minutes. Add tarragon and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.574', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.068');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('beaeefcf-e15d-4c78-af6d-3e7ef719cd6c', 'Stir salt and 1 gallon warm water in a large bowl until salt is dissolved. Let brine cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.578', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.069');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94f05d0c-bcb5-4bde-a682-36979015337b', 'Layer beans with remaining ingredients in a large ceramic, glass, or stainless-steel mixing bowl. Add brine to cover. Pour remaining brine into a resealable plastic bag; seal and place on beans to submerge. Cover bowl with a clean kitchen towel. Let stand at room temperature until bubbles form around edge of bowl, 4-5 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.582', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.069');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95474a4e-6bae-4460-9701-3b40eddf9af6', 'Spoon off any foam from surface of brine. Continue to let stand at room temperature, discarding foam as necessary, until beans are pickled, about 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.586', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.07');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82f70b44-4562-4467-ae7a-44e975515051', 'Using a slotted spoon, divide beans, herbs, and spices among 3 clean 1-quart jars. Set a strainer with 2 layers of cheesecloth over a large pitcher; pour brine through strainer. Pour over beans in jars, leaving 1/2" space on top. Cover; chill up to 2 months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.07');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68bfffd4-9e25-4d94-a018-f23a6c2d18bf', 'Halve 3 of the bell peppers lengthwise, leaving the stem ends intact, and core and seed them. Arrange the halves on a steamer rack set over simmering water, steam them, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until they are tender, and invert them on paper towels to drain. In a small bowl whisk together 1 tablespoon of the oil and 1 teaspoon of the vinegar and brush the insides of the halves with the mixture. In a large heavy skillet cook the onions in the remaining 3 tablespoons oil over moderate heat, stirring, until they are softened, stir in the garlic and the remaining 5 bell peppers, cut into julienne strips, and cook the mixture until the peppers are just tender. Remove the skillet from the heat, stir in the olives, the remaining vinegar, and salt and pepper to taste, and divide the filling among the bell pepper halves. Serve the stuffed peppers at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.594', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.07');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('07032cc5-d5a3-4023-8215-11ca91779486', 'Whisk oil, vinegar, shallot, and mustard in medium bowl to blend. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.598', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.071');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de1b1ded-76e3-4c83-86dd-306675791473', 'Cut cores from heads of lettuce, keeping heads intact; rinse and dry. Arrange 1 head of lettuce on each of 2 plates, forming rose shape. Tuck radish and avocado slices between lettuce leaves. Scatter fresh herb leaves over lettuce on each plate. Drizzle salad with dressing and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.602', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.071');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0017e1ac-f91d-4cf4-8cd8-f3301a7cdaa6', '1. Place a layer of paper towels over a baking sheet. Arrange the eggplant in single layers and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt. Let stand for 30 minutes. Pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.606', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.072');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d235bf4-f8c5-4552-bd99-9f880e151281', '4. Divide the eggplant, zucchini, red onions, peppers, and endive between 2 large baking pans with sides. Gently toss the vegetables with 3/4 of the blended oil and vinegar. Place 1 baking sheet on the bottom oven rack and the second on the middle rack. Roast the vegetables for 15 to 20 minutes, turning them once and rotating the pans between the shelves after 10 minutes. The vegetables should be crisp to the bite when they are done.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.618', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.073');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec99096c-1569-4a52-a738-7dd390083c84', '5. Arrange the vegetables in colorful bunches on round or oval platters, mixing together the different types of vegetables. Sprinkle the vegetables with salt and pepper, and drizzle them with the remaining olive oil/balsamic vinegar dressing. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.622', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.074');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ae43a7af-adf7-4e38-b594-e007c0b7373a', 'In a large saucepan cook the onions in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until they are softened. While the onions are cooking, in a bowl combine the raisins, 1/2 cup hot water, the vinegar, the cloves, and the sugar, let the mixture stand for 15 minutes, and stir it into the onions. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring, top it with the rhubarb (do not stir in the rhubarb), and cook the mixture, covered, at a slow boil for 5 minutes. Stir the mixture, cook it, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes more, or until the rhubarb is just tender, and season the chutney with salt and pepper. The chutney may be made 1 week in advance and kept in an airtight container and chilled. Serve the chutney warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.626', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.074');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d73c70a0-3686-41fc-96d5-eb105d1f9533', 'Finely grate enough lime zest to measure 1/2 teaspoon and in a small cup stir together with salt. Peel sweet potato and using a vegetable peeler shave as many long strips as possible from potato.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.63', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.075');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0746176-4138-4ce5-bd18-bae0453a5a30', 'In a deep 10-inch heavy skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until a deep-fat thermometer registers 375°F. and fry potato strips in 3 batches, stirring frequently, until lightly browned and bubbling stops, about 1 minute. Transfer chips as fried with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain and sprinkle with lime salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.634', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.075');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7eef28d0-be46-41f0-8cf0-ad4dfbe3ba97', 'Preheat oven to 450°. Toss potatoes with 1/4 cup oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with salt and pepper. Roast, tossing once, until golden brown and tender, 30-35 minutes. Let cool slightly, then lightly flatten.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.638', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.076');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee0a7e2f-b553-48b2-bc82-587fb6af7d4c', 'Meanwhile, whisk vinegar and mustard in a large bowl. Gradually whisk in remaining 1/4 cup oil until emulsified; season with salt and pepper. Add potatoes, jalapeño, and parsley and toss; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.642', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.076');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af9da873-eeeb-4ad4-8610-51719a9e976b', 'Steam or boil the chard leaves for 3 to 4 minutes, then plunge them into cold water. Gently squeeze as much moisture as possible from the chard. You should end up with a ball a little bigger than a baseball. Chop the chard on a cutting board, salt and pepper liberally, and divide into 4 equal portions. Make a small chard wreath on each of 4 plates and fill the middle with avocado pieces and orange sections, artfully arranged however you like.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.646', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.076');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2f129ae-9580-4797-97d2-3363eb394941', 'Put the olive oil, vinegar, chutney, and salt and pepper to taste into a jar and shake vigorously. Carefully drizzle everything with the dressing, using a light hand, then scatter the almonds and grated orange zest over them. Give each plate a final flick of salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.65', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.077');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('28c6f75e-bca3-420a-93c2-9dea7e299384', 'Combine sugar, 2 cups water, and kumquats in large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until kumquats are almost translucent, about 8 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer kumquats to small bowl. Add cranberries to sugar syrup in pan; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until berries burst, about 7 minutes. Add raisins; simmer until soft, about 4 minutes longer. Transfer cranberry sauce to medium bowl. DO AHEAD Kumquats and cranberry sauce can be made 5 days ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.655', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.077');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74fa0fa8-39e8-4aa9-88fc-9e63560b8519', 'Just before serving, add kumquats to cranberry sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.66', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.077');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60f1d593-8bb1-4af8-bb23-648bbb1a19a8', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Spray rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Cut fennel bulbs lengthwise in half. Cut halves lengthwise into 1/2-inch-wide wedges, with some core still attached to each. Combine fennel and shallots in large bowl. Add 3 tablespoons oil; stir to coat. Arrange fennel and shallots in single layer on prepared sheet. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Roast until tender and golden, stirring every 10 minutes, about 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.664', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.078');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8894a4ff-09da-4eb3-971d-4490210514ae', 'Cook haricots verts in large saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Drain. Rinse with cold water and drain again. Pat dry. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add roasted vegetables and haricots verts; toss until heated through, about 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.668', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.079');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61ba4a41-df73-4755-b8b3-33e852ffe99a', 'Preheat oven to 500°F. Combine mushrooms, rosemary, and garlic in large bowl. Mix in oil. Spread mushrooms in single layer on large rimmed baking sheet; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast mushrooms until brown, stirring occasionally, about 18 minutes. Transfer mushrooms to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.08');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c2d57d3e-5eef-4a4d-a690-8e2afa11c3d6', 'Cover potatoes with salted cold water by 1 inch in a 4-quart saucepan, then simmer, uncovered, until just tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain in a colander and let stand until cool enough to handle, about 15 minutes. Peel potatoes and halve lengthwise.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.08');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02c8211f-210d-46d5-8be9-4b9661831143', 'Cook garlic in oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderate heat, stirring, until garlic is pale golden, about 2 minutes. Discard garlic, then stir potatoes and red pepper flakes into oil and sauté over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until potatoes begin to turn golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.68', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.08');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f1d8dabc-91c0-4d39-9cda-c140c11376bc', 'While sautéing potatoes, cook zucchini in a pot of boiling salted water until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes, then drain in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.684', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.081');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0339b637-b87b-47d0-b7fa-89130ce813d1', 'Transfer potatoes with a slotted spoon to a bowl, then add zucchini to oil in skillet and sauté over moderately high heat, stirring, until hot, about 1 minute. Return potatoes to skillet and stir in salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.687', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.081');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7445b7d2-ea9e-4dd5-bc19-5655412bd22d', '1. Arrange the cucumber, potato and pepper slices, and the pitted olives on a serving plate or in a dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.691', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.082');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c66e766a-1588-4886-882d-54c92c8e71f3', '2. Season with salt, if you like. (Olives tend to be very salty so you may not wish to add any extra salt.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.695', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.082');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d5db3f2-1088-43ba-996e-7deb9b544b42', '3. Sprinkle the garlic, onions, olive oil, vinegar, and lemon juice over the salad. Chill for at least 1 hour. Before serving, sprinkle with the chopped mint leaves and cilantro leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.699', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.083');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d0e3ced-37ec-4920-a47e-258158d3aa2b', 'Combine 1 cup wine, sugar, orange peel and cinnamon in small saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat; simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat; add remaining wine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.707', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.084');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac5e159b-104f-4245-bb97-dd4e429879b9', 'Blanch peaches in large pot of boiling water 20 seconds. Transfer to bowl of cold water, using slotted spoon. Drain. Pull off skin with small sharp knife. Slice peaches and transfer to large bowl. Add raspberries and wine mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. (Can be prepared 6 hours ahead. Stir occasionally.) Divide fruit and wine among glass goblets. Serve with biscotti.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.711', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.084');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('666005b0-dfb8-49fc-ae3e-e52ff74d3796', 'Whisk oil, vinegar, and salt in medium bowl to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.715', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.085');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a5a04d0-8cc0-41be-8b7f-28b838298f1a', 'Cook green beans and turnips in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain. Transfer vegetables to bowl of ice water. Drain well. (Vinaigrette and vegetables can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover separately and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.719', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.085');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d7aabe2-84b8-470b-b77e-3d6eaee4857a', 'Heat vinaigrette in heavy large skillet over medium heat until warm. Add beans, turnips, and peas; toss until heated through and coated with vinaigrette, about 5 minutes. Add all herbs and toss to coat. Season to taste with additional salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.723', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.086');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca63d033-cd0c-45b0-8e62-ce0e0b2e7fb5', 'Whisk together vinegar, sugar, and salt in a small bowl until sugar and salt are dissolved, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified. Season with pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.728', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.087');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c7a321a-9599-4234-9b2f-027cfdfd30c2', 'Cut off tops and bottoms from clementines to expose fruit, then, resting fruit on a cutting board, remove peel, including all white pith, by cutting off vertical strips with a sharp paring knife. Cut segments free from inner membranes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.733', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.087');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f53585c-06b0-4468-ae74-3e2d52f567e9', 'Halve endives lengthwise, then cut out and discard cores. Cut endives diagonally into 1/2-inch-wide strips and put in a large salad bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.737', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.088');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12eb7221-f41e-4ecc-b8a4-bc46211b7d22', 'Separate celery leaves from ribs and cut ribs diagonally into very thin slices, then add leaves and ribs to endives along with olives, onions, parsley, and clementine segments. Whisk dressing, then gently toss salad with enough dressing to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.741', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.088');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12d7e530-6ab6-4af5-bf84-7c07d9ef14cf', 'Line 2 large baking sheets with paper towels. Attach candy thermometer to side of large deep pot (do not let tip touch bottom). Add enough peanut oil to pot to reach depth of 3 inches. Heat oil over medium heat to 300°F. Place potatoes between 2 kitchen towels and pat dry. Working in batches, add potatoes to oil and cook until potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally and maintaining heat at 300°F, about 3 minutes per batch. Transfer potatoes to 1 prepared baking sheet to drain. Heat same oil until temperature reaches 360°F to 365°F. Working in batches, add same fries to oil and cook until golden brown, maintaining temperature between 360°F and 365°F, about 2 minutes per batch. Transfer to second prepared baking sheet to drain. Transfer french fries to serving dish; sprinkle with salt, then toss with truffle oil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.745', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.089');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61382289-e508-4caf-a78c-98cc3dbb62bb', '*Truffle oil is available at Italian markets, specialty foods stores, and some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.75', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.089');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5879a19-5e54-473c-9d83-3f013693b2c2', 'Bring first 6 ingredients to boil in small saucepan over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer until mixture is reduced to 3/4 cup, about 25 minutes. Cool. Strain mixture. Add rum and stir to combine. Refrigerate until cold, at least 1 hour. (Cinnamon-clove syrup can be prepared 2 days ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.753', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.09');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e98c2f1-da78-44a2-8aa3-e4c346e9ea15', 'Scoop out enough melon balls from honeydew and cantaloupe to measure 4 cups total. Divide melon balls among 6 bowls. Top with syrup and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.758', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.091');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bfa71eea-09b0-4537-852b-94d4713be037', 'Heat oil in heavy large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add shallots and sauté until beginning to brown, about 8 minutes. Add Marsala and sugar and stir until sugar dissolves. Add cranberries, curry powder and mustard. Bring to boil, reduce heat to medium and boil gently until berries pop, stirring occasionally, about 7 minutes. Remove from heat and mix in ginger. Cool. Season relish to taste with salt. Cover and refrigerate. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.762', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.091');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0af4cbda-1139-44bc-93aa-b1fe7a220e39', '1. Preheat the oven to 350°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.766', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.092');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('890698d8-6072-4537-997f-0426455d1bfc', '2. On a sheet pan, roast the tomatoes, garlic, and onion until tender and lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Transfer them along with the chiles and vinegar to the jar of an electric blender and purée until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.771', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.092');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3235a84c-f519-4abb-b127-8188e1596f93', '3. Pour the mixture into a medium-size saucepan and gently simmer for about 20 minutes; season to taste with salt and reserve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.775', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.093');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fa1a9d6-c34d-43f9-b65e-5864df635c65', 'Stir cumin in dry skillet over medium heat until lightly toasted, about 2 minutes. Transfer to mortar or spice mill; grind.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.78', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.093');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3a62478-b699-4c7f-b1ce-6dc0f067d8cc', 'Heat 1/4 cup oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cumin; stir 1 minute. Add chickpeas, 1 teaspoon coarse salt, paprika, and cayenne; sauté until chickpeas begin to darken, about 5 minutes. Pour chickpea liquid into 2-cup measuring cup; add enough water (if necessary) to measure 2 cups. Add liquid to chickpea mixture; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium; simmer until chickpeas begin to soften, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Pour chickpea mixture into strainer set over bowl; reserve cooking liquid. Transfer chickpeas to processor; add 3/4 cup of reserved cooking liquid. Add 1/2 cup oil; puree until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Cool. Do ahead Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover; chill. Bring to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.784', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.094');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33865f8b-860b-4c9f-b089-baf38958aa9d', '1. Preheat oven to 375°F. Toss cauliflower with 1 teaspoon olive oil and arrange in a single layer on one side of a rimmed baking sheet. Toss tomatoes with 1 teaspoon olive oil and arrange on other side of sheet. Season with salt and pepper. Roast until florets are browned in spots and tomatoes are soft, about 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.789', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.096');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c12b3332-5abf-4f07-949f-b2bb4ad1765c', '2. In a medium pot, heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium-high. Cook onion, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Add garlic, ginger, and curry powder and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.793', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.096');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5675b82f-dadc-471b-9f1e-0128f7b8a9ac', '3. Add chickpeas, tomatoes, and 2 cups water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and simmer 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.798', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.097');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15ec6e86-47bb-4012-9ddc-220bd5a85542', '4. Add cauliflower and cook until warmed through and chickpeas are tender, about 8 minutes. Stir in spinach and cilantro and season with salt. To serve, divide among 4 bowls (over rice, if desired).', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.801', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('654ef4d3-e5b0-44bb-892c-c10dd79cb9fd', '• 1 tablespoon ketchup or tomato paste', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.523', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.335');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('258e8eec-81c2-488b-b397-5db3e30bca88', 'Arrange arugula on a large platter. Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with red onion. Drizzle with your favorite vinaigrette and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.805', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f1959c7-4ad1-405e-a7e7-f848464465ee', 'Combine oranges and next 6 ingredients in large bowl; toss to combine. Cover and chill at least 1 hour and up to 6 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.81', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff32626c-274e-43da-993a-5bf721ab897c', 'Spoon fruit and syrup into bowls. Top each with scoop of sorbet and mint sprigs and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.815', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('864a84c8-30ac-44f1-bde8-1b183ddc1a9c', '*A flavoring extract available at liquor stores and in the liquor or specialty foods section of some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.819', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1116722-a9b4-451c-97f0-87616d42ea0b', 'Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat. Add 2/3 cup onion and turmeric and sauté 5 minutes. Mix in rice. Add water, lemongrass and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to simmer. Cover, reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 18 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand covered 10 minutes. Discard lemongrass.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.824', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3672a10-aa14-4c45-97bc-f6cb720f5790', 'Heat remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add green onion and sauté 1 minute. Add rice and stir until heated through. Season to taste with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.828', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.101');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe26b058-1d24-4856-a52f-34564aa41f50', 'Peel and core the quince, and grate coarsely or slice into the finest slivers. Pile in a bowl, sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1-2 hours. Rinse under cold running water, drain well, and dry thoroughly with a clean tea towel. Mix with the remaining ingredients, cover and chill until required.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.833', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.102');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aafc6fec-1f9e-4f8d-87f2-399025c89576', 'Combine vinegar and fennel seeds in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.837', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe71ae01-998f-4e0b-82dd-af6fdcaea95d', 'Cut all peel and white pith from grapefruits. Cut grapefruits between membranes to release segments. Stir segments into dressing. Let stand at least 15 minutes and up to 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.841', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6687a35c-d253-4e30-a6df-afef1a3ea392', 'Toss radicchio, spinach and olives in bowl. Add grapefruit segments and dressing to coat. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('efefc26c-d97b-4bdd-ad07-c5d23b51a094', 'In a food processor or blender puree the raspberries, the peaches, the sugar, the oil, and 1/8 teaspoon of the crushed peppercorns, force the mixture through a fine sieve set over a bowl, pressing hard on the solids, and chill the sauce, covered, until it is very cold. Divide the melon wedges among 4 chilled dessert plates and pour some of the sauce over each serving. sprinkle each serving with some of the sliced basil and some of the additional crushed peppercorns and garnish the plates with the basin sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.849', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d51596ba-e214-4a6e-a976-b0eb5e082a57', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Place smoke chips in 8x6-inch foil packet with open top. Set packet atop coals about 5 minutes before grilling. Brush eggplant with 2 tablespoons corn oil. Grill until cooked, about 5 minutes per side. Cut into 3/4-inch cubes. Place in large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.853', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f70320e0-4507-45cf-806b-b7727198200c', 'Toast sesame seeds in heavy small skillet over medium-low heat until light brown, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.857', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('030ce984-0300-41b9-b08a-fb48718723be', 'Whisk vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil, crushed red pepper and 2 tablespoons corn oil in medium bowl. Add watercress to eggplant in large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle sesame seeds over salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b84b5207-db51-49df-8598-1fe929c938cf', 'Simmer tomatoes, chickpeas, Onion and Garlic Mix, Broccoli and Red Bell Pepper Mix, salt, oregano, pepper, pepper flakes and ½ cup water in a medium pot until liquid reduces by half, about 20 minutes. Add artichokes, peas and olives; cook 10 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.865', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f90757f4-c681-4ed1-a28e-ce9690de9f8e', 'While cooking, make the filling for the shepherd''s pie. If not eating immediately, pour into an airtight container and freeze. Otherwise, toss with penne and basil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.87', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9e04201-f927-40b6-a8f6-12353a5974ab', 'Microwave on high 2 minutes; stir; microwave 2 minutes more. Mix with penne and basil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.874', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a3bd712-6880-4b8a-a59d-2a513ea0dfcf', 'Bring a large saucepan of heavily salted water to a boil. Add onions and cook until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Drain and transfer to a large heatproof bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.878', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed072d11-b1c7-4756-b23c-cfe779789e97', 'Cook coriander seeds, fennel seeds, and peppercorns in another large saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly toasted, about 2 minutes. Add chile, thyme, vinegar, and sugar; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat; add to bowl with onions. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and chill at least 12 hours before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.882', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e13e6526-67cb-4a92-9851-adc6bab5ec02', 'In a large pot, heat oil over medium heat. Sauté onion, 5 minutes. Add garlic and ginger; cook, stirring often, 5 minutes. Add beets and 4 cups stock; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until beets are fork-tender, 20 minutes. With an immersion or regular blender, puree soup, adding remaining 1 cup stock as needed to reach desired consistency. Stir in milk, salt and pepper. Garnish with parsley and julienned beets and serve with bread, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.886', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.109');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a2410353-4906-41a3-bda2-36405ee32a48', 'In a nonreactive saucepan, bring to a boil the vinegar, water, salt, and sugar, stirring to dissolve the salt and sugar. Let the liquid cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.89', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.11');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('766af0a8-a818-41ed-a616-604a9e244075', 'Pack the peas, garlic, chile peppers, and tarragon into a 1-quart jar. Pour the cooled liquid over the peas, and cover the jar with a nonreactive cap.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.894', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d6f296b-36d6-48ad-9712-7fb6be3f4814', 'Store the jar in the refrigerator for at least 2 weeks before eating the peas. Refrigerated, they will keep for several months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.899', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91f2c371-21ff-4858-af7a-309b814396f8', 'In a steamer set over boiling water steam the squash, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until it is very tender. Reserve the steaming liquid and force the squash through a ricer or food mill set over a large bowl. Stir in the oil, the lime juice, and enough of the reserved steaming liquid to reach the desired consistency and season the squash purée with the nutmeg and salt and pepper. The squash purée may be made 3 days in advance, kept covered and chilled, and reheated, adding additional water as needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.903', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63be1a9f-4aa7-45f6-8e10-5237687ffdca', 'Toss together all ingredients and chill, covered, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.917', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d58e5fd-dfbf-465a-b283-8aa95da3c2e3', 'Puree cantaloupe in blender. Add 1/2 cup Essencia and 1/2 cup sugar; blend until sugar dissolves. Transfer to ice cream maker; process according to manufacturer''s instructions. Freeze in covered container. (Can be made 1 week ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.921', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.113');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51c640e1-2cdd-4baa-953e-80dcfa186783', 'When pears are cool enough to handle, fill cavities with quince paste and stand pears upright in dish again.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.609', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.21');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a2225ef-327f-4df0-a6e8-acf2b0aba2bf', 'Combine 3/4 cup Essencia, 1/4 cup sugar and star anise in heavy small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Simmer until reduced to 1/2 cup, about 4 minutes. Chill until cold. (Can be made 1 day ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.926', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.114');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('950dbdc9-18cb-4514-9b0e-d3e1dbd6e250', 'Remove star anise from syrup. Add diced melon to syrup and toss gently. Scoop sorbet into glasses. Spoon compote over. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.114');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b91466a5-4ded-4df2-9e46-2d3e783adca5', 'Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and stir thoroughly to distribute the ingredients well. Season to taste with more chile, lemon juice, or salt, if you want. I like to let the salsa sit for at least 30 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.935', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.115');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf166578-833a-43af-950b-e0a5c22aa99d', 'Holding the parsley in a bunch, trim off and discard an inch or so from the bottom of the stems. Cut the bunch crosswise into thirds. Place in a colander, rinse, and drain. Bounce the colander up and down to shake off excess water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.939', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.115');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60696830-479a-4ae5-a893-c3152d50ae93', 'Place the tahini, parsley, garlic, 4 tablespoons lemon juice, and 2 tablespoons water into the bowl of a food processor. Blend well, scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed and adding enough additional water and/or lemon juice to create a sauce with a smooth, pourable consistency and a nice puckery taste. (The amount of liquid you''ll need to add will depend upon the thickness of the tahini and how much water adhered to the parsley.) Add the salt and cayenne (if using). Refrigerate until needed, for up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.943', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.115');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64b5983b-a208-43f0-8dcd-84cf92da33fe', 'Bring carrots, 2 Tbsp. sugar, and 1/4 cup water to a simmer in a medium skillet over medium-low heat, stirring to separate carrots. Cook until carrots are soft, about 5 minutes. Increase heat to medium and cook, stirring, until liquid is reduced to a thick syrup (if syrup starts to color, reduce heat). Add several generous pinches of sugar, tossing constantly, then cook, tossing, until carrots are coated. Spread out on a parchment-lined baking sheet and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.116');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be2c5d6a-dd97-4b19-9664-1255601d0703', 'Separate carrots with your fingers and toss each piece in more sugar to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.953', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.117');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4da7260d-af17-4075-b524-8b283f7d21bc', 'Carrots can be made 1 day ahead. Store tightly wrapped at room temperature. Toss in sugar before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.957', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.119');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e85fe3e7-1707-460b-b42c-67cc004e21e8', 'In a small saucepan simmer all ingredients except brandy, stirring,', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.961', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.12');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d5c867e9-cea6-4bbf-b9f7-787939608389', '5 minutes, and remove pan from heat. Stir in brandy and cool. Brandied fruits may be made 2 days ahead and chilled, covered. Bring brandied fruits to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.965', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.12');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7103399-f60d-459c-88c6-20fc15aeab91', 'Combine tomatoes, scallions, jalapeño, corn, and lime juice in a medium bowl. Season with salt. Using a fork, gently smash avocado slices evenly onto each toast. Top each generously with tomato-corn salsa.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.97', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.121');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4a069b2-342a-4d55-a8c1-2c853b03b25f', 'Stir 1/4 cup water, sugar and mint in medium saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves and syrup comes to simmer. Remove from heat. Cover and let steep 5 minutes. Add thawed blackberries with juices, reserved blackberry puree from Frozen Blackberry-Cream Pops, and cassis. Transfer mixture to blender and puree until smooth. Strain sauce into medium bowl, pressing on solids to extract as much liquid as possible; discard solids in strainer. Chill until cold. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.973', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.121');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c56385d7-b69c-41c2-9ed4-10c5d494af3b', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Toast cumin seeds and coriander seeds in small skillet over medium heat until beginning to brown, about 2 minutes. Cool. Transfer to spice mill; process until finely ground. Place chickpeas, olive oil, pinch of cayenne, and ground spices in medium bowl. Sprinkle with coarse salt; toss to coat evenly. Transfer to small rimmed baking sheet. Roast in oven until lightly browned and crunchy, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes. DO AHEAD: Can be made 4 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Reheat in 400°F oven until warm, about 5 minutes, before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.977', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.122');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88c34f39-d494-4116-a770-4de18cf27849', 'Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Divide smoothie between 2 glasses and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.982', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.123');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6713b855-3bdd-4203-9cd4-3bd266c55ac6', 'Mix all ingredients in small bowl. Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes, tossing occasionally. Serve chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.986', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.123');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e24de642-092e-4dcd-b680-fe584b0b2a17', 'Preheat oven to 300° F. and coat bottom of a 13-by-9 inch baking dish with 3 tablespoons oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.99', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.124');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc7f5bac-b640-41f4-81c1-82f1f0055d0d', 'Cut a thin slice from stem end of each tomato and arrange tomatoes, cut sides down, in dish. Bake tomatoes 30 minutes. Baste tomatoes with pan juices and bake 30 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.995', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.124');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f50ac4e-ae0c-4021-91d9-26b93ff3a19f', 'In a small bowl stir together sugar, salt, and pepper and sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake tomatoes 30 minutes more (1 1/2 hours total).', '2023-06-12 17:13:23.999', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.125');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6d080d4-1c34-4748-ac42-be193091920e', 'Mince garlic and in a skillet cook with parsley in remaining 3 tablespoons oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until garlic is softened, 3 to 5 minutes. Season parsley mixture with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.004', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.127');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36d50e61-ffb3-4847-a533-55b12b83618e', 'Serve tomatoes topped with pan juices and parsley mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.007', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.127');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3a07186-afc4-41cd-8104-07a145c71a59', 'Nectarine-Thyme Saladita
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea8fb653-f5fa-4621-adec-ea7227b41838', 'Apple-Parsley Saladita
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1c3db7a2-45e6-44e3-ae92-fe4b1331a812', 'Pomegranate-Mint Saladita
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b64a33bb-be08-4d3d-8fc5-7c6d0e80691f', 'Mango-Cilantro Saladita
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b1e2b5f-e1a5-4cd1-bb6a-c9576819a203', 'Serve dip with fennel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.455');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('96f911f9-6b1d-4730-a28a-b67d7e3d866b', 'Stir water, sugar and juice in saucepan over low heat until sugar dissolves. Add berries; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer until mixture thickens slightly, about 2 minutes. Cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.028', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.129');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7dbf344f-f29c-4c12-860c-b1e58931e39f', 'Whisk minced shallots, olive oil and lemon juice in medium bowl to blend. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.033', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.13');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43df05b9-9f49-4085-a876-0c813075912d', 'Cut all peel and white pith from oranges. Using small sharp knife, cut between membranes to release segments. Combine arugula, fennel and onion in large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Add orange segments; toss to combine. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.037', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.13');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef889996-6111-4440-8117-a3da6cb4ea3d', 'Char poblano chilies and bell pepper over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Enclose in paper bag 10 minutes. Peel and seed chilies and pepper; cut into 1/2-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.041', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.131');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('45cd316c-7768-4c46-beca-18bb142cc190', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add half of zucchini; sauté until brown, about 7 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer to medium bowl. Repeat with remaining zucchini. Discard oil from skillet; wipe skillet clean. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; sauté until onion begins to soften, about 5 minutes. Add chilies and pepper and stir until heated through, about 3 minutes. Stir in zucchini and corn. Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook until corn is tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.132');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a639e86-a1cd-4c0b-80b9-8aaa718e2595', '*Fresh green chilies, often called pasillas; available at Latin American markets and some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.048', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.132');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('736ec610-f167-4974-97da-40232d90adf5', 'In a small saucepan combine all ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Cool sauce to room temperature. Sauce may be made 3 days ahead and kept chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.053', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.133');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e27b45f-9965-44e4-8ce8-32e756bf677b', 'Serve sauce at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.057', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.133');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3ff3a0fa-b805-4220-b5f4-b0ac7442181a', 'In a large bowl, mix together all the ingredients. Cover and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours or up to 2 days to allow the flavors to meld and permeate the carrots. Served chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.061', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.134');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('271de9f3-cc84-4043-ba30-9abc79872f18', 'Moroccan Cooked Carrot Salad (Shlata Chizo Metbucha): o not grate the carrots, but cut them on a diagonal into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Cook in gently boiling water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. Drain, rinse under cold water, and drain again. Toss with the dressing as above.
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8a5313a-ea78-43ad-8625-4d058d8f31fc', 'Preheat broiler.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.07', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.137');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2be225a2-8fe1-4c38-81c6-3ea12555be1d', 'Halve eggplants lengthwise. Brush cut sides with 1/4 cup oil and season with salt. Arrange as many eggplants, cut sides up, as will fit in 1 layer on rack of a broiler pan and broil 2 to 3 inches from heat until browned, about 5 minutes. Turn oven setting to 450°F. and move pan to middle of oven. Roast until tender when pierced with a fork, about 12 minutes. Repeat with remaining eggplants.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.074', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.137');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa892b6e-8e29-4826-b4c9-3c0f0588cd5d', 'Blend remaining 1 1/2 cups oil and remaining ingredients in a blender until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.078', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.137');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b089bda-45a4-49bc-bb46-01149707731d', 'Serve eggplants at room temperature, drizzled with vinaigrette.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.081', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a6ad4e0-a003-4336-849e-690f610a5de7', '6 small (4-oz.) eggplants', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.086', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0978d155-4951-4a7e-ab1b-71fd18b62cc2', '8 tablespoons olive oil', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.089', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('69f77b15-2467-475f-9a8c-66ff742ae0f3', '1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds, toasted', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.093', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23e9d462-f6ac-4cbf-89d5-63d4c2492900', '1/4 cup fresh cilantro', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.139');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('140c60a1-8ad5-46ee-aadf-00007805696b', '1/4 cup fresh flat-leaf parsley', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.101', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.139');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('20ce2fe6-f101-461b-bf5c-868fea3c6483', '1 garlic clove', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.105', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.139');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('feb0e27d-d9a2-427a-9384-1a7396ed03e3', '1/4 teaspoon salt', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.109', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.14');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b6127db-55e1-48cf-a032-6a114aee6427', '1/8 teaspoon cayenne', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.112', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.14');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c8cf7bd-0b73-4e57-8650-5a6dcf1a3a0d', '3 tablespoons lemon juice', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.116', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.14');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('06fa1099-ebe4-48b1-b4c1-9ac0b5f05f7e', 'Bring sugar and 1/4 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar. Add mint sprigs and chile. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean. Remove syrup from heat; cover and let steep for 15 minutes for flavors to infuse.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.12', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.142');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b29f917-cbf6-47d5-98bb-067a17e20b84', 'Strain syrup through a fine-mesh sieve into a small bowl; stir in lime juice. DO AHEAD: Syrup can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.126', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.142');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81b8c962-23bb-4feb-ac4e-15f4f9ddced0', 'Arrange melon slices in a 13x9x2" glass baking dish. Pour syrup over melon in baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 2 hours to allow flavors to meld.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.13', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.142');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94e7a51a-2e29-4465-8b6a-d46c9aab1504', 'Divide melon slices among plates, overlapping them decoratively. Pour remaining syrup in dish into a small pitcher. DO AHEAD: Melon carpaccio can be made up to 5 hours ahead. Cover and chill melon and remaining syrup separately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.135', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.142');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f490023-f2a9-4554-bcad-fff33a93d037', 'Drizzle some of syrup over melon. Place a scoop of sorbet in center of each plate, if using; garnish with mint leaves and lime zest.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.139', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.143');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3099de2f-b12b-496d-ae64-120f2ccbe654', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl. Slowly whisk in oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.143', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.143');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11509ae9-91db-4b8b-9391-66d820a090e7', 'Combine mixed greens, cucumber, carrot, and onion in large bowl. Toss with dressing to coat and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.147', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.144');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b6146dc-586d-483c-a08a-186da6a13e37', 'Prick sweet potatoes and roast on a foil-lined baking sheet in middle of oven 1 hour, or until very soft. Cool potatoes just until they can be handled and scoop flesh into a food processor.Purée potatoes until smooth. Add lime juice and salt to taste and purée mixture until combined well. Sweet potato purée may be made 2 days ahead and chilled, its surface covered with plastic wrap.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.151', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.144');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7fb3b0f-02f4-47b1-b4f1-cd228aa644b7', 'Combine bananas and 1/4 cup orange juice in processor and puree. Transfer to pitcher. Combine pineapple chunks and 1/4 cup orange juice in processor and puree. Transfer to same pitcher. Mix in water, syrup, grenadine, lemon juice and 1 1/2 cups orange juice. (Can be made 6 hours ahead. Chill. Stir well before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.154', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.145');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8da3099c-6810-4e0b-97a1-1a95927c51f8', 'Pour fruit mixture into tall glasses. Garnish with strawberries and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.158', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.145');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('92b9100c-0bfe-45d1-ba3d-1292989d0a47', 'Make spice sachet by wrapping together in cheesecloth the cinnamon sticks, coriander seeds, cloves, peppercorns, bay leaves, and cardamom pods. Tie with kitchen string.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.146');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('142332cb-d430-4c3e-be2d-358ab26ed0ed', 'In heavy, large pot over high heat, stir together 4 cups water, tomatoes, garlic, ginger, cilantro stems, 1 teaspoon salt, and spice sachet. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until reduced by 1/3, about 30 minutes. Strain through fine-mesh sieve into large clean pot, reserving solids. Discard spice sachet. Measure 1 cup of strained liquid in pot and transfer to blender. Add reserved solids and pureé until smooth. Strain through fine-mesh sieve back into pot with liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.165', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.146');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c8e8f7b5-ed4e-4450-9e6a-42b458ea5da4', 'Place pot over high heat and bring to simmer, about 5 minutes. Stir in ground pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt. Serve immediately, topping each portion with chopped cilantro leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.169', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.147');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f905db15-ac8d-445e-bddf-b7af28a8f27d', 'Heat the olive oil with the almonds in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring every couple of minutes or so, until the almonds are evenly light brown in color and the oil is highly fragrant.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.173', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.148');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d075f81-6fd2-4593-8fd2-c53a5b64d449', 'Cool the oil to room temperature. Store it tightly covered in the refrigerator; the oil will congeal, so take it out about 20 minutes before you need it. It will keep for a couple of weeks in the fridge and can also be frozen for months, until the next sale!', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.177', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.148');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f3d15abe-87ec-479b-856e-cee0aa736dcc', 'In a small bowl whisk together the vinegar, the oil, and salt and pepper to taste. In a large saucepan of boiling salted water cook the green beans for 4 minutes, add the snow peas, and cook the vegetables for 30 seconds. Drain the vegetables, transfer them to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop the cooking, and drain them. Pat the vegetables dry between several thicknesses of paper towels and in a bowl toss them with the sunflower seeds and the dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.149');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5806a4b3-2087-4056-9001-305f2fa219ef', 'In a large saucepan combine the cranberries, the apples, chopped coarse (not peeled or cored), the wine, and the sugar, bring the mixture to a boil, stirring, and simmer it, covered, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes. Simmer the mixture, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes more, or until it is very thick and is reduced to about 3 cups. Force the mixture through a food mill fitted with the fine disk into a bowl, spoon it into an oiled 3-to-4 cup decorative mold, and chill it, covered, overnight. Run a thin knife around the edge of the mold and dip the mold into warm water for 10 seconds. Invert the mold onto a serving plate and garnish the cranberry sauce with the mint sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.149');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fba5cc4f-8f12-4c5d-8311-69acdc5f22ef', 'Remove the stems and roots from the spinach. Rinse in many changes of cold water until any trace of sand is removed. Place in a large pot with a pinch of salt and no water other than that retained from washing. Cook over moderately high heat, covered, for 5 minutes. Drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.19', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.15');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89fcbcb5-215b-4212-8324-9aa980421a32', 'Soak the raisins in the lukewarm water for a couple of minutes, then drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.195', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.151');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c88f02f-b366-40a2-af27-4ef302aa0676', 'Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet, add the onion and sauté until the onion is soft and translucent; add the raisins, pignoli, and small amounts of salt and pepper. Sauté, stirring, 1 minute. Add the spinach and nutmeg and sauté, stirring frequently, until the spinach looks dry and crisp.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.199', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.151');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d30c362b-a4a0-43bf-8ff1-12035d8b839b', 'In a jelly-roll or large baking pan toss the potatoes with the garlic, the oil, and salt and pepper to taste and roast them in the middle of a preheated 500°F. oven, stirring once, for 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.203', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.152');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f3ad0421-fbfb-4764-87db-ccfc3a4475f3', 'Seed and dice 10 tomato halves; transfer to large bowl. Place remaining tomatoes in blender; add onion, lime juice, chiles, salt, and pepper. Blend until smooth. Add cilantro. Pulse just to mix in cilantro. Pour tomato puree into bowl with diced tomatoes. Stir to blend. Season salsa to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.207', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.152');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('383f6cef-c7e6-4fc0-8b97-698412619dfc', 'Whisk 1/4 cup olive oil and 2 tablespoons Sherry vinegar in a large bowl; season with salt and pepper. Add 1 thinly sliced small shallot and 1/2 cup torn fresh herbs (such as dill, mint, and/or chives).', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.153');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('08eed131-d3ac-4dc6-998c-ffa69b7c642f', 'Fold in 3 cups raw or cooled blanched fresh corn kernels; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.215', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.153');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79b7362e-c3e5-4e7e-b291-e65a81b393ff', 'Prepare a gas grill for direct-heat cooking over medium-high heat; see Grilling Procedure .', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.219', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.154');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('72813f69-fa0c-4aa3-bfa0-34659a622e37', 'Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch-thick slices and cook in a large pot of well-salted boiling water 10 minutes (potatoes will not be cooked through).', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.222', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.154');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('72b6e531-6076-4388-a878-153548845e18', 'Meanwhile, stir together herbs, garlic, oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a large shallow dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.226', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.155');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('872c9b11-5c95-4e6f-8101-2cb30033db39', 'Drain potatoes well and transfer to herb oil, tossing gently to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.23', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.155');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05e12876-9761-41b9-b2f4-b9b4135f2806', 'Transfer potatoes to grill, letting excess oil drip into dish (reserve oil in dish). Grill potatoes, covered, turning once or twice, until tender, about 5 minutes total. Return potatoes to dish and toss again with herb oil. Squeeze lemon wedge over potatoes. Season with salt and serve with additional lemon wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.235', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.156');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c0df9122-6d62-4a9f-9764-eb2796dade1f', 'In a kettle bring the water to a boil, sprinkle in the rice and salt to taste, stirring until the water returns to a boil, and boil the rice for 10 minutes. Drain the rice in a large colander and rinse it. Set the colander over a large saucepan of boiling water and steam the rice, covered with a kitchen towel and the lid, for 15 minutes, or until it is fluffy and dry. The rice may be made 2 days in advance and kept chilled in an airtight container. Reheat the rice in the colander set over a saucepan of boiling water. Transfer the rice to a large bowl, sprinkle it with the paprika, and toss the mixture to coat the rice thoroughly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.238', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.158');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d87d1627-3764-45b3-8c97-b7e9a2b793ec', 'Slice star fruit crosswise with slicer into 1/16-inch-thick slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.243', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.158');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8baf7e0d-5069-4aeb-bff2-d9aa0a23f230', 'Bring sugar and water to a boil in a 2-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add star fruit, then remove from heat and let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes. Pour star fruit into a sieve set over a bowl and drain 15 minutes. Reserve syrup for quince apple strudels .', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.247', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.159');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25570ac6-e412-4646-abd4-9faad61719c0', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 200°F. Put liner on a large (17- by 11-inch) baking sheet, then arrange star-fruit slices in 1 layer on liner (discard extra along with any broken slices). Bake until dry, 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Immediately transfer chips to a rack to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.25', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.16');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aea58b93-093f-4496-8d23-34956726b66a', 'Heat oil in heavy large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and sauté 5 minute Add green beans and cayenne pepper and sauté until onion is translucent, about 3 minutes. Add zucchini, potatoes and parsley. Pour tomatoes and their juices over vegetables. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, stirring frequently, about 45 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.) Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.255', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.16');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e1fcb4a-f3b4-4cef-b601-d3e8a664ed71', 'Place bulgur in large bowl. Whisk lemon juice, oil and garlic to blend in small bowl; pour over bulgur. Mix in cucumbers, parsley, green onions, dill, and mint. Cover and chill until bulgur is tender, about 6 hours. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Keep chilled.) Serve cold or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.259', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.161');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('90c489fc-f75d-42cf-b9fc-ce7919149e76', 'Soak corn husks in large bowl of hot water for 1/2 hour, then separate and continue to soak until pliable, up to 1/2 hour more. Tear one or two husks into 1/4-inch strips to use for tying the tamales.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.263', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.161');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e83b9a38-2f20-4e0e-a002-e37b14886ca2', 'Boil 1 cup water in medium saucepan. Remove from heat and gradually stir in masa. Cover and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.266', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.162');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a13c1655-272a-4e7a-ad8b-153233e39d80', 'Combine 1/3 cup water, sugar, small pinch salt, and vanilla bean, if using, in small saucepan. Bring to simmer, simmer for 5 minutes. Take pan off heat and stir in coconut and vanilla flavoring or extract, if using. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.27', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.163');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74706571-40c1-47f8-a6f0-0cb95761b221', 'In standing mixer fitted with whisk attachment, cream butter or shortening with baking powder, if using. Add masa and coconut mixtures, and beat until dough is smooth, fluffy, and light.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.163');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2188e020-a777-41ee-ba23-3d7d9db1ff46', 'Arrange steamer rack in very large stockpot and add water to just below bottom of rack. Cover and bring water to boil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.279', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('326a283b-de2f-4ec9-9296-d408ebf20a84', 'Place 12 drained corn husks on work surface. Put 3 to 4 tablespoons masa dough into center of one husk and spoon some raisins on top. Fold long sides over filling, then tie ends of tamale shut with husk strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.282', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c74025b5-a9ba-41b2-952c-ef1b06846500', 'Repeat process to make 12 tamales. Place upright, leaning against one another, in steamer. If necessary, insert pieces of crumpled foil between tamales to keep them upright. Cover and steam until dough is firm to touch and separates easily from husk, adding more water to pot as necessary, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.286', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e772dd35-2763-44ed-81ec-7fd2843e7f99', 'Serve with Slow-Braised Lamb Shanks with Guajillo-Pineapple Sauce .', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.29', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04995063-09ae-408b-821d-39ba69d0a4c3', 'Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to a boil. Add the rice and cook, stirring occasionally, just until tender, about 25 minutes. Drain and rinse well with cold water until cool. Transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.293', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('814a448e-9ef8-4a58-9b0c-2324a65842f1', 'Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in the same saucepan over medium heat until hot. Add the chile, onion and garlic and stir until slightly softened, about 3 minutes. Add the corn and salt and cook, stirring, just until heated through, about 1 minute. Transfer the vegetables to the bowl with the rice and toss to mix.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.297', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.165');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8069162d-44de-448c-b3dd-fcf78f833284', 'Add the beans, the remaining 2 tablespoons oil and the vinegar and toss well. Season with plenty of pepper and toss again.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.165');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7ff681e-0cba-444c-9258-a04eac92b477', 'Combine the water, apple juice, pineapple, arugula/rocket, mint, macadamia nuts, chia seeds, and salt in a blender. Blend until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.305', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.165');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f402c8c9-b9f0-481d-9734-2b47af2b6a74', 'Place 1/4 cup warm water in medium bowl. Sprinkle yeast and sugar over; stir to blend. Let stand until very puffed, about 6 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.309', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.166');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7cd58319-63da-4242-a579-ed3b5619b31b', 'Mix both flours, cornmeal, and salt in processor. Mix 3/4 cup warm water and 2 tablespoons oil into yeast. With machine running, gradually add yeast mixture to dry ingredients. Mix until dough just comes together, adding more water by teaspoonfuls if needed. Process 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.313', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.166');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14faca27-63fb-44ff-947a-bed71c32ef7d', 'Transfer dough to lightly floured work surface. Knead 1 minute. Lightly brush large bowl with oil. Transfer dough to prepared bowl; turn to coat. Cover bowl with plastic wrap. Let dough rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in volume, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.316', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.166');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f23c14fd-b434-4eff-b968-00bb9e67eb36', 'Transfer dough to lightly floured work surface; knead gently. Form dough into 2 balls. Place each on 1 sheet of parchment paper and press out to 9-inch round. Cover with plastic wrap. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Freeze 45 minutes. Transfer to refrigerator. Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.321', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a88fe612-7ad8-4e98-b77a-3029d859fccb', 'Roll out dough as directed in recipe.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.325', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2504282f-fac4-4658-b0da-2c4997b9fe46', 'Bring ruby Port and broken cinnamon sticks to boil in heavy medium saucepan. Reduce heat to medium and simmer mixture 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.329', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9725bc5a-3671-47bf-bdf0-a9c6fce7e2a3', 'Add dried cranberries to saucepan; simmer until slightly softened, about 3 minutes. Add fresh cranberries, 3/4 cup water, and sugar; bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer until cranberry sauce thickens and is darker in color and berries collapse, stirring often, about 20 minutes. Transfer sauce to bowl; cool. Discard cinnamon sticks. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.333', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c0e96262-a94a-4db3-a7af-15b740b5b062', 'Combine juices and liqueur in a large pitcher. Slowly add sparkling wine and stir.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.337', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f8270def-410a-4113-96d2-3b5ae191b9ce', 'In a 10-inch heavy skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and sauté onions and Brussel sprouts, stirring, until onions begin to turn golden, about 1 1/2 minutes. Add water, sugar and salt and pepper to taste and cook, covered, over moderately low heat until vegetables are just tender, about 3 minutes. If any liquid remains, boil mixture until nearly all liquid is evaporated and stir in minced dill. Garnish vegetables with dill sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.34', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('96c2d6fc-3714-417c-abe7-c293e42a2492', 'In a kettle cover potatoes with salted cold water by 2 inches and simmer until just tender, about 25 minutes. Drain potatoes in a colander. When potatoes are just cool enough to handle, halve larger ones and in a large bowl toss potatoes with 2 tablespoons vinegar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.344', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('06e3fb44-3b15-4e72-b555-33377d751509', 'In a small bowl whisk together mustard, remaining 3 tablespoons vinegar, and salt and pepper to taste. Add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified. Dressing may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Bring dressing to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.348', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4d96e26-8d2a-432d-b610-7037dce1e959', 'Using oval-shaped ice cream scooper, place 1 scoop of each sorbet on each plate. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.354', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9ed45d64-499a-498d-9643-c38bd70c1f62', 'Trim beans and, working over a bowl, cut corn kernels from cobs. Have ready a bowl of ice and cold water. In a large saucepan of boiling salted water cook beans until crisp-tender, about 1 minute for haricots verts or about 5 minutes for regular green beans, and transfer with a slotted spoon to ice water to stop cooking. Drain beans well and add to potatoes. Return water in pan to a boil and blanch corn 30 seconds, or until crisp-tender. Drain corn in a sieve and rinse under cold water to stop cooking. Drain corn well and add to salad. Salad may be prepared up to this point 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Bring salad to room temperature before proceeding. Gently toss salad with dressing and salt and pepper to taste until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.352', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8ac2010-a163-4f83-b858-debaf84cb48c', 'Using fork, mash avocado, lime juice, garlic and jalapeño in small bowl until almost smooth. Season guacamole with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.355', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9df8d8e0-b73a-4db2-8337-1e47f6b46a5d', 'Divide guacamole among all bread slices, spreading evenly (guacamole will be thinly spread). Place 5 tomato slices atop guacamole on each of 4 bread slices. Top each with 4 cucumber slices, then 2 onion slices, then cilantro. Top with remaining 4 bread slices, guacamole side down, pressing lightly. Cut sandwiches in half. (Can be prepared 3 hours ahead. Wrap in plastic; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.359', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8eeb762f-d657-4422-8905-cd922ccb4000', 'Heat 14-inch-diameter flat-bottomed wok or heavy 12-inch-diameter skillet over high heat until drop of water added to wok evaporates on contact. Add 1 tablespoon peanut oil and swirl, then add tofu and stir-fry until tofu just begins to brown, about 1 minute. Transfer tofu to plate. Add remaining 1 tablespoon peanut oil to same wok (do not clean). Add carrots, celery, and Szechuan preserved vegetable and stir-fry until carrots are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Return tofu to wok; add rice wine, salt, sugar, and white pepper. Stir-fry to blend, about 1 minute. Remove pan from heat; stir in sesame oil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.364', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d78b685a-976a-4cd3-84bf-f540181e3f92', 'Cut thick stalks and ribs from chard leaves. Chop stalks and ribs into 1/2-inch pieces. Cook stalks and ribs in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 5 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer stalks and ribs to plate. Add chard leaves to boiling water in pot. Cook just until wilted, stirring occasionally, about 3 minutes. Drain well. Squeeze excess moisture from chard leaves. Coarsely chop leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.367', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a506bcdc-38f9-4702-9b83-41c91607f84f', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and sauté until golden, about 2 minutes. Add chard stalks, ribs and leaves to skillet and sauté until liquid evaporates and mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.371', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.17');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5dee7dfa-34f7-49b5-81d5-1bcc8777dbc0', 'Slit chiles lengthwise, then discard stems, seeds, and veins.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.17');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b084098f-c80a-4ab2-a29f-b3df8e8d7691', 'Heat a large heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron) over medium heat until hot, then toast chiles in batches, opened flat, turning and pressing with tongs, until more pliable and slightly changed in color, about 30 seconds per batch. Tear into pieces and put in a blender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.17');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b875baa-a492-4f5f-916b-5cf43315dad7', 'Half-fill a 2 1/2- to 3-quart saucepan with water and bring to a boil. Add tomatillos and simmer until tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to blender and add onion, chipotle in adobo, garlic, and 3/4 teaspoon salt. Blend until smooth (use caution when blending hot liquids). Transfer to a bowl and cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.383', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ff9369f-6d6f-434d-8579-2de437bf29a6', 'Cook onion and garlic in oil in a large nonstick skillet over moderately low heat, stirring, until softened. Add tomato and chick-peas and cook, stirring, 5 minutes. Add Swiss chard and cook, covered, until wilted, about 2 minutes. Add lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.387', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5bed26e-0262-4a92-82b9-7b560b8dfa9f', 'Dissolve the sugar in the boiling water, then allow to cool. Once cooled, add the lemon juice and soy sauce and mix well to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.391', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a81c88c9-c53a-4fa8-9833-d4461084af56', 'Bring sugar and 1 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Chill syrup until cold, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.395', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6137fe3e-0851-46b0-bc0a-4826eadb4d3d', 'Purée syrup and 2 cups pineapple in a food processor until smooth. Set a fine-mesh strainer over a medium pitcher; strain, pressing on solids to extract purée. Stir in lime juice and remaining 2 cups pineapple. Divide among molds. Cover; insert ice-pop sticks. Freeze until firm. Dip bottoms of molds into hot water for 20-30 seconds to loosen pops. Remove pops and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.398', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e9cfa59-1b51-41fd-b30f-bb2d3dd4faa8', '1. Wash the tomatillos well with warm water to remove the naturally sticky coating, which is bitter. Cut them into quarters.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.402', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.173');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ddb6133a-def4-40ad-9878-eb2ea24ba451', '2. Pulse the tomatillos in a food processor with the remaining ingredients until a slightly chunky texture is achieved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.406', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.173');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('961406ab-0d22-4f72-a244-e2e65f1fb00d', '3. Taste for salt and serve as soon as possible to enjoy maximum bite and crunch.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.41', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.173');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37837d88-c672-4eac-8c19-aaf12db73918', 'Position 2 racks in center of oven; preheat to 450°F. Divide green beans and garlic between 2 heavy large rimmed baking sheets, spreading in single layer. Drizzle with olive oil; sprinkle with salt and crushed red pepper. Roast until green beans begin to brown, about 15 minutes. Divide radicchio and vinegar between sheets; toss. Continue roasting until vegetables are tender and browned in spots, about 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.414', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.174');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4386434-4c67-40da-b673-0f17ca864391', 'Grind fennel seeds in grinder until ground but not powdery. Transfer to a small bowl or cup, then stir in oil until combined. Let stand 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.418', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.174');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b2dc501-7cb4-4b64-a7af-5092c5970fe2', 'Whisk together lemon juice, shallot, salt, and sugar in another small bowl or cup until salt and sugar are dissolved. Stir fennel oil, then add to shallot mixture in a slow stream, whisking until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.423', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.174');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d37d2da-0423-4427-bc27-cdd518ab1133', 'Toss frisée, endives, and celery in a large bowl with just enough vinaigrette to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.426', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.175');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5512e3f7-df61-442c-a9df-467385daac88', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Combine all vegetables except zucchini in large bowl; toss with 3 tablespoons oil. Spread out vegetables on large rimmed baking sheet; reserve bowl. Sprinkle vegetables with salt and pepper. Roast vegetables 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.43', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.176');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ffb6c61-6b01-45be-b771-0817f199311c', 'Meanwhile, add zucchini to reserved bowl. Drizzle with 1 teaspoon oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.434', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.176');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('674e9234-0208-4b58-b541-345e9b72cae2', 'Add zucchini to baking sheet with vegetables. Roast until all vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. DO AHEAD: Vegetables can be made up to 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Rewarm vegetables in 350°F oven 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.438', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.177');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c3b7efd-a5bb-4f5a-8c90-695ce598c4cb', 'Cook green beans, potatoes, and garlic in oil with 2 teaspoons salt and 1 teaspoon pepper in a 5-quart heavy pot over medium-high heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until vegetables begin to soften and stick to bottom of pot, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.446', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.178');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fba99fa6-8e7c-4293-95c4-12321893fa2a', 'Pulse tomatoes with their juice several times in a food processor until coarsely chopped, then add to vegetables. Add water and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Mash a few potatoes into sauce and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.45', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.178');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42341edc-9537-4af4-8983-62f6d9eeb875', 'Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a cookie sheet with foil. Cut the squash lengthwise in half. Seed and cut it into 3- to 4-inch squares, with skin intact. Score the flesh with crosshatch cuts about 1/2 inch deep. Rub all over with olive oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.454', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.179');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6bbc27e7-7a6b-4bd0-9d71-d58cbb9dcc03', 'Set the pieces, skin side down, on the cookie sheet and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake 45 minutes, or until easily pierced with knife and lightly browned. Serve hot or at room temperature, sprinkled with balsamic vinegar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.458', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.18');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4bba290c-679f-4892-bdba-f73c48ea4c9b', 'Working in batches, purée watermelon in a blender until smooth. Pour into a large bowl and let stand for 10 minutes. Skim foam from surface and discard.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.461', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.181');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af244cca-906e-45f9-9af0-7c83418170d7', 'Set a fine-mesh sieve over a large pitcher; line sieve with cheesecloth. Strain purée into pitcher (you should have almost 7 cups juice). Stir in grapefruit juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.465', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.182');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04b2f6ec-9bab-457e-bf0d-70d80ced713b', 'Fill glasses with ice. Divide agua fresca among glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.469', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.183');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e3ced04-fe81-4ec3-aac2-63589df951ab', 'Combine tomatoes, onions, peppers, and 1/4 cup coarse kosher salt in large glass bowl. Stir to mix. Cover and let stand in cool place at least 12 hours and up to 1 day, stirring occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.472', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.183');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42e7dfc0-606b-4ee8-b6b0-0b8f324ce333', 'Drain tomato mixture in large colander. Rinse with cold water; let drain well, at least 30 minutes. Using hands, squeeze any excess liquid from tomato mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.476', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.184');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95f60500-9307-4725-801b-2e9311dac8c0', 'Combine tomato mixture, 1 1/2 teaspoons coarse salt, and next 5 ingredients in large pot. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer until almost all liquid evaporates, stirring frequently, about 1 hour 10 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.479', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.184');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6642764-19e9-49fe-82f6-1e8f742cc9ab', 'Ladle mixture into 6 hot clean 1/2-pint glass canning jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at top of jars. Remove air bubbles. Wipe jar threads and rims with clean damp cloth. Cover with hot lids; apply screw bands. Process jars in pot of boiling water 10 minutes. Cool jars completely. Store in cool dark place up to 1 year.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.483', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.185');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ffda33b-dc2d-4ad5-8bc3-82ea42cfc45f', 'Cook sugar in a dry 1-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, undisturbed, until it begins to melt. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally with a fork, until sugar is melted into a deep golden caramel. Remove from heat and carefully pour in orange juice, then rum (caramel will harden and steam vigorously). Cook over moderately low heat, stirring, until caramel is dissolved. Cool sauce to warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.487', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.186');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('733f9655-fd2b-48bb-8e70-4047d9e1a945', 'Cut the tofu crosswise into 4 slices and let the slices drain between a double thickness of paper towels for 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.186');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1769794-670b-4ee9-b512-f4963e78fda7', 'While the tofu is draining, in a small bowl dissolve the cornstarch in 1/4 cup of the water and stir in the remaining 3/4 cup water, the soy sauce to taste, the vinegar, the Scotch, the sugar, and the salt. In a heavy saucepan heat 1 1/2 tablespoons of the vegetable oil over moderately high heat until it is hot but not smoking and in it stir-fry the garlic until it is pale golden, being careful not to let it burn. Add the gingerroot and stir-fry the mixture for 30 seconds. Stir the soy sauce mixture, add it to the garlic mixture, stirring, and bring the sauce to a boil, stirring. Simmer the sauce for 2 minutes, stir in the sesame oil, and keep the sauce warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.493', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.187');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55c20216-0879-42c6-a368-d6630a44c87c', 'In a non-stick skillet heat the remaining 1 tablespoon vegetable oil over high heat until it is hot but not smoking and in it brown the tofu on all sides, turning it with tongs and transferring it as it is browned to paper towels to drain. Divide the tofu between 2 plates and spoon the sauce over it. Sprinkle the scallion over each serving and serve the tofu with the rice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.189');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('057930d1-82e6-4de9-84df-4c99547e1242', 'Peel and cut 4 medium carrots into long matchstick-size pieces. Heat 1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil in a large skillet, preferably nonstick, over medium heat. Add carrots and cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, 3-4 minutes. Season with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.501', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.189');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a34a40e4-24c9-4702-a676-0b76274c0292', 'Preheat oven to 450°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.505', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.19');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a48669d5-cb03-4942-b7e5-635d7284c2ed', 'Quarter potatoes and in a bowl toss with shallots, 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, and salt and pepper to taste. Transfer mixture to a shallow baking pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.508', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.191');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b594fdfe-ecd4-4167-a8bd-3ba2f7f8714b', 'Wrap garlic tightly in foil and put in pan with potatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.511', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.191');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('811a27c0-071a-4dc5-a80a-d422927a05ec', 'In a large bowl toss kale with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and salt and pepper to taste until combined well. Arrange kale in one layer in another shallow baking pan. Roast kale, potato mixture, and garlic in middle and bottom thirds of oven, switching position of pans in oven halfway through roasting and stirring vegetables occasionally, until potato mixture is golden brown and tender, kale is crisp, and garlic is soft, about 15 minutes. Transfer vegetables (except garlic) to a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Carefully remove garlic from foil and peel. In small bowl with a fork mash garlic with vinegar until smooth and season with salt and pepper. Add dressing to vegetables and toss. Potatoes may be made 4 hours ahead.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.516', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5dd9573e-47dc-496f-a3ea-ecebcde1b506', 'Serve potatoes hot or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.519', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39b94934-eafe-4d93-8d1b-c18dc39a3d98', 'Cut grapefruit in half; using a small knife, cut along membranes to release segments. Dividing evenly, sprinkle grapefruit halves with sugar, red pepper flakes, and rosemary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.523', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.193');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8cdd78f3-aa40-4dd7-8425-c83a7c3a1589', 'In a large saucepan over high heat, bring 3 quarts water and 1/2 cup kosher salt to a boil. Prepare an ice bath of 3 quarts water and ice with 1/2 cup kosher salt stirred in until dissolved. Add the shelled English peas to the boiling water and cook until tender, 2 to 4 minutes. When sweet and tender, immediately remove the peas from the boiling water with a slotted spoon and transfer to the ice bath to stop the cooking. Let sit until the peas are fully cooled, 1 to 2 minutes, then drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.527', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.195');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a37e1e4-be80-4efa-bb61-933102336f98', 'Add spinach to boiling water; cook 1 minute. Drain; wring out. Toss with oil and salt. Add lemon juice; toss again.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.919', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.456');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3474b88b-b119-40da-8742-4025c6b9e9f0', 'Combine blanched peas, green garlic, mint, chervil, lemon, olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and the pepper in a food processor and puree until smooth. Taste for seasoning and adjust as needed. Serve with crudités or Crackers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.53', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.196');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2cefa77-47db-4b28-967c-af4ffd032783', 'Position rack in center of oven; preheat to 425°F. Toss cauliflower and 2 tablespoons oil in large bowl. Heat heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower and sauté until beginning to brown, about 5 minutes. Transfer cauliflower to rimmed baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.533', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.197');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c190659-c0c4-4ecb-948a-aa9c2bcbed19', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil to same skillet. Add onion wedges. Cook until browned on 1 side, about 3 minutes. Using spatula, carefully transfer onions to baking sheet with cauliflower, arranging wedges browned side up. Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to same skillet. Add fennel; sauté until fennel softens slightly and starts to brown, about 5 minutes. Transfer to same baking sheet. Scatter garlic and marjoram over vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until vegetables are caramelized, about 25 minutes. Serve hot or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.537', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.197');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac717f43-089c-498d-80f4-fc0b884839a3', 'Place 5 radishes in processor. Add oil, vinegar, mustard and garlic; process until thick dressing forms. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to small bowl. Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover; chill. Bring just to room temperature before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.54', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.198');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cefe178a-37d5-42fe-a975-339a571912d1', 'Cook green beans in large pot of boiling salted water until just crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain beans and rinse under cold water. Drain. Pat dry with paper towels. Wrap in kitchen towels and place in plastic bag. Chill until cold, at least 1 hour and up to 1 day.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.544', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.199');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('07e449d8-8503-4a04-a657-23a991ab16c6', 'Place beans, mixed greens and onion in large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with sliced radishes, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.548', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49946e61-1ecc-45ef-9a27-aa63248f446e', 'Heat oil in medium saucepan over mediumhigh heat. Add garlic and turmeric; stir 1 minute. Add 1 2/3 cups water, lemon peel, and 1/2 teaspoon coarse salt; bring to boil. Remove pan from heat. Stir in couscous. Cover; let stand until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Fluff with fork; mix in cilantro and lemon juice. Season with pepper and additional coarse salt, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.551', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abd376b1-261a-4d6d-9f9d-4f4b74d693b4', 'Bring wine, 1 cup sugar, and cinnamon to boil in large saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil until reduced to 1 cup, about 18 minutes. Cool syrup completely. Cover and chill until cold. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep chilled.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.555', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.201');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a39f369-be08-4732-b2e3-2abd7654547c', 'Finely grate peel from 2 oranges. Mix peel and 1 tablespoon sugar in small bowl. Using small sharp knife, cut off peel and white pith from all oranges. Working over large bowl, cut between membranes to release segments. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover orange segments and sugared peel separately and chill.) Divide oranges and juice among 8 bowls. Drizzle syrup over and sprinkle with sugared orange peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.558', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.201');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dfc4a95b-b177-4f49-a65c-4693085f5f31', 'Cook all ingredients in a 4- to 5-quart heavy pot, covered, over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until fruit is very tender and falling apart, 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Force mixture through a large medium-mesh sieve using a rubber spatula, discarding peels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.562', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('69933f50-275c-487c-9918-1dad63b8edfc', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Whisk oil and thyme in small bowl to blend. Place sweet potatoes, onion, and bell pepper in large bowl. Drizzle with 1/4 cup oil mixture and toss to coat. Grill vegetables until tender and slightly charred, turning often, about 15 minutes for pepper and about 20 minutes for sweet potatoes and onion. Transfer vegetables to platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.565', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5725ad3a-11bd-4bba-ae1c-3ce3cb352b02', 'Whisk vinegar into remaining oil mixture. Season vinaigrette with salt and pepper; drizzle over vegetables. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.569', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.203');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('feba92d4-ce15-4972-8743-9359c6d1dc3a', 'Combine 3 cups water and 3 cups sugar in medium saucepan. Stir sugar and water over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase the heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer 3 minutes. Transfer syrup to bowl and chill thoroughly. DO AHEAD: Syrup can be made 2 weeks ahead. Cover and keep refrigerated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.573', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.204');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d5ee004e-b998-46be-884c-b70b4f73e486', '1. Trim and discard the rough bottoms from the baby bok choy. Separate the leaves, rinse, and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.576', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43e47446-0a08-4a70-8bce-41ab15b648a7', '2. In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce, rice wine, and sugar. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.58', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8972c6ba-c339-434f-9c9e-28125ee67903', '3. Heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat until a bead of water sizzles and evaporates on contact. Add the peanut oil and swirl to coat the bottom and sides. Add the garlic and ginger and stir-fry until aromatic, 20 to 30 seconds. Add the bok choy and stir-fry for about 2 minutes, until crisp-tender. Add the soy sauce mixture and cook for another 30 seconds. Turn off the heat, and drizzle with sesame oil. Transfer to a serving plate and serve hot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.584', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59d8a250-3948-4401-878e-756a16ae62e6', 'Bring a 5- to 6-quart pot of water seasoned with 1 tablespoon kosher salt to a boil. Cook asparagus and string beans until just tender, 5 to 6 minutes. Drain, then transfer in a single layer to paper or kitchen towels to dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.587', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('816cc412-44c0-4820-900a-9e85f077721f', 'Separate white parts from green parts of scallions. Halve whites lengthwise. Halve green parts lengthwise and again in half crosswise. You should have approximately 3-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.591', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.206');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c30967e-c9e8-4348-8cb9-a94731fc12ef', 'Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat until oil shimmers. Add white parts of scallions and sauté until they just begin to wilt and turn golden, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.595', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.206');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6afd21a3-a9cf-4f10-bf5d-aa061d931be6', 'Add asparagus, green beans, and 1/4 teaspoon salt and sauté to heat through, 1 minute. Add green parts of scallions and continue to sauté until they just begin to wilt, about 1 minute more. Adjust seasoning if necessary and serve with a fresh grind of black pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.598', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.207');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37d6c3e4-4e53-4d64-aecd-7c0af7f35f00', 'Peel pears, leaving stems intact, then core from bottom with melon-ball cutter to create a 2 1/2-inch-deep cavity. Rub pears all over with lemon juice in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.601', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.207');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc2937ea-0c66-4596-84ed-19bfe78b4084', 'Bring wine, sugar, vanilla bean, and zest to a boil in a wide 6-quart heavy pot (at least 12 inches in diameter) over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add pears, arranging them on their sides in 1 layer, along with any lemon juice from bowl (pears will not be covered by liquid), then reduce heat to low and poach pears, covered, turning occasionally, until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Carefully transfer pears with a slotted spoon to a 13- by 9-inch baking dish, standing pears upright and reserving liquid in pot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.605', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.208');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c076b55-8b7b-49e4-b5eb-fcd339c3ee20', 'DO AHEAD: Beets can be roasted 2 days ahead. Cover separately and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.456', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.987');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce3096df-94bc-4525-8960-a19b4a9f3465', 'Boil liquid in pot over high heat until syrupy and reduced to about 3/4 cup, 10 to 15 minutes. Pour syrup over pears and cool, basting occasionally with syrup. Chill, covered, basting occasionally with syrup, until cold, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.612', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.212');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3fd411a3-5b0f-4807-b644-cad104422f63', 'Drizzle each pear lightly with syrup and slip a parmesan cloak over stem. Serve with cheese shavings on the side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.616', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.212');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f4f04e9-3fa1-4b0b-9364-d83cadca6eb6', 'Mix first 2 ingredients in large saucepan. Cover with water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer until soft, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand 15 minutes. Drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.619', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.213');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b48cadd-448c-4ad9-95f9-6654fcbe3e83', 'Coarsely chop tomatillo mixture, garlic, and cumin in processor using on/off turns. Add next 3 ingredients; blend until herbs are chopped and salsa is chunky.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.623', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.214');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be0ec974-c481-4644-815b-91c2986d04e2', 'Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add salsa and simmer until slightly thickened and reduced to 4 cups, about 10 minutes. Stir in salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.626', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.214');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fc0a35f-590f-4e1d-97ba-829570d783ee', 'Put oven rack in upper third of oven and preheat oven to 475°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.63', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.215');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22c7663a-a088-4358-a6f6-22d8be0772e3', 'Cut parsnips lengthwise into quarters, then cut out and discard any tough core. Cut parsnips diagonally into 2-inch pieces. Cut squash crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices, then cut slices into wedges. Toss vegetables with salt, pepper, and 1 1/2 tablespoons oil, then spread in 1 layer in a large shallow baking pan. Roast, turning occasionally, until vegetables are tender and browned, 20 to 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.634', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.216');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf3b5103-071e-4568-8506-ae0b3016be57', 'While vegetables are roasting, heat remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil with garlic in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until garlic just begins to sizzle. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.638', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.216');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f65282a-9064-4bee-bd95-0eeaed587f21', 'When vegetables are done roasting, remove garlic from oil (discard garlic) and toss vegetables with garlic oil, olives, and parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.642', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.216');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('99caaf5e-68fb-46ba-adad-0c53184050e6', 'Stir together all ingredients in a bowl and let stand 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.645', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.217');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bda890ac-b393-48fc-b62a-7ce2b8021097', 'Preheat oven to 450°F with a 4-sided heavy sheet pan in upper third.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.649', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.217');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2223b48-b6bf-4d35-bbd0-d52181dea1f1', 'Toss ingredients with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Spread in 1 layer on hot pan and roast 20 minutes. Loosen potatoes with a metal spatula and turn, arranging pale potatoes around outer edge of pan and golden potatoes in center (for even roasting). Roast 15 minutes, then loosen and turn potatoes over again. Roast until potatoes are golden and cooked through and edges are crisp, about 10 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.652', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.218');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7954a824-0b66-454b-bc50-3b473e315805', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl. Mix in bitters, if desired. Pour mixture into 15x10x1-inch baking sheet. Freeze until icy at edges of sheet, about 25 minutes. Whisk to distribute frozen portions evenly. Freeze again until mixture is icy at edges of sheet and overall texture is slushy (for beverage), about 25 minutes longer. Then freeze until mixture is solid (for granita), about 45 minutes. Use fork to scrape granita into icy flakes. Cover and freeze at least 1 hour and up to 2 days. Scoop granita into goblets. Garnish with fruit and mint and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.656', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.219');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f12460fc-bb2b-43f6-8bbf-d4be05843d3d', 'Divide nectar and bitters between 2 chilled champagne flutes. Add champagne. Drop 2 berries into each drink. Garnish with orange.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.659', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.219');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35306cec-b684-441f-b66a-be83144903a5', 'Whisk first 3 ingredients in small bowl until blended. Mix in chives. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 2 hours head. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.221');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf23275e-8258-49de-aa58-85b9b9290784', 'Combine lettuces, cucumber, jicama, bell pepper, grapes and mushrooms in large bowl. Add dressing and toss to blend. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.665', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.222');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f26b0f2c-86e2-4f79-aa3b-1f03c3fb9e16', 'In a heavy skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and sauté corn, stirring, until golden. Add onion, bell pepper, garlic, cumin, and 1/4 cup water and cook over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until bell pepper is crisp-tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.668', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.222');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ea155d8-c7b1-4c3e-a66f-a5dcba345535', 'While vegetables are cooking, in a small heavy saucepan bring remaining cup water to a boil and stir in couscous and salt to taste. Cover pan and remove from heat. Let couscous stand 5 minutes and fluff with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.223');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1804772-c2d2-4820-9a02-dc100e63a75d', 'In a bowl whisk together vinegar, remaining tablespoon oil, and salt to taste until emulsified. Add vegetable mixture, couscous, coriander, and cayenne and toss to combine well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.223');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8bfa980b-bba1-4f2e-bb81-e1f316ac9d13', 'Finely grate enough zest from orange to measure 2 teaspoons, then squeeze 1 tablespoon juice into a large bowl. Whisk in zest, vinegar, salt, pepper, and oil until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.68', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.224');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e8e5cf0-a0a1-4558-9148-845465d1c4c3', 'Cut fennel bulbs lengthwise into very thin slices with slicer. Halve endives lengthwise, then halve crosswise and cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch-wide strips. Add endive and fennel to vinaigrette and toss to combine. Chill, covered, 15 minutes to allow flavors to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.683', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.224');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9316039d-afc2-4ac0-b739-654a4e3a976d', '*Available at cookware shops and Uwajimaya (800-889-1928).', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.686', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.225');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43d2264c-c7db-4b28-b024-58c10ac0ee75', 'Toss onion, sugar, and sumac in a medium bowl; season with salt and let sit 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.69', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.225');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('45cd4ae8-025c-47d0-af90-3b748e9684b1', 'Add oil, vinegar, and pomegranate molasses and toss to combine; let sit 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.693', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09675d33-2a2f-43e2-aa7a-7dea8e98d149', 'Just before serving, toss in parsley and pomegranate seeds; season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.697', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e383c2bc-a69d-489b-bdcd-be95052600e2', 'Peel strings from celery with a Y-shaped vegetable peeler and cut celery into 1/4-inch-thick matchsticks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.7', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0554e38f-0e00-45c6-9687-b970099316d6', 'Whisk together juice, vinegar, and ginger and stir in celery and remaining ingredients with salt and pepper to taste. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.703', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8693ce8b-152f-4a9c-bbb2-da7dbbecc4ee', 'Bring water, sugar, vanilla bean and 2 bunches mint to boil in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cook until reduced to 3/4 cup, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes. Strain into small bowl. Add extract. Cool. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.707', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.227');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('236809ef-8398-4c18-b470-1e71eca874e4', 'Combine fruits in medium bowl. Pour over enough syrup to coat well. Let stand 15 minutes. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.71', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.227');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('deefdd75-719a-4be4-88a5-11c2976de939', 'Milder than vinegar, verjus is a tart juice made from unripe grapes; available at specialty foods stores and from chefshop.com and terrasonoma.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.009', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.269');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18c137cb-5150-4667-bc1a-ba3f76320fe9', 'Prepare grill for medium-high heat. Toss 1/2 small white onion, halved lengthwise, keeping root intact, 1/2 head of garlic, unpeeled, halved crosswise, 1 jalapeño, 1 pound husked tomatillos, and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a large bowl. Grill vegetables, turning often, until tender and charred, 5-8 minutes. Transfer to a plate and let cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.714', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.227');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa0d6815-c726-4c98-aeb8-d3ec86215f14', 'Squeeze garlic cloves into a food processor and pulse with onion, stemmed jalapeño, tomatillos, 1/2 bunch cilantro, leaves and tender stems only, and 1/4 cup fresh lime juice just until a chunky sauce forms; season with kosher salt, freshly ground black pepper, and more lime juice, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.721', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.227');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3887c1f7-482c-4a49-946f-6df4d782be9c', 'DO AHEAD: Salsa verde can be made 5 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.727', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.228');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('99032c09-7e88-460b-bc23-aa6fe95b2305', 'Wrap beets in foil and roast in middle of oven until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Unwrap beets and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.732', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.228');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('03c3e05a-6ac9-44ff-874b-46accc34a4cd', 'While beets are roasting, cook almonds in oil in a small skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until pale golden. Cool almonds in oil (nuts will get darker as they cool). Transfer almonds with a slotted spoon to a small bowl and season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.736', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.228');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e496681-be27-4fbb-b34f-4854cbb2cdaf', 'Stir together shallot, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar, salt, and oil from almonds in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.739', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.229');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b9c14fe-0344-459d-8620-41ad3fb9f6b5', 'Slip skins from beets and halve large beets. Cut beets into 1/4-inch-thick slices and add to dressing, tossing to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.743', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.229');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8e39636-d2ac-4d92-9458-cf69a65aa214', 'Quarter and core pear and cut into julienne strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.746', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.229');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f58fd655-c4a7-4a1d-aeae-8e0f8ca84d4d', 'Arrange beets on a platter and drizzle with any dressing remaining in bowl. Top with mâche, then pear. Sprinkle with almonds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.749', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.23');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77b858da-e0ef-44c1-a9e8-9d243c768bfe', 'Pulse first 4 ingredients in a blender until combined; season with salt and pepper. With blender running, slowly drizzle in oil. Process dressing until well blended.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.753', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.23');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef7044ac-1132-4a44-892f-437e70d3e03e', 'Place remaining ingredients in a large bowl; drizzle with 3 tablespoons dressing and toss to coat. Pass remaining dressing alongside for drizzling over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.756', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.23');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('429c4d49-dac4-4d15-9019-0680d7e7ee5f', 'Preheat broiler. Toss plums with sugar, vanilla, and cinnamon in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart (9- to 10-inch round) gratin or other flameproof shallow dish (not glass). Let plums stand 5 minutes in dish to macerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.759', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.231');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4da12d38-8462-45ae-8b54-fbf38401b38d', 'Add water to dish and broil plums 6 to 8 inches from heat, gently stirring once or twice, until fruit is softened, 7 to 10 minutes. Serve fruit and juice from pan topped with sorbet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.762', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.231');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d46c3b3f-8521-471d-9bd4-836887b2c18c', 'Peel potatoes and halve lengthwise. Cut lengthwise into 3/4-inch-thick wedges, then cut wedges crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Steam potatoes in a steamer over boiling water in a large pot, covered, until just tender, 10 to 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.766', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.231');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fa480ee-8583-429b-b288-37faa9d7fcb5', 'While potatoes steam, whisk together mustard, vinegar, and salt in a large bowl, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.77', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('093aa97c-b058-4822-aabc-c97f5affd360', 'Add hot potatoes to dressing and gently toss to combine well. Cool salad to room temperature, about 15 minutes. Add scallions and salt to taste and gently toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.773', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd022914-a84e-4845-a3b0-2b5bb9b4307a', 'Stir together seeds, salt, sugar, and cayenne in a small bowl. Stir together water and cornstarch separately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.777', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4d8c3b5-20d8-4335-a39f-fb20af27040c', 'Heat oil in a 5-quart heavy pot over moderate heat until a deep-fat thermometer registers 360°F. Brush 1 side of 2 wrappers with cornstarch mixture and sprinkle with seed mixture. Shake off any excess seeds and add wrappers to oil, seeded sides down. Fry, turning over once, until golden, about 10 seconds. (Some seeds will fall off during frying.) Transfer crisps with tongs to paper towels to drain, then make more, 2 at a time, in same manner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.78', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c5cb7b00-3116-4257-8b72-d622fb2506f9', 'In a heavy 3-quart saucepan spread 2/3 cup of the sugar, add the cinnamon stick, and top the sugar with half the papaya strips. Sprinkle 2/3 cup of the remaining sugar on top, add the remaining papaya strips, and top the strips with the remaining 2/3 cup sugar. Cook the mixture, covered, over moderately low heat, shaking the pan occasionally (do not stir), for 35 to 45 minutes, or until the sugar is dissolved completely. Simmer the papaya strips, uncovered, for 10 minutes, or until they begin to appear translucent. Let the mixture cool and chill it, covered, overnight. The papaya in cinnamon syrup keeps, covered and chilled, for 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.784', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.233');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff43145a-be20-4f9e-9a34-0898bf9475a4', 'In a 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan cook onion, bell pepper, coriander, and garlic in oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.787', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.233');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3405e5e-7402-408f-87a0-7d8fc648d29d', 'Add turmeric and cook, stirring, 30 seconds. Stir in rice, water, and salt and bring to a boil, uncovered. Boil rice, uncovered, without stirring, until surface of rice is covered with steam holes and grains on top appear dry, 5 to 8 minutes. Reduce heat to as low as possible and cook rice, tightly covered, 15 minutes more. Remove pan from heat and let rice stand, covered, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.791', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.233');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ebd427e6-8426-49de-a557-7b8905ea2807', 'Whisk together vinegar, shallot, salt, and pepper in a small bowl, then add oils in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified. Toss lettuce and celery leaves with just enough vinaigrette to coat in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.794', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.233');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68a87dca-1b1d-4f79-9841-beee7429671a', 'In a 2 1/2-to-3 quart heavy saucepan with a tight-fitting lid over rice with cold water by 2 inches. Swirl rice around in water several times with your hand and drain. Repeat procedure 2 more times, or until water runs clear, and drain rice well in a sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.798', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.233');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1958487c-d8f4-4d5e-a832-2473249b854b', 'Return rice to pan and add enough water (about 3 3/4 cups) to cover rice by about 3/4 inch. Measure by placing the tip of an index finger in the surface of the rice and ensuring that water surface is at the first joint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.801', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2dd1cd05-feb8-4d6e-b02d-13237c55437b', 'Bring water to a boil, uncovered, and boil rice 15 seconds. Cook rice, covered, over very low heat without lifting lid, 15 to 29 minutes, or until water is absorbed and rice is tender. Remove pan from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Turn rice gently with a flat wooden spatula and keep warm, covered. Rice is best served within 1 hour of cooking.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.804', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ebfa8d08-7357-4247-91c6-238237739202', 'In a large bowl (large enough to hold at least twice the volume of rice, about 6 cups) cover rice with cold water by 2 to 3 inches. Soak rice 8 to 24 hours. Alternatively, soak rice in warm water (about 110°F.) 2 hours. The longer soak allows more flavor to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.808', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0136569-7ae9-4927-bf1a-c046b488b0d3', 'Drain rice and transfer to a Southeast Asian rice-steamer basket or sieve. Set steamer basket or sieve over several inches of boiling water in a large pot or deep kettle. It is important that the rice not touch boiling water. Cover rice with a lid and steam, checking water level occasionally to make sure pot or kettle doesn''t boil dry and adding more boiling water if necessary, 25 minutes, or until rice is shiny and tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.811', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ccf198b4-d288-4031-96ab-22d4f5ed38df', 'Transfer rice to a basket or bowl, breaking it up into smaller lumps, and immediately cover with a lid or clean kitchen towel. (Rice dries out if exposed to air as it cools, so keep covered until serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.814', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.235');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c74badcb-81e5-4231-9c0f-8afdd1bc83dd', 'Finely grind coriander seeds in an electric coffee/spice grinder or with a mortar and pestle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.818', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.236');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47c8cdd4-f8a8-48f4-8f6e-23e812cc45ad', 'Bring water, 2 tablespoons oil, and salt to a boil in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart heavy saucepan. Stir in couscous and coriander seeds, then cover pan and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.821', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.237');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61be2fc4-207e-430d-8d25-d05623950e8a', 'Fluff couscous with a fork and stir in remaining tablespoon oil, apricots, parsley, and salt and pepper to taste', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.824', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.237');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d314108e-efb8-4200-a1b5-4e0c21681dde', 'Preheat oven to 350° F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.827', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.237');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8176d6ef-6e5f-4517-a410-8c5512c65d4d', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the flax and water. Let sit for 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.831', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.239');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('54fef79a-a38f-4225-a836-7a1bd9831ef1', 'In a separate bowl, whisk together the oats, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.834', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.239');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a7cb93e-f1c2-4a03-b78b-ebb494a2a698', 'In the bowl of a standing mixer, or with an electric mixer, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add the flax mixture and vanilla extract and stir until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.838', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.239');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('98d16cf2-505f-491a-8c15-2129825583cb', 'Gradually add the flour mixture until just combined. Add the raisins and stir to thoroughly combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.842', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.24');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b69c9df-d5cf-4ce5-b9a1-3e3e6d2c13a3', 'Using a 2 tablespoon measure, place cookie dough onto Silpat or parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until golden brown.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.24');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d959cd1-40ad-4d5a-8898-34be68814a38', 'Juice the lemon using a manual citrus juicer. Juice the remaining ingredients in a juicer, and then combine with the lemon juice. Store in an airtight glass container in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.848', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.241');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e6add7b-cbb9-4a0a-a878-0459aa903c77', 'Whisk coconut milk, cinnamon, turmeric, ginger, honey, coconut oil, peppercorns, and 1 cup water in a small saucepan; bring to a low boil. Reduce heat and simmer until flavors have melded, about 10 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into mugs and top with a dash of cinnamon.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.852', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.241');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('20366e60-7cc2-40b6-bf7d-3531e649d118', 'Golden milk can be made 5 days ahead. Store in an airtight container and chill. Warm before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.855', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.242');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10926642-6950-409d-99e9-7e71a185d96c', 'Working in batches, purée cantaloupe in a blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.858', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.243');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a8a3817-ca87-498c-ba9d-a8951d384257', 'Set a fine-mesh sieve over a large bowl; line sieve with cheesecloth. Strain purée into bowl; gather cheesecloth into a bundle and squeeze any remaining juice into bowl. Repeat process with fresh cheesecloth, straining into a large pitcher (you should have about 5 cups juice).', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.243');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('72f3b51b-07e0-41ab-b938-f09d3ecca01d', 'Add lemon juice, basil, and 2 cups cold water to pitcher. Let steep at room temperature for 1-2 hours. Fill glasses with ice. Divide agua fresca among glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.864', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.244');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9082c028-e342-4acd-8df3-bbcf887ce71f', 'In a small bowl stir together zest, citrus juices, vanilla, and mint sugar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.867', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.244');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25abb4cd-c168-43b4-a521-0e722a8ab6bc', 'Butter six 1-cup shallow flameproof gratin dishes or bowls. Quarter figs. Halve and pit apricots. Divide figs, apricots, raspberries, and juice mixture among dishes or bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.87', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.245');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11d39e2f-ec04-4e8c-8290-6cf2b8816bee', 'Just before serving, sprinkle sugar evenly over fruit and caramelize with blowtorch, moving flame evenly back and forth just over sugar (alternatively, broil fruit under a preheated broiler set 2 to 3 inches from heat) until most of sugar is melted and deep golden in places.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.874', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.246');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4fdea810-9f37-46ec-ad24-e2fa06c07f0e', 'Immediately serve brûlées with crème fraîche.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.877', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.246');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('643f9e2e-66df-4201-a792-8f26d98281e4', 'Stir 3/4 cup sugar and 3/4 cup water in heavy small saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to simmer. Remove from heat; cool syrup completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.88', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.247');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d1b69ae-3a2a-4acf-aafc-5222d2f16989', 'Purée 3 cups strawberries in blender just until smooth. Strain puree through fine strainer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.883', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.248');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6a2c371-a51d-44c8-9a73-49bdfc46d6f7', 'Transfer sugar syrup and 1 1/2 cups strawberry purée to large bowl (reserve any remaining strawberry purée for another use). Stir in corn syrup, lemon juice and vanilla. Refrigerate mixture until cold, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.887', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.248');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a793cd5-34cc-47d3-9d83-14534a2d0c22', 'Stir Champagne into strawberry mixture. Process in ice cream maker according to manufacturer''s instructions. Transfer strawberry ice to container; freeze until firm, at least 4 hours. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep strawberry ice frozen. Cover and chill remaining strawberries.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.89', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.249');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e5f6ab73-a2b1-4f85-9bee-6c7ce8bd250d', 'Toss remaining 2 1/4 cups strawberries with 2 tablespoons sugar in large bowl. Let stand until juices form, about 1 hour. Divide strawberries among 6 dessert cups. Top each serving with 1 scoop strawberry ice. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.894', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.25');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3fdb0e5c-a396-41aa-a20c-97300adc46b4', 'Peel potatoes, putting them in a bowl of cold water as peeled to prevent discoloration. Drain potatoes, then steam in a steamer set over boiling water, covered, until tender, 18 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.897', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.25');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8088d4c6-1b3f-445f-8cc5-95deb22a7707', 'Toss hot potatoes with wine in a large bowl, then add oil, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper and toss again. Cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.9', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.253');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d59c9e53-a0e2-4292-83cc-bb104dd09f69', 'Bring broth to boil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Mix in rice. Return to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook without stirring until rice is tender, about 40 minutes. Spread out rice in large baking pan and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.904', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.253');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95999215-6e1b-426f-b17d-7d50f36490ef', 'Transfer rice to large bowl. Add cashews, dates, and green onions; toss to blend. Whisk olive oil, lemon juice, chopped cilantro, and ground cinnamon in small bowl. Add to rice and toss to coat. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.907', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.254');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8ba1046-6020-44c8-9a9e-a382a1687355', 'In a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes, combine the vodka and orange juice. Stir well. Float the Galliano on top and garnish with orange slice', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.91', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.254');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc7c7b60-d247-4040-ab83-9c7098604c2d', 'Blanch onions in large pot of boiling salted water 15 seconds. Using slotted spoon, transfer to large bowl of ice water to cool. Trim root end if necessary, leaving core intact. Peel onions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.914', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.255');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14d91321-a714-4be2-81ff-973af14deb7b', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over high heat. Add onions and sauté until onions have deep golden brown spots, about 9 minutes. Add orange juice and vinegar; bring to boil, scraping up browned bits. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until onions are just tender when pierced with knife, about 8 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer onions to medium bowl. Boil juices in skillet until syrupy and reduced to 2/3 cup, about 3 minutes. Pour over onions. Serve warm or at room temperature. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewarm or bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.918', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.255');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8534b328-1f64-4c26-9014-430a61402f48', 'Heat oil in medium skillet over medium heat. Add 1 cup onion and 1 minced garlic clove and sauté until tender and golden brown, about 10 minutes. Set aside. Combine 3 cups water, lentils, remaining 1 cup onion, 2 minced garlic cloves, turmeric, cumin and ginger in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until lentils are tender, about 15 minutes. Transfer half of lentil mixture to processor; purée until smooth. Return purée to same saucepan. Mix in sautéed onion mixture. Simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.921', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.256');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f84583b-5a7c-4b6f-af84-fc7eab837a9d', 'Spoon rice into bowls. Spoon dal over. Top with tomatoes, cilantro and chili.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.924', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.256');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78e7b561-1175-4180-8922-2257f63fb244', 'Heat 1 inch oil to 375°F in a 4- to 5-quarts heavy pot over medium-high heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.927', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.257');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be55da74-a2f3-4786-96e6-54de5092a87c', 'Meanwhile, cut ends from (unpeeled) plantains, then halve plantains crosswise. Cut a lengthwise slit through peel and discard peel. Cut plantains lengthwise into very thin slices (less than 1/16 inch thick) with slicer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.257');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1a79947-9e52-439f-a464-73421e7fa6a6', 'Fry plantains in batches of 10 to 12 slices, turning frequently, until golden, about 1 minute per batch. Drain on paper towels, immediately seasoning each batch with salt. Return oil to 375°F between batches.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.934', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.258');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb778669-3765-4427-99c3-5b25459d4c10', 'To make the dressing, place all of the dressing ingredients in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth, or use an immersion blender to blend all the ingredients in a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.937', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.258');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fbe03dee-feb8-42e8-9c62-33f47d336c7d', 'To make the salad, bring a small pot of salted water to a boil. Add the farro and cook until tender, 16 to 18 minutes. Drain, rinse with cold water until cool, then drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.941', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.259');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02f90a1b-dc96-4f70-92c6-20833999ff4e', 'Remove the stems from the kale. Cut away any tough ends, then finely slice the stems and tear the kale leaves into small bite-size pieces. Place both the stems and leaves in a large salad bowl. Add the avocados, carrots, and farro. Add half of the dressing and toss to combine. Add more dressing if desired. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.945', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.259');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5345fd40-fa17-49c8-bca3-94fbee8e5dcc', '1. Mix together all of the ingredients except the dressing in a medium bowl. Toss so that they are well combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.26');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51a120c1-5c78-47e5-a95d-c5529d896c54', '2. Pour the dressing over the ingredients.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.26');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27268a56-494b-48c1-84f3-830e59ed5063', '3. Store in six 4-ounce (120 ml) airtight containers. Refrigerate overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.955', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.261');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d711e0f6-59d4-427e-92f9-1063a3850264', 'Remove zest from 1 lime in strips with a vegetable peeler and cut any white pith from strips with a sharp knife. Squeeze 3 tablespoons juice from limes. Bring zest, water, and sugar to a boil in a 1-quart saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then boil, uncovered, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lime juice. Let syrup stand 20 minutes, then remove zest with a slotted spoon and discard.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.959', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.261');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ccd0fcb-9b15-475f-9821-b9edc7ac5593', 'Toss together mangoes, blueberries, and syrup in a large bowl and sprinkle with ginger.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.962', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.262');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('218b16de-9a23-4d64-8bb3-266f7d2cd5f6', 'Prep fruit except for coconut 1 day ahead; refrigerate. In a pan, toast coconut over medium heat, tossing until golden, 1 to 2 minutes. Transfer to a plate. Top salad with coconut before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.966', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.262');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e721312-b816-4756-b5ec-c4951fb4e7f2', 'Rinse beets. Wrap colors separately in foil and roast in middle of oven until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.969', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.263');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3910cbe9-5997-4bbf-8c43-e110502d0050', 'Peel beets and halve lengthwise. If using medium beets, cut each half crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices, keeping colors separate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.972', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.264');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c7d8fc2-1e1e-40a4-923a-f45de3fd13ae', 'Whisk together shallot, juices, zest, and mustard. Whisk in oil until emulsified and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle lettuce with three fourths of dressing. Sprinkle with beets and drizzle with remaining dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.976', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.264');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4bb1e51-3f33-4f74-a841-81a9c44a03a6', 'Sprinkle both sides of the squash slices with salt and let the slices drain between paper towels for 10 minutes. Pat the slices dry and brush the top sides with some of the oil. Heat a well-seasoned ridged grill pan over moderate heat until it is hot and in it cook the squash slices, in batches if necessary, oiled-side down first and brushing the tops with some of the remaining oil before turning them, for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, or until they are just tender. Transfer the slices with a spatula to a small platter. In a small bowl whisk together the lemon juice, the orégan, the remaining oil, and salt and pepper to taste, drizzle the dressing over the squash, and sprinkle the squash with the parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.98', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.265');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2eb5e98-9232-4a57-8e1f-f99da533035d', 'Working with 1 zucchini at a time, cut lengthwise into very thin (julienne) strips with slicer, turning zucchini and avoiding core. Discard core.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.983', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.265');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11ebf875-e56b-4a4c-ab43-2c2b402a4114', 'Toss zucchini strips with 1 teaspoon salt and let drain in a colander set over a bowl, covered and chilled, 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.987', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.267');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('039bfe94-211c-46c4-b225-7304bcdf08e9', 'Gently squeeze handfuls of zucchini to remove excess water and pat dry with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.991', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.267');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dab9f288-91bc-4aab-9d74-99ea6410e80c', 'Cook corn in a small saucepan of boiling water until tender, about 3 minutes. Drain, then rinse under cold water and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.995', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.267');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4690804-f7ff-4ab9-ae87-7d038e9e0c79', 'Whisk together lemon juice, sugar, pepper, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large bowl, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking. Add zucchini, corn, tomatoes, and basil and toss well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:24.998', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.267');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ffa80f73-0e8c-4dd0-bf0a-35f527724b8f', 'Whisk first 3 ingredients in small bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in both oils. Season dressing to taste with sea salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.002', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.268');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c427c7eb-0eb5-49c7-a8ae-b914fe4fb099', 'Arrange lettuce on platter. Top with avocado and grapefruit, then dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.006', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.268');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec1514df-ae22-418d-bbaf-250734fd7fb0', 'Place 5 pitted Medjool dates in a small bowl; cover with boiling water and let sit until softened, about 10 minutes. Drain; transfer dates to a food processor. Add 1 cup gochujang (Korean hot pepper paste) and 2 tablespoons toasted sesame oil. Purée until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.013', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.269');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc99fa6f-3f12-4346-ab29-53978008dfcd', 'Working with 1 artichoke at a time, cut off top inch of artichoke and gently pull open center. Scoop out sharp leaves and fuzzy choke from center with a melon-ball cutter or a spoon. Trim bottom 1/4 inch of stem (if present), keeping stem attached, and peel stem. Put artichoke in a large bowl of cold water. Repeat with remaining artichokes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.017', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.27');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3433bf76-4045-4b84-93e2-aa7155fba476', 'Remove artichokes from water and push 3 parsley sprigs into center of each. Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in pot over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then add artichokes, thyme sprigs, garlic, 1/4 cup water, pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover pot and braise artichokes, turning occasionally, until artichokes are browned in spots and bases are tender when pierced with a knife, about 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.021', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64c44245-5e80-4656-b19b-646accba0c2d', 'Transfer artichokes, thyme, and garlic to a platter. Add remaining 3/4 cup water to pot and deglaze by boiling over high heat, stirring and scraping up brown bits, 1 minute. Pour pan juices (they will be dark) into a small bowl and stir in extra-virgin olive oil and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt. Squeeze pulp from 2 of garlic cloves into juices and mash into sauce with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.026', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('175060f6-6d89-4509-be0b-6dff71370ebc', 'Divide artichokes and remaining garlic cloves among 6 plates and drizzle with sauce. Garlic cloves can be peeled and spread on crusty bread.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4237e271-5d05-42c2-988a-3a6e2b3b4e10', 'With a vegetable peeler remove three 3 x 1/2-inch pieces zest from lemon. In a saucepan bring water to a boil with zest, gingerroot, star anise, sugar, and 1 teaspoon lemon juice and simmer, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Cool syrup and discard star anise. Syrup may be made 2 days ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.033', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.272');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88fc4d94-4e5a-4257-bb6c-45c5f6170688', 'Halve and pit nectarines and plums. Cut nectarines into wedges. In a bowl toss cut fruit together with blueberries, syrup, and remaining lemon juice. Mixture may be made 8 hours ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.036', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.273');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e2569e2-66bc-4560-a822-d00cd9cf1f43', 'Finely grate enough peel from lemon to measure 1 1/2 teaspoons; set lemon peel aside. Squeeze enough juice from lemon to measure 2 tablespoons. Combine 2 cups water, lemon juice, garlic oil and ground cinnamon in medium saucepan. Bring to boil. Simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 cup couscous. Cover and let stand until water is almost absorbed, about 5 minutes. Mix in garbanzo beans, golden raisins and reserved lemon peel. Cover and let stand 5 minutes longer. Fluff couscous with fork. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer couscous to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.04', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.273');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb77ca7a-7adb-4296-9d19-b5c2ef9ac902', 'Bring apricots, wine, water, sugar, zest, and a pinch of salt to a boil in a small heavy saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced and very syrupy and apricots are very soft, about 15 minutes if using California (about 45 minutes if using Turkish). (If apricots are not yet softened, pour in an additional 1/4 cup water and continue cooking.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.043', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.274');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8479155-6b68-4e0a-8600-44cc8572aa09', 'Remove from heat. Discard zest, then stir in rum. Transfer apricot mixture to a bowl and cool slightly, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.046', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.274');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('712ddd6d-4647-40f0-90cf-72a4163e2e44', 'Purée in a food processor until mixture is very smooth. Add water to purée if necessary to achieve a spreadable consistency.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.05', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.274');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('117b375f-729f-4f39-8ee5-f35649561c31', 'Serve at room temperature or chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.053', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.275');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a63ee1a-74d7-468e-9638-cf0dc5349e06', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and stir 1 minute to coat with oil. Add vinegar and sugar and stir until onion begins to soften slightly, about 3 minutes. Transfer onion to baking sheet or platter; spread in single layer. Sprinkle with salt. Cover and chill at least 8 hours or overnight (onion will turn pink). DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.057', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.275');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7f84da5-a128-428f-a595-c5f073fc7c90', 'Whisk red wine vinegar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, and sugar in small bowl. Gradually whisk in both oils. DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature and rewhisk before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.061', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.276');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c668fa9-5ef5-45f4-b5cc-6858ed5688fb', 'Combine Port and figs in large saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until figs are plump and tender, about 30 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer figs to small bowl. Increase heat to medium-high and boil Port syrup until thickened and reduced to 6 tablespoons, about 8 minutes. Transfer syrup to another small bowl. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover figs and Port syrup separately and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.065', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.276');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c29f6cc-8f81-4acd-aa6f-7b5da3ac0f52', 'Combine endive, and pickled onion Toss salad with vinaigrette Port syrup over each salad among plates. Sprinkle salads and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.069', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.277');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f61ac0f0-13ad-44f6-94e0-a9632f1dc72f', 'Combine avocado, cilantro, green onion, and serrano chiles in processor. Puree until smooth. Add 1/4 cup water and 21/2 tablespoons lime juice and process to blend. Add more water to avocado mixture by tablespoonfuls if needed and blend until thick sauce forms.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.072', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.277');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c143a234-2bd1-4aae-a72a-4b6921dbee56', 'Transfer to small bowl; season to taste with coarse salt and pepper and more lime juice, if desired. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.076', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.278');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ebab065-d017-4dbc-b284-60f0d4c980c3', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss pistachios and 1 tsp. oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with salt. Roast, tossing once, until pistachios are golden brown, 5–7 minutes. Let cool, then coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.08', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.278');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a19a4056-35c3-455d-9124-b58ca926702d', 'Meanwhile, bring curry powder and remaining 1/2 cup oil to a simmer in a small saucepan over medium heat, swirling occasionally. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.084', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.279');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d63b2dac-21cb-4d33-9a1e-328183df2cdd', 'Blend garlic, vinegar, and mustard in a blender, then, with motor running, stream in curry oil. Blend until dressing is very smooth and thick; season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.087', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.28');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8fc07692-0f92-4adc-81b0-8da00df6c277', 'Toss beets and half of dressing in a medium bowl; season with salt. Let sit until beets soften slightly, 8–10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.091', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.28');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cd21408-60b8-41b3-a84a-e729fb0b4f3b', 'Add carrots and remaining dressing and toss to combine; season with salt and lemon juice. Serve topped with pistachios.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.095', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.283');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1bf47af5-3656-4c56-befc-a689eba56038', 'Curry dressing can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.283');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53509d46-be02-4257-9235-eb3ad24a3208', 'Peel remaining cucumber and halve lengthwise. Cut crosswise into 1/3-inch-thick slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.075', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.089');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad820cd9-1be2-4e7c-b6b3-fd13a653bdd5', 'In a 1-quart glass jar with a tight-fitting lid combine the sliced lemon, the lemon juice, the shallots, the rosemary, and the red pepper flakes. In a saucepan of boiling water blanch the olives for 1 minute, drain them well in a colander, and add them to the jar while they are still warm. Add enough oil to the jar to just cover the olives. Seal the jar with the lid and shake it several times to combine and distribute the ingredients. Let the olives stand in a cool, dark place, shaking them daily, for 3 days. The olives keep, covered and chilled, indefinitely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.102', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.284');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('456c90a6-2c93-41f7-85ab-e1c0a605dcbd', 'Combine first 5 ingredients processor; puree. If necessary, mix in enough water to thin to consistency of thick mayonnaise. Mix in 2 tablespoons minced thyme. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl. Sprinkle with fresh thyme leaves. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.106', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.284');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f8ceb3b4-878f-4b25-b430-dfc69a55c93b', 'Steam potatoes until just tender, about 25 minutes. Transfer to bowl. Cut off stems of artichokes and rub cut surface with cut side of lemon. Cut artichokes lengthwise into quarters and rub cut surfaces with lemon. Cut out choke and rub with lemon. Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Add 1 remaining lemon half and artichokes. Cover and boil until a leaf pulls off easily, about 35 minutes. Drain and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.109', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.285');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc2957b3-cc8f-43e0-bb00-706810387683', 'Cook broccoli and cauliflower in large saucepan of boiling salted water until just tender, about 5 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer to bowl of cold water. Add green beans to same boiling water and cook until just tender, about 4 minutes. Drain. Rinse with cold water to stop cooking. Drain. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Wrap vegetables tightly and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.113', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.285');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a877a305-fc28-428c-874a-6ef72033a3dc', 'Arrange all vegetable on large platter. Serve with hummus and pita bread.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.117', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.285');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8f2acb7-9863-4aaf-93e2-7be0f0cb0cc9', 'In a large bowl stir together salt, cayenne, paprika, and coriander. In a 4-quart heavy kettle heat oil over moderate heat until a deep-fat thermometer registers 325°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.286');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2f288dd2-bbb1-47c4-96ad-d777104ea73d', 'While oil is heating, cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick sticks. Fry potatoes in oil 1 1/2 minutes (potatoes will not be golden) and with a slotted spoon transfer to brown paper or paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.286');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55119132-b2cd-4c82-b102-43d2c1956557', 'Heat oil to 350°F. Return potatoes to oil and fry until golden and crisp, about 5 minutes. Transfer fries with a slotted spoon to clean brown paper or paper towels to drain and toss fries in spice mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.129', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.287');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('21f96739-4ba0-4f06-9186-c49d4f569e7a', 'Combine all ingredients in processor. Using on/off turns, process until chunky puree forms. Transfer to medium bowl. Season with salt. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Press plastic wrap directly onto surface of salsa and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.133', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.287');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef660f36-b198-4236-b686-6bcfd4581944', 'In a steamer set over boiling water arrange the boiling potatoes, top them with the sweet potatoes, and steam the potatoes, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes, or until they are just tender. Transfer the potatoes to a bowl and let them cool. In another bowl whisk together the vinegar, the mustard, and salt and pepper to taste, add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified. Add the dressing to the potatoes with the onion, the bell pepper, and the gherkin and combine the salad well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.137', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.288');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95a922e2-b4b0-4aa5-adbe-ba9c79f1b6fc', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to simmer over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Uncover and simmer until figs are very soft and filling is thick, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Mix in lemon juice and vanilla, then walnuts. Cool completely. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.142', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.288');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a533d46e-9e9a-4727-a81a-83ef49b6df9b', 'Position rack in top third of oven and preheat to 350°F. Spray 13x9x2- inch metal baking pan with nonstick spray. Combine oats and next 5 ingredients in large bowl and whisk to blend. Add cubed "butter." Using fingertips, blend until mixture forms small moist clumps.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.146', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.289');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8cba5c0a-393c-4435-bab6-46448746a0b7', 'Firmly press half of crust mixture (about 3 cups) over bottom of prepared pan. Spread filling evenly over crust. Sprinkle remaining crust mixture over filling; press to adhere.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.15', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.289');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb6eeccc-57f5-49df-92bf-689992644865', 'Bake bars until deep brown and firm to touch, about 35 minutes. Cool in pan on rack. Cut crosswise into 6 strips. Make 8 lengthwise cuts, forming 2x1-inch bars. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover pan with foil; store at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.153', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.289');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1ceaf91f-9c0d-4b20-a22e-5b925591f846', 'Place powdered sugar in medium bowl. Using narrow spatula, remove as many bars as desired from pan. Roll half of bars in powdered sugar to coat. Arrange coated bars and plain bars alternately on platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.289');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63bd9dd4-31af-40aa-9ad3-9c974e50c3ab', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Toss potato wedges, oil, paprika, garlic powder, and cayenne pepper on a foil-lined large rimmed baking sheet to evenly coat; season potatoes with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.29');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1232dac-6777-4955-977f-343e9a73b648', 'Roast, turning once, until wedges are golden brown and crisp, 25-30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.166', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.29');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a60e6dc8-0136-45f4-82c4-e4505fc2146f', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Toss beets with oil in roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt. Cover pan with foil. Roast beets until tender, about 50 minutes. Let beets stand covered at room temperature 20 minutes. Peel beets. Place in bowl; cover and chill at least 1 hour. DO AHEAD Can be made 2 days ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.17', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.29');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f53486c-e8ff-4e5a-9870-b5473c513a3f', 'Toss onion, oil, capers, and chives in small bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Thinly slice beets. Arrange beets in concentric circles on each of 6 plates. Mound arugula atop center of beets on each. Spoon onion-caper mixture over. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.174', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.29');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a915c38-da2a-449c-81e8-b33d649e9104', 'Soak seaweed in warm water to cover, 5 minutes. Drain, then squeeze out excess water. If wakame is uncut, cut into 1/2-inch-wide strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.291');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e91809a-ac79-43a2-b763-34a4106a8ce2', 'Stir together vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil, sugar, ginger, and garlic in a bowl until sugar is dissolved. Cut apple into 1/4-inch dice and add to dressing with seaweed, scallions, and cilantro, tossing to combine well. Sprinkle salad with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.291');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6159d684-3421-49e8-9ca3-7357958323dd', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 350°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.291');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89c0ea66-92d9-4582-9404-2279f47664a1', 'Toast bread on a baking sheet until crisp and pale golden, 12 to 15 minutes, then transfer to a rack to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.19', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.291');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e23b61b0-2ef1-4cb3-a34e-ee61f7d29b76', 'Toast sesame seeds in a dry 12-inch heavy skillet (not nonstick) over medium heat, stirring, until pale golden, then transfer to a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.299', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.302');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cea72e81-8beb-44d2-9165-df25bc921232', 'Heat vegetable oil in a 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan over high heat until it registers 375°F on thermometer. Fry eggplant in 4 batches, stirring frequently, until pale golden, about 3 minutes per batch, transferring with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Return oil to 375°F between batches.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.194', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.292');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2e40d2f-c0ca-49b3-879c-704e168cb959', 'Cook onion in olive oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add tomato paste and cinnamon and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Stir in water, vinegar, and sugar until combined, then add olives, capers, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add eggplant and celery and cook, stirring gently, 1 minute. Transfer caponatina to a bowl and cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.2', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.292');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a74c355e-3eda-4e7c-b94f-b0c6c3a4082d', 'Serve toasts topped with caponatina.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.204', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.292');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('701dbb3d-5628-42fd-875a-cb5d237e45b6', 'Place a large cast-iron skillet over high heat for about 3 minutes, or until smoking. Add the tomatoes to the skillet and char on both sides until black and somewhat soft, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from the skillet and set aside. Reduce the heat to medium, and after two minutes, pour the olive oil into the skillet. Immediately add the onions, jalapeños, and garlic and sauté for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are soft. Transfer the onion mixture to a food processor with the griddled tomatoes. Process until all the ingredients are well blended. Transfer to a mixing bowl, add the chile puree, cilantro, lime juice, and salt, and stir well to combine. Serve at room temperature. Keeps for up to 1 week, refrigerated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.209', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.292');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6435dba3-c792-4ac3-b878-fdf1966d4769', 'Lightly oil a baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.213', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.292');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70648a8c-e00f-45a3-a4ab-dd747df45ac7', 'In a dry heavy saucepan cook sugar over moderate heat, stirring with a fork, until melted and cook, without stirring, swirling pan, just until a golden caramel. Add hazelnuts, stirring until coated well. Immediately pour mixture onto baking sheet and cool completely, about 30 minutes. Remove praline from baking sheet and break into pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.217', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.293');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('369bb55a-88e1-4dcf-93ae-0ec695ed272a', 'Praline may be eaten as candy or ground in a food processor and used as a dessert topping.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.221', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.293');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1bf1771-6d81-42f2-ac52-62dc6e4e8aba', 'Store the can of coconut milk upside down in the refrigerator overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.225', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.293');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c37db67-cf92-4a02-b07a-2fc4fd6515f7', 'The next morning, turn the can right-side up and open it. Drain the liquid into a separate container and discard.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.229', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.293');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9611b4ed-991e-4e83-a37c-7b3856a6c60e', 'Place the coconut milk solids in a large bowl and add the confectioners'' sugar and vanilla. Beat with an electric mixer on medium-high speed until the mixture resembles whipped cream, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.233', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.294');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97df9566-6a77-4b42-b6ba-b19cb40682e9', 'Use immediately in place of whipped cream as a frosting or as an accompaniment.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.237', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.294');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('692db6a4-51dc-4873-9eda-e6d74ea6fad8', 'Remove zest from oranges in long 1/2-inch-wide strips with a vegetable peeler and remove any white pith from zest. Julienne zest diagonally and transfer to a small saucepan. Cover zest with cold water and bring to a boil, then drain and repeat. Drain again and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.294');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bc8a602-0b73-4d86-aea7-70210d6cd8e6', 'Bring 2 cups water with sugar to a boil in a small heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add zest and simmer, stirring occasionally, until translucent and tender, about 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.245', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.295');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c11f0161-b49f-4f72-89cf-d3db9634fc55', 'Cool zest in syrup, then drain, discarding syrup. Set on a rack over a baking sheet to catch drips and arrange zest on rack, separating strips with a fork. Dry zest 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.249', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.295');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3436de48-241a-480a-9c25-25a81445de5d', 'Preheat oven to 350F (175C). Lightly oil an 8-inch-square baking dish, place on a baking sheet with a rim, and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.254', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.296');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c826eb0-4ac0-4e84-8379-42e646b24871', 'In a large bowl, combine both coconut milks and sugar; stir until the sugar dissolves. Add the remaining ingredients and stir well to combine. Pour into the prepared baking dish and carefully transfer on the baking sheet to the center of the oven. Bake 1 hour. Reduce temperature to 250F (120C) and bake 1 more hour, or until a golden crust forms and a knife inserted halfway from the center comes out almost clean. Let cool about 30 minutes before serving. Serve warm or at room temperature (the pudding will firm as it cools). Or cover and refrigerate completely cooled pudding up to 3 days and serve chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.258', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.297');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4858acf2-9f60-47dd-b7fa-8531ba6dcb43', 'Whisk first 4 ingredients in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.261', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.298');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71d39377-fadc-4686-b47f-6dac7e1e373f', 'Using large melon baller, scoop out 72 balls of honeydew. Using 1 1/4-inch round fluted cookie cutter, cut out 48 rounds from watermelon slices. Alternate 3 honeydew balls and 2 watermelon rounds on each skewer. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover dressing and kebabs separately; chill.) Serve kebabs with dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.265', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.298');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3a7b303-b448-4cf1-9604-257e6d4152a5', 'Pass cabbage, fennel, apples, celery, lemongrass, and ginger through a juicer. Transfer juice to an airtight container; cover and chill until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.27', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.298');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70637274-f107-4240-add2-f82afe721fed', 'Just before serving, add baobab powder to juice and stir until dissolved. Divide juice among glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.299');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be72f1d6-db29-4821-a59c-2e5383068509', 'Put a 9-or-10 inch metal cake pan in the freezer. In a blender blend the strawberries, the sugar, and the lemon juice until the mixture is smooth and the sugar is dissolved. Add the ice cubes, blend the mixture until it is smooth, and pour it into the cold pan. Freeze the mixture for 30 to 40 minutes, or until it is frozen around the edge but still soft in the center, stir the strawberry ice, mashing the frozen parts with a fork, and spoon it into 2 bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.278', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.299');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec7d8e25-6545-4628-bfb3-eef6d6da760c', 'Using melon baller, remove core from bottom end of pears. Combine wine, pear nectar and cinnamon stick in large pot. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean. Bring to simmer. Add pears (liquid should cover pears halfway). Reduce heat to medium-low; cook until pears are tender, about 10 minutes, turning pears halfway through. Transfer pears and cooking liquid to large bowl. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.282', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.3');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca71bb17-5368-459b-bc06-613a09ca38ea', 'Drain poaching liquid back into pot. Mix 2 tablespoons liquid with arrowroot in small bowl; return to pot. Boil until sauce thickens and is reduced to 2 cups, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Cool sauce to room temperature. (Pears and sauce can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.287', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.301');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff2b92cd-d857-4d0d-a8da-59c89e4a9fea', 'Spoon sauce into 6 shallow bowls. Place pears atop sauce. Sprinkle kiwi, cantaloupe and strawberries around pears. Garnish with mint and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.291', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.301');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('225f7d51-669e-4126-8ba9-32418bc437c1', 'Stir together all sauce ingredients until brown sugar is dissolved, then set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.295', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.302');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13453ca2-7da2-48b0-9bf2-8a9c688a4e45', 'Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then sauté ginger and garlic, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add shiitakes and sauté, stirring frequently, until tender and starting to brown, about 6 minutes. Reduce heat to medium, then add cabbage and most of scallions (reserve about a tablespoon for garnish) and cook, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 6 minutes. Add sauce and simmer 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.304', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.303');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c1d3371-6692-44bc-9ed6-eb50fe2edb63', 'While cabbage is cooking, cook soba and edamame together in a pasta pot of boiling salted water (2 tablespoons salt for 6 quarts water) until noodles are just tender, about 6 minutes. Drain in a colander and rinse under cool water to stop cooking and remove excess starch, then drain well again. Transfer to a large bowl and toss with sesame seeds and vegetable mixture. Serve sprinkled with reserved scallions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.309', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.303');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4defb06e-f07f-4c6c-96e0-de6261ecaa83', 'Place peas in large saucepan. Add enough water to cover by 3 inches. Let peas soak 2 hours. Drain peas; return to same pan. Add 4 cups water, onion, bay leaf, and salt. Bring to boil; reduce heat to medium, cover partially, and simmer until peas are tender, about 30 minutes. Discard onion and bay leaf. Drain. Transfer peas to rimmed baking sheet to cool. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.313', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.304');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30022de2-f70e-493c-9a2c-8b56d34edb20', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange pumpkin in single layer in 8x8x2-inch glass baking dish. Drizzle with 3 tablespoons water and oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake until tender when pierced, turning occasionally, about 15 minutes. Add garlic; stir to coat. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.318', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.304');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59687577-da15-4430-b4eb-25019d7da435', 'Whisk oil and lime juice in bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Combine all remaining ingredients and peas in large bowl. Add dressing; toss. Season with salt and pepper. Add pumpkin; toss. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.305');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b0c3566-922d-4503-aa76-e52a0c45a60a', 'In a 5-quart heavy kettle bring water with rice to a boil over moderately high heat and boil mixture, uncovered and undisturbed, until water has evaporated and steam holes appear on surface of rice, about 8 minutes. Reduce heat to low and cook rice, covered and undisturbed, 15 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.327', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.305');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('453c9d1d-7cab-4d5a-942d-19af69883484', 'Boil water, rice, and salt in a 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan, uncovered and undisturbed, until steam holes appear and surface looks dry, about 8 minutes. Reduce heat to very low and cook, covered and undisturbed, 15 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.331', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.306');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c4d25701-c77c-40a0-a585-d37490394e92', 'While rice cooks, simmer lentils in water to cover by 2 inches 18 to 20 minutes, or until just tender, then drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.335', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.306');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b2e84fbd-b24b-4a2a-883d-e99a1349a909', 'Stir together shallot, vinegar, and lemon juice and let stand. Finely grate zest from orange and cut away remaining peel and pith. Cut sections free from membranes and cut sections into 1/2-inch pieces. Toss warm rice with lentils, shallot mixture, orange, zest, cherries, oil, and parsley and season with salt and pepper. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.34', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.307');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4bc305c-e4fb-42f3-8e17-b66367517760', 'Combine all ingredients except pear in a small saucepan. Add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 5 minutes to meld flavors. Remove from heat and let sit until warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.344', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.307');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af35314a-d3b4-433d-8777-826dfae121a9', 'Place pear cubes in a 12-ounce jar with a tight-sealing lid. Add warm pickling liquid. Let cool at room temperature for 30 minutes. Cover and chill. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.348', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.308');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3840d067-e35a-4255-b699-845eca7fe4a3', 'Combine wine, sugar and lime juice in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to simmer, stirring until sugar dissolves. Simmer gently 3 minutes. Cool completely. Puree cubed watermelon in processor. Strain puree through sieve set over large bowl, pressing on solids with back of rubber spatula. Discard solids in sieve. Stir wine mixture and orange juice concentrate into watermelon puree.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.352', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.308');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76b2be7e-5834-46cc-9e18-4b54d73f7489', 'Pour melon mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish. Freeze until semi-firm, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours. Cover; freeze until solid, at least 8 hours or overnight. Chill processor work bowl and metal blade. Transfer melon mixture to processor. Using on/off turns and scraping bottom and sides of bowl, process until very smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.356', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.309');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b31e26c-fa1a-4bd6-84ee-f09a1d50f824', 'Transfer melon mixture to ice cream maker; process mixture according to manufacturer''s instructions. Transfer to container; cover and freeze until firm, about 2 hours or overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.36', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.309');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea550d8a-52ee-4bd6-8746-3ed212bd8825', 'Freeze 6 small bowls 30 minutes. Scoop sorbet into frozen bowls. Garnish with lime slices and watermelon wedges. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.365', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.31');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9ed9fdb-d4b4-4a9a-98a9-f4bd72fadba4', 'Melt coconut oil over medium heat in a large pot. Add onion, ginger, tumeric, and 1/2 tsp. salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is translucent, 8–10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.37', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.311');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60dc88a7-73c9-4082-a903-a214b2fb82e9', 'Break corn cobs in half and add to pot along with corn kernels, potato, coconut milk, lime zest, and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce to a simmer and cook until potato is tender, 20–25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.374', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.311');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('650144e0-b0d7-47f9-a6c8-0d8267f7c813', 'Discard corn cobs and lime zest, then transfer soup to a blender. Add 1/2 tsp. salt and purée until smooth. Let cool to room temperature. Transfer to a large bowl and chill, covered, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.378', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.312');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('99730ee3-e2ee-4ae7-9a74-aa3c868be533', 'Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°F. Spread coconut flakes on a small rimmed baking sheet and toast, tossing occasionally, until golden, about 5 minutes; transfer to a plate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.383', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.315');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7c7dc77-969c-42d6-815d-4144f9aa181d', 'Stir lime juice into soup and adjust seasonings, thinning with water, if needed. Divide soup among bowls, then top with toasted coconut, avocado, and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.388', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.316');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('acddbb1a-6caa-4974-9498-2d1535df6c32', 'Soup can be made 4 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.316');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf0f230a-3244-4506-9bf6-f7d51b4f354c', 'Stir together all ingredients and freeze in ice cream maker. Transfer sorbet to an airtight container and put in freezer to harden, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.397', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.317');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f07952af-8611-4499-b85f-66de497eaa2c', 'Char peppers over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Wrap in paper bag; let stand 10 minutes. Peel peppers. Set strainer over bowl. Holding peppers over bowl to catch any juices, seed peppers. Cut into thin strips. Place in bowl. (Can be made 1 day ahead; chill. Bring to room temperature before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.402', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.317');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('656e04cc-f8aa-4929-8341-9bb5c64cdb2a', 'Preheat broiler. Arrange bread on baking sheet. Broil until toasted, about 2 minutes. Trun bread over. Brush with 1 1/2 tablespoons oil. Broil until golden, about 2 minutes. (Can be made 8 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.406', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.318');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aad5ad56-cbd3-4a29-8c28-bd6d1b4e694c', 'Stir first 6 ingredients in medium saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and boil syrup 1 minute. Reduce heat. Add nectarines. Simmer until nectarines are tender but still hold shape, about 10 minutes. Transfer sauce to bowl; cool. DO AHEAD Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover; chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.419', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.319');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f69c2272-7a1c-4d34-b604-a3b5c4451cdf', 'Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.423', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.32');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8101bf6d-0238-492b-a239-a0a3b2d14216', 'Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add tortilla strips and cook until crisp, about 4 minutes per batch. Using slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels. Combine cabbage, lettuce, mango, jicama, onion, peppers, pumpkin seeds and cilantro in large bowl. Add tortilla strips. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.427', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.32');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c915a922-681d-4b59-a9b2-1bcbe900c00d', 'In a blender blend half the grapefruit juice, half the orange juice, and half the pineapple until the mixture is smooth and transfer the mixture to a large pitcher. Blend the remaining juices and pineapple in the same manner, transfer the mixture to the pitcher, and chill it, covered, overnight. Stir the juice before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.432', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.321');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee76efe5-901f-4e3e-9be7-54e2676cd3d6', 'Cut ends off kumquats, then cut into 1/4-inch-thick rounds, removing seeds. Place kumquat slices in medium saucepan; pour enough cold water over to cover by 2 inches. Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Immediately remove from heat; strain. Return kumquat slices to pan; repeat blanching 2 more times. Transfer kumquat slices to medium bowl. Combine 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water in same saucepan. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves, then bring to boil, brushing down pan sides with wet pastry brush. Add kumquat slices; press gently to submerge. Reduce heat so that mixture barely simmers. Cover surface with parchment round. Cook without stirring until kumquats are translucent, 15 to 18 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.436', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.321');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('41c73c44-2414-4cd5-b642-ffed1020c72d', 'Using slotted spoon, transfer kumquat slices to medium bowl. Add lemon slices and lemon juice to syrup in pan, pressing to submerge. Bring to boil. Reduce heat so that syrup barely simmers. Cover surface with parchment round. Cook without stirring until lemon slices are translucent, occasionally pressing on parchment to submerge slices, 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand 15 minutes. Transfer lemon slices to cutting board; cut each into quarters. Add lemon quarters and syrup to bowl with kumquat slices. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover; chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.439', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.322');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22f35704-ee57-41c1-bd56-66e5fe8cfeea', 'Cut off peel and white pith from blood oranges. Working over bowl to catch juices and using small knife, cut between membranes to release segments. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.443', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.322');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('73d640a7-a028-44f4-b546-72507ac1710e', 'Drain syrup from kumquat-lemon mixture, reserving syrup. Drain orange segments. Combine fruit in medium bowl, adding some syrup if mixture is dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.447', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.323');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e74f357-9791-497c-bcfe-ac360685b4c1', 'Place 1 ounce wakame (dried seaweed) in a medium bowl; cover with boiling water and let sit until softened, about 10 minutes. Drain seaweed, squeeze out excess water, and coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.451', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.324');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02428a7f-8617-4f28-9870-d24a2f72c4e5', 'Combine the water, lime juice, sugar, lime zest, saffron threads, and cardamom pods in a medium saucepan over high heat. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 7 minutes, which is just long enough for the flavors to fuse. Remove from the heat and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.455', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.324');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('21b4e90b-9f42-4d65-af16-d3967f00ee29', 'In a large skillet cook leeks in oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until softened, about 10 minutes. Stir mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Stir in scallions, soy sauce, and vinegar and cook 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.459', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.325');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a33d5bee-24a3-40ff-b1a0-49a5df110169', 'In a kettle of salted boiling water cook noodles 5 minutes or according to package directions. Put pea shoots in a colander and drain cooked noodles over shoots to wilt them. Rinse mixture in cold water and drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.462', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.325');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7e910b23-cb42-4d1d-b0f5-775be5f682dd', 'In a bowl toss noodles with pea shoots and stir in cooked vegetables. Season mixture with salt and pepper and serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.466', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.326');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97e9a372-e407-401b-8336-891869db8801', 'Char peppers directly over gas flame or in broiler. Enclose in plastic bag; steam 15 to 30 minutes. Peel, seed, and cut peppers into 1/2-inch-wide strips. Mix peppers, raisins, oil, garlic, capers, vinegar, thyme, paprika, and cayenne in large bowl. Season with coarse salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: can be made 1 day ahead. Cover; chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.47', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.326');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('103ade4f-d356-45de-b206-31630310d989', 'Tie zest, cinnamon, and peppercorns together in a cheesecloth bag. Bring wine, water, sugar, and cheesecloth bag to a boil in a 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Boil syrup until reduced to about 1 1/2 cups, 8 to 10 minutes. Add figs and simmer, covered, until soft and plump, 25 to 30 minutes. Discard cheesecloth bag and stir lemon juice into fig mixture. Cool at least 1 hour, then serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.474', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.326');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa2891c9-46fe-46f8-9b86-528614fa3b55', 'Whisk oil and vinegar in small bowl to blend. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Place baby greens, pitted olives, and thinly sliced fennel in large bowl. Add dressing; toss to coat. Season salad with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.478', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.327');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8faa28ee-8489-4e5d-9341-bcf548a64b86', '1. Combine the tamari, vinegar, and Pickapeppa in a nonreactive dish and stir to combine. If using additional seasoning (see below), add it here. Add the tempeh. Marinate at room temperature, turning occasionally, for 20 minutes to 1 hour or refrigerated for up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.481', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.329');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51b3b00a-53c5-4677-b06a-312361534084', '2. Fifteen minutes before you are ready to cook the tempeh, preheat the oven to 375°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.486', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.329');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac382acb-2ee9-4c05-8745-b19b6383d029', '3. Place the marinated tempeh pieces on a nonstick baking sheet or one that has been sprayed with cooking spray, allowing plenty of air space between chunks. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, then flip the pieces over and bake for another 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and use as desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.33');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b883c14-4056-4cc3-bbf7-e66f347949ba', 'The above is a basic recipe, designed to be compatible with almost any finished recipe. But the marinade can certainly be zapped up to good effect.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.494', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.33');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e78e5bf-7d0b-4712-81af-380a797abffa', '• 1 to 3 cloves garlic, pressed', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.33');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d651c096-8a47-487f-9b0c-0929ee56e05e', '• 1 to 2 teaspoons peeled grated ginger', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.501', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.331');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97ec7a8c-85ce-46c9-ab8d-4f159c40d5db', '• 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.505', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.332');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af0abe59-73a0-4456-bce0-780697ad5305', '• 1 to 2 teaspoons honey', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.508', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.333');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cae00ecf-a350-4f37-a53a-6dc71599069d', '• 1 teaspoon ground coriander', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.512', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.334');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9988c40-a6c8-4f9f-860d-37b62e215747', 'Rinse kale; shake dry, leaving some water clinging. Heat olive and sesame oils in a large skillet over medium heat. Add kale; season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and cook, tossing occasionally, until just tender, 7–10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.526', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.336');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76e295a3-626c-400a-9ed7-bd6fbb668450', 'DO AHEAD: Kale can be made 5 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.53', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.337');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a843293-3b8e-422c-a2cf-7be39a104d15', 'Toss pumpkin with sugar and a pinch of salt in a large bowl. Let stand at room temperature, stirring occasionally, 1 hour. Chill, covered, 8 hours. (Sugar will liquefy.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.534', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.337');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3d9dc4c-6680-4c4f-a402-bcc20836c079', 'Simmer pumpkin mixture, water, and wine in a wide 6-quart heavy pot until pumpkin is just tender, about 10 minutes. Transfer pumpkin with a slotted spoon to a bowl and stir in raisins, then boil cooking liquid until reduced to about 1 cup, about 10 minutes. Transfer syrup to a measuring cup, then slowly whisk into mustard in a small bowl until smooth. Stir into pumpkin mixture. Cool, then chill, covered, at least 8 hours for flavors to meld. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.538', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.341');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('797b3f1a-806b-45a3-be0f-646bee70aa9a', 'Fill a large pot partially with water. Bring to a boil, and note the temperature of the boiling water with a candy thermometer. (Since water boils at different temperatures in different locations, it is important to follow
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00e4e130-cb07-431c-ba59-0f41e7ca2166', 'Empty the large pot and place the syrup in it. Add a few drops of oil. (Boiling maple syrup will foam up; the oil keeps the foam down. Buttering the rim of the pot will also help.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.547', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.374');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b247e3b-7638-4206-bc16-015524222758', 'Boil carefully over high heat, without stirring, until the temperature of the boiling syrup is 28°F/17°C above the boiling point of your water (212°F/100°C at sea level).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.55', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.376');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6debe27f-6565-4224-8a8e-16dcae0459b4', 'Remove from the heat and let cool for 3 to 5 minutes. Do not stir or disturb the candy at this point; if the thermometer is attached to the pan, leave it there during the cooling period.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.38');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f87be645-9eb7-419e-992a-4bd56acea5e2', 'Stir evenly until the liquid loses its gloss, starts to become opaque, and begins to thicken. (This is the tricky part; if you stir too long the thickened syrup will “set up,” or harden, in the pan. If this happens, add a cup of water, and reheat slowly to dissolve the sugar, then start over. But if you don’t stir long enough, the sugar may not “set up” in the molds at all.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.559', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.38');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed339d3d-6db1-46b0-865a-4b486c00f345', 'Carefully pour the candy into the molds. It’s helpful to have an assistant spread the syrup in the molds while you continue to pour the mixture into the other molds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.563', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.381');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c80f180-7767-42fb-8331-baaee22842ca', 'Allow the candies to cool, remove from the molds, place on a rack to dry for a few hours, and enjoy.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.567', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.381');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1db487ae-a798-44c9-bbf1-6ddd5d3fa8cb', 'Prepare a charcoal or gas grill for grilling over high heat, or turn 3 gas burners to high. Place the eggplants directly onto the coals or flame and grill, using tongs to turn them as the skin chars, until blackened all over. Set aside to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.571', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.382');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c96e2283-b0fe-484f-b93d-9b7982eb5a94', 'Alternatively, roast the eggplant in the oven. Preheat the oven to 400°F and line a baking sheet with aluminum foil. Pierce the eggplants in a few places with a sharp knife, place them on the prepared baking sheet and roast, turning every 5 minutes or so, until the skin is blistered and begins to crack all over. Set aside to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.575', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.383');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6aeccd61-a907-4f7f-a761-dbe9c1b317bd', 'Slice the eggplants in half lengthwise and scoop out the flesh, transferring it directly to a strainer to allow the liquid to release.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.579', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.383');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d38fc882-7ab6-4b2d-81fe-c16f5730fe1b', 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the tomatoes with the chile peppers, if using, garlic, shallot, 1/2 cup parsley, 3 tablespoons oil, lemon juice, cumin, pepper and salt. Add the drained eggplant and mix together with a fork. Transfer the eggplant mixture to a serving bowl and drizzle with the remaining 3 tablespoons oil. Garnish with the remaining parsley and surround with the cucumber slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.582', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.383');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e91bf191-a1d6-4925-aa4f-9135ecf48e7d', 'Cook green beans in a 4-quart pot of well-salted boiling water, uncovered, until crisp-tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.586', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.384');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('03b3b976-ba04-42ab-af60-c69384a22c28', 'Meanwhile, heat oil with red pepper flakes in a 12-inch heavy skillet (preferably straight-sided) over medium-high heat until it shimmers. Sauté Brussels sprouts with 1/2 teaspoon salt until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.59', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.384');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7ceea98-17dd-4b2c-9542-95d8748443be', 'Add beans and sauté 2 minutes. Add water and boil until evaporated and vegetables are just tender, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in mint. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.595', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.387');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6bd7547-16a9-4cc2-894f-040badcbbc95', 'Toss together cabbage, carrot, and salt in a bowl. Put kombu in a narrow straight-sided container (5 to 6 inches in diameter) and top with cabbage mixture. Cut a piece of cardboard to fit just inside container and enclose it in a sealable plastic bag. Top cabbage with plastic-covered round and stack 4 to 6 pounds of canned goods on top to weight it. Chill weighted cabbage at least 3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.599', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.397');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c6fe1e02-0f0b-47c3-9e94-f731c29dabb0', 'Discard kombu. Squeeze excess liquid from cabbage and toss with shiso.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.602', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.4');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a5b912f-8053-4556-8570-ced6d8ff87da', 'Place carrots in a heatproof resealable container or jar. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, peppercorns, mustard seeds, and 1/2 cup water in a small pot. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally. Immediately pour over carrots. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.606', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.401');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c72da434-7727-417c-b668-e8d0fae2016c', 'Preheat oven to 225°F. and line 2 large baking sheets with parchment paper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.61', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.402');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63f0c112-4eca-4c8c-8f19-b9b1ea4d32ce', 'Sift 3 tablespoons confectioners'' sugar evenly onto lined baking sheets. With a mandoline or other manual slicer cut apples crosswise into paper-thin slices. Arrange apple slices in one layer on sheets and sprinkle evenly with remaining 3 tablespoons confectioners'' sugar. Bake slices in upper and lower thirds of oven, switching position of sheets halfway through baking, 2 1/4 hours total, or until slices are pale golden and starting to crisp. Immediately peel apple chips off parchment and cool on a rack. Apple chips keep in an airtight container at room temperature 2 weeks. Recommended for garnish on ice creams and apple desserts or as a crisp, cookie-like accompaniment.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.615', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.402');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c7da0ab-726a-456b-a8ea-8a0d2cce1e82', 'Place all the ingredients in a food processor and puree until smooth (you want tiny pieces of vegetables to remain, but small enough for little ones to swallow).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.619', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.413');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65c7341b-de6c-405b-9e4a-6b5bb4967737', 'Serve (it''s delicious served chilled too).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.623', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.415');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3ee4d688-8a18-470b-aa64-b88a75e0f068', 'Whisk orange juice concentrate, rice vinegar, and canola oil in small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD Dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.626', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.416');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcdcee19-7d2f-4de4-b3f8-b435fab66995', 'Combine slaw mix, corn kernels, carrots, red bell pepper strips, sliced green onions, and chopped cilantro in large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Season slaw to taste with salt and pepper. Let stand 15 minutes for flavors to blend. Toss again and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.63', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.416');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91dcf139-23c7-486f-8694-2f7dc70f81a4', 'Finely grind fennel seeds in an electric coffee/spice grinder or with a mortar and pestle, then stir together with cider and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Pour mixture through a fine sieve into an 8- to 9-inch baking pan, discarding solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.635', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.417');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7004540-dc23-4828-ad17-d135ba0eaeac', 'Freeze, stirring and crushing lumps with a fork every 30 minutes, until evenly frozen, about 2 hours total. Scrape with a fork to lighten texture, crushing any lumps.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.638', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.417');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('16edc469-fd78-48f4-921b-8d3f410d329e', 'Serve immediately or freeze, covered, up to 3 days (rescrape to lighten texture again if necessary).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.642', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.418');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05aaeb1b-ac24-4910-8d62-6455219c7406', 'Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid. Whisk hummus into liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.646', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.418');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc5944f6-65e0-45d6-b4fb-64614838ce6b', 'Meanwhile, heat oil in large heavy skillet over high heat. Add cherry tomatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook until blackened in spots, shaking skillet occasionally, about 8 minutes. Mix in chickpeas, garlic, and smoked paprika. Crush some of tomatoes to release juices. Add pasta and enough hummus mixture to coat. Mix in olives and cilantro; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.65', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.419');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b15352d-003b-4859-b688-c71ea89921f3', 'In a kettle stir together well wine, vinegar, garlic, rosemary, and sugar and bring mixture to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Stir in pectin quickly and bring mixture back to a full rolling boil. Boil jelly, stirring constantly, 1 minute and remove kettle from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.654', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.421');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bde3748f-87ab-48a1-8849-1b1c4fcc0464', 'Skim off any foam and ladle jelly immediately into jars, filling to within 1/8 inch of top. Wipe rims with dampened cloth and seal jars with liquids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.659', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.422');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18e6e48a-e0f3-4405-a2ff-134d62fdfdfd', 'Put jars in water-bath canner or on a rack set in a deep kettle. Add enough hot water to cover jars by 2 inches and bring to a boil. Boil jars, covered, 5 minutes and transfer with tongs to a rack. Cool jars completely and store in a cool, dark place.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.663', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.422');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a976f369-fad6-4e08-949d-64e64d5f69ff', 'Wash jars in hot suds and rinse in scalding water. Put jars in a kettle and cover with hot water. Bring water to a boil, covered, and boil jars 15 minutes from the time that steam emerges from the kettle. Turn off heat and let jars stand in hot water. Just before they are to be filled invert jars onto a kitchen towel to dry. (Jars should be filled while still hot.) Sterilize jar lids 5 minutes, or according to manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.668', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.423');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6ebf2775-cc52-4eed-a20e-3ca185f9b591', 'Bring water, 1 tablespoon oil, and salt to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan, then stir in rice. Return to a boil and cover pan. Reduce heat to low and simmer rice until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 15 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork and let stand, covered, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.423');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c94d0d7-53c7-4db7-a809-03941ad48aa5', 'While rice is simmering, cook lentils in a saucepan of boiling water until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain in a sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.424');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89993447-419c-456d-afb0-641f8103f28f', 'Spread rice and lentils in a shallow baking pan and cool 10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and toss gently with remaining 2 tablespoons oil, remaining ingredients, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.681', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.425');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9c6605d-0fe5-4dab-814a-6dc6e352f8a2', 'Whisk first 6 ingredients in small bowl to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.685', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.425');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5849ea72-bfcb-4188-9752-ab331ba5c69e', 'Combine collard greens, cabbage, and carrots in very large bowl. Pour dressing over; toss to coat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Refrigerate until collard greens soften and wilt slightly, tossing occasionally, at least 1 hour and up to 3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.689', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.425');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5eb176ab-ccca-4bc5-9133-a9574189a00a', 'Remove outer dark green ribs of celery and reserve for another use. Remove leaves and reserve in a bowl. Cut off and discard base of celery heart, then cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices and add to celery leaves along with remaining ingredients. Toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.693', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.426');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9693e4e8-c7ea-4814-81a2-63038570b226', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Spray large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Arrange tomatoes and next 6 ingredients on sheet. Drizzle with oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until vegetables are tender and brown around edges, stirring occasionally, about 55 minutes. Peel garlic and reserve. Coarsely chop half of vegetables and reserve. Transfer garlic and remaining vegetables from sheet to large pot (reserve sheet).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.697', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.427');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38d83121-c9da-49b9-b745-856641078def', 'Add 1/2 cup vegetable broth to baking sheet and scrape up browned bits; add to pot with vegetables. Add 7 1/2 cups broth, dried porcini, thyme, and bay leaf to pot. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer until vegetables and porcini are very tender, about 20 minutes. Pour vegetables and broth into large strainer set over bowl. Transfer vegetables in strainer to processor and puree until smooth; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.701', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.427');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53c30be9-2458-43c4-be53-bcb45bd238b5', 'Return broth and bay leaf to pot; add barley and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer until barley is tender, about 40 minutes. Add reserved vegetable puree and chopped vegetables to pot; simmer until soup thickens and flavors blend, about 10 minutes. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cool soup slightly. Chill soup uncovered until cold, then cover and keep chilled. Rewarm over medium heat, thinning with additional broth if desired before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.706', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.427');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f349d48-d8d5-42c5-9e29-6b4809948ae9', 'Ladle soup into bowls. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.711', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.428');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29efdf0f-7d09-4db5-96fb-b5af71e14874', '*Dried porcini mushrooms are available at Italian markets, specialty foods stores, and many supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.715', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.429');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e4370a1-740b-4994-9415-86c5c127358f', 'Whisk vinegar, mirin, vegetable oil, carrot, miso, ginger, turmeric, and sesame oil in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.719', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.43');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('218a7366-252b-48a4-90d2-9f937183b208', 'Veggies can be made 5 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.724', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.43');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e4d0a5c-9a9c-4d24-b661-e14277c60c62', 'Combine snap peas, radish matchsticks, red cabbage, and peas in a medium bowl. Add remaining ingredients to a jar with a lid. Shake to mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.728', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.43');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6f9c6db-4da2-46aa-a278-6c6dc7bf912c', 'Toss salad with dressing just before serving. Scatter radish rounds over the top.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.731', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.431');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4f53f7c-c495-42ac-80de-53a248a5f1bf', 'Place onion, 1/4 cup vinegar, and bay leaf in large jar or medium bowl. Add just enough water to cover. Season generously with salt and pepper. Cover and chill overnight. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.735', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.431');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f972127b-779f-41c6-b726-d46d72689aed', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Place large piece of foil on baking sheet. Place beets in center of foil. Drizzle beets with 1 tablespoon oil and 2 tablespoons water. Top with another piece of foil; crimp edges to seal tightly. Roast beets until tender when pierced with fork, about 1 hour 15 minutes. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.431');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a92c95dd-e3d9-48f5-a705-585e46ec0661', 'Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes. Rinse under cold water to cool. Drain and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.744', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.432');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3943dd82-cbee-49d7-881b-8ea42ae14007', 'Whisk remaining 6 tablespoons balsamic vinegar, 1/2 cup oil, shallots, and thyme in small bowl to blend. Season dressing with salt and pepper. (Beets, beans, and dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.748', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.432');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('903fd319-de53-4dd3-ab41-ccffbdb8ed7a', 'Peel and cut beets into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Arrange large radicchio leaves over very large platter to cover (reserve small leaves for another use). Drain red onions; scatter over radicchio. Arrange beans over onions. Arrange beet slices decoratively over beans. Pour dressing over salad and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.752', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.432');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d554f69-69cd-4f34-822f-6287b4cef3eb', 'Steam sugar snap peas until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Transfer to bowl. Toss with seeds and oil. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.756', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.432');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc18a66e-c24b-4fbb-a195-f45880b92e47', 'Position 1 rack in top third and 1 rack in bottom third of oven and preheat to 375°F. Spray 2 heavy large rimmed baking sheets with nonstick spray. Cut carrots and parsnips into 3- to 4-inch lengths. Fit processor with 1/4-inch-thick slicing disk. Working in batches, place carrot pieces upright and fitting snugly side by side in feed tube of processor. With machine running, use plunger to push down firmly on carrots and cut uniform round slices. Transfer carrot coins to extra-large bowl. Repeat with parsnips, then potatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.76', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da9410f6-48f8-443c-9186-910dcdccb90c', 'Add olive oil, 2 teaspoons coarse salt, coriander, cardamom, and freshly ground black pepper to vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Divide mixture between prepared baking sheets. Roast vegetables until tender and golden brown around edges, about 1 hour. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Rewarm in 350°F oven until heated through, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2585e4b-1c26-4d6a-b952-8876c7ba1be8', 'Transfer roasted vegetable coins to large bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.768', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f8024548-75fd-471d-9063-913308319913', 'Makes 6 servings. Line baking sheet with heavy-duty foil. Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water just until tender when pierced with sharp knife, about 10 minutes. Drain; cool 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.772', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b58b9745-9b22-4cc2-98c7-afe4d7af6e6e', 'Meanwhile, whisk oil and next 5 ingredients in large bowl to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.776', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('824465f9-fc34-41e8-9509-8d5e719445dd', 'Add potatoes to dressing and toss to coat. Thread potatoes onto skewers, cut side up. Place on prepared baking sheet. (Skewers can be assembled 4 hours ahead. Cover; let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.78', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('21c217bf-16d5-4297-ad41-c367561c100f', 'Preheat broiler, positioning rack 6 inches from heat source. Broil potato skewers until browned and bubbly, turning halfway through cooking time, about 10 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.784', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94174c92-988b-472b-87f9-8b704dd26a78', 'Fill a 4-quart kettle three-fourths full with salted water and bring to a boil for cooking fusilli.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.788', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2bb79128-aade-43cf-85c6-fc6409f3e780', 'Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes and transfer to a colander set over a bowl. Sprinkle eggplant lightly with salt and let drain 10 minutes. While eggplant is draining, discard stems from mushrooms and cut caps into 3/4-inch pieces. Cut scallions diagonally into thin slices. Quarter tomatoes and chop jalapeño including seeds (wear rubber gloves). Rinse eggplant and squeeze dry, discarding any liquid in bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.792', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.435');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('936a2874-2048-4085-ae10-0fb1ad24f507', 'Boil fusilli until al dente.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.796', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.435');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd598a3e-11f2-4613-86eb-3c719073d227', 'While fusilli is boiling, in a large non-stick skillet cook gingerroot and garlic in oil over moderately high heat, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add eggplant and mushrooms and sauté, stirring constantly, until softened, 3 to 4 minutes. Add scallions and sauté, stirring, until eggplant is tender, about 2 minutes. Stir in coconut milk, tomatoes, jalapeño, basil, and salt and pepper to taste and cook just until heated through, about 30 seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.8', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.435');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f20bb245-93bc-40bb-bd6e-95bf4315bc1f', 'Drain fusilli in a colander and in a bowl toss with sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.805', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.436');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1410f0af-4f10-4dc6-a57f-4222cfcb33ee', 'Bring 4 quarts water to a full boil. Add 1/4 tsp salt and stir in pasta. Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until noodles are tender but firm. While pasta cooks, warm oil in a large sauté pan over medium heat. Add garlic, swirl for a moment and reduce heat to low. Do not let garlic brown. Add zucchini and yellow squash and sauté gently until zucchini softens slightly, about 5 minutes. Season mixture with 1/4 tsp salt and remove pan from heat. When pasta is finished cooking, drain noodles. Using tongs or 2 kitchen spoons, combine noodles thoroughly with zucchini mixture over low heat. Add basil, arugula, and tomatoes and season with remaining 1/4 tsp salt. Sprinkle with lemon zest and juice and stir to combine. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.808', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.437');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee1f34bd-d07d-43d2-a21f-a650211e0b72', 'Cut 2 bunches scallions into 3" lengths, then thinly slice lengthwise. Place in a bowl of ice water (to crisp). Just before serving, drain well, pat dry, and transfer to another bowl. Add 1 tablespoon distilled white vinegar and 1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil; toss to coat. Season with kosher salt, freshly ground black pepper, and gochugaru (coarse Korean red pepper powder).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.812', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.438');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b748e80-eb89-450a-8c6e-fd211743f258', 'Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise and squeeze lightly to remove the seeds. With a serrated knife, dice the tomatoes and transfer to a strainer to drain. In a salad bowl, mix together the cucumber, greens, scallions, herbs, jalapeños, and capers. Add the tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.817', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.438');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca0d28d8-9510-4490-80d2-0d661e4e8f18', 'To make the dressing, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, vinegar, lemon zest,and salt and pepper to taste. Pour over the salad and toss. Taste and adjust the seasoning. Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes to give the flavors time to meld. Sprinkle with sumac before serving if you like.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.82', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.438');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4e7465d-bf94-48e8-939d-a06d7c882116', 'Just before serving, pour dressing over corn mixture and toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.826', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.439');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('40410a7d-d407-45da-bf44-fae1eadf5288', '1. Coarsely grate the sweet potatoes, preferably using the grating disk of a food processor. (You should have about 5 cups.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.021', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.47');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79fd40d9-233d-4616-bd60-381458707f8a', 'Toss sliced cucumber with watermelon, remaining 1/3 cup mint, and lime juice in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.079', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.09');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e781e80e-6296-491c-9bda-fada7de6d8ad', 'Combine maple syrup, 1/2 cup water, and vinegar in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Add all dried fruit, garlic, and salt; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add fresh cranberries and chipotle chiles; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer until cranberries pop and mixture thickens, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Transfer to bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep refrigerated. Bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.83', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.441');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a868f38-4fb0-466e-b0c3-c62fdfc09ad8', '*Chipotle chiles canned in a spicy tomato sauce that is sometimes called adobo are available at Latin American markets, specialty foods stores, and some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.835', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.441');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('58635ca3-6ec9-4ee7-aa8c-4b6c341c75d1', 'Preheat broiler. Brush 2 large baking sheets with olive oil. Gently toss apples, pears, 1/4 cup oil, and minced rosemary in large bowl. Arrange fruit in single layer on sheets. Broil until fruit is tender and edges begin to brown, watching closely to avoid burning and turning sheets for even browning, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.838', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.442');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8798127c-34a1-4f4e-ad23-0a017cee3c44', 'Transfer fruit to platter. Sprinkle with pepper. Garnish with rosemary sprigs, if desired. Serve warm or at room temperature. (Can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.842', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.443');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4f8ecb1-5011-4ec6-8a42-7c908748b0f6', 'Pat tofu dry with paper towels, then wrap in fresh paper towels and put in a microwave-safe dish (see cooks'' note, below). Microwave at high power 30 seconds. Pour off any liquid and wrap tofu in fresh paper towels. Microwave 1 or 2 more times for 30 seconds each time, pouring off any liquid, until tofu feels firmer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.443');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fa03872-16b8-441b-9cf3-efd49e144d32', 'Stir together miso, sugar, and sake in a small saucepan. (If miso mixture is very thick, stir in 1 tablespoon water.) Cook over medium-high heat, stirring, until bubbling, glossy, and the consistency of ketchup, 1 to 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.85', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.444');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b636c9b0-d16d-47ee-9fc0-525889226495', 'Cut tofu in half horizontally and arrange, cut sides up, on a cutting board. Cut each half into 6 squares (pieces might not be perfectly square).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.854', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.445');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a0e9b69-2422-443e-adf7-dd815b702eca', 'Arrange tofu on a foil-lined broiler pan, cut sides up, and broil about 2 inches from heat until a crust just forms, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from oven and spread crusted side of each square with about 3/4 teaspoon miso mixture. Broil until tops are just bubbling and starting to color, 1 to 2 minutes. Transfer to a plate. Skewer each square with 1 two-pronged pick or 2 parallel straight picks. Sprinkle with seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.858', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.446');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00fad819-fe1d-42ad-8ec4-c9ba4d8f942b', 'Bring rice and water to a boil with 1 tablespoon oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a 2-quart heavy saucepan. Cover and cook over low heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 50 minutes. Let stand, covered, 10 minutes, then transfer to a shallow baking pan and cool to warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.446');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91407c89-8464-4326-b471-85f9f0664003', 'While rice is standing, cook coriander and cumin seeds in remaining 2 tablespoons oil in 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, until fragrant and a shade darker, 1 to 2 minutes. Add garlic, zucchini, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook, stirring frequently, until zucchini is crisp-tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Toss zucchini mixture with rice, herbs, lemon juice, pecans, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.865', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.446');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('240b7702-32fa-4ec5-a12e-a2928d175a8b', 'Stir first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat, cover and let steep 1 hour. Strain mixture into 8-inch square metal baking pan. Freeze until edges begin to set, about 1 hour. Whisk; freeze again until mixture is slushy, about 1 hour. Whisk again to blend well. Freeze without stirring until granita is frozen solid, at least 3 hours or overnight. Using fork, scrape granita until entire mixture is mass of crystals. Cover and freeze until ready to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.869', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.447');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30fc23bf-cc7e-4e4e-bbbc-f2bfb8548b27', 'Scoop granita into 6 chilled glasses. Top with Ginger Whipped Cream.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.873', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cbe0ec1-7532-47a4-9194-acb7c8d61775', 'Trim 1/8 inch from bottom of bok choy, then quarter lengthwise and thinly slice crosswise.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.877', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4185169-2ef2-4d3c-99e3-edc36ecd7b47', 'Heat a 14-inch flat-bottomed wok or 12-inch heavy skillet over high heat until a drop of water evaporates instantly. Pour vegetable oil down side of wok, swirling to coat sides. Add garlic and stir-fry 10 seconds. Add cabbage and 1/4 teaspoon salt and stir-fry 3 minutes. Add bok choy and stir-fry until ribs are crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Serve drizzled with sesame oil and sprinkled with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.881', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ca36181-a6f6-432e-8d73-225bdb5f602c', 'Peel potatoes and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Transfer to a bowl and cover with cold water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.884', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('654dbdc1-f43c-4b74-b4f1-f3a98b4c89a4', 'Toast coconut in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, about 3 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl and wipe out skillet. Toast cumin seeds in skillet over medium heat, shaking skillet frequently, until fragrant and just a shade darker, about 30 seconds. Transfer to another small bowl. Reserve skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.888', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('34caaba0-ebfe-438f-9701-1d77e98ea602', 'Purée jalapeño, ginger, and garlic in a blender with curry powder, cinnamon, turmeric, oil, 1/4 cup water, and 1 teaspoon salt until smooth. Transfer purée to skillet and cook over medium-high heat, stirring, until thickened slightly, about 1 minute. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until it begins to soften, about 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.892', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.45');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f2b55bcd-5f33-46e0-95e6-91627ea20956', 'Drain potatoes, then add to onion mixture with cumin seeds and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are barely tender, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.897', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.451');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95d4c127-046a-4523-961c-b1cabbcb1968', 'Add chickpeas and remaining 1 1/2 cups water, scraping up any brown bits, then briskly simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender, 16 to 20 minutes more. Add peas and cook, covered, until just tender, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in toasted coconut and cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.901', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.452');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('945de857-ec9f-4a15-b68a-706f9445e683', 'Whisk flours, cumin seeds, salt, and water in a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.904', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.454');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e261e6e-9a75-4883-ada9-f4d47a93d433', 'Generously brush a 12-inch nonstick skillet with oil and heat over medium-high heat until it shimmers. Pour 1/2 cup batter into skillet, swirling until bottom is coated. Cook, undisturbed, until dosa is set and edges are golden, about 2 minutes. Flip using a rubber spatula and cook dosa until underside is golden in spots, about 1 minute more. Transfer to a plate. Make more dosas with remaining batter, stacking and covering loosely with foil to keep warm. To serve, spoon masala filling into dosas.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.908', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.454');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('83e7d65d-1da0-490c-a8a2-5028f001d1a5', 'In a food processor purée artichoke hearts with oil until very smooth, about 2 minutes. Transfer purée to a bowl and stir in garlic paste, olives, and salt and pepper to taste. Chill dip, covered, at least 4 hours and up to 24 hours. Stir chopped parsley into dip and garnish with parsley sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.912', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.455');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dadcec61-7600-4484-adad-acb6ed7ecae8', 'In a dry heavy saucepan cook sugar over moderate heat, stirring with a fork, until melted and cook, without stirring, swirling pan, until a golden caramel. Stir in pecans with salt until coated well. Immediately pour mixture onto baking sheet, tilting baking sheet to make a thin layer, and cool completely, about 20 minutes. Carefully remove praline in shards from baking sheet. Break about one eighth shards into smaller pieces and in a food processor pulse until ground coarse. Break remaining praline into 12 shards for garnishing desserts. Praline may be made 2 days ahead, ground praline kept in an airtight container at cool room temperature (if it clumps, regrind in food processor before using), and shards kept between sheets of wax paper in another airtight container at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.923', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.456');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15fa65e9-fc2b-411f-8655-9642f706d9af', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Toast walnuts on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing occasionally, until fragrant and slightly darker, 8–10 minutes. Let cool; coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.927', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.457');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8a1982e-e01d-4181-9544-aa3b80a5c514', 'Heat broiler. Broil bell peppers on a broiler-proof rimmed baking sheet, turning occasionally, until softened and skins are blackened in spots, 20–25 minutes. Transfer bell peppers to a bowl, cover with plastic wrap, and let steam 15 minutes. Peel peppers, seed, and chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.457');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8306476f-b48c-4ec2-b86c-41a3e84df176', 'Toss bell peppers, garlic, mint, oil, Aleppo pepper, lemon juice, pomegranate molasses, and walnuts in a small bowl; season with salt, black pepper, and more Aleppo pepper and lemon juice, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.934', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.458');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c258a1b-06fa-4234-890c-a38437ebda79', 'DO AHEAD: Relish can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.938', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.458');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('db10ec79-4060-4935-943c-28713889d1e5', 'Wash rice in several changes of cold water in a bowl until water is clear, then drain in a sieve. Combine with water and salt in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.942', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.459');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('08bb043a-539a-4ca3-b95b-bc3feb930d1b', 'Peel potatoes, then cut lengthwise into 1/3-inch-thick sticks, submerging in a large bowl of ice water. Rinse potatoes in several changes of cold water in bowl (more ice isn''t necessary) until water is clear. Drain in a large colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.946', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.459');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c343a80a-9e4f-4bb5-8caf-92194ab8267e', 'Spread potatoes out in a single layer on several layers of kitchen towels to drain, then pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.95', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.46');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81154d7d-4c42-4ce5-9606-6d3af5eca6f2', 'While potatoes are being rinsed and dried, heat 2 inches oil slowly in a 5- to 6-quart pot over medium-low heat until thermometer registers 300°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.953', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.46');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('32e66cb3-7682-445a-87c3-e28bb6dd10ca', 'When oil is ready, increase heat to high and fry potatoes in four batches, stirring occasionally, until just cooked through but still white, about 3 minutes. (Adjust heat to keep oil as close to 300°F as possible and return oil to 300°F between batches.) Transfer fried potatoes with a slotted spoon to a baking sheet lined with dry towels to drain. When all potatoes are fried once, cool potatoes to room temperature, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.957', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.461');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e42086c7-29fd-46d8-912e-3f16fc5a3d9d', 'Reheat oil over medium-high heat until thermometer registers 375°F. Fry potatoes again in four batches, stirring, and adjusting heat to keep oil as close to 375°F as possible, until deep golden, 3 to 4 minutes. (Return oil to 375°F between batches.) Transfer with slotted spoon to dry towels to drain briefly, then season with salt and serve immediately, with sauce(s) for dipping.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.96', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.463');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb9d92ec-b48e-4981-81a6-b5c4c0af1199', 'Toss strawberries and sugar in medium bowl to blend. Let stand at room temperature until juices form, tossing occasionally, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.463');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2946cc07-72ef-43dc-bd35-dea80c1e99b9', 'Bring water to boil in heavy large Dutch oven over high heat. Mix in paprika and cumin; season lightly with salt and pepper. Add turnip and carrot. Cover and cook 2 minutes. add zucchini, celery and potatoes. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes. Cook uncovered until tomatoes soften, about 2 minutes. Drain vegetable, reserving cooking liquid. Transfer vegetables to medium bowl and cover with foil to keep warm. Return cooking liquid to same pot and boil until reduced to 1 1/2 cups, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.464');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('69979685-ca7e-4b7f-b586-71577edb74ff', 'Meanwhile, bring 4 1/2 cups vegetable broth and oil to boil in heavy large skillet. Mix in couscous; cover skillet. Remove from heat and let stand until couscous softens and absorbs broth, about 10 minutes. Fluff couscous with fork. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.971', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.464');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23dc96ea-5686-42bf-b03d-ef75749396ba', 'Mound couscous on large platter. Top with vegetables. Drizzle sauce over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.975', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.465');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf05f0a1-0c9b-4346-80b5-b45d854aa474', 'Stir together juices in a pitcher and add ice (if desired).', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.978', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.465');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2421eeed-1e43-4449-9dcc-06a98dd6694d', 'Preheat the oven to 400°F. Sprinkle a pinch of cinnamon, if using, on each apricot half and place flesh down on a glass baking dish. Pour in the water and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until the flesh is very soft when pierced with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.982', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.465');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6e049bb-d81a-4aa8-bef1-edc1e9b29e1a', 'Remove the skin from the flesh with a knife. Using a handheld immersion blender, a blender, or a food processor, puree the fruit and add some or all of the pan juices until the desired consistency is reached. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.986', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.466');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68a8310f-079c-4344-9765-0eeaa9e09480', 'Place coleslaw mix and cilantro in large bowl. Whisk canola oil, lime juice, salt, and pepper in medium bowl to blend. Add to cabbage mixture; toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.99', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.466');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c110b0a5-e76d-4ec6-b762-bc4556644640', 'Whisk first 6 ingredients in large bowl to blend. Add vegetables and olives. Toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep refrigerated. Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:25.993', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.466');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4f2bafe5-a02b-4370-ad12-5d6cb024a345', 'Transfer mixture to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.001', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.467');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7314b7d-372c-4086-a45b-63ffb2168057', 'Prepare a grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.005', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.468');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63563684-7cf6-4ace-88d6-dd823644a82f', 'Grill the pineapple slices for 2 minutes per side, or until tender and grill-marked. Transfer the slices to a cutting board and chop them. Put the chopped pineapple in a medium bowl and stir in the cilantro, serrano chile, and lime juice. Season the salsa to taste with sugar, salt, and pepper. Serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.008', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.469');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c03f1a92-1103-46ca-9e66-76d915b6fe69', 'Combine red cabbage, parsley and capers in large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.012', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.469');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee1e729e-be61-4775-8fbd-ccd1dee824d1', 'Whisk oil, vinegar, 2 tablespoons water and garlic in small bowl to blend. Add to cabbage mixture and toss to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared up to 3 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.016', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.47');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f511d84-6b10-42a5-bdd0-d442b44fb5bb', '2. Heat the oil in a large skillet over high heat until hot. Reduce the heat to medium-high; add the sweet potatoes and cumin and sauté, stirring constantly, until the potatoes are almost tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Add the chipotle, pepitas, and salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 2 minutes more or until the sweet potatoes are tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.025', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.47');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('54da3456-de8c-4c72-aa04-d31feb7fa995', 'Halve carrots lengthwise, then cut diagonally into 2-inch pieces. Cook carrots in a 4- to 6-quart pot of boiling salted water until just tender, 5 to 6 minutes. Drain in a colander and transfer to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. Let stand 5 minutes, then drain again and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.029', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.471');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15705abc-a1d2-46d3-be9a-961a53d6f4d8', 'While carrots cool, stir together cilantro, onion, oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.033', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.471');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f1b98be-cdae-4327-bb15-42cd11195309', 'Quarter avocado lengthwise, then peel and pit. Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and add to dressing along with carrots. Toss to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.037', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.472');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a1beeb6-d9e7-4323-8181-5f67375bf897', 'Bring water, rice, lime juice, cilantro, and salt to boil in a small saucepan. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 20 minutes Discard cilantro before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.041', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.472');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('847d61bb-ae93-4898-9422-72ad8cc07ae0', 'Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain. Transfer pasta to medium bowl; toss with 1 tablespoon oil and parsley. Season generously with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 1 hour ahead. Let pasta stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.474');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fd9524fc-657e-406c-a8c0-a2eba4ed84c8', 'Lightly oil large plate. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy medium skillet over medium heat. Add pasta to skillet, spreading evenly, flattening top, and pressing down with spatula to compress. Cook until brown and crisp, about 3 minutes. Carefully invert cake onto prepared plate. Return skillet to medium heat. Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Slide noodle cake into skillet and cook until brown and crisp on bottom, about 3 minutes. Transfer cake to cutting board, cut into wedges, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.048', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.474');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe2405a2-7488-425d-9a37-da0eeab08888', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange onions on a rimmed baking sheet and roast, shaking baking sheet halfway through, until the innermost layers of largest onions are just tender (some of the onions will be jammy and others will have some bite to them), 30–40 minutes. If you have one, a cake tester is a great tool to check doneness.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.052', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.476');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('048c3231-bbe6-419b-adfb-4ca73005ab67', 'Transfer onions to a clean surface and let cool slightly. Halve through root ends and remove papery layers. Separate layers into individual petals and transfer to a platter or a large bowl. Drizzle with oil and vinegar and toss gently to coat; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.057', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.476');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('911afbfe-84a9-43fe-ad09-fdba945832ee', 'Whisk all ingredients in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.061', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.477');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('84fe54e2-9766-4732-b5b3-8291d7aa7fcf', 'DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.065', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.478');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff92139e-fb1c-45b6-9760-f779d6fd9336', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Cut eggplant in half lengthwise, then score flesh in crisscross pattern at 1-inch intervals, 1/2 inch deep. Rub cut sides with 1 1/2 tablespoons oil; sprinkle with salt. Place eggplant on rimmed baking sheet, cut side down; bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Cool slightly, then scoop flesh into processor (discard skins). Add garbanzo beans, remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil, lemon juice, tahini, and garlic; puree until mixture is almost smooth. Transfer to bowl; stir in parsley. Season hummus to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.069', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.478');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f044026e-1010-40ec-928a-8c31fe74575e', 'In small bowl, whisk together lime juice, zest, salt, and pepper. Gradually whisk in oil, whisking until mixture emulsifies.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.073', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.479');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fdb1d766-1761-4ec7-9929-4c460d7fc930', 'In medium bowl, toss together jícama and 1/4 cup vinaigrette, reserving remaining vinaigrette. Let marinate while preparing rest of ingredients.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.076', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5054193e-1661-4297-94cd-491556c1a2d8', 'Using paring knife and working over large bowl to catch juice, remove peel and white pith from oranges, then cut between membranes to remove segments (discard membranes).', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.081', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce8a37df-20b4-4afb-9a1f-9458fd4bbf0d', 'To bowl with orange juice, add orange segments, jícama (including vinaigrette), and watercress. Toss well to combine. If desired, add additional vinaigrette, or reserve remainder for another use. Sprinkle with pumpkin seeds if using. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.084', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcfc205b-c3d5-4cb5-986f-73861bbbe6c4', 'Stir caraway seeds in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in oil and crushed red pepper. Add all peppers, onion, lemon peel and garlic. Increase heat to medium-high and sauté until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 7 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.088', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.481');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3966ab03-5c83-467a-ab97-ff66e255a6e0', 'Transfer pepper mixture to large bowl. Mix in dill. Cool. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.) Remove lemon peel. Mix in lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.091', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.482');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cb0571f-6b49-42d6-bf8d-c102f2817c71', 'Stack several collard leaf halves and roll up tightly into a cigar shape. Cut crosswise into very thin slices (no wider than 1/8 inch). Roll and slice remaining leaves in same manner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.095', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.482');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e8b9820-5b3d-46ae-a11f-40d09a1faba2', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté collards, tossing with tongs, just until bright green, about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.1', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.483');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d7a67369-a2a7-4a8b-ba0d-0dcab87504bd', 'Using vegetable peeler, remove peel (pink-yellow outer layer only) from 1 grapefruit in strips. Cut peel into 2-inch-long, 1/8-inch-wide strips (about 1/2 cup). Squeeze 1 cup juice from grapefruits.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.104', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.484');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c9500ce-cf0c-4089-9e78-6d6acb35843f', 'Stir 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water in medium saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add grapefruit peel; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer until peel is soft, about 15 minutes. Add 1 cup grapefruit juice and cranberries; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until berries burst, about 10 minutes. Transfer to medium bowl. Stir in mint. Cover; chill until cold. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 days ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.109', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.485');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fbb7990e-6bcd-426d-a02d-ca1c764cdeb3', 'Grate coconut in bowl. Add peeled and sectioned oranges; discard membrane and seeds. Add pineapple, fruit cocktail, apples, bananas, and nuts. Sweeten with sugar, being careful not to add too much as the syrup from the fruit is usually sufficient. Chill before serving. This dessert is pretty garnished with cherries and served in a crystal bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.112', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.485');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35aa6010-b840-4187-b7c3-c602f150718a', 'Whisk shallot, vinegar, orange juice, miso, ginger, and orange peel in medium bowl. Let stand 10 minutes to allow flavors to blend. Gradually whisk in oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.116', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.486');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fbbf2d3e-4996-4d84-aa40-a8b629a0c794', 'Mix cornmeal and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne in small bowl. Add okra and toss lightly to coat. Pour okra into sieve and shake off excess cornmeal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.882');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('64401365-88d8-4261-b592-844ea7062193', 'Toast coriander seeds in small skillet over medium heat until beginning to brown, about 2 minutes. Cool. Transfer to spice mill; process until coarsely ground. Add sesame seeds to same skillet. Toast over medium heat until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Add 3/4 teaspoon coarse salt; stir 30 seconds. Transfer sesame salt to small bowl and cool. DO AHEAD: Dressing and toasted spices can be made 1 day ahead.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.486');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c8af0b6-30f8-4139-aea3-4ef95d8bd1a0', 'Cover and chill dressing. Store toasted coriander and sesame salt in separate airtight containers at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.124', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.487');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa9d4afd-d359-468f-8332-fa827aa92e99', 'Using shredding disc on processor or a box grater, coarsely grate beets and carrots. Transfer vegetables to large bowl. Add enough dressing to coat lightly. Add coriander and 1 tablespoon sesame salt. Toss to coat. Let marinate at room temperature 30 minutes. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.128', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.488');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1ce90285-de50-406d-8e12-8ad7bf54d5c4', 'Toss salad, adding additional dressing, if desired. Sprinkle with remaining sesame salt and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.132', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.488');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8858ca61-68b7-4829-91da-ed3662bb336a', 'Cover rice with plenty of water in a large bowl and soak at room temperature at least 3 hours. Drain and put in a cheesecloth-lined steamer basket. Steam rice, covered, over boiling water until shiny and tender, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.136', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.489');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('90579dcf-c6cd-433a-a127-5bc110547556', '1. Put on a kettle of water to boil. Cut the onion into very thin slices or a mince and place it in a colander in the sink.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.14', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.489');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb5049da-8f16-417f-9f1b-ced4f6322373', '2. In a bowl large enough to comfortably fit all the onion, combine the vinegar, sweetener, and salt and whisk until blended.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.144', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.49');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0aa0e99-1ad1-45be-9a92-1a1c23246506', '3. Pour the boiling water over the onion and shake to drain. (It''s fine if a little water still clings.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.147', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.49');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eceee9a3-de11-4b55-873d-b43bc234370d', '4. Add the onion to the vinegar solution and stir to coat. Let it sit for at least an hour or up to several days, covered and refrigerated, occasionally stirring and/or shaking to allow maximum exposure to the liquid. Store in a jar with a tight-fitting lid in the refrigerator.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.151', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.491');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91e2f439-94b2-4895-820e-c70b5bf84031', 'For beautiful, exotic pickled fruit, add fresh or frozen cherries, blueberries, or raspberries—or some small watermelon chunks—to the onion after the first hour of sitting time * Add any of the following to the pickle mixture: Raw broccoli stems, peeled and cut into slender matchsticks * Raw fennel, cut into thin slices * Lightly steamed carrot slices * Lightly steamed cauliflower, cut into 1-inch florets', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.154', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.491');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49f76977-0a82-48e4-bd34-39775a057440', 'Whisk first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl. Add fruit and scallions; toss gently to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.16', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.492');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d158094d-ce82-4ce5-8120-695ff09b1f85', 'Using mandoline or V-slicer and working with 1 zucchini at a time, thinly slice lengthwise, discarding first strip. Slice up to seeded core; turn zucchini and continue to slice until only rectangle of seeded core remains; discard core. Place slices in medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.164', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.492');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46ac356b-4b84-4292-9708-c6d0930895a3', 'Add cucumber, onion, 1/2 of chopped mint, and lemon peel. Whisk lemon juice and pistachio oil in small bowl, then pour over zucchini mixture; toss to coat. Season with salt and generously with pepper. Cover zucchini mixture and refrigerate at least 1 hour and up to 3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.176', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('84dd562f-d290-4983-85bc-31b9b9135959', 'Sprinkle remaining chopped mint over salad and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.18', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f40943f-e4ca-4bf8-bbcc-e117ddc155ab', 'In a kettle of boiling salted water blanch the cabbage for 2 minutes and drain it. In the kettle, cleaned, cook the onion, the bay leaf, the thyme, the allspice berries, the garlic, and salt and pepper to taste in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until the onion is softened, add the cabbage, the apple, the wine, 1/4 cup of the vinegar, the sugar, and 3/4 cup water, and bring the liquid to a boil. Simmer the mixture, covered, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the cabbage is tender, discard the allspice berries, and add the currants. Simmer the mixture, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes more, or until most of the liquid has evaporated, discard the bay leaf and the garlic, and season the confit with salt and pepper and the additional vinegar. The confit may be made 2 days in advance, kept covered and chilled, and reheated just before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.187', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('604d3f60-a6ac-4065-92fb-08d487fc6356', 'In a 3-quart heavy saucepan stir together all ingredients except scallion and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork and stir in scallion.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.191', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9343296d-e7d0-468a-bec2-8eb17aa271c0', 'Cook onion with salt to taste in 3 tablespoons oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until deep golden and some wedges are crisp, 15 to 20 minutes. Meanwhile, stir together spices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.196', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48df3b50-6360-446f-a124-fc03e0819d30', 'Add cashews to onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until nuts are 1 shade darker, about 3 minutes. Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons spice mix and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Remove skillet from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.201', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6aeed5f6-e183-414c-a753-f6945c9af640', 'Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a 5-quart heavy pot over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then cook remaining spice mix, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Immediately stir in the 3 greens and water and cook, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid is evaporated and greens are tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.205', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f536ff3-0f8e-41da-a95f-08dd8b76819f', 'Serve greens sprinkled with onion mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.209', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4f9e25f7-1bbc-4807-8e3c-b162185678e6', 'In a large stockpot, combine the onion, garlic, celery, carrots, parsley, parsnip, peppercorns, bay leaves, and thyme with 4 qt/3.8 L water. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Uncover the pot and simmer for another 20 minutes to slightly reduce the stock to intensify the flavor. Remove from the heat and let cool for at least a half hour before straining. The stock can be refrigerated, covered, for up to 1 week and frozen for up to 1 year.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.213', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1618ea21-85cb-47f9-aba0-60efd255a94c', 'Rinse rice in several changes of cold water until water is clear, then drain well in a large fine-mesh sieve. Bring rice and water (3 3/4 cups) to a boil in a 4-quart wide heavy pot and boil, uncovered, without stirring, until steam holes appear in rice and grains on surface look dry, 5 to 7 minutes. Reduce heat to very low, then cover pot with a tight-fitting lid and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Gently fluff rice with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.221', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('845456aa-a370-499a-be5b-3ed43590c60b', 'Serve fruit with tsatsiki. Sprinkle with sea salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.083', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.09');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee172578-bfa5-46c6-a742-f948a7872c74', 'Purée cantaloupe with 3 tablespoons lemon juice in a blender until very smooth, about 2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and stir in cider and curry. Season with salt and additional lemon juice. Serve immediately, at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.225', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('232595a1-3640-4f0c-946e-6a5619c35373', 'In a food processor, purée mango, adding 1 tbsp water, if necessary, to achieve a puddinglike consistency. Add spices; blend thoroughly. Add sugar to taste. Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours. When ready to serve, cut watermelon in half. Using a melon baller, scoop out about 2 cups of balls. Pour purée into 4 shallow bowls and arrange melon balls on top. Garnish with mint sprigs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.229', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c4629a6f-6b73-4d21-9195-eca2118cdfd6', 'Preheat oven to 425°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.233', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9877c020-0f2c-4ee3-a932-5a2de52b3733', 'Toss squash and bell peppers with garlic, thyme, red pepper flakes, oil, and 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a 17- by 11-inch 4-sided sheet pan. Roast, stirring once, until vegetables are just tender and browned in spots, 25 to 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.237', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('519bb648-f360-45f8-88ce-2bdbdcb209ba', 'While vegetables finish roasting, cook linguine in a pasta pot of well-salted boiling water until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup cooking water, then drain pasta and return to pot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bced94e8-f66e-411a-9efb-0f9a576b6401', 'Remove sheet pan from oven and pour reserved water over vegetables, stirring to loosen from pan. Stir in olives, then add vegetable mixture to pasta in pot and toss to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.244', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c12fe42c-7b37-4e61-b4ca-daaa1d7bf5b5', 'Cut peel and white pith from oranges. Working over large bowl to catch juices and using small sharp knife, cut between membranes to release segments. Add strawberries, kiwis, 2 tablespoons orange juice, sugar and cinnamon to bowl; toss to blend. Chill at least 30 minutes and up to 3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.25', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a36ca5c9-0ebd-4bfe-8080-89563e95dd79', 'Divide compote among 8 bowls. Garnish with mint sprigs, if desired. Serve with Hazelnut-Cinnamon Biscotti.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.253', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e6c22045-d2b5-4af6-ab30-c8964db17486', 'Position 1 rack in bottom third of oven and 1 rack in center of oven and preheat to 400°F. Spray 2 heavy large baking sheets with nonstick spray. Combine all remaining ingredients except garlic in very large bowl; toss to coat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Divide vegetable mixture between prepared sheets. Place 1 sheet on each oven rack. Roast 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Reverse positions of baking sheets. Add 5 garlic cloves to each baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.257', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1f3cd71-efd7-4e89-ae5e-96f47ebfdc58', 'Continue to roast until all vegetables are tender and brown in spots, stirring and turning vegetables occasionally, about 45 minutes longer. (Can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Let stand on baking sheets at room temperature. Rewarm in 450°F oven until heated through, about 15 minutes.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.261', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.498');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3e8ce37-5f23-4a46-80fd-816ec2d3a428', 'Transfer roasted vegetables to large bowl and then serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.265', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.498');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('17719f56-d1e2-4acc-9468-a2ec62097607', 'Mince garlic and in a small dry skillet toast sesame seeds over moderate heat, stirring, until golden. In a heavy 6-quart kettle heat oil over moderate heat until hot but not smoking and cook garlic and gingerroot, stirring, 30 seconds, or until fragrant and golden. Add spinach by handfuls, stirring, and cook until just wilted.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.271', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.499');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3976c318-02cc-4c7c-9619-b1695e1c8a24', 'Serve spinach sprinkled with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.275', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('576f50c1-9e2a-4fd3-8b4d-77863b6440a3', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high. Add onion and 1/2 tsp. salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until caramelized, about 15 minutes. Stir in fennel and cook 30 seconds. Add beans, remaining 1 tsp. salt, and 2 Tbsp. water and heat through, stirring to combine. Transfer to a food processor or blender and purée until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.279', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0ba3714-34d9-4f6c-821d-a25659815d46', 'Bean spread can be stored in an airtight container and chilled for up to 3 days. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.283', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f34f15b5-9f4a-4734-aa2e-3e2a5e6bfb8f', 'Soak oats and chia seeds in coconut milk in a small bowl at least 10 minutes and up to overnight. Transfer to a blender and add avocado, ginger, mango, spinach, almond butter, and matcha. Puree until smooth, then divide among 2 bowls. Top with coconut, granola, and/or raspberries and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.291', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.501');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f2159f51-d404-4989-a5ef-4d2f431d21f7', 'In a bowl, combine the black rice, oranges, orange juice, pumpkin seeds, orange zest, salt, and chipotle. Gently mix in the avocado. Add more salt, if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.295', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.501');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81580e48-defd-4fd6-b926-e1aa9aeb4e93', 'Place a lettuce cup on each plate and spoon the salad into the lettuce cups. Garnish with orange wedges, if you wish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.299', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.501');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8b24f246-4c11-4418-a8d9-02134551be00', 'A very high-quality Chinese black rice is distributed by Lotus Foods under the registered trademark name "Forbidden Black Rice." This rice bleeds beet­red when you rinse it and, once cooked, ends up a striking deep burgundy. It holds its shape very well and is pleasantly chewy. With a subtle sweetness and a rich taste, it''s a stunning rice that has everything going for it. Put it high on your list of rices to try.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.303', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.501');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8f2c184-8ae0-4fca-b20c-d423e731fe71', 'Rinse the rice. Combine the rice, water, and salt (if using) in a heavy Dutch oven or saucepan. Over high heat, bring to a boil. Skim off any foam floating on the surface. Cover, reduce the heat, and simmer until the rice is tender, 30 to 35 minutes. Quickly drain off any excess water. Return the rice to the hot pot, cover, and let sit for 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.502');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a2228a5-e4d5-4bc5-a1f9-6cecaa7a48da', 'Preheat oven to 350°. Toast hazelnuts on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing occasionally, until golden brown, 8–10 minutes. Let cool, then chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.314', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.502');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ae185a09-83be-4c3b-b910-82959d7f8025', 'Meanwhile, toss rhubarb, sugar, Cointreau, and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Let sit until rhubarb is slightly softened and releases its juices, about 30 minutes. Toss with strawberries, mint, and hazelnuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.319', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.502');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eea7ab22-2a12-454a-97e6-c2d28ce86265', 'Purée celery, apple, water, lemon juice, and salt in a blender until smooth. Chill mixture in blender, covered, 1 hour. Reblend, then strain through a fine-mesh sieve. Soak bread in strained soup 3 minutes. Rinse blender and pulse almonds until finely ground. Add soup with bread and blend. Then, with motor running, add oil in a slow stream, blending until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.502');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d21173a9-a7a2-4045-96c0-cf4196609f3d', 'Preheat the oven to 375°F. Line 10 cups in a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners, or grease them well with coconut oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.327', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d0583437-724b-4800-9e27-9c05f61b32d2', 'In a large bowl, mix together the brown rice flour, almond flour, arrowroot, Sucanat, baking powder, and salt. Make a well in the center, then add the maple syrup, orange juice, orange zest, and vanilla. Gradually stir the dry ingredients into the wet ones, mixing just until blended. Stir in the almonds and coconut.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.331', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d19aa79-8883-4c69-89b8-62f691134cf2', 'Spoon the batter into the prepared cups, filling them two- thirds full, and smooth the top of each muffin. Bake for 12 to 16 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center of the muffins comes out clean. Cool the muffins in the pan set on a wire rack for at least 15 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.335', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7dd9d395-e420-460a-ba2b-12b5a749f836', 'Mix 1/4 cup oil and 4 tablespoons tarragon in bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Brush over both sides of bread. Toast bread in large skillet over medium heat until crisp, about 6 minutes per side. Transfer croutons to plate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.339', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f0cf156-3b58-4f77-95ed-d48ed5a9d12f', 'Meanwhile, heat 1/4 cup oil in another large skillet over medium heat. Add 4 cups tomatoes, next 3 ingredients, and 3 tablespoons tarragon. Sauté until vegetables just begin to soften, about 6 minutes. Stir in tomato paste. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover; cook until tomatoes and shallots are soft, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.343', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.504');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc9508c0-444f-4e8d-acbf-ca434a474d6e', 'Strain soup into bowl, pressing with rubber spatula to extract as much of the juice and solids as possible. Discard solids in sieve. Season soup with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.348', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.504');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b00eaac2-c250-4a84-b80a-a3a15cbc45af', 'Freeze soup just until cold, about 30 minutes. Ladle into bowls. Top with croutons; sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.352', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.504');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42e144e0-75a3-4f55-8bf9-d96ce59705b9', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray 9-inch round cake pan with 1 1/2-inch-high sides with vegetable oil spray. Line bottom of pan with parchment. Sift flour, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa powder, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt into large bowl. Whisk juice, oil and vinegar in medium bowl to blend. Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Using spatula, smooth top.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.356', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.504');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd474385-e41f-495f-a4a6-5896a01621c7', 'Bake until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan and tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Transfer pan to rack and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.36', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.504');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d0b7371f-be77-4c3f-ac3d-ba7abe4b7fb7', 'Using knife, cut around sides of pan to loosen cake. Turn cake out onto platter. Turn cake right side up. Sift powdered sugar over top. Cut into wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.363', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.505');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('874efcda-44b3-416e-a21b-628ef41594cc', 'Mix rhubarb, lemon rind and sugar in a bowl and let stand overnight. The next day, pour into a large pot, add lemon juice and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thickend. Pour into hot, sterilized jelly glasses. Cover with a thin layer of melted paraffin. When hardened, cover glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.37', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.505');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1da23bfe-a904-466c-be79-f6fa6f4d2805', 'Squeeze juice from lemon into bowl of cold water. Cut stem off 1 artichoke, leaving about 1 inch. Snap off bottom 3 rows of leaves. Cut off tip of artichoke. Halve artichoke lengthwise. Scrape out choke. Place in lemon water. Repeat with remaining artichokes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.374', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.505');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ccc71b5e-17dc-4ae9-9fee-c1f4600c9f9d', 'Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Add artichokes and boil until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes. Drain; pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.505');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e61db2f-40c2-4027-aff6-e070568a2404', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Mix oil and 1/3 cup lemon juice in small bowl. Brush artichokes with some of dressing. Grill until tender and charred in spots, about 5 minutes per side. Transfer to large bowl. Mix in dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer artichokes to platter. Pour dressing into small bowl. Serve artichokes warm or at room temperature, offering dressing alongside. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.382', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5dc4bd3-7a45-402d-9fdd-3a34a245093c', 'In a large pitcher stir together well the champagne, the cranberry juice cocktail and the Grand Marnier.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.387', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f35dc8ee-5b01-4afb-a332-23a2d3aa0894', 'Put bell peppers on rack of broiler pan about 5 inches from heat and broil, turning occasionally with tongs, until skins are blackened, about 15 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and let stand, covered, until cool enough to handle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d52b26ca-007d-4f1d-9baa-3c0ddc25ed70', 'Peel peppers over bowl (to catch any liquid) and discard stems and seeds. Cut peppers lengthwise into 1-inch-thick strips and add to liquid in bowl with vinegar, thyme, and capers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.397', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95edc920-1b2f-4440-827d-8f0a7d946ce8', 'Add salt and pepper to taste and toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.402', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5de588ec-bf5e-444d-b000-27b787d6a04b', 'Divide arugula among 4 plates. Top with peppers and drizzle with any remaining dressing. Serve at room temperature or chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.405', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3ab7f119-5fe4-44b9-9962-be819dd08d7f', 'Combine garlic (if using), chives, parsley, tarragon, oregano, lemon zest, and peppercorns in a small mixing bowl. Stir in salt and transfer herbed salt to a serving bowl. Pour oil into another small bowl. Serve radishes with oil and herbed salt for dipping.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.411', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b943625a-7b8c-4c1f-95fe-2611b4950e17', 'Puree watermelon in processor (there should be about 4 cups). Mix in sugar by tablespoonfuls to sweeten to taste. Pour into 2 to 3 ice cube trays. Rinse mint leaves and place 1 leaf atop puree in each cube. Cover and freeze until cubes are solid, at least 4 hours and up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.416', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02895774-fc84-4dd9-8d29-df8f8dba2c68', 'Stir juice and sugar in medium saucepan over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves. Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium; simmer until mixture is reduced to 3 cups, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Cool. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.42', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4250266-24f5-40a1-9b13-ea520a6ed493', 'Pulse onion, carrot, celery, whole garlic cloves, parsley, and red pepper flakes in a food processor until finely chopped; transfer to a small bowl and set aside. Wipe out food processor bowl and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.424', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.508');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8a8296c-d92e-4f6e-8517-39eddbe40eaa', 'Heat 1/4 cup oil in a large heavy pot over medium heat; add reserved vegetable mixture, season with salt, and cook, stirring often, until golden, 8-10 minutes. Stir tomato paste and 1 cup water in a small bowl to combine; add to pot. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until liquid has almost evaporated, 5-8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.43', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.508');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1943345f-8639-43fa-9e9d-c1319d38ab46', 'Add chickpeas and 2 cups water to pot and simmer for 15 minutes to let flavors meld. Transfer 1 cup chickpea mixture to food processor; purée until smooth, then stir back into sauce to thicken.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.434', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.508');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9005210b-5f50-4386-b4ce-834c890518ab', 'Meanwhile, cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water, stirring occasionally, until al dente. Drain pasta, reserving 1 1/2 cups pasta cooking liquid. Add pasta and 1/2 cup pasta cooking liquid to sauce and stir to coat. Increase heat to medium and continue stirring, adding more pasta cooking liquid as needed, until sauce coats pasta.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.438', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.508');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61402571-e1c5-4af9-ba6d-c7ffdeffd93d', 'Heat remaining 1/4 cup oil in a small saucepan over medium-low heat; add chopped garlic and rosemary and cook until sizzling stops, about 1 minute. Divide pasta among bowls and drizzle with garlic-rosemary oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.442', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1e5cd00-26b4-42b9-88db-d9ccf7b47ef0', 'Preheat oven to 425°. Toss brussels sprouts and 4 tablespoons oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with salt and pepper. Roast, tossing once, until softened (but not soft) and browned, 20-25 minutes. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.446', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('589d6498-f416-4338-8630-641a9a9998dd', 'Meanwhile, mix cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water in a small bowl until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.45', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('067b8d1c-1db7-4a2a-b8d1-c4e0e4f26044', 'Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in a medium saucepan over medium-high. Add garlic and ginger and cook, stirring often, until garlic is golden brown, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.454', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81c9091c-9b75-4aa6-90af-a9491e69f9bd', 'Add chili paste and cook, stirring, until darkened, about 2 minutes. Add chiles, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar, and 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil; stir in cornstarch slurry. Simmer, stirring, until sauce coats spoon, about 2 minutes. Let cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.458', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.51');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d32c2bd-d322-4f85-acdc-29d673fea6de', 'Toss brussels sprouts with sauce and serve topped with peanuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.462', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.51');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('494c4bc9-c4bd-4711-927c-dea31a45f18f', 'Preheat oven to 250°. Whisk first 6 ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon salt in large bowl. Whisk coconut milk, 1 1/4 cups warm water, 2 tablespoons maple syrup, and vanilla in medium bowl. Whisk coconut milk mixture into dry ingredients until batter is pourable.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.465', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.51');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22f24af0-9777-45c3-a007-9fa56058543a', 'Heat griddle or skillet over medium-high heat; brush with vegetable oil. Working in batches, add batter by 1/4 cupfuls. Working quickly and using back of spoon, spread each pancake to about 4-inch round. Cook until small bubbles appear on surface and bottoms of pancakes are golden, reducing heat if browning too quickly, 2 to 3 minutes. Turn over; cook until golden, 1 to 2 minutes. Transfer to baking sheet. Keep warm in oven.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.469', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.51');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7ffcf32-33b8-4afc-bd02-19f3c0316164', 'Place 2 to 3 pancakes on each plate. Top with tropical fruit salad, maple syrup, and chopped pistachios.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.473', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.511');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18b51ac3-83a4-485b-a708-f1d340dba72d', 'Pick through the beans to remove any dirt or stones, then place in a large colander and rinse thoroughly. Transfer the beans to a large bowl, cover with 3 quarts of water, and soak overnight in the refrigerator.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.477', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.511');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f596c9c3-828e-414f-baa6-2cf941d6418f', 'Drain the beans, reserving the liquid. Measure the liquid and add water, if needed, to make 2 1/2 quarts. Place the beans in a stockpot or large clay olla. Add the onion, garlic, oil or lard, and the reserved soaking liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.48', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.511');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e64a337-b717-4aaa-91af-66c1dd5a4519', 'Bring to a simmer, adjusting the heat to maintain a gentle simmer. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the beans are tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Keep the beans covered with 1 inch of water as they cook, adding boiling water if needed. Remove the onion and garlic and season to taste with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.484', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.511');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a201f9ba-35ea-4369-b60c-6b3d303ece12', 'Put bread, brushed with 2 tablespoons oil and seasoned with salt and pepper, on a baking sheet. Broil 2 minutes per side. Rub with cut garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.512');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f563634-5fca-49f3-b2de-3101324ac95b', 'Cook broccoli rabe in boiling salted water until tender, 5 to 6 minutes. Drain well. Wipe pot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.494', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.512');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2b317c9-468e-4994-a97a-bcaf781eff1d', 'Cook garlic and pepper flakes in remaining 1/4 cup oil over medium heat, stirring, 2 minutes. Add broccoli rabe, 3 tablespoons water, and salt and cook, covered, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.498', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.513');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4438251a-aaef-4c7f-868a-1ff6d1431e83', 'Spoon topping onto each toast.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.501', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.514');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf72c7eb-d1b8-4320-96d5-12563f2b6b91', 'Heat butter in a 6- to 8-quart wide heavy pot over moderately high heat until foam subsides, then cook onion and cabbage, stirring frequently, until wilted and slightly browned, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.505', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.515');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c984a419-1b84-4667-82b2-739f2cbf18e5', 'Add wine, water, vinegars, apple, sugar, and salt and bring to a boil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.515');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('283a2230-8557-4ceb-bc59-7a8d5f086962', 'Wrap peppercorns, cloves, and bay leaf in cheesecloth and tie with string. Add to cabbage mixture, then cover cabbage directly with a round of parchment or wax paper and cover pot with lid. Reduce heat and simmer until cabbage is very tender, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.514', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('519bc5ea-a2f9-4931-9460-1c846c02b408', 'Discard cheesecloth bundle and season cabbage with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.518', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77a25295-9b5f-4fb6-acb2-6a49129ebf5a', 'Cook sugar, water and cloves in heavy small saucepan over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and bring to boil. Add cranberries. Simmer until cranberries are soft but still retain shape, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes. Cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.522', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4f496fa-2fe2-4ad1-bede-a4603b42bcf0', 'Bring marmalade, Grand Marnier, orange peel and brandy to boil in heavy medium saucepan. Boil until mixture registers 220°F. (jelly stage) on candy thermometer, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.526', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b70a6350-f4c8-4d74-abf6-9155859ba134', 'Using slotted spoon, transfer cranberries from cooking liquid to marmalade (discard liquid). Mix gently. Spoon into four 1-cup jelly jars. Seal tightly. Cool completely. (Can be prepared 4 weeks ahead. Refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.53', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.517');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af7c8688-bc37-4f83-ba32-ba4c3a64b07a', 'Heat oven to 350°F. In a bowl, whisk 5 teaspoons olive oil with 5 teaspoons pure maple syrup and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper. Stir in 1 tablespoon chopped fresh rosemary and 2 teaspoons chopped fresh thyme. Add 2 cups walnut halves; toss well to coat. Spread evenly on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake until fragrant and crisp, 10 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon chopped fresh thyme and 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.534', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.518');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('000639c1-a8a9-4870-a1b6-0529ec99ea3c', 'Separate garlic head into cloves, discarding loose papery outer skin but keeping skin intact on cloves, and wrap in foil, crimping seams to seal tightly. Roast garlic in middle of oven 30 minutes, or until soft. Unwrap garlic and cool slightly. Peel skins from each clove and in a bowl with a fork mash garlic pulp until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.538', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.519');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a29710ce-c9f2-4287-9054-474e4c84fe9b', 'Rinse and drain enough beans to measure 1 cup, reserving remainder for another use, and add to garlic. Cut 2 tomatoes into 1/4-inch dice and add to beans. Quarter remaining tomato and in a blender or food processor puree until smooth. Add puree to bean mixture. Finely chop onion and basil and add to bean mixture with lemon juice, tossing to combine. Season salsa with salt and pepper. Salsa may be made 1 hour ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.542', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.521');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71b58535-0ebc-49a0-91f6-a5f501569901', 'Whisk together shallot, mustard, and vinegar. Add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified, and season with salt and pepper. Just before serving, toss salad greens with just enough dressing to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.546', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.521');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c94dae9d-db9c-48fb-b152-1235b25295f8', 'Preheat oven to 250°F. Line large rimmed baking sheet with foil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.55', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.521');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('678e008b-f0f5-44fa-aee4-e03aaa5a261b', 'Spoon compote into shallow bowls or wine glasses. Top with sorbet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:34.46', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c979113f-931e-4b94-957e-9b7336dc0ef6', 'In large bowl, stir together olive oil, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Dip tomato halves into oil, shake off excess, and arrange on baking sheet, cut sides down. Roast until skins are wrinkled and beginning to brown, about 2 hours. (Tomatoes can be roasted ahead and refrigerated, covered, up to 2 days. Bring to room temperature before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.553', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.522');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('990a7f7e-95b5-49eb-bd75-87562f18ae85', 'In large bowl, whisk together remaining 1/2 cup olive oil, vinegar, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Add arugula and tomatoes and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.557', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.522');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94776f49-e3f4-44f5-84a5-68dc5dff182f', 'Cook broccoli rabe in boiling salted water until just tender, about 4 minutes. Drain and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.561', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.523');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('917bef99-93e4-4ad5-91fa-3f6a9ff02f40', 'Combine 1/4 cup water and fresh ginger in heavy medium saucepan. Cover; simmer until ginger is tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in syrup, whiskey, lemon juice, lemon peel and nutmeg. Simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover; chill. Bring to simmer before continuing.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.566', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.523');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('08c68da8-ba20-4d71-ae84-43d710415aa8', 'Slice pears into rounds. Overlap 6 rounds on each plate. Drizzle sauce over. Top with crystallized ginger and mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.57', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.524');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c949d80-5a01-4f0f-a9ea-ebaf5ef67570', 'Whisk first 5 ingredients in medium bowl to blend. Add strawberries; toss. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or chill up to 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.575', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.524');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8b348603-9cf9-42bc-9b77-c075960796d0', 'Combine bulgur and boiling-hot water in a large bowl and let stand 20 minutes. Fluff with a fork and stir in herbs, oil, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.581', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.525');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14bbd53b-67b8-490a-ace6-b99d03ba9873', 'Divide asparagus into 4 bunches. Align each bunch in a flat row and thread 2 skewers crosswise through each bunch (see photo, above). Brush asparagus with oil and season with kosher salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.585', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.525');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dc3e41fe-25b0-4999-a797-4659b624f7ef', 'Grill asparagus on an oiled rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals until tender, 3 to 5 minutes on each side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.526');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cfcf4d55-5887-42c4-ada0-19d9c1f2deeb', 'Preheat the oven to 350°F. Pierce the sweet potatoes with a fork and bake until tender, 30 to 40 minutes. While they''re baking, make the sauce. In a saucepan over medium-low heat, combine the orange juice, water, ginger, miso, soy sauce, garlic, and brown sugar. Cook until the sauce reduces and is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon, about 15 minutes. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.593', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.526');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3cd2f6cb-733c-49eb-b8d8-fd3403e55011', 'When the sweet potatoes are cool enough to touch, slice them in half lengthwise and lay them face up on a sheet pan. Spoon the sauce over the flesh of the potatoes, sprinkle with the sesame seeds, and broil until the sesame seeds are toasted.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.597', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.527');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcc03fb1-da1e-484c-801d-c64621312d28', 'Heat oven to 350°. In a medium saucepan, warm 4 teaspoons vegetable oil over medium-low heat. Add 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon dark brown sugar, 4 teaspoons water, 1 1/2 teaspoons five-spice powder, 1/4 teaspoon ground cumin and 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper; stir until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles. Add 2 cups pecan halves; cook, stirring, until pecans are thickly coated, about 3 minutes. Spread evenly on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt. Bake until fragrant and crisp, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.601', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.527');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee38c88c-a92c-4e1e-88d9-4d5f5f3b2d73', 'Gently combine all the ingredients in a bowl. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use, up to 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.605', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.528');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('255c6b93-a9ca-4fee-8275-68312b52be25', 'Place berries, wine and 4 tablespoons sugar in blender; puree. Pour into medium saucepan. Add cloves, bay leaves, and allspice. Bring to simmer, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.619', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.528');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6024c6c-f8ef-4529-aafd-d0edbf3e15fd', 'Strain into medium bowl. Discard solids in strainer. Whisk in brandy; sweeten with remaining sugar, if desired. (Can be made 5 days ahead. Cover and chill. Rewhisk before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.623', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.532');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4afa1cf0-58b7-40c3-b770-e936b47deb92', 'Use a vegetable peeler to remove the peel from the lemon in vertical strips. Try to remove only the yellow zest, avoiding as much of the white pith as possible. Save the lemon for another use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.627', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.532');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6746348f-7418-4028-b4db-aaf360ebb7aa', 'In a small saucepan, combine the peels with 2 cups cold water. Bring to a boil, then drain off the water. Again add 2 cups cold water, bring to a boil, and drain. Repeat the process a third time, then remove the peels from the pan and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.631', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.533');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b562fef-d480-4031-b002-39a6b1a39fb2', 'Measure 2 cups of the sugar into the pan and add 1 cup water, whisking until the sugar dissolves. Add the peels and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, until the peels are tender and translucent, 10 to 15 minutes. Drain the peels and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.635', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.533');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9a732e4-f536-476a-9d90-6e33ee6ea84e', 'Measure the remaining 1/2 cup sugar into a medium bowl and add the peels. Toss to coat. Using a fork or your fingers, remove the peels one at time, gently shaking each to remove excess sugar. Store in an airtight container. The peels will keep for several weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.64', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.534');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0226339c-390d-4d0b-ba15-3fa1ffd3cce8', 'Puree beans, garlic, 3 tablespoons olive oil, and lemon juice in processor. Add 3 tablespoons oil, sugar, and cumin. Puree until very smooth, about 1 1/2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl. Cover; chill at least 1 hour. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.644', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.534');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea8ae8c9-9876-4d4b-9b6d-b98a2a200c77', 'Cut tops off onions. Cut tops lengthwise into thin strips; cut strips into 2-inch pieces. Chop half of onion bottoms. Place remaining bottoms in blender; add vinegar and ginger. Puree, occasionally scraping down sides of blender jar. Strain puree into measuring cup, pressing enough solids through to yield 1/2 cup dressing; season with pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.647', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.535');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0fe9c60-ab5b-418e-95fb-e946b1bf65ea', 'Place carrots and cranberries in large bowl. Add onion tops and bottoms. Toss with enough dressing to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.651', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.535');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b831293e-d50a-4819-9c72-e318e1d64f1e', 'Prick eggplant in 3 places and coat lightly with additional oil. In a shallow baking dish roast eggplant in middle of oven, turning once, 1 hour, or until collapsed and soft, particularly at stem end. Cool eggplant slightly and halve lengthwise. Scoop out flesh into a bowl and cool. Discard liquid that accumulates in bowl and in a food processor purée eggplant. Eggplant purée may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Bring purée to room temperature before proceeding with recipe.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.656', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.536');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4be40542-8dd8-44bb-971e-f8f84f00f0bf', 'Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain pasta. Rinse under cold water and drain again. Transfer to large bowl. Mix in 2 tablespoons vinaigrette.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.77', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.554');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('842efe1c-efed-4322-aaab-448d71cb429e', 'Serve eggplant steaks topped with vegetable ragout.', '2023-06-12 17:13:34.552', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.653');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b9ee5edd-0b59-494e-a5a8-a78211d4a5b9', 'In a large heavy skillet, cook onion in 2 tablespoons oil over moderate heat, stirring until softened. Add garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add bell peppers, zucchini, squash, thyme and salt and pepper to taste and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 8 to 10 minutes. Add tomato and cook, stirring, 3 minutes. In a bowl, stir together eggplant purée, vegetable mixture and parsley and season with salt and pepper. Dip may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.536');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0d8a7306-3e10-4584-8b7d-f7ddbb6e80f0', 'Serve dip at room temperature with toast or crackers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.666', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.537');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35e4a41c-b643-49b4-b5ea-bb1ff2b3934f', 'Wash rice in several changes of cold water in a bowl until water is almost clear. Soak rice in cold water 30 minutes, then drain well in a sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.669', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.537');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39663e39-9d72-4ad4-9e36-75749f134858', 'Spread coconut in a shallow baking pan and toast in oven, stirring occasionally, until pale golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.673', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.539');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef9fb7c6-1c90-4821-9c14-66c14ad4701b', 'Cook ginger and jalapeño in 1 tablespoon oil in a 4-quart heavy pot over moderate heat, stirring, until chile is softened, about 2 minutes. Add rice and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Stir in water and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil, covered. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 12 to 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.54');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3596550a-c06a-46f2-a379-5a2dc68ef56e', 'Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork and transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.68', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.541');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8380874e-34b7-4776-a4b2-e3c717dd9fbb', 'While rice cooks, pulse together coconut, cilantro, scallions, and remaining 2 tablespoons oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a food processor until finely chopped.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.684', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.541');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('394ac346-b9bf-4173-9acb-944d73a49666', 'Add cilantro mixture to cooked rice and stir gently until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.688', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.542');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('580b8302-4022-4774-b36e-8756d322f218', 'In a large deep skillet cook the onion and the garlic in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until the onion is softened, add the zucchini, the yellow squash, the bell pepper, and the corn, and cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, for 4 minutes. Add the tomatoes, the oregano, and salt and pepper to taste and simmer the stew, covered, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Simmer the stew, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes more, or until the excess liquid is evaporated, sprinkle it with the basil, and serve it warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.692', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.542');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71cbed55-26bf-4955-893e-8aaf36e8aca2', 'Preheat oven to 500°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.696', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.543');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bfa8b012-ac01-4632-ba2e-f4cb39cadb8b', 'Peel potatoes and halve lengthwise, then cut each half lengthwise into 4 wedges. Transfer to a shallow baking pan and toss with oil to coat. Combine salt and spices and sprinkle over potatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.701', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.543');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0844eaef-7971-4c74-ae2b-dc60756a9081', 'Roast potatoes in lower third of oven, turning over halfway through roasting, until tender and browned, 15 to 20 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.704', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.544');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('41d7365d-2031-4330-ad78-452fdb3955cb', 'Combine olives and lemon juice in medium bowl. Let marinate at least 3 hours at room temperature, tossing occasionally. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.709', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.546');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('078efb45-fa4a-4b7c-b390-e4fb8a1a1e4c', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium heat. Add onions and sauté 5 minutes. Add potatoes, paprika, black pepper, cayenne pepper, and olives with lemon juice; stir to blend. Add 1 1/2 cups water and bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Mix in tomatoes. Simmer uncovered until flavors blend, about 10 minutes longer. Season stew with salt. Transfer to bowl. Garnish with lemon wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.712', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.547');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ecd63da2-c6b1-4365-b2dd-7da350c6c782', 'Prick eggplant with a fork several times and on a baking sheet rub with just enough oil to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.717', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.547');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('221eccdd-71a2-431c-a03b-381e1280932c', 'Cut off and discard top quarter of garlic head to expose cloves and set garlic in middle of a large piece of foil. Drizzle garlic with 1 teaspoon oil and enclose completely in foil. Place foil packet next to eggplant on baking sheet and roast in middle of oven, turning eggplant after 30 minutes, 45 to 50 minutes, or until eggplant is very soft and collapsed. Unwrap garlic carefully and cool eggplant and garlic on baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.721', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.548');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff17ad2d-6278-4cb6-9745-6981756fd404', 'Transfer eggplant to cutting board. Cut off and discard stem end and halve eggplant lengthwise. Scoop flesh out into a bowl, scraping as close to skin as possible. Pour off any liquid accumulated in bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.725', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.549');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8c42566-9d3d-4ec9-a3fb-d6122f7748b2', 'Squeeze roasted garlic from skins into a food processor. Add eggplant, lemon juice, tahini, parsley, and salt to taste and blend until smooth and parsley is minced fine. Dip may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.549');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('07e64bab-0b4f-4382-a229-7ae98c485330', 'Transfer dip to a bowl and serve with pita wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.734', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.55');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cc96693-83f7-4c29-b6c9-b1aa1eab2251', 'Cut figs into 1-inch pieces. Boil cider with figs and remaining ingredients, uncovered, until it is slightly syrupy and figs are plump, about 20 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.551');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ab569b2-f32b-4694-ae74-de8ab7b63e4d', 'In a large saucepan of boiling salted water cook beans until-crisp-tender, about 6 minutes, and drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.745', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.551');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dfa9731e-812e-4986-ac13-82c022c3a04e', 'Serve green beans with mustard sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.749', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.552');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcabc3dc-6e42-429f-b8e0-a87827d5dada', 'In a bowl whisk together mustard, sugar, and vinegar until sugar is dissolved and whisk in oil until sauce is emulsified. Whisk in water to thin sauce to the desired consistency. Sauce may be made 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled. Serve sauce at room temperature. Makes 1 1/2 cups.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.753', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.552');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aee10b95-3c0a-464f-ba0a-6047a93eb9c0', 'Stir all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and boil until syrup is reduced to 1 1/2 cups, about 20 minutes. Refrigerate until cold. Cover and keep refrigerated up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.757', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.553');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46fe3bca-e095-49ec-a6f9-324dbd1a103e', 'Using a vegetable peeler, remove the peel from 1 orange and the lemon. Transfer to a large punch bowl and add the sugar. Muddle to release the citrus oils, then let stand 1 to 2 hours. Add the lemon and pineapple juices and the bourbon, and stir to combine. Just before serving, stir in 3 to 4 cups of ice, then top with Champagne or sparkling wine and garnish with the orange slices and pineapple chunks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.761', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.553');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53ac1d52-22d3-4ab7-a605-dd9c70585ee3', 'Blend parsley, vinegar and garlic in processor until parsley is finely chopped, scraping down sides of bowl twice. With machine running, gradually add 1/2 cup olive oil. Season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.765', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.554');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef62c34e-241a-4cb5-b1ac-ff13cdef5d9a', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Place smoke chips in 8x6-inch foil packet with open top. Set packet atop coals about 5 minutes before grilling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.774', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.555');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b225d12-2ad6-41c6-ad72-d44d2378b45d', 'Brush corn, zucchini and onion with remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill vegetables until cooked through and beginning to brown, turning often, about 12 minutes. Cool slightly. Cut kernels from corncobs. Cut zucchini and onion into 1/2-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.78', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.556');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6336a516-a899-4544-aef4-aedb8be1ce14', 'Add corn kernels, zucchini and onion to pasta in large bowl. Mix in enough vinaigrette to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 8 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.785', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.556');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf608e12-514c-4d32-9e32-c9eda6f59f6b', 'Stir all the ingredients in a slow cooker until the maple syrup has dissolved and all the grains are moistened. Cover and cook on low for 6 hours, or until the porridge is creamy and the grains are tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.79', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.557');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e66680fb-2254-4afc-8984-e6ef8edde82f', 'Cook garlic in oil in a 2- to 3-quart wide heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until golden, 1 to 2 minutes. Add water and salt and bring to a boil. Stir in remaining ingredients, then cover pan and remove from heat. Let stand, undisturbed, 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.793', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.557');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4256da2-33af-441e-8168-d26a107ab410', 'Heat oven to 375°F. Combine cumin seeds with bay leaf and paprika in a spice mill or clean coffee grinder and process briefly. Add sugar and salt and process to combine. Set aside. Toss squash with oil, then cumin mixture. Spread on 2 baking sheets and roast until tender, about 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.8', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.558');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04877318-c446-4cd3-b596-c504ddddb941', '1. Place sugar in an ovenproof shallow pan and warm in a 250°F (120°C) oven for 15 minutes. (Warm sugar dissolves better.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.804', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.558');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cbf9f103-1126-4b5d-94c0-5ffe77ff9d57', '2. Place berries in a large stainless steel or enamel saucepan. Bring to a full boil over high heat, mashing berries with a potato masher as they heat. Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.809', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.559');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3dd341e1-24dd-4178-80b6-0f799a8a6a16', '3. Add warm sugar, return to a boil, and boil until mixture will form a gel (see tips, below), about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.813', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.562');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d44ff404-4ca4-4b9e-a3ad-c235beb18512', 'Tip: To make a small boiling-water canner, tie several screw bands together with string or use a small round cake rack in the bottom of a large covered Dutch oven. Be sure the pan is high enough for 2 inches (5 cm) of water to cover the jars when they are sitting on the rack.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.82', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.562');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d93dbf7e-c3c7-4ede-89ea-eac0eeae15e1', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss eggplant with 2 teaspoons salt in large bowl. Turn eggplant out onto paper towels and let drain 30 minutes. Pat eggplant dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.825', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.562');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad6fa7bf-39fe-43e2-ae81-f76745ac8f04', 'Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat to 350°F. Working in batches, add eggplant to oil; cook until golden, turning occasionally, about 6 minutes per batch. Using slotted spoon, transfer to clean paper towels. Reserve 5 tablespoons eggplant frying oil. Toss shallots and whole bell pepper with 3 tablespoons reserved oil on large baking sheet. Roast until shallots are tender, turning occasionally, about 25 minutes. Place shallots and eggplant in large bowl. Continue roasting bell pepper until skin blackens, about 10 minutes. Wrap in plastic bag; let stand 10 minutes. Peel, core and seed pepper. Cut into thin strips lengthwise, then cut strips crosswise in half. Add bell pepper strips, olives and garlic to eggplant and shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.83', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.563');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b1289318-f29c-4d44-ae02-09b9d171c25c', 'Cook artichokes in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, turning occasionally, about 40 minutes. Using tongs, transfer to bowl; cool. Remove leaves from artichokes and reserve for another use. Scoop out chokes. Cut artichoke hearts into 1/3-inch pieces; combine with other vegetables. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.835', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.565');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6cd80a68-1832-4c76-9886-1a95615c5a17', 'Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain. Return pasta to pot. Add all vegetables and remaining 2 tablespoons reserved eggplant frying oil and toss over medium heat until heated through. Season with salt and pepper. Divide pasta among plates and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.841', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.565');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a7c6874-c5b8-4892-b8a2-f822f7cf5bfb', 'In a blender purée shallot, ginger, and garlic with rice vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil, and Tabasco. With motor running add olive oil in a stream and blend until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.566');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee81bf3c-e492-4857-adca-cf9036f1f69c', 'In separate bowls toss carrots with half of the dressing and beets with remaining half. Divide carrot salad and beet salad among 6 plates and garnish with spinach leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.849', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.566');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4de8826f-d939-445c-bc23-ed567d171d33', 'Purée about two thirds each of honeydew, cucumber, and lime juice in 2 batches in a blender until very smooth, transferring to a pitcher.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.854', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.567');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('858a6157-a19a-469c-a896-b18cfe7890a2', 'Purée remaining honeydew, cucumber, and lime juice in blender until very smooth, then add ice and sorbet and blend until smooth. Add mint and a pinch of salt and pulse until mint is finely chopped. Stir into purée in pitcher.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.567');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4be7a200-1f4a-42cc-89c8-6576224e1096', 'Stir together coconut, cumin, coriander, cayenne, turmeric, chile, garlic, 1/4 cup water, and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.866', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.568');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6462737f-c4ac-4aa3-a2e1-09b2bf4fe74f', 'Heat oil in a wok or 12-inch heavy skillet (not nonstick) over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then cook mustard seeds and red pepper flakes until mustard seeds begin to pop and/or turn gray. Add curry leaves (if using), covering skillet immediately as they crackle for a few seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.87', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.568');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef57d327-a983-4a3b-bc97-7a891964bc8d', 'Add green beans and corn and stir-fry 8 minutes. Add coconut mixture and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender, 8 to 10 minutes. If mixture becomes dry and begins to stick to bottom of wok, add a few tablespoons water. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.875', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.569');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6256e81e-1ff6-4314-a713-cbd52e74c1cb', 'Peel mango and cut flesh from pit. Cut mango into 1/4-inch dice and transfer to a small bowl. Halve and seed cucumber. Cut cucumber into 1/4-inch dice and add to mango. Stir in remaining ingredients until combined well and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.88', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.569');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e53a32eb-7935-40f1-8f37-1e73d19ae375', 'Crush saffron, if using, with the handle of a wooden spoon (or crush between your fingers) in a small bowl until a powder forms. Add 1 Tbsp. hot water. Swirl gently; set aside to steep.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.884', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.57');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7dc11660-d0c1-464d-b7c4-7d916993c71b', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a large pot over medium-high. Add almonds, cinnamon, cayenne, and 1/4 tsp. salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until toasted and fragrant, about 2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer almonds to a small bowl; reserve oil in pot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.888', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.57');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78bee7a0-f0f1-4754-b1bc-a5c4374f6398', 'Heat oil in pot over medium-high. Add onion and remaining 2 Tbsp. oil and 1 1/2 tsp. salt, reduce heat to medium, and cook until onion is light brown and translucent, about 5 minutes. Add quinoa and cook, tossing to coat, until fragrant and beginning to brown, 1–2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.891', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.571');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3ec50655-0d79-4df2-b480-10f3778916dd', 'Stir in 4 cups water, cover pot, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until quinoa is cooked and water is absorbed, 20–30 minutes. Remove from heat, sprinkle cherries over, cover, and let sit 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.896', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.571');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48b1063b-2d4c-457d-b876-f3544016abe4', 'Transfer 2 cups quinoa mixture to a medium bowl. Reserve 1/2 cup toasted almonds, then toss remaining almonds with remaining quinoa mixture and transfer to a platter. Toss quinoa in bowl with saffron water until coated, then garnish platter with saffron quinoa. Top with remaining toasted almonds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.9', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.572');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e4fe535-e9a9-48b6-9319-ef69f01cbd37', 'Quinoa, with cherries, can be cooked 3 days ahead. Transfer to a resealable container and chill. Reheat over low on stovetop or in a 300°F oven until warmed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.904', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.572');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b89cd5a0-311d-433a-af77-86b8ad65790c', 'In a bowl, mix together the water, lemon juice and agave.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.908', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.573');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('364c7573-efa5-4616-ba05-9b101fa270f4', 'Place 3-5 blueberries and 1 or 2 kiwi slices in each ice pop mold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.911', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.573');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b176553e-2570-477e-a103-e1e06b3a4a96', 'Gently pour the liquid mixture into each mold. You can reposition the fruit after you''ve poured in the liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.574');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1b18113-ef55-4bf6-ad43-e736957d7d42', 'Freeze 6 hours or until frozen through.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.92', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.574');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a2b021a4-2930-443a-8022-c1557a8d90ba', 'Serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.924', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.576');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e1582bdd-e6ee-4327-a2c1-90c4946f4e09', 'Cook carrots in medium saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Drain. Cool completely. Transfer carrots to large bowl. Add cabbage, bell pepper, onion and cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.928', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.577');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1b59d2e-9333-48c5-9221-d79825a6380f', 'Whisk lime juice, cumin, garlic and hot pepper sauce in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Season with salt and pepper. (Cabbage mixture and dressing can be made 8 hours ahead. Cover separately; chill. Rewhisk dressing before continuing.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.932', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.579');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5a0f0d4a-466f-48a2-8026-296bc6855d35', 'Toss salad with enough dressing to coat. Season with salt and pepper; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.936', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.579');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c1af225-f8f5-40c7-9d7a-909cbcad22cd', 'Place cooked leftover vegetables in large strainer. Lower strainer into large pot of boiling water until butter and seasonings are removed, about 30 seconds. Rinse with cold water; pat dry. Transfer to large bowl and mix in tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.95', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.581');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b44b3405-27fd-4e13-8458-a2fe75d8e49a', 'Whisk all remaining ingredients in bowl; toss with vegetable mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours and up to 2 days. Bring vegetables to room temperature. Season with salt and pepper; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.954', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.581');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ca1deb4-22bd-4c73-9a5a-bc16515b932c', 'Seed cucumber and peel jícama. Cut cucumber, jícama, and carrots into 1 1/2-inch-long thin strips. Toss vegetables together with remaining ingredients and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.962', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.582');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c335675b-2d71-47c9-be2b-3e390382f760', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook shallots and squash, stirring, until shallots are softened, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.966', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.583');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5dfbd6b-59ae-4358-9257-bea53de6b7f9', 'Add broth, brown sugar, sage, and salt, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until squash is tender, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vinegar, pepper, and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.97', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.583');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('31cd99b9-cf25-4966-930b-ab77e6c5233a', '1. In a bowl, reserve 2 tablespoons each of the tomato, cucumber, pepper, and onion to garnish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.974', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.584');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2345e5e6-7712-4ae0-910c-6b59285a8559', '2. In the food processor or blender, purée the remaining ingredients (except the croutons) until smooth, adjusting the seasoning to taste with lemon juice, salt, and cayenne pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.979', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.584');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48f56762-9517-4280-8add-f576dda4f1b3', '3. Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 3 hours but preferably overnight. Adjust the consistency as desired with water. Serve in chilled bowls garnished with the reserved vegetables and croutons.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.983', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.585');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('759dfe7e-3578-4fd0-9092-a5e5fafc227d', 'Preheat the oven to 350ºF. Line a cupcake pan with cupcake liners and set aside. In a small bowl or measuring cup, combine the almond milk and vinegar and let sit for 5 minutes. In a large bowl, combine the Earth Balance and sugar and beat with an electric mixer until creamy, about 2 minutes. Add in the yogurt and vanilla extract and mix on low until combined. In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cardamom, cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg. Alternate adding the dry ingredients and the almond milk mixture to the creamed butter, mixing on low speed until everything is mixed together.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.987', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.585');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71f62c19-ed3a-4b15-8787-d37c3a545144', 'Pour the batter into the cupcake liners until each liner is about two-thirds full. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. Remove from the oven and allow to cool on a wire rack.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.991', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.586');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('28993d69-d62e-4434-ac6d-3512a5b29a88', 'Prepare grill for medium-high. Whisk lemon zest, Meyer lemon zest, lemon juice, Meyer lemon juice, mustard, and 1/4 cup oil in a medium bowl to combine; season dressing with salt and pepper (if you don’t have Meyer lemons, use regular lemons in their place).', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.994', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.586');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0837e417-bdd6-4917-b6c9-281eaa6ed68f', 'Place asparagus and spring onions on a rimmed baking sheet and lightly drizzle with oil. Season with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Grill, turning once, until lightly charred and crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Serve drizzled with dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:26.998', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.587');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7247534e-b980-4cb4-b7f8-1fde4bc948ce', 'Whisk vinegar, sugar, salt, and pepper in medium bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in oils. DO AHEAD: Dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.002', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.587');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f33b8062-1c14-46c9-b4d5-31ca2a56d64b', 'Place cabbage, radicchio, sugar snap peas, onion, and parsley in large bowl. Add dressing and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.006', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.588');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7cebd9df-8891-4e15-8823-69d178928962', 'Bring 5 cups water to simmer in medium saucepan. Cover; keep warm over low heat. Pour 5 cups water into large pot. Add salt, oil, and bay leaves; bring to boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium; gradually add cornmeal, whisking to avoid lumps. Reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer uncovered until polenta is thick, whisking often, about 3 minutes. Whisk in 1 cup of reserved hot water. Continue to simmer until polenta is smooth and thick, whisking often, about 3 minutes. Add remaining hot water, 1 cup at a time, and cook until very thick after each addition, whisking often, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.009', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.588');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91450170-3519-4b69-a74e-88913ffdd389', '*Available at Italian markets, natural foods stores, and some supermarkets. If unavailable, substitute regular yellow cornmeal and cook for about half the time.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.013', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.589');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a993a6d1-78c3-46bc-9c00-9af93ff945a1', 'In a blender or mini-processor purée 1 tablespoon of the walnuts with the vinegar, the oil, and salt and pepper to taste. In a steamer set over boiling water steam beans, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes, or until they are crisp-tender, transfer them to a bowl, and toss them with the dressing and the remaining chopped walnuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.017', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.59');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8296b021-fdec-4c55-954e-f4d4eafd45af', 'Preheat oven to 250°F. Lightly spray rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Toss oats and next 3 ingredients in large bowl. Whisk syrup, brown sugar, oil, 2 tablespoons warm water and salt in small bowl to blend. Pour syrup mixture over oat mixture and stir to combine. Transfer to prepared baking sheet. Bake until evenly browned, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour 15 minutes. Cool. Transfer to large bowl. Mix in raisins. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Store in airtight container.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.021', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.59');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55a1f935-a192-4e1e-9597-55f844b1070f', 'In a steamer set over boiling water steam the beans, covered, for 6 to 8 minutes, or until they are just tender. While the beans are steaming, in a blender blend together the vinegar, the oil, the dill seeds, the chopped dill, and salt and pepper to taste. Transfer the beans to a serving bowl and toss them with the dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.024', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.591');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1928ef16-6acc-431e-b97b-b472dab6e34f', 'Blanch peaches in medium saucepan of boiling water 30 seconds. Transfer to bowl of cold water using slotted spoon. Pull off peel, using small sharp knife. Pit and slice peaches. Transfer peaches to medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.028', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.591');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('641239ca-2dda-4462-bf31-7445692080a5', 'Add all remaining ingredients to peaches and mix to dissolve sugar. Refrigerate at least 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.031', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.592');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7e49f4c2-7fab-482f-845e-ef28ce6bcf55', 'Process all ingredients in a food processor until as smooth as possible.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.035', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.592');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8df90865-4f3d-4918-afa2-3ecd79860c71', 'You should have about 4 cups. Reserve 2 cups for the sauce, and set aside the remainder.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.039', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.592');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fdb8d4b8-4ae6-4c25-b085-794f76a85a90', 'Puree all the ingredients in a high-speed blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.042', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.593');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30d3a92d-a0e8-4325-b18f-7dd630082e17', 'Using a mandoline, slice the beets very thin (so they are pliable and not stiff, approximately 1/16 of an inch or less).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.046', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.593');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d94b0cb5-f810-4a9d-b7d4-8e4baf74208d', 'Make small stacks of the larger pieces and use a sharp knife to cut into squares-the size doesn''t matter much, as long as they are all roughly the same. Alternatively, use a round-, heart-or other- shaped cookie cutter to cut the slices. Cut at least 40 slices-10 per serving, with a few extra to spare.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.05', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.593');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e961946b-022a-443c-a0b5-554d65fd5b66', 'In a medium bowl, place the beet slices, oil, lemon juice, and salt and toss gently to coat evenly. Allowing the beets to sit for a half hour or more will soften them; this is optional but a good idea if your slices are on the thicker side and still a bit stiff.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.054', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.594');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('790ae309-6851-4e9c-b860-4efbd0415d26', 'Lay half the beet slices on a clean work surface and top each with a rounded teaspoonful of the cheese. Top with the remaining beet slices and press down gently.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.057', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.594');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c679b4e2-dfbc-4281-91e2-52f81c472bad', 'Spoon the sauce onto serving plates, and arrange the ravioli on top. Garnish with a few drops of aged balsamic vinegar and a few sprigs of either microgreens or fresh herbs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.061', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.597');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9cfc061-3451-4fd7-876a-c337e55c12b9', 'Trim 1/4 inch from bottom of each head of bok choy. Slice bok choy crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices. Wash bok choy in several changes of cold water and dry in colander or salad spinner until dry to touch.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.065', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.597');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6d6f745f-7299-436e-97f8-de0b08320b3d', 'In wok or large sauté pan over moderately high heat, heat oil until hot but not smoking. Add ginger, scallions, and garlic and stir-fry until aromatic, about 15 seconds. Add bok choy, salt, sugar, and pepper and stir-fry 1 minute. Add 1 tablespoon water, cover, and cook until wilted, about 30 seconds. Uncover, stir-fry 5 seconds, then cover again, turn off flame, and let steam in residual heat until just tender, about 30 seconds more. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.068', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.598');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2d156220-0fa7-4cf9-9191-804ef1df9c3c', 'Toast chiles in a large heavy skillet over medium heat until slightly puffed and lightly darkened on both sides, about 2 minutes. Remove from pan; let cool. Add garlic to same skillet; cook, turning often, until skins brown in spots and cloves are soft, 10-15 minutes. Remove from pan. Let cool; peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.072', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.598');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a868153-b6e2-4f8e-9863-0cb44f4c250d', 'Stem chiles and halve lengthwise; discard seeds. Cut into pieces; transfer to a medium bowl. Cover with boiling water; let soak, mixing often, until softened, 25-30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.076', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.599');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('528280c0-ee17-4941-b3ae-8acb61eccd9f', 'Drain chiles, reserving soaking liquid. Transfer chiles, garlic, 1/2 cup soaking liquid, and 1 tablespoon vinegar to blender. Purée, adding soaking liquid as needed, until a smooth, thick sauce forms. Season with salt and more vinegar, if desired. DO AHEAD: Salsa can be made 1 week ahead. Cover; chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.08', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.6');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a283ead-734e-47bf-ba60-afe4136ace86', 'Heat oven to 400°F. Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. In a food processor, chop garlic. Add beans, oats, cornmeal, chili powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper; process, stopping once or twice to scrape down sides, until mixture is combined, 1 minute. Crumble bean mixture with hands, sprinkle on prepared sheet, and coat with cooking spray. Bake until firm and crisp on bottom, 10 to 15 minutes. Use a spoon to break up pieces, coat with cooking spray, and bake until crisp all over, 10 to 15 minutes. Stack tortillas and wrap in foil; warm in oven 5 minutes. In a bowl, combine corn, bell pepper, chile, scallions and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper; sprinkle with lime juice. Divide bean crumble among tortillas; top with corn salsa and cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.084', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.6');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('590d889c-7ba3-4328-a0c1-cea0492e0bad', 'Combine raspberries with juices, sugar and lemon juice in processor; blend until smooth. Pour into strainer set over bowl. Press on solids to extract as much juice as possible; discard solids in strainer. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.088', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.601');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2a6f0a9f-d212-420e-972b-a226d0308f16', 'Combine all ingredients in large bowl; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour and up to 2 hours to allow flavors to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.092', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.601');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('95aba126-dbe8-404e-932a-ec7fc1b02904', 'Toss pistachios, fennel seeds, and 1 tablespoon oil in a small skillet over medium heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, about 3 minutes. Season with salt. Transfer to a small bowl; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.096', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.602');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a54f46e-8dcb-4171-bc02-07e21dd02172', 'Toss fennel, lettuce, parsley, tarragon, chives, lemon zest, and horseradish in a large bowl. Add lemon juice; season with salt and pepper and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.099', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.602');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de4a66a5-4c1c-408d-8deb-b18ad37814ab', 'Add remaining 1/4 cup oil and toss to coat, then add half of pistachio mixture and toss just to combine. Season with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.103', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.604');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2d2a08c0-59ff-4b8d-84da-9e4437f473da', 'Serve salad topped with remaining pistachio mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.107', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.605');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('83e8d030-d64c-419f-b52e-171b31aa6456', 'Do ahead: Pistachio mixture can be made 2 days ahead; store tightly wrapped at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.11', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.605');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('54627469-595a-4ec2-a105-0ad9d0a0ffd4', 'Blend ingredients and freeze in an ice-cream maker.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.114', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.606');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('995b05c3-7dcc-44d3-8772-0500fe72b9a0', 'Heat oil in a large stockpot over medium-high heat. Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables begin to soften, 5-7 minutes. Add 4 quarts cold water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until stock is reduced by half, 1-1 1/2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.119', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.608');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('85e6e4e6-f7f2-4530-8aa7-3f71bd9136aa', 'Strain stock through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl; discard solids. DO AHEAD: Stock can be made 3 days ahead. Let cool completely, then cover and chill, or freeze for up to 3 months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.123', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.609');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9002c828-dbf6-4446-b54e-f12bb77edca1', 'In a 3-quart heavy saucepan wash rice in several changes of water, pouring off each change of water carefully, until water is almost clear. Drain rice in a sieve and return to pan. Add 3 cups water and salt and bring to a boil, uncovered, without stirring. Boil mixture until surface of rice is covered with steam holes and grains on top appear dry, 8 to 10 minutes. Reduce heat to low and cook rice, covered, without stirring, 15 minutes. Remove pan from heat and let rice stand, covered, 5 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.127', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.609');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('914732ef-170d-4d0c-aebd-26d00abcb605', 'Combine all ingredients in heavy 3-quart saucepan. Cover and cook over medium-low until apples are tender, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.131', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.61');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b9429b15-9f13-4069-83db-8d44c6a1e832', 'In a large saucepan combine the potatoes with enough water to cover them by 1 inch, bring the water to a boil, and boil the potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they are tender. While the potatoes are cooking, in a blender blend the tofu, the lemon juice, the tarragon, and 2 tablespoons water until the mixture is just combined, with the motor running add the oil in a stream and blend the "mayonnaise" until it is emulsified. Drain the potatoes, quarter them, and in a bowl toss them with the onion, the parsley, the mayonnaise, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.135', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.61');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('96f46710-dad9-4502-b02e-2bc0d9f9b5a6', 'Combine shallots, vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and sugar in a small bowl. Gradually whisk in oil to blend. Set vinaigrette aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.14', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.611');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d56d0cfb-c9bf-47e0-98fe-e50c053d7f94', 'Arrange tomatoes on a large platter. Sprinkle capers over; season with salt and pepper. Scatter basil on top. Whisk vinaigrette again; drizzle over salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.144', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.611');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0105a52-47be-44b4-80ce-6930e0621d95', 'Char pepper over gas flame or in broiler until blackened. Enclose in plastic bag 15 minutes. Peel, seed, and cut pepper into 1/3-inch cubes. Place in large bowl. Add tomatoes, cucumber, olives, onion, and parsley. Whisk oil and lemon juice in small bowl to blend; season with salt and pepper, then mix into vegetables. Let vegetables marinate at least 15 minutes before serving. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.148', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.612');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df3b0321-8b5e-4c2c-ab8a-81bf183982c8', 'Pulse beets, apple, shallots, sugar, zest and salt in a food processor until pureed. Add reserved beet liquid; pulse until smooth. Transfer beet mixture to a bowl; stir in orange juice, vinegar and lemon juice. Cover and chill until cold, 1 hour. Divide among 4 bowls; garnish with chives and cheese before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.152', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.613');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24c2cd37-d70f-430e-85a5-8866a8020501', '1. Separate the stalks from the broccoli crowns. Thickly peel and trim the stalks and chop them into 1/2-inch pieces. Peel the base of the broccoli crowns, then separate them into florets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.613');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4a01432-77ed-471c-a441-9bafa4bc260a', '2. Bring 2 quarts water to a boil; add salt, then the broccoli. Cook for 5 minutes (even if the water barely returns to the boil), then scoop into a colander to drain, reserving a cup of the water. Chop into small pieces just smaller than bite-sized.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.614');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c2d9eea8-f25b-41b3-9529-b478499b1064', '3. Warm the olive oil in a wide skillet, then add the onion, marjoram, and garlic. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring now and then, until the onion is softened, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in the olive paste; add the broccoli and stir to coat well. Taste for salt, season with pepper, and add the lemon zest. Add the reserved broccoli water and simmer gently until the broccoli is very tender, 15 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.165', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.614');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('030d4c4c-6e57-40bd-bd37-67c9f32e7d4a', 'Whisk together vinegar, mustard, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Add oil in a slow stream, whisking, until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.169', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.614');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe9cf78b-f684-4c50-961e-c1e176110b98', 'Cut peel, including all white pith, from oranges and grapefruit with a paring knife. Working over a bowl, cut segments free from membranes. Squeeze juice from membranes into a small bowl, then whisk 3 tablespoons juice into vinaigrette. Drain citrus segments, then add to vinaigrette.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.173', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.615');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('650eae50-acdb-4d07-8ecd-6f867bff4fea', 'Quarter fennel bulbs lengthwise, then cut lengthwise into paper-thin slices (about 1/16 inch thick) with slicer. Add to fruit along with celery and toss gently to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.615');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04408b84-58ee-4575-a1e2-99b0ec68ac79', 'Available at Asian markets, many cookware shops, and Uwajimaya (800-889-1928).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.616');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('467e2412-f9a6-4b9b-ac6f-581c20c3681e', 'Cook baby artichokes in large saucepan of boiling salted water until tender when bottom is pierced with sharp knife, about 8 minutes. Drain and run under cold water to cool. Cut artichokes in half through stem; pat dry. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.616');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a2f6cbf6-a10e-4528-8a7b-daeaa96eef91', 'Prepare Barbecue ( medium heat). Brush cooked artichokes, Japanese eggplant, and cut side of lemons with olive oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill vegetables until tender and slightly charred, about 2 minutes per side. Grill lemons, cut side down, until charred, about 2 minutes. Transfer vegetables to platter. Garnish with grilled lemons for squeezing over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.216', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.617');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b5930eb-5f60-4c7c-8aa3-c2b450dad8b8', 'Place the pineapple, mint, jalapeño(s), lime juice, and brown sugar in a nonreactive mixing bowl, but don''t mix them until 5 minutes before you are ready to serve. Taste for seasoning, adding more lime juice and/or brown sugar as necessary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.22', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.617');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c870f3f-379f-40cc-b4bb-f04ed87a439d', 'Slivered mint keeps this "salsa" in the realm of a salad. If you really want to push the limits try substituting chopped fresh cilantro for the mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.224', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.617');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9875c2ed-5836-476b-9e69-928d0b5491e5', '1. In a sauté pan, heat the olive oil and add the onion and peppers. Cook until softened, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.228', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.617');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a1450b3-cd2a-463c-ab4b-bd1ea806a48d', '2. In a small bowl, mix together the cumin, turmeric, coriander, chili powder, paprika, thyme, cayenne, salt, and pepper, and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.233', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.618');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4a42cbf-8bfe-4515-8644-a501a59f7ebf', '3. Crumble the tofu into bite—sized pieces with a fork and add to the sauté pan. Sprinkle the spice mixture over the tofu to coat and sauté for about 5 minutes. Serve at once with the home fries.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.237', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.618');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('895475aa-39bf-4cbb-81aa-12d7e0a6f3b7', 'Pour the water into a large pot. Add the cinnamon and ginger and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.618');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fad75f3c-b5dd-4b52-9b07-5d3dde4bd3b5', 'Strawberries can be pickled 5 days ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.019', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.717');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30fef6f9-c408-4111-8750-9bc3d74b5b71', 'Remove from the heat and carefully remove the cinnamon and ginger. Add the brown sugar and stir until completely dissolved. Let cool, then refrigerate for several hours (preferably overnight) until chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.246', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.618');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0d3453c-6f3f-4cb2-87c0-b462894b11db', 'If you wish, sprinkle a few pine nuts in each cup before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.25', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.619');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d4c942b-663c-401f-9370-13b50bfd1bce', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 450°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.255', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.621');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c039e595-9818-4e0b-8a3e-3de1fb1cc987', 'Toss cauliflower with oil and salt in a large bowl. Spread in 1 layer in a large shallow baking pan (1 inch deep) and roast, stirring and turning over occasionally, until tender and golden brown, 25 to 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.259', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.621');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('717e1b93-ffca-43bd-8bc2-ce856cba3e7e', '1. Slice the tofu crosswise into scant 1/ 2-inch slabs, then cut each slab into 2 triangles. Blot with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.264', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.621');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9a5b4ef-ad6d-4ab5-b0a4-cbaf8becad86', '2. Heat a large cast-iron or nonstick skillet and add the oil. When hot, add the tofu and fry over medium-high heat until golden. Turn and cook on the second side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.269', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.622');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1c20f9b-c266-466b-a6e9-3903b2658bff', '3. Meanwhile, combine all the ingredients for the sauce in a small food processor and puree until smooth. Taste for salt and add a little extra, if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.273', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.623');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fedd6056-9551-4f36-87ee-52024efbb5b2', '4. When the tofu is done, pour in half the sauce and cook until bubbling and partially reduced.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.277', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.624');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6930de96-1da8-4e6a-aec4-4f09cae6fd74', '5. Turn off the heat, scatter the scallions and sesame seeds over the top, and bring to the table.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.282', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.624');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e6474c8-239a-4684-b0f5-8f19d6c91f95', 'Steam okra in a steamer over boiling water, covered, until just tender, about 7 minutes. Transfer to a serving dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.286', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.624');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fe00d5e-e5be-4468-9b90-dfb69a77a122', 'Cook scallions in oil with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a small skillet over medium heat, stirring, just until softened, 1 to 3 minutes. Pour over okra and toss with ginger. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over okra.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.29', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.624');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a8a5e902-a7ba-49af-9422-528924ba119a', 'Whisk 1/4 cup fresh orange juice, 1 tablespoon white wine vinegar, 2 1/2 teaspoons honey, 1 teaspoon finely grated peeled ginger, and a pinch of salt in a medium bowl. Cut 3 large red plums into thin wedges and thinly slice 1/2 small fennel bulb. Add to dressing; toss to coat. Cover and chill 30 minutes to allow fennel to soften and flavors to get to know one another.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.296', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.625');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('399519af-5378-4a33-b8dd-c237860029bd', 'Toss 1/2 teaspoon finely grated peeled ginger into fruit salad. Serve drizzled with olive oil and topped with toasted sesame seeds and fennel fronds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.625');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4698712e-f6c4-45f7-bda6-0a24dac61286', 'In a food processor, finely mince the garlic cloves. Combine the remaining ingredients in a large measuring cup. Add to the garlic and pulse until completely blended. Use a rubber spatula to stir the ingredients and pulse again if necessary. Transfer some of the seasoning salt to small containers with shakers and the remainder to an airtight container. Store for up to 3 months in the refrigerator.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.305', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.627');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da4cdc6e-4e92-45e0-acaa-e6ead0e320f2', 'Preheat oven to 325°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.627');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89c2016e-1f32-4252-8a9f-687bfd9f27c4', 'Slice tangerines (including peel) crosswise about 1/4 inch thick. Remove and discard any seeds, then arrange tangerines in a 13- by 9-inch baking dish, overlapping if necessary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.314', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.627');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('345d8df8-0eef-4bae-98c5-7cd55bc4bf12', 'Bring sugar and water to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring occasionally, then simmer 2 minutes. Stir in wine and lemon juice and return to a simmer. Pour over fruit.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.319', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.628');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f6588ce-8545-408f-b267-39e3b714a598', 'Lay a sheet of parchment paper directly over fruit to keep submerged, then poach in oven until tender but not falling apart, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Discard parchment and cool fruit to warm or room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.628');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed3a5868-0bf2-4f3a-94ac-8e31cdc5f628', 'Place the tofu, cashews, lemon juice, sugar, mustard, vinegar, and salt in a blender or food processor and process until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.327', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.629');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c915340-a216-4db2-9a28-d8477391ea30', 'Slowly drizzle in the oil and pulse until you get the consistency that you like.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.629');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('199b7ec0-e9c5-490a-ad36-f0210c1da452', 'Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.336', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.63');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e094b3ed-bc2f-49f3-9704-9e8b5f36e413', 'In a bowl stir together all ingredients and let stand, covered, 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.34', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.631');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('568d1be7-afb5-4145-a940-e40ea81e6207', 'Serve salsa with tortilla chips or as a condiment.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.345', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.631');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e5c69989-3148-480e-927d-78551ac09b01', 'Wash and pat your sweet potatoes dry. Cut the sweet potatoes into small 1-inch cubes. Roast the sweet potato cubes with 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, 1 tablespoon granulated garlic powder, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Place onto a sheet tray and roast at 375° F for approximately 40 minutes, remove from the oven, and cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.349', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.632');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ace4a8b6-dc42-4d72-8d88-8b89ae82f444', 'In a food processor, add the roasted/cooked sweet potato, tamari soy sauce, and Worcestershire sauce; pulse to combine. Add the onion and chickpeas and pulse until fully combined, periodically stopping the food processor and using a spatula or wooden spoon to move the mixture around. Mix just until the chickpeas and onion are fully incorporated; look for the consistency of mashed potatoes. Do not overmix.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.353', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.633');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14baf9d9-8379-4325-b57c-153362e92523', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the oats, walnuts, chia seeds, and flaxseed meal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.358', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.633');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ca5e9bb-9384-41fc-8019-b33719763770', 'Remove the sweet potato mixture from the food processor and fold into the dry ingredients. Measure out 1/3 cup of the mixture at a time and, using your hands, form into round burger-shaped patties.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.362', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.634');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55122c9f-e031-422f-b34d-54e4ab61ccbf', 'In a medium sauté pan, heat the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the patties and sauté for about 4 minutes per side, or until they are warmed through and golden brown on each side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.367', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.634');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b60ffc2c-b441-4ef0-938e-3bf9a5c5ce86', 'To serve, place the patties on toasted buns, if desired, and add your choice of toppings. I love avocado, kale, and Worcestershire sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.371', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.635');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29a9d517-4a3e-49ef-ac52-1f56cbda16b2', 'Heat oil in very large heavy skillet over medium-high heat. Add all peppers; sauté until slightly softened, stirring occasionally, about 7 minutes. Add raisins and fennel seeds. Continue to cook until peppers are soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.) Add 8 cups arugula to peppers and stir until arugula begins to wilt, about 1 minute. Transfer mixture to large platter; garnish with additional arugula and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.635');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('318b3469-6ca4-41ca-9659-d5e20d68ae92', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cool syrup slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.023', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.717');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5da7e904-f29f-491d-95a0-7033ecad0862', 'Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-low. Add onions, celery, and garlic and cook, stirring often and adding a splash or so of water if the bottom of pan gets too brown, until golden brown, 30–40 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Add cashews, sugar, red pepper flakes, and 3 cups water and bring mixture to a simmer. Cook until vegetables are very soft and losing their structure, 10–15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.636');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47d1d646-6a7c-4e0e-8063-85afe0ddfd96', 'Blend one-third of sugar snap peas with one-third of vegetable mixture in a blender, adding some cooking liquid from vegetable mixture as needed to thin, until very smooth, about 2 minutes. Press purée through a fine-mesh sieve into a medium saucepan; discard solids. Working in 2 batches, repeat with remaining peas and vegetable mixture, adding water as needed if you run out of cooking liquid. If soup is still very thick, thin with water until you get a velvety, pourable consistency. (You should have about 7 cups soup.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.384', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.636');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f48b2f54-cd15-452e-a2e3-da202d3b6b63', 'Stir vinegar into soup; season with more salt and pepper and warm over medium-low until heated through.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.389', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.637');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9f1d729-f31a-4136-9009-1e2421c97b50', 'Serve soup topped with scallions and potato chips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.393', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.637');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('caf210bf-e0dc-4b71-93f7-8ce05e2f3ceb', 'Soup can be made 2 days ahead. Let cool; cover and chill. Reheat over medium-low, thinning with water as needed until pourable.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.397', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.641');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3bb90c1-4178-453d-b3eb-c24bc399b1f6', 'Following package directions, prepare curried couscous. Add currants while couscous steams.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.401', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.641');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e29656f9-035c-484a-824c-c7b62e082f31', 'Heat olive oil in very large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add tofu in single layer and cook without stirring until just golden, about 4 minutes. Turn tofu over and cook 2 minutes longer. Transfer tofu to couscous. Add broccoli, onion, and bell pepper to skillet; cook over medium-high heat 2 minutes without stirring. Continue to cook vegetables until crisp-tender, stirring constantly, about 4 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water; increase heat to high and bring to boil, stirring to scrape up browned bits. Mix in 1/2 cup cilantro. Season vegetables to taste with salt and pepper. Mix couscous, vegetables, and cooking liquid in large serving bowl. Garnish with remaining 1/4 cup cilantro and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.405', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.642');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('938ac04f-0934-4b99-bcc5-5634a29a5a35', 'In a saucepan bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved, and cool syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.409', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.642');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5b66475-237a-40a2-869a-557ee40b560b', 'In a blender or food processor purée pineapple with 1/4 cup plus', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.413', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25415f83-7147-4192-b626-621e710f7f5a', '2 tablespoons syrup (reserving remaining syrup for another use). Stir in nectar or juice and Champagne. Pineapple mixture may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.417', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.643');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5cae037a-fa27-4bec-9e85-951131da308d', 'Transfer pineapple mixture to a shallow metal baking pan and freeze, stirring and crushing lumps with a fork every hour, until mixture is firm but not frozen hard, about 3 to 4 hours. Granita may be made 2 days ahead and frozen, covered. Just before serving, scrape granita with a fork to lighten texture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.421', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.644');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('425b3e09-62b8-42a3-964f-b9f4d44140ac', 'Scoop granita into serving bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.425', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.644');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7cf9d821-97dc-4953-9f61-3bd1e5bd901e', 'Combine 3/4 cup water, wine and sugar in small saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Chill syrup until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.429', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.644');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e793ef1-e3fc-4471-b94f-84d3b9355e97', 'Combine pineapple, kiwis, mango, lime juice, lime peel and chilled syrup in large bowl. Mix well. Cover fruit mixture and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.433', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.645');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e14030a-e176-4062-a7d8-720efe30c7b7', 'Scoop 1/2 cup mango sorbet into each of 6 compote dishes or wineglasses. Spoon fruit mixture around sorbet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.436', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8557e8bb-6faf-4577-89a1-b60a4d5f4ba5', 'Peel parsnips and halve each crosswise where it becomes narrow. Diagonally cut narrow portions into 3/4-inch-thick slices. Quarter wider portions lengthwise and core, then diagonally cut flesh into 3/4-inch-thick slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.44', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff2f4a94-62f0-4646-b613-65c7d778201a', 'Toss parsnips and carrots with oil, salt, pepper, rosemary, and sage in a large bowl. Spread in a large shallow baking pan (1 inch deep) and pour in water. Roast vegetables in lower third of oven until tender, 50 to 55 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.444', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('45748deb-c2b2-411c-89b0-6990b3b573b1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl. Mix in oil and lemon juice. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.448', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.646');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e9b2295-8639-4554-8c4c-2c3c8529cd16', 'Blanch fava beans in a pot of boiling well-salted water 1 minute, then transfer with a slotted spoon to an ice bath to stop cooking. Transfer favas with slotted spoon to a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.451', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e53e6ef-15ea-430a-8699-4203cc3130c9', 'Cook Romano beans in same pot of boiling water, stirring occasionally, until just tender, about 5 minutes, then transfer to ice bath to stop cooking. Drain well and transfer to a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.455', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.647');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9a0b389-cdd3-41d6-ac18-daa280287bb1', 'Cook green beans in same pot until just tender, 6 to 7 minutes, then transfer to ice bath. Add to Romano beans.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.459', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48cadf05-16d6-4ad3-94bf-df9bdd755ef2', 'Gently peel skins from fava beans (it''s not necessary to peel edamame, if using), then add to other beans.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.463', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9b63a40-e9e9-4024-aec2-1ba71907ee3a', 'Cut basil into very thin shreds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.466', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.648');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a05a0a1-6f09-4235-9d5f-ed840da6cd3f', 'Cook garlic in oil with a rounded 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 1 minute. Add beans, water, and zest and cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through. Stir in basil and 2 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and remove from heat. Season with salt and additional lemon juice if desired. Serve beans warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.47', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09c7a98b-32c1-4a89-a74c-d487161295f8', 'Stir first 3 ingredients in small bowl until sugar dissolves. Blend 3 cups strawberries in processor until smooth. Add sugar syrup and blend until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.474', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('06280e49-8d22-42b9-a210-2d989dcd443b', 'Pour mixture into 13x9x2-inch nonstick metal baking pan. Freeze until icy around edges, about 25 minutes. Using fork, stir icy portions into middle of pan. Freeze until mixture is frozen, stirring edges into center every 20 to 30 minutes, about 1 1/2 hours. Using fork, scrape granita into flaky crystals. Cover tightly and freeze. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep frozen.) Scrape granita into bowls. Garnish with berries and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.478', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48bb9d8c-6b53-4511-966f-2d3d7dac8e5d', 'Bring sugar, ginger, and 1/3 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat; let steep for 10 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a medium pitcher (you should have 1/2 cup); discard ginger. Cover and chill syrup. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.481', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.649');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a126667-bcfa-492b-9d74-276298e02a34', 'Fill four 6-ounce glasses with ice cubes. Add carrot juice and lime juice to ginger syrup in pitcher; stir well. Divide elixir among prepared glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.485', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76f557b9-90b5-45ad-b88b-3d8b21443de9', 'Place onion slices in medium bowl. Bring next 5 ingredients to boil in heavy medium saucepan; pour over onions in bowl. Cover; cool to room temperature. Chill overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.489', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c3530822-e8a6-43fa-81e2-8c4fdaa61dd4', 'Onions can be pickled 3 weeks ahead. Keep chilled. Drain before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.493', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b9409c6b-092d-4943-839c-1a0d665f5e6d', 'Heat a wok or 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until a drop of water vaporizes instantly. Pour oil around side of wok, then tilt wok to swirl oil, coating side. When oil just begins to smoke, fry shallots in 3 batches, stirring, until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes per batch. Transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. Toss fried shallots with 1/4 teaspoon salt (shallots will crisp as they cool).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.497', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.65');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('21a8a2eb-7866-4732-84f3-882027fe61c5', 'Pour off all but 3 tablespoons oil from wok, then add garlic, bok choy, and remaining teaspoon salt to wok and cook over moderate heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Serve topped with fried shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.5', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.651');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61d4b090-0174-4fce-8a0b-30ce2312d861', 'Remove husks from and rinse tomatillos under warm water to remove stickiness. Pat tomatillos dry and cut about three fourths into 1/4-inch dice. In a blender or food processor puree remaining tomatillos until smooth. Cut celery into 1/4-inch dice and finely chop cilantro. Slice radishes and cut into julienne strips. In a bowl toss together all ingredients and season with salt. Salsa may be made 1 hour ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.504', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.651');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e65a3064-4673-417e-b31d-c09db981be3b', 'Toss arugula with olive oil, lemon juice, and peel. Toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.508', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.652');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('56250f7e-aaa9-4910-a131-28f507f55db7', 'Bring a pot of lightly salted water to a boil, add the pasta, and cook until tender, about 10 minutes, or according to package instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.513', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.654');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9ade7690-5e50-47cd-8bfa-05caf44b3dda', 'Meanwhile, put the beans and carrots in a steamer and cook for 4 minutes. Add the corn to the steamer and cook for 3-4 minutes, or until tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.517', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.655');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('563cfae5-7b07-4fe2-abf1-f279a81ab258', 'Combine all the ingredients for the dressing in a blender or food processor, adding only a little salt and pepper, and process until smooth. Combine the cooked pasta with the vegetables and cherry tomatoes and toss with some of the dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.521', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.655');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35992622-90e1-4f92-b7f2-be2b6129cd9b', 'Variation: Add 2 Tbsp (30 g) diced cucumber, 1/2 cup (75 g) diced cold chicken or tuna to this salad, and vary the vegetables, according to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.525', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.655');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d8ea9be-dc48-4edc-b834-106b028a9a86', 'Quarter zucchini lengthwise. Cut off and discard seed portion in center of each zucchini spear. Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch cubes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.529', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.656');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27b2beb5-1b73-4c1f-ad1f-3cd6a69aeb53', 'Heat a 12-inch non-stick skillet over moderately high heat until hot enough to make a drop of water scatter over surface. Add olive oil and heat until oil is hot but not smoking. Sauté zucchini and bell peppers with salt and pepper to taste, stirring, until just tender and beginning to turn golden, about 7 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.533', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.656');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('502d5c46-2065-4b48-9e81-bb8ac253d08f', 'In a large saucepan combine all ingredients and a pinch salt and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, or until apples are very tender. Strain mixture through a sieve into a blender and add half of solids in sieve to blender, discarding remaining solids. Purée apple mixture and chill until cold. Freeze sorbet in an ice-cream maker. Sorbet may be made 1 week ahead.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.538', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.656');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6ef65b38-c13e-4637-ab10-112f202ed049', 'Gently toss sliced peaches, golden brown sugar, and fresh lemon juice in large bowl to blend. Let stand at room temperature until juices form, tossing occasionally, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.542', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.657');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c842ab29-16db-4e6c-af5a-eab680f75b8e', 'Place sesame seeds in heavy skillet; sprinkle lightly with salt. Stir over medium heat until seeds are light golden, about 6 minutes. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.546', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.658');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23c8a474-49d1-4767-8f04-423cb41fa275', 'Line large colander with kitchen towel. Pack spinach, with water still clinging to leaves, into heavy large pot. Cook over high heat until wilted but still bright green, turning spinach with tongs for even cooking, about 4 minutes. Transfer spinach to prepared colander. Cool slightly. Wrap towel around spinach and squeeze out as much moisture as possible. Transfer spinach to work surface and chop coarsely. Place in medium bowl. Add sesame oil, vinegar, and hot pepper sauce. Toss to blend evenly. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with sesame seeds. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.55', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.658');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fd41132-a407-4b9f-92ca-7781dd180a21', 'Stir together oil, thyme, salt, and pepper. Toss squash with 2 tablespoons thyme oil in a shallow baking pan (1/2 to 1 inch deep) and arrange in 1 layer. Toss mushrooms with remaining 1/4 cup thyme oil in another shallow baking pan (1/2 to 1 inch deep) and arrange in 1 layer. Roast squash and mushrooms, stirring occasionally and switching position of pans halfway through roasting, until vegetables are tender and liquid mushrooms give off is evaporated, 25 to 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.659');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('017c066c-139d-4b80-a25d-1697af94fae5', 'Peel and trim the parsnips and carrots. Cut the slender ends into 1 1/4- to 1 1/2-inch lengths. Cut the fat ends in half lengthwise and then into 1 1/4- to 1 1/2-inch lengths.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.558', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.659');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00140fac-90b1-42d1-9094-907c2bf3b562', 'Peel and trim the turnips. If small, cut them into wedges about 1/2- to 3/4-inch thick. If large, cut the turnip in half through the equator, then cut into wedges. Peel the sweet potatoes. Cut in half lengthwise and then slice lengthwise about 1/2 inch thick; cut slices into 1 1/4- to 1 1/2-inch sections.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.563', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.66');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('67a5b8ff-c6f4-40cd-ac3e-4a42f42a1c09', 'In a 9x13-inch baking dish, toss the parsnips, carrots, turnips, sweet potatoes, and shallots with the oil and salt. Roast for 25 minutes. Add the rosemary and garlic, toss again, and continue roasting until the vegetables are browned and tender, another 20 to 25 minutes. Scrape out into a serving dish, sprinkle with the pepper, and serve hot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.567', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.66');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c472343-1d5a-4c60-9fd2-19031ba6079a', 'Blanch and peel peaches. Cut into 1/4-inch-thick wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.572', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.661');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df6ad2d2-8965-40c1-9e09-0885f5fe7231', 'Simmer peaches, wine, and sugar in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes, then remove from heat. Immediately transfer mixture to a bowl and add berries, tossing to combine. Cool compote completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.576', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.661');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd3ce505-1140-4494-93a0-7e13f113c064', 'Serve compote chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.58', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.662');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2d5c53db-936e-4630-ba6d-0cadf8af72cf', 'Cook asparagus in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 3 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer asparagus to small bowl. Cool. Add pasta to same pot and cook until just tender but still firm to bite. Drain well. Transfer pasta to very large bowl. Toss with 1 tablespoon oil. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.585', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.663');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57e35a19-cd2b-4057-b078-cfef65c45d23', 'Blend cup oil, green onions, vinegar and soy sauce in blender until smooth, about 2 minutes. (Asparagus, pasta and dressing can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover separately; chill.) Pour dressing over pasta. Add asparagus, spinach and cashews; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.663');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('871663d7-2cfc-4818-8d50-03c1cbd7f686', 'Prepare Honey-Ginger Barbecue Sauce and divide equally into two bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.594', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.664');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eb9dd6d2-85bf-42cf-a97c-728cf2f0ac20', 'Prepare grill for direct-heat cooking over medium-hot charcoal (medium-high for gas); see Grilling Procedure. .', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.599', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.664');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cedda55a-c259-41ac-88bd-077408119247', 'Drizzle corn with oil on a large rimmed baking sheet, and sprinkle evenly with salt. Lightly rub oil and salt into corn.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.603', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.665');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cccb1b62-e6fd-4a77-b7f0-78b01e3c1e58', 'Oil grill rack, then grill corn (covered only if using gas), turning frequently, until lightly browned and tender, 6 to 8 minutes. Move corn to different positions on grill if hot spots are present. Brush corn with some of prepared sauce and grill, turning, until sauce is hot, 1 to 2 minutes. Serve with reserved sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.607', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.665');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9d314069-479b-42d3-8214-11946217e6e5', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 375°F. Lightly oil a large shallow baking pan with vegetable oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.611', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.666');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6071faaa-3b83-4c57-b910-503b541baf19', 'Arrange rhubarb in 1 layer in pan and sift confectioners sugar evenly over top. Bake, stirring occasionally, until rhubarb is very tender, 25 to 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.616', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.666');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c99e8a69-b7c8-4c8a-b777-8cf66ff0480c', 'Transfer rhubarb to a food processor and purée until smooth. Force through a medium-mesh sieve into a bowl, discarding solids, and cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.62', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.667');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6acdb2dd-c03e-4b27-82ae-e7a04c0a0e07', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss almonds, oil, and paprika on a rimmed baking sheet to coat; spread out in a single layer and toast, tossing occasionally, until dark golden brown, 8-10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl, sprinkle with salt, and toss to coat. Let cool. DO AHEAD: Nuts can be toasted 1 week ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.624', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.667');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4107d2d-262a-4857-97c7-5a3af44fe373', 'In small mixing bowl, toss together tomatoes, strawberries, oil, vinegar, zest, salt, and pepper. Let marinate at room temperature 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.628', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.668');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('914e6325-bd38-4cfc-b018-519ee3c71ec5', 'To serve, place lettuce-head halves on 4 plates. Top each with tomato-strawberry mixture. Sprinkle with chives.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.633', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.668');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e30537a-fd2d-4180-8d40-341d2e329ff2', 'Whisk vinegar and shallot in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.637', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.669');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('764ffd51-7770-40db-baf3-c71f1927731e', 'Place arugula, sliced fennel, and apricots in large bowl. Whisk chopped fennel fronds into dressing. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss to coat evenly. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer salad to large serving bowl. Sprinkle pistachios over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.641', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.669');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('417ce1f1-3081-4f4a-953f-f02f11e52f8f', 'Preheat oven to 375°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.645', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.67');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a3c98a5d-75b8-457a-bc7d-4ba93eca4c64', 'Rub eggplant with 2 tablespoons oil and bake, cut sides down, in a small baking pan in middle of oven until flesh is browned and very tender, about 50 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.649', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.672');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fac306dc-ed7d-41f6-bd2c-29fab4dae9e8', 'Scoop flesh from eggplant into a food processor, discarding skin, and purée with olives, capers, remaining 2 tablespoons oil, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.653', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.673');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59dddb95-4980-4aef-a9c6-bb6e956dcff7', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the brown and white rice flours, sweet rice flour, tapioca flour, and xanthan gum thoroughly. Transfer the mix to an airtight container. Store in a cool, dark place for up to 6 weeks or in the refrigerator for up to 4 months.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.658', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.673');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d298e2fa-186f-4a00-ab3b-9900630423db', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Pulse oats, whole wheat flour, coconut oil, agave, cocoa, salt, and cinnamon in a food processor until oats are coarsely ground and mixture looks like wet sand.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.663', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.674');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a88fbf29-d10e-434b-9b1b-3bc0c58b0d56', 'Firmly press into bottom and up the sides of tart pan. Bake until crust is golden brown and smells toasty, 20–25 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.667', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.674');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f969d664-b704-4bfd-91da-450e4d69ed87', 'Dissolve espresso powder in 3/4 cup very hot water in a food processor. Add cocoa and let sit 5 minutes. Add melted chocolate, agave syrup, vanilla, 2/3 cup coconut oil, and 2/3 teaspoon kosher salt and process until mixture is very smooth and thick, about 30 seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.671', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.675');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f3540133-e30f-43bd-bf9d-b086f6712110', 'Scrape filling into cooled tart shell and smooth top (if making tart in a rectangular shell, you may have a little filling left over; save for another use, like truffles). Tap tart lightly against counter to pop any air bubbles in filling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.675', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.675');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6617df4-3761-494b-9ae7-d15b1898492f', 'Cook oats and remaining 1 teaspoon coconut oil in a small skillet over low heat, stirring constantly, until oats are toasted, about 3 minutes. Gradually add half of demerara sugar, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted, then remove from heat and stir in remaining demerara sugar just to coat. Season with kosher salt; let oat mixture cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.679', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.675');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('696df1bd-68a0-4bbc-b224-0ea5a0a41004', 'Scatter oat mixture over tart, sprinkle with sea salt, and chill until filling is set, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.683', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.676');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bad87eb0-89f3-4ccb-8d5b-80031c125aba', 'Cut chilled tart into slices with a dry, hot knife; let sit at room temperature 15–20 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.687', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.677');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81da537d-08f9-43b1-bb54-b78cb80681dd', 'Tart can be made 2 days ahead. Once filling is set, cover and keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.691', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.677');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1991580b-9c62-48c1-94ef-e0516d4c837d', '• In a saucepan over low heat, warm the oil. Add the onion, cumin, cayenne, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and sauté until the onions start to caramelize, about 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.695', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.678');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6762db5d-43ef-4a4c-8413-4a3ec06fef6d', '• Stir in the garlic and chile and sauté for 2 minutes more. Add the tomato paste, tomato sauce, vinegar, and water. Mix well, and simmer until it starts to thicken, about 5 to 7 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.699', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.678');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ecf12b5-adba-4b9a-b0c9-9b8600cfd2cd', '• Transfer all the ingredients to an upright blender, add the white pepper, and puree until smooth. Season with additional salt to taste. Store in a tightly sealed jar in the ­refrigerator.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.702', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.679');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9dacbc0a-670c-4f51-9df5-af662e34416b', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Toss broccoli and 3 tablespoons oil in large bowl to coat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Transfer to rimmed baking sheet. Roast 15 minutes. Stir remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil, garlic, and red pepper in small bowl. Drizzle garlic mixture over broccoli; toss to coat. Roast until broccoli is beginning to brown, about 8 minutes longer. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.706', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.679');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d4bab76-4548-4025-97ca-9018024cc592', '4. For the dressing, put the ginger, mustard, oil and vinegar in a bowl and, using a hand-held blender, blend until combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.203', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('695f957b-d1c7-4e57-8a9e-0fa0ed466d81', 'Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until beans are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain. Rinse beans under cold water to cool. Dry beans on clean towels. Chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.71', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.68');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c612f409-99af-466a-96bc-eb7bd77cd511', 'Combine beans and radishes in large bowl. Whisk remaining ingredients to blend in small bowl. Add enough dressing to beans and radishes to season to taste. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.713', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.681');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6d5a2d90-7145-47b0-8140-d309a64d59f1', 'Heat vegetable oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then stir-fry garlic, ginger, and red pepper flakes until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add sugar snaps and snow peas and stir-fry until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add frozen peas and stir-fry until hot, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat, then stir in soy sauce and sesame oil. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.717', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.681');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7493b008-e422-47a2-8f52-cae1a5e38b17', 'Stir together tomatoes, cucumber, scallions, parsley, and salt and pepper to taste. Squeeze lemon juice over salad and stir. Drizzle oil over salad and stir.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.721', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.681');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47954199-45c0-4559-80d1-ac44198127cb', 'Cook onion, bay leaves, and lentils in a large saucepan of simmering salted water until lentils are tender but still firm, 15–20 minutes. Drain; discard onion and bay leaves and transfer lentils to a medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.725', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d98440b-25fa-43c9-ba0e-5f47f2b5c658', 'Heat oil in a small skillet over medium. Cook coriander seeds and cumin seeds, swirling skillet, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add spice mixture and vinegar to lentils, season with salt and pepper, and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.729', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('779ea71b-6547-4e59-9638-7a058f0f979c', 'Just before serving, top lentils with radishes, scallions, herbs, and celery; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.732', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('97e7620b-84e6-466c-9c0f-34308322c737', 'Lentils (without herbs and vegetables) can be marinated 3 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.736', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa17bf14-6078-4c25-9a17-66a7e9e285e7', 'Squeeze juice from lemon halves into large bowl; add lemon halves. Fill bowl with water. Trim stem of 1 artichoke. Starting at base, bend leaves back and snap off where leaves break naturally, continuing until all tough outer leaves have been removed. Using small sharp knife, trim outside of base until smooth and no dark green areas remain. Cut artichoke lengthwise in half. Using tip of knife, remove any purple-tipped leaves from center. Add artichoke to lemon water. Repeat with remaining artichokes. Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Drain artichokes. Add to boiling water; cook until just tender, about 8 minutes. Drain; set aside. (Can be made 1 day ahead; cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.682');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68c876eb-0487-4582-979f-bd1e0ed46157', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Spray 3 large rimmed baking sheets with nonstick spray. Arrange artichoke halves, fennel and leeks in single layer on 2 prepared sheets. Arrange asparagus and carrots in single layer on third sheet. Brush vegetables with olive oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast vegetables until tender, turning over halfway through, about 35 minutes total for artichokes, fennel and leeks and 20 minutes total for asparagus and carrots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.744', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.683');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43da6a8a-c9a8-4c02-9e85-bfb3d48793d1', 'Divide vegetables among 6 plates. Drizzle Salsa Verde over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.748', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.683');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('309a2780-b05b-4c56-a4b2-b945afab7311', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Cut top 1/4 inch off heads of garlic to expose cloves. Place garlic in small baking dish. Add oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Turn garlic cut side up. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake until garlic skins are golden brown and cloves are tender, about 55 minutes. Cool. Squeeze garlic cloves from skins.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.752', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.683');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ba688d3c-a4d3-4f93-a48c-8db9e457a5d8', 'Mix all frozen berries, jelly, and sugar in large nonstick skillet. Let stand until berries thaw and mixture is juicy, stirring occasionally and breaking strawberries into smaller pieces with spoon, about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.756', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.683');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c6ca5c9-a398-4e9e-9c3c-70bad477c4b3', 'Boil until mixture thickens but is still chunky, stirring frequently, about 7 minutes. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Cover and chill. Rewarm over medium heat, stirring frequently.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.76', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.684');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e54f47c5-2c0d-41c0-a000-2d06b338e9da', 'Combine garlic and a pinch of salt in a large salad bowl. Mash to a paste with a fork. Mix in vinegar, then oil and chives; season with salt and pepper. Add greens and herbs and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.684');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c397b10-904e-4ff8-91ee-b09bd6c24c1a', 'In a bowl wash rice well in several changes of cold water until water is clear. Soak rice in cold water to cover overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.768', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.684');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c34d401-f1ad-4e82-aed6-e0a12b4c2830', 'Drain rice well in a sieve. Set sieve over a large deep saucepan of simmering water (sieve should not touch water) and steam rice, covered with a kitchen towel and a lid, 30 to 40 minutes, or until tender (check water level in pan occasionally, adding more water if necessary).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.771', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.685');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa325a47-88f7-4cf4-9d46-3dfcf88c74d7', 'While rice is cooking, in a small saucepan bring 1 cup coconut milk to a boil with 1/3 cup sugar and salt, stirring until sugar is dissolved, and remove from heat. Keep mixture warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.775', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.686');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e3e40ca-efd2-4847-bdbe-84cf71c28359', 'Transfer cooked rice to a bowl and stir in coconut-milk mixture. Let rice stand, covered, 30 minutes, or until coconut-milk mixture is absorbed. Rice may be prepared up to this point 2 hours ahead and kept covered at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.779', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.686');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ccd86b7d-0b9b-4210-b9d7-236a5cf49757', 'While rice is standing, in cleaned small pan slowly boil remaining 1/3 cup coconut milk with remaining 3 tablespoons sugar, stirring occasionally, 1 minute. Transfer sauce to a small bowl and chill until cool and thickened slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.783', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.686');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('553cb0ac-bf8a-452f-9436-9022c31d2eb3', 'To serve, mold 1/4 cup servings of sticky rice on dessert plates. Drizzle desserts with sauce and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Divide mango slices among plates.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.786', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.688');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5a3adb2-7e07-4dac-9ceb-917efc81f7be', 'Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté shallots, ginger, and garlic, stirring, 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.791', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.688');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70c30cd1-edfe-4056-b7c1-1668a30e7b17', 'Add peas and sauté, stirring, 2 minutes. Add water and simmer, stirring occasionally, until peas are crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.795', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.688');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cdc987ed-7afd-4f33-9c19-4a55130e0bc0', 'Purée herbs, oil, and salt in a blender until smooth, then pour through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, pressing hard on and then discarding solids. Chill if not using immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.8', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.689');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e5f8b357-8064-4ea9-b617-8ba8c00f798b', 'Combine walnuts, sugar, 2 teaspoons oil, and 1 tablespoon vinegar in medium nonstick skillet. Stir over medium heat until syrup coats nuts thickly, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer nuts to piece of foil. Separate nuts; freeze on foil 5 minutes or cool completely at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.804', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.69');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('def3f543-6df3-4db0-87ad-11dbf455bb53', '5. Drizzle the dressing over the salad and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.207', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('17176be1-38bc-414f-866b-af6e8e05ec77', 'Whisk remaining 1/4 cup oil, 2 1/2 tablespoons vinegar, and garlic in large bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Add Bibb lettuce, radicchio, haricots verts, and nuts; toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.808', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.69');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('144092b0-d387-4e37-9e55-1ac5a02b3591', 'Place the dates in a small bowl, cover with the water, and soak for about 1 hour, or until soft. Drain, reserving the liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.812', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.691');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c14df5d5-1284-4401-ab24-62c3ff123845', 'To make the nut kreme, place the soaked nuts and half of the dates in a blender and blend slowly, adding up to 1/4 cup of the reserved soaking liquid, until the mixture is smooth yet thick.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.816', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.691');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0762129a-968e-4176-a2ed-de8d00dc6a4a', 'To make the raspberry sauce, blend the remaining half of the dates, the raspberries, and the remaining 1/4 cup of the reserved (soaking) liquid until smooth. The sauce should have a thin consistency; if needed, add additional filtered water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.82', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.692');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7abb039a-50a7-481d-8934-607a3c882e2e', 'To prepare the parfaits, starting from the top, cut the figs lengthwise into quarters (leaving the bottoms intact) and gently press open. Spoon some of the nut kreme into the middle of each fig. Arrange the parfaits on a platter and drizzle raspberry sauce over the top of each parfait. Garnish with the fresh mint leaves or shredded coconut.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.823', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.692');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('875336e1-ba65-49dc-b70b-30c8a45cd940', 'Combine bok choy, apple, carrot, and chopped onion in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.828', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.693');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f91d4508-2e1f-4114-ae22-5b8d9cf45b10', 'Blend soy milk, cashews, vinegar, raisins, and mustard in a food processor or high-powered blender. Add desired amount to chopped vegetables.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.832', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.693');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f43e13a4-c151-4b85-a745-f215c03be453', 'Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover; chill.) Spoon fruit into 6 small bowls or goblets. Drizzle Papaya-Mint Sauce over fruit. Sprinkle with coconut. Garnish with mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.836', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.694');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('366618ac-b641-4ff9-b67b-b8ae59218fe7', 'Mix Campari and orange juice in a small bowl. Divide sorbet among 4 small serving bowls or coffee cups. Pour 2 Tbsp. Campari mixture into each bowl. Top with orange zest.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.84', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.694');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2b07d8a-3c55-44c3-a089-86deb0a47746', 'Cook cauliflower florets in a large pot of boiling salted water until just crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Drain cauliflower. Transfer to a rimmed baking sheet and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.844', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.695');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f24bd5c8-68ff-4d44-8100-04a663bb460e', 'Meanwhile, combine vinegar, onion, sugar, mustard seeds, dry mustard, and celery seeds in a large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.848', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.696');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c847769b-82af-4326-9faa-d2931c7210fc', 'Add cauliflower to saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until cauliflower is tender, about 3 minutes. Transfer mixture and pickling juices to a 1-quart jar. Let cool slightly, cover, and chill. Serve within 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.852', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.696');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c8b6208-70fc-4e66-9ff7-330ba6b0379d', 'Place peppers and shallots in medium bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.857', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.697');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1576006c-7d0b-47db-8435-110ab7781e0a', 'Mix vinegar and next 6 ingredients in medium saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar and salt. Remove brine from heat; carefully pour over peppers and shallots. Cover bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Uncover; cool to room temperature. Transfer to quart-size jar, pressing peppers into brine. Cover; chill at least 4 hours and up to 10 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.697');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6612e7bf-b882-4e91-8d2d-f07a6747de10', 'Heat olive oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion, chopped celery and chopped green bell peppers and sauté until vegetables begin to soften, about 7 minutes. Add tomatoes and 1/2 cup reserved juice and bring to simmer. Add corn. Reduce heat to medium, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Mix in ginger, lemon peel and black pepper. Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft and corn is tender but not mushy, adding more reserved tomato juice if mixture is dry, about 10 minutes longer. Season to taste with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.865', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.698');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('224c8238-2ace-4d85-84cc-79322186167a', 'Peel a 1-inch-wide strip of skin lengthwise from each eggplant half opposite cut side. Sprinkle eggplants with salt on both sides and let drain on a rack set over a shallow baking pan 20 minutes. Rinse eggplants well, then firmly squeeze out moisture and pat dry with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.869', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.699');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('34d13927-8c84-4604-bc36-383fbc976888', 'Stir together soy sauce and mirin in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.873', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.699');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c5b8eee-d347-465d-917f-5e4784e93e75', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy nonstick skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then fry eggplants, peeled sides down, until undersides are browned, 5 to 6 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.877', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.7');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b7a5ef8-cff3-44d8-8cbe-db5911e45565', 'Turn over and brush with soy mixture. Fry eggplants until tender, 4 to 6 minutes more, then add remaining soy mixture to skillet and cook, turning eggplants once or twice, until liquid is absorbed, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.881', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.702');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8de7245b-d6b7-4722-a584-b7c3bb408167', '*Available at Asian markets, specialty foods shops, and Uwajimaya (800-889-1928).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.884', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.702');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1da897c9-5d6b-4615-91de-e1e0ebc22eb3', 'Combine cucumber, cabbage, and onion in a bowl. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in saucepan, stirring, and immediately pour over cucumber mixture. Toss mixture and let stand at room temperature, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. To cool quickly, chill in freezer 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.888', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.703');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('00479113-3063-4dba-a67e-db533c672832', 'Whisk 4 tablespoons oil, vinegar, and horseradish in large bowl to blend. Add beets and onion; toss to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.892', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.704');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8280298f-9493-4ee6-bf9a-fbcc41309119', 'Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add cabbage and toss until wilted and just crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Stir into beet mixture. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Let stand 10 minutes before serving, stirring occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.895', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.704');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ddb3d061-4b55-4d9f-a747-632402ab6cab', 'This vinegar can be found at specialty foods stores. Regular balsamic can be substituted.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.899', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.705');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee716da7-8301-45a6-a801-3c1907917b32', 'Whisk white wine vinegar, curry powder,and pressed garlic in medium bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in olive oil. Season dressing to taste with salt and freshly ground pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.903', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.705');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f301087-da6a-4011-baa7-6ef5e5719b64', 'Cook lentils and kohlrabi leaves in heavy large saucepan of boiling salted water until lentils are barely tender but not too soft, about 6 minutes. Drain; rinse under cold water to cool. Drain again.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.907', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.706');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a992f921-a704-46f3-8391-1ef38c8890d5', 'Bring 1 1/4 cups water to boil in same saucepan; remove from heat. Add 3 tablespoons dressing, sprinkle with salt, then stir in couscous. Cover pot and let stand 5 minutes. Transfer couscous to medium bowl. Fluff couscous with fork to separate grains and cool slightly. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.911', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.706');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46a76345-a995-4dd9-87da-9c1e38f1450a', 'Meanwhile, transfer lentils to large bowl. Add 1/2 cup dressing, diced kohlrabi bulb, and chopped green onions; toss to coat. Season mixture to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.706');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7344030e-dd8a-465c-9d4f-ce50251085a6', 'Arrange baby spinach leaves over large rimmed platter. Drizzle spinach with 2 to 3 tablespoons remaining dressing. Sprinkle spinach leaves with salt and pepper. Mound lentil mixture in center of platter over spinach leaves. Stir mint into couscous. Spoon couscous around lentils and serve with remaining dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.919', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.707');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('261b41fc-6d74-496f-b3dd-7e4a5d7595a9', 'Bring sugar and water to a boil in a 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer syrup, without stirring, washing down any sugar crystals on side of pan with a pastry brush dipped in cold water, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.922', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.707');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4eaa521b-32bb-401e-8180-b3331b769b35', 'While syrup simmers, cut oranges, including peel and pith, into 1-inch pieces, discarding any seeds, and combine with cranberries, cinnamon, and cloves in a food processor.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.926', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.708');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49c9ed44-dd13-4026-9e2b-275905e9bfdb', 'Add sugar syrup and pulse until fruit is finely chopped. Transfer relish to a bowl and stir in ginger. Chill, covered, 1 day for flavors to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.709');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c38c67e3-26b0-467d-b3b2-5225a930a1b2', 'Stir water and sugar in small saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and bring to boil. Add kumquats and return to boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until fruit is tender and liquid is syrupy, about 20 minutes. Transfer to bowl; cool to room temperature. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.935', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.709');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('688355ec-ae1f-4238-9296-4f657a3c94b4', 'Wash rice in several changes of water until water runs clear, then drain rice well in a sieve. Bring rice and 3 cups water to a boil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan and cook, covered, over very low heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Remove pan from heat and let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Fluff rice gently with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.939', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.709');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee41db72-03fe-40f0-852f-4e57547d7ad0', 'Heat oil in a deep 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then cook mustard seeds, stirring, until seeds begin to pop. Add ginger and 1/4 cup peanuts and cook, stirring, 2 minutes. Add turmeric, rice, and salt to taste, stirring to coat rice thoroughly. Remove skillet from heat and stir in lemon juice. Sprinkle with remaining peanuts and zest.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.943', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.71');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91f8c49c-2cee-4972-bdfa-e8c58ec97a2f', 'Combine water, sugar, allspice and cinnamon in heavy small saucepan. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat and simmer until liquid is reduced to 3/4 cup, about 2 minutes. Cool syrup completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.71');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22f83702-8b45-4ae4-8dec-07da3cb91f50', 'Puree 1 1/2 pounds plums in processor. Press enough puree through sieve to measure 1 1/2 cups. Strain syrup into puree and blend well. Transfer mixture to 9x5x3-inch glass loaf dish. Freeze plum mixture until flaky crystals form, stirring every 30 minutes, about 4 hours. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover; keep frozen.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.711');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4d7879d-c379-46ec-91f1-ebfdf3d44cbe', 'Spoon granita into 4 glass goblets. Top with peach, nectarine and plum slices and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.955', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.712');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2dce7e4-4bf3-435c-92ca-f210ec1cfbe4', 'Place the curry paste in a medium saucepan over medium heat and cook, stirring, for 1 minute or until fragrant. Add the coconut milk, water, salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Add the broccoli, cover and cook for 10 minutes or until the broccoli is tender. Remove from the heat and add the spinach leaves and half the cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.96', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.712');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12048384-b9e2-4cd2-9089-676e8781d2d0', 'Using an immersion blender, blend the soup until smooth. Divide among serving bowls and top with the extra spinach, remaining cilantro, scallions and shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.712');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f375c5c2-ebaf-4d9b-876e-6956db7cf137', 'Bring water, sugar, and lemon juice to a boil in a 2- to 3-quart saucepan. Scrape seeds from vanilla bean into saucepan using tip of a paring knife and add pod. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar has dissolved, then boil until reduced to about 1 cup, 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in Sambuca.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.713');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f4efecd-f8bc-4f03-b1a2-dcd280499c5b', 'Transfer syrup to a bowl and let cool completely. Stir in strawberries and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes to 1 hour. Discard pod.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.972', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.713');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e5aa169-32b2-4148-a527-6a0367af7e11', 'Add enough hot water to porcini soaking liquid to measure 3/4 cup if necessary. Heat liquid in small saucepan to 105°F to 115°F. Pour into processor. Sprinkle yeast over. Let stand until yeast dissolves, about 12 minutes. Add oil, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon rosemary. Process 3 seconds. Add 2 cups plus 2 tablespoons flour and process until moist clumps form, adding more flour if necessary. Mix in olives, using 4 on/off turns. Turn out dough into large bowl. Add porcini and knead until mixed in (dough will be firm and sticky).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.976', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.713');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b932b05-fab0-477b-92ee-a1b2d11a87a9', 'Generously flour heavy large baking sheet. Turn out dough onto sheet. Using floured hands, press out dough to irregular 13 x 9-inch rectangle. Sprinkle dough with remaining 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon rosemary. Cover baking sheet with plastic wrap. Let dough rise in warm draft-free area until puffy, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.98', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.714');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b9d27f7-f533-4bce-a871-8c4fe2be0d17', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Bake bread until crusty, about 25 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.985', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.714');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eca70362-f499-414d-bf6e-49028338c240', 'Combine porcini and water in medium bowl. Let stand until porcini soften, about 40 minutes. Pour mixture into strainer set over small bowl. Press porcini to release excess liquid. Coarsely chop porcini. Pour soaking liquid into measuring cup, leaving any sediment behind; reserve soaking liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.989', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.714');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42146c53-fe38-43d1-93c4-349968a0d26a', 'Peel layers from carrot lengthwise on one side with peeler until you begin to get wide slices. Peel wide strips, reserving them, until you get about 15 (there will be a few extra).', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.993', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.715');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('19469ccd-1a8a-4aa8-ab85-4061c53ce9cb', 'Bring water and sugar to a boil in a small heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Add wide carrot strips and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Strain through a sieve into a bowl, discarding syrup. Let stand 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:27.997', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.715');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c455fad-bdb2-4b40-9d9b-851245d17d29', 'Preheat oven to 225°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.002', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.715');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8416e0e2-092c-4be2-8314-df38fc1fd118', 'Line a large baking sheet with nonstick liner, then arrange candied carrot slices flat in 1 layer on sheet. Bake until dry but still flexible, about 30 minutes. (Leave oven on.) Wind carrot strips, 1 at a time, around end of handle of a wooden spoon in a loose spiral, then slip off each curl and return, seam sides down, to lined baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.006', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.715');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49a3bbf8-af82-4626-ad7d-cbd9612bcbd6', 'Return curls to oven to dry until crisp, 30 to 45 minutes more. Cool completely on baking sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.01', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.717');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c05de229-a6f6-4c19-8d42-e504aca7b7d7', 'Place strawberries in a 1-qt. heatproof jar. Bring vinegar, sugar, salt, and 2/3 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar and salt. Pour over strawberries. Let cool; cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.015', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.717');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3229a45a-392e-40dd-b8e7-13c4c67b1c8c', 'Puree mangoes, syrup and lime juice in processor until smooth. Transfer mixture to pie plate. Freeze, stirring occasionally until slushy, about 2 hours. Continue freezing until firm. Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. Break up into chunks. Return mixture to processor and process until smooth. Serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.027', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.718');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('078f4148-72b4-476a-a1b6-77c3010a9b83', 'In a saucepan simmer water with sugar, stirring, until sugar dissolves. In a blender purée watermelon, sugar syrup, lemon juice, and 1/2 cup raspberries and strain though a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing hard on solids. (Chill mixture, covered, until cold, about 2 hours.) Freeze mixture in an ice-cream maker. Serve scoops garnished with remaining 1/2 cup raspberries. (Sorbet may be made 1 week ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.032', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.718');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d32e2f3d-052b-4e82-8634-072aeea22ab7', 'Finely grate enough peel from oranges to measure 1 1/2 tablespoons. Combine 1 1/4 cups water, sugar, and 1 1/2 tablespoons orange peel in heavy medium saucepan. Stir over high heat until sugar dissolves and syrup boils; remove syrup from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.036', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.719');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('62821f24-ea52-46bb-b7ed-cbe04d784f80', 'Cut all peel and pith from oranges. Working over bowl to catch juices, cut between membranes to release orange segments. Discard any seeds. Transfer orange mixture to processor; puree until smooth, about 30 seconds. Measure 2 1/3 cups orange puree and mix into orange syrup (reserve any remaining puree for another use). Cover orange mixture; refrigerate at least 6 hours and up to 1 day to blend flavors.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.04', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.719');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fd0841b8-05df-4cf9-9c32-5b65207b2420', 'Process orange mixture in ice cream maker according to manufacturer''s instructions. Transfer to container; cover and freeze. (Can be made 2 days ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.045', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.72');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3072e6cd-a894-4967-9797-5360fccf78bc', 'Purée raspberries with juices and sugar in processor until smooth. Transfer mixture to strainer set over bowl; press on solids to extract as much liquid as possible; discard solids in strainer. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.05', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.721');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5634c92-70e2-40a0-a001-911ea71a7156', 'Bake chestnuts on a baking sheet in middle of oven until slightly dried and a shade darker, about 30 minutes. Cool chestnuts completely on a rack.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.054', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.721');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b464c55c-4b1f-465b-bbd1-c999d98ac7a3', 'Cook sugar in a dry 10- to 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderate heat, swirling and shaking skillet (to help sugar melt evenly), until caramel is deep golden. Remove from heat, then prop skillet up against a ramekin or metal cookie cutter, tilting it just enough for caramel to pool. Add 1 chestnut to caramel and evenly coat by turning with 2 forks, then transfer with forks to a sheet of foil to cool. Coat remaining chestnuts in same manner. (If caramel starts to harden, melt over moderately low heat, stirring.) Once completely cooled, peel chestnuts from foil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.058', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.721');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('319f5b03-689a-45f0-8742-5a9b61c5998a', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Oil a 3-qt. baking dish. Cook potatoes in a large pot of boiling salted water until very tender, about 12 minutes. Drain; let sit in colander 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.062', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.722');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1e96176-ef57-4cd3-8834-4f88c4fc4f91', 'Meanwhile, heat 1/2 cup syrup in a large skillet over medium-high. Add pecans, 3/4 tsp. salt, and 1 tsp. pepper and cook, stirring constantly, until syrup has evaporated and pecans are glazed, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a parchment-lined rimmed baking sheet and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.066', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.722');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2486990f-3b84-41c9-b2ca-7117affc410b', 'Purée potatoes, 1 1/2 cups water, and remaining 3/4 cup syrup, 1 1/4 tsp. salt, and 1/2 tsp. pepper in a food processor until smooth. Transfer potato mixture to prepared baking dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.07', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.723');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc8a5ffc-e7e1-419e-b592-3af45a154b8d', 'Coarsely chop pecans and sprinkle evenly over potato mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.074', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.723');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e08906af-e72e-446e-b89d-160d1514b61f', 'Bake casserole until top is lightly browned, about 40 minutes. Let sit 15 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.079', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.724');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('170bcbff-dce8-497e-a735-bc0a6d6203c2', 'Casserole can be assembled, without topping, 2 days ahead; cover and chill. Candied pecans can be made 2 days ahead; store in an airtight container at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.082', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.724');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fda60fdc-6a6b-4a43-b99d-450c152b0c71', 'In a small bowl, combine butter, orange zest, orange juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; stir well to combine. Set the citrus butter aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.086', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.725');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5d7a431-4a7d-4c48-bee2-d48e0e5a0e1a', 'Peel the carrots and parsnips and cut them lengthwise into long wedges, which that will get a bit browned and crisp at the ends. If I am roasting young carrots small enough to cook whole or halved lengthwise, I like to leave a half inch or so of the greens attached—looks pretty. Parsnips will cook at about the same rate as carrots, so cut them into similar-size pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.09', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.725');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a1bd549-57be-444a-a5d9-ac0c0eb1cc98', 'On a rimmed baking sheet, toss vegetables with oil; season with 1 teaspoon salt and toss again. Spread the vegetables flat and roast until tender and lightly browned (and more than lightly browned on the thinner edges), tossing halfway through, 20 to 30 minutes. If they seem to be getting too browned before tender, sprinkle them with a little water and keep roasting.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.094', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.726');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b630f969-abea-44d1-8818-46d5247cefd3', 'When vegetables are roasted, place in a warmed dish and spoon the citrus butter on, tossing them gently to melt the butter and coat the roots. Serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.727');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b48063bc-0b1f-42ab-bcfd-f784d78b4c52', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Toss tomatoes, oil, garlic, and cumin seeds in 13x9x2-inch glass baking dish. Roast until tomatoes are slightly wrinkled and softened, about 13 minutes. Cool slightly. Mix in orange juice and orange peel. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer relish to small bowl. do ahead Can be made 1 day ahead; chill. Bring to room temperature before serving. Stir in basil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.102', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.727');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74721e60-3eac-48d1-b87b-ad280b855e45', 'In a blender or a food processor, combine the soy milk, soy powder, coconut flour, agave nectar, and vanilla. Blend the ingredients for 2 minutes. With the machine running, slowly add the oil and the lemon juice, alternating between the two until both are fully incorporated. Pour the mixture into an airtight container and refrigerate for 6 hours or for up to 1 month. (If you plan to use it as a sauce, store the mixture at room temperature for up to 1 week.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.106', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.728');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a5b6dd0-723d-453b-8de3-278d759a1302', 'Using a homogenizing juicer with the blank plate in place, homogenize the garbanzo beans and parsley and place in a large bowl. Place the tahini, lemon juice, onion, cumin, and Braggs in a blender and blend. Stir the tahini mixture into the garbanzo paste. In a spice grinder, grind the sesame seeds into a fine powder. Mix into the garbanzo paste. Press into 1/4-inch-thick crusts, each 4 or 8 inches in diameter. Dehydrate for 12 to 14 hours, flipping at least once during the drying time.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.11', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.728');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a82ce278-c498-4c5d-b7fe-a9174c85b80d', 'Combine hoisin sauce and vinegar in a bowl. Slowly whisk in both of the oils until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.304', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.816');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9e1e1d5-bc1a-4924-b42f-01aa10f43898', 'combine mesclun and water chestnuts in large bowl and toss with enough vinaigrette to lightly coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.308', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.817');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f74e8330-13d4-43a5-8bb1-4187c0434521', 'In a small saucepan stir together the sugar, the water, the lemon juice, and the ginger root and simmer the mixture, covered, for 5 minutes. Add the apricots, baste them with the syrup, and poach them, covered, over moderately low heat for 3 minutes, or until they are just tender. Stir in the raspberries gently, poach the mixture for 1 minute, and divide it between 2 bowls. Sprinkle the compote with the almonds, garnish it with the mint, and serve it warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.114', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.729');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c730f3a8-c989-4826-984e-8813afd810fc', 'Cook carrots in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 7 minutes. Drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.119', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.729');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4780e6ee-0ffb-48b8-93ea-a9a8ea36a95b', 'Whisk oil, lemon juice, orange peel, and coriander in large bowl to blend. Add hot carrots and toss to coat. Cool, tossing occasionally. Season with salt and pepper. Drizzle with honey, if desired. Stir in olives and green onions. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.123', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.73');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ec3a086-0abd-4274-8dd8-085d71091bd5', 'Stir salad to redistribute dressing. Garnish edges of platter with orange slices and parsley. Mound carrots in center.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.126', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.731');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa8f96d1-4220-4f43-9a43-45a3e2dd2323', 'In a bowl whisk together the lemon juice, the vinegar, the garlic paste, the gingerroot, the cumin, the cayenne, and salt and pepper to taste, add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.13', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.731');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcddacb1-aa44-4199-be1a-33ab239885ed', 'In a large bowl stir together the chick-peas, the bell peppers, the scallions, the coriander, and the dressing and chill the salad, covered, overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.134', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.732');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b94c2c0-410e-4748-8c49-b1880a1644f1', '1. Purée the peaches in a blender and strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a medium glass or metal bowl, pressing on the solids with a rubber spatula to remove as much liquid as possible. Discard the solids. You should have about 2 cups of purée. Add the tea, sugar, vodka, and corn syrup and stir until the sugar dissolves. Cover and refrigerate until the mixture is very cold (under 40°F), at least 4 hours, then mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.138', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.734');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1c454ec9-b80c-412d-8561-7d3d8fd874b0', '2. Churn the sorbet in an ice cream maker according to the manufacturer''s instructions. When finished, the sorbet will be thick and soft and can be served as a slushy. To make the sorbet firm enough to scoop, transfer into an airtight container, press plastic wrap directly onto the surface of the sorbet, and freeze until firm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.141', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.735');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51b406c4-e739-4193-bef5-dc233f14da87', 'Cut ends from each plantain with a sharp small knife, then cut a lengthwise slit through peel. Cut plantains crosswise into 1-inch-thick pieces and, beginning at slit, pry off peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.145', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.735');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('952bf151-dcdb-4bf8-8802-76d8f3be8f4e', 'Heat 1/2 inch oil in a deep 10- to 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until just hot enough to sizzle when a piece of plantain is added. Fry plantains in 2 batches, turning occasionally with tongs, until tender and just golden, 5 to 7 minutes per batch. Transfer plantains to paper towels to drain, reserving oil in skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.149', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.736');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cd5d7407-b23d-4051-ac0e-e7b6a9d449cc', 'Flatten each plantain to 1/4 inch thick with a tostone press or bottom of a heavy saucepan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.153', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.736');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68e2403e-acd4-4456-a2f7-f9449b019b8b', 'Stir together warm water and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bowl. Heat reserved oil over medium heat until it shimmers. Dip a flattened plantain in salted water and gently place, without patting dry, in hot oil. (Plantains will not spatter.) Repeat with several more pieces and fry plantains (without crowding) in 4 or 5 batches, turning occasionally, until golden, about 3 minutes per batch. Transfer with tongs to clean paper towels to drain. Season with salt and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.737');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d413e7a-2b1a-4d6f-aa6f-c17f1f0ad1f4', 'Bring vinegar, oil, sugar, and 1/4 teaspoon salt to a simmer in a small saucepan. Stir in shallots and remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.16', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.737');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9e43961-3f1d-4596-88f5-38b8b81d1872', 'Bring water to a simmer in a large pot, then add kale, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook, uncovered, stirring, until kale is wilted and crisp-tender and liquid has evaporated, 5 to 8 minutes. Toss with shallot mixture, then season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.164', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.737');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e735e268-2983-4658-a82d-6567343094ef', 'Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, oregano, basil, marjoram and crushed red pepper. Cover and cook until onion is translucent, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; simmer gently, uncovered, until sauce thickens and measures 8 cups total, breaking up tomatoes with spoon and stirring occasionally, about 1 hour 15 minutes. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cool slightly. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.168', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.738');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ecfa92fa-c023-48ca-9269-c2713cb4db81', 'In a large skillet, heat the vegetable oil over medium heat. Add the onions and cook, tossing and stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until softened. Reduce the heat to low and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for another 50 to 60 minutes, or until the onions are completely soft and caramelized. They will look dark brown and mushy. Remove from the heat and add the salt, pepper, and thyme and mix well to combine. The onions will keep in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.172', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.739');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25894436-5761-4c1f-a9e4-d2e5ec5840a2', 'Divide soup among 6 soup bowls. Garnish with: Additional sliced green onions', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.176', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.739');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8888220c-a24d-46d2-aaf3-e11bad0820f5', 'Cook beets in large pot of boiling salted water until tender when pierced with skewer, about 30 minutes. Drain. Cool slightly. Peel and cut beets into 1/4- to 1/2-inch-thick slices; set aside. Combine beet greens and 3 tablespoons water in large skillet. Cover and cook over medium-high heat until greens are wilted, about 1 minute; set aside. Cook potato in small saucepan of boiling salted water until tender, about 15 minutes. Drain. Return to saucepan and mash.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.18', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.74');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf9eab56-9a8d-4664-ba12-f28aed0ff79e', 'Blend walnuts, breadcrumbs, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, garlic, and 2 tablespoons water in processor until smooth. Transfer to bowl. Mix in 1/2 cup mashed potato, 1/4 cup olive oil, and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. If thick, thin sauce with 2 to 3 tablespoons water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.184', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.74');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e21eba66-67a0-4332-b426-98f7c619243a', 'Spoon sauce onto center of platter; drizzle with 2 tablespoons oil. Surround with beet greens and beet slices; drizzle with vinegar. Sprinkle with capers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.187', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.741');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3166db04-3c10-4211-bca5-777736833faf', '1. For the lentils, put them in a saucepan, cover with water, bring to a boil the reduce the heat and simmer for about 15–20 minutes, or until all the liquid has evaporated and the lentils are not mushy and still with a bite.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.191', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.741');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('540c8c62-350d-4633-8f92-4c208ed88588', '2. As soon as the lentils are cooked transfer them to a large bowl and leave to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.196', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7488974a-d178-4f6f-903a-19d4f85f8535', '3. Once the lentils are cool, add the beetroot, spring onions, hazelnuts and herbs and stir until everything is combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.199', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.742');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e64f780-15e5-4802-ab84-1bd7ce3ba574', 'Combine 2 1/2 cups water, sugar and cinnamon sticks in large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add figs and simmer uncovered 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Mix in apricots, cherries and then brandy. Return to heat and simmer uncovered until all fruits are tender but still retain shape, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in crystallized ginger. Cool. (Compote can be prepared 3 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.) Serve at room temperature or chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.743');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f53ed86-c150-4e7f-a604-8dbcdea4287c', 'Gently mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.215', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.743');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7dd7397-6b0e-400e-8fe7-e6d0ae2710a9', 'The skinny 48 calories per cup 0.6 g fat (0.1 g saturated), 2 g fiber, 11 g carbs, 2.2 g protein', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.219', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.744');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('28f61973-089c-47be-b78b-ed38f3ee1a5f', 'Bring vinegar, sugar, salt, and 2 cups water to a boil in a medium pot over high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.223', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.755');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d3edcd6f-526b-40d8-ab91-155d235a85b3', 'Place garlic, chile, mushrooms, and red pepper flakes in a heatproof resealable container or jar (divide among several containers if necessary). Pour hot brining liquid over mushroom mixture. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.226', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.761');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa163e09-57b9-4e6c-8d9a-7f079d8f9784', 'In a pitcher stir together the orange juice, the pineapple juice, and the lemon juice. Fill tall glasses with ice cubes, drizzle a little grenadine into each glass, and pour in the orange juice mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.23', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.765');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d425eae-fb62-4e09-b6eb-559c7d7ddc5a', 'Cut tofu crosswise into 6 slices. Arrange in 1 layer on a triple layer of paper towels and top with another triple layer of towels. Weight with a shallow baking pan or baking sheet and let stand 2 minutes. Repeat weighting with dry paper towels 2 more times.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.234', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.777');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68da83cb-3070-4bf3-9bb2-1512d83f9366', 'Stir together soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, ginger, garlic, Tabasco, and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a glass pie plate. Add tofu slices in 1 layer and marinate, turning over every couple of minutes, 8 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.238', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.777');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4814e8b0-0202-4f05-824d-e304f2084a72', 'Heat a lightly oiled well-seasoned ridged grill pan over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking. Lift tofu from marinade with a slotted spatula (reserve marinade) and grill, turning over once carefully with spatula, until grill marks appear and tofu is heated through, 4 to 6 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.78');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1c122df9-c6e1-4918-9aac-1b03bb116dd7', 'While tofu grills, heat remaining teaspoon vegetable oil in a 12-inch skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté greens, tossing with tongs, until beginning to wilt. Add reserved marinade and sauté, tossing, until greens are just wilted, about 1 minute. Lift greens from skillet with tongs, letting excess marinade drip off, and divide between 2 plates.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.245', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.78');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef3609d7-ee29-4135-b654-a7d6c9b94ec0', 'Serve greens with tofu slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.249', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.805');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f09833b-c1ed-4fa3-b340-f36db1ba500b', 'Purée all ingredients and 1/4 cup water in a food processor until smooth. Set a fine-mesh strainer over a small pitcher; strain, pressing on solids to extract about 1 1/4 cups purée. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.252', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.805');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('330909eb-09a6-4068-a0f7-2a86712b4f20', 'Purée all ingredients and 3 tablespoons water in a food processor until smooth. Set a fine-mesh strainer over a small pitcher; strain, pressing on solids to extract about 1 1/4 cups purée.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.256', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.806');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4b0cc6d-bef9-46b2-a751-5e6b68d32be6', 'Pour 1 tablespoon strawberry purée into each mold; freeze until just firm, about 30 minutes. Add 1 tablespoon blueberry purée to each mold. Freeze until just firm, about 30 minutes. Repeat until molds are filled. Cover; insert ice-pop sticks. Freeze until firm. Dip bottoms of molds into hot water for 20-30 seconds to loosen pops. Remove pops from molds; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.259', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76cae7e4-b310-4311-9d77-f461524d3b04', 'Working in batches by type, cook beans in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 1–4 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to a large bowl of ice water; let cool. Drain and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.263', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.807');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9033ef73-650e-4271-ab66-c2f8e2140964', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a small skillet over medium and cook shallot, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 3 minutes. Add ginger, lemongrass, garlic, and coriander and cook, stirring, until very fragrant, about 1 minute. Transfer to a large bowl; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.267', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.808');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ae498a08-8178-476c-b479-66a9d7a4b7a6', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in same skillet over medium-high. Cook peanuts, tossing often, until golden brown and fragrant, about 2 minutes. Transfer to paper towels; let cool, then coarsely chop. Set aside 1 tablespoon peanuts for serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.271', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.808');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13e59555-8fc4-467d-9d57-870abf1b502e', 'Whisk kaffir lime leaves, lime zest, lime juice, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and remaining 3 tablespoons oil into shallot mixture. Add beans, remaining peanuts, and 1/3 cup cilantro and toss to coat; season with salt and pepper. Serve topped with more cilantro and reserved peanuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.275', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.809');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fff92c7-765d-45a7-9be1-4bb5c537a0d8', 'Juice the lime using a manual citrus juicer. Juice the remaining ingredients in a juice, and then combine with the lime juice. Store in an airtight glass container in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.278', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.809');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2caeb47e-9a74-4c24-8a0e-8d87ba324877', 'Cook onion, garlic, and red pepper flakes in oil in a small heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until pale golden, about 4 minutes. Whisk in remaining sauce ingredients. Simmer, whisking, 1 minute, then cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.282', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.812');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36aba80d-2be3-47b5-a49c-0c4095165f2f', 'Cover noodles with boiling-hot water and soak 15 minutes, then drain well in a sieve. Pat dry between paper towels and toss with vinegar and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.285', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.814');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2538d170-c3b4-439c-8c8f-e7bddd29dbcc', 'Put a double thickness of paper towel on a work surface and fill a shallow baking pan with warm water. Soak 1 rice-paper round (make sure there are no holes) in warm water until pliable, 30 seconds to 1 minute, then transfer to paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.289', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.814');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('865a844c-c55f-4bc0-b431-7835a9a95697', 'Arrange 1 piece of lettuce on bottom half of soaked rice paper, folding or tearing to fit and leaving a 1-inch border along edge. Spread one fourth of peanut sauce over lettuce and top with one fourth each of mint, basil, cabbage, and noodles. Roll up rice paper tightly around filling and, after rolling halfway, arrange one fourth of cilantro and carrot along crease. Then fold in sides and continue rolling. Transfer summer roll to a plate and cover with dampened paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.293', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.815');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c96dee16-0061-4152-8480-389da83e38be', 'Make 3 more rolls in same manner. Serve rolls halved on the diagonal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.297', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.815');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d100b034-1878-4199-a91e-8bcb57750aa4', 'Bring cranberries, sugar, Port, and zest to a simmer in a small heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until cranberries burst, about 12 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in juice. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.3', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.816');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('17c1e4ad-a9a3-47f3-9378-91776ed03ceb', 'Beat together besan, rice flour, and water in a bowl with a handheld electric mixer at high speed 6 minutes. Beat in nigella seeds and salt, then let stand, covered, at room temperature 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.315', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.818');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2cdad3d1-46a2-487b-8d3d-338cb9bdeb35', 'Test batter: Drop a teaspoon of it into a bowl of water. It should float, even though part may be submerged. If it sinks, batter should be beaten more, testing after each minute of mixing. Be careful not to overbeat, because that will produce a honeycomb texture, and then fritters will absorb too much oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.319', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.818');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36538083-67a1-4162-b071-e017b172ef3c', 'Cut eggplant lengthwise into 1/8-inch-thick slices, then halve each slice lengthwise, forming roughly 5- by 2-inch slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.819');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d04670b1-d49b-41e0-9f04-342725c61949', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking. Dip about 4 eggplant slices in batter, 1 at a time, letting excess drip off, and fry until browned and tender, about 1 minute on each side. (You will have just enough batter for all of eggplant.) Transfer to paper towels to drain. Keep fritters warm in 1 layer on a baking sheet in oven and fry remaining eggplant in batches in same manner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.326', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.819');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33b1cccb-1c54-4f3c-9d67-6265293e4b8b', 'Available at Indian markets and Kalustyan’s (212-685-3451).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.33', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.82');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad1de08e-77e9-4d01-bb5e-73208b9efba9', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss garbanzo beans with next 5 ingredients in medium bowl. Transfer mixture to rimmed baking sheet. Bake until garbanzos are golden and crisp, stirring occasionally with metal spatula, about 20 minutes. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Keep at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.334', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.82');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be8b4f17-0324-4790-8f3b-f94117f54a67', 'Stir pistachios and thyme into garbanzo mixture. Bake until beans and pistachios are crunchy, about 12 minutes. Transfer mixture to bowl and serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.338', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.821');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8805a199-e30d-4689-8f08-e5e580f0255c', 'Place tomatoes in a large Dutch oven or other heavy pot, crushing with your hands; add wine, red pepper flakes, 2 tsp. salt, 1/2 cup oil, and 2 cups water; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.343', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.821');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fff1111-e404-49db-8b22-7a1ed2045416', 'Pulse anchovies and garlic in a food processor until finely chopped. Add mint and pulse until coarsely chopped. With the motor running, stream in remaining 1/2 cup oil; process until a coarse paste forms. Set pesto aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.347', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.822');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('914928a5-bca8-46fa-8700-e20abb2f42e9', 'Remove several layers of dark-green outer leaves from artichokes (keep going until you get to the tender light-green leaves). Using a serrated knife, cut off top 1" of artichokes and trim stem ends. Rub cut ends with lemon halves to prevent browning. Working with 1 artichoke at a time, use a paring knife or vegetable peeler to remove tough outer green layer from base and stem to reveal pale-green underneath; rub all over with lemon. Halve through stem and rub cut sides with more lemon. Use a spoon to scoop out choke, then pull out spiky inner leaves; rub insides with lemon. Rub reserved pesto all over artichoke halves and place artichokes in a single layer inside reserved pot, submerging in tomato mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.351', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.822');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a9e7d90-8e3e-4f94-80b4-43bec54865de', 'Bring to a simmer over medium-low and cook, turning artichokes occasionally, until hearts are fork-tender, 55–65 minutes. Transfer artichokes to a platter and tent with foil to keep warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.355', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.823');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('98646173-e539-4113-ab4b-e27c3ce4a8bb', 'Increase heat to medium, bring sauce to a boil, and cook until slightly thickened, 10–15 minutes. Taste and season with more salt if needed. Spoon over artichokes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.359', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.823');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b986262c-bb1c-4472-9431-0b0284fe81c0', 'Pulse nuts in a food processor until coarsely chopped. Add dried fruit and pulse until chopped. Add Sherry, zest, and spices and pulse until incorporated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.363', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.824');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b76b3b9-5925-4dc1-981d-c91dc96f2b59', 'Place almonds in heavy medium skillet. Stir over medium heat until almonds are pale golden, about 4 minutes. Transfer almonds to bowl. Add oil to same skillet.Increase heat to medium-high. Add vegetables, cumin and coriander; sauté until vegetables just begin to soften, about 3 minutes. Add wine and raisins. Boil until wine is reduced by half, about 3 minutes. Add broth. Partially cover skillet; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 6 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.366', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.824');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc01a3f0-9d70-478e-a03e-21b5c92ea9b8', 'Meanwhile, prepare couscous according to package directions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.37', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.825');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6409498a-bd03-4e5c-8c31-92f5fc5a2782', 'Mound couscous on platter. Spoon vegetable topping and juices over. Sprinkle with almonds and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.374', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.825');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4f4acc6-5cf5-44d1-b429-234002a88c4d', 'Cut two wafer-thin slices off one of the beet halves and reserve. Feed the beet and carrots, then the celery and cucumber, and finally the apples through a juicer. Stir in the walnuts. Fill a glass halfway with ice (if using), then pour in the juice. Thread the beet slices through a toothpick, lay it on top of the glass, and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.377', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.825');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f481c1d9-b13d-45e4-afb6-181ff8d5efa7', 'Toss arugula and endive in large bowl. (Can be prepared 6 hours ahead. Cover with damp kitchen towel; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.381', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.826');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f3ec497-8b93-4f7b-a68b-0d553a79b5e8', 'Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add apples and shallots; sauté 5 minutes. Add chestnuts; sauté 1 minute. Stir in vinegar, scraping up any browned bits. Remove from heat; stir in walnut oil and remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Pour chestnut mixture over arugula mixture; toss. Divide salad among 8 plates.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.385', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.827');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b4a90995-ca0a-4bf4-9859-8838987258fb', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Bring vinegar and mustard seeds to boil in small saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer until almost dry, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Transfer to large bowl. Add Dijon mustard and coriander. Season with coarse salt and pepper. Place potatoes in large saucepan; add water to cover by 1 inch; sprinkle with coarse salt. Boil 3 minutes. Drain; return to pan. Cook over medium-high heat until dry, shaking pan occasionally, 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.388', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.828');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a27e7c9b-b4f2-49c0-888e-347c329b04ca', 'Meanwhile, drizzle 6 tablespoons oil over large rimmed baking sheet. Place sheet in oven 10 minutes to heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.391', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.829');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e47b6c1-45d6-4cb6-81ff-11df7a107a82', 'Add potatoes to mustard mixture; toss. Spread potatoes on hot baking sheet (oil may splatter). Sprinkle with coarse salt and pepper. Roast 15 minutes. Turn potatoes; roast until browned and tender, about 15 minutes longer. Season with coarse salt and pepper and serve hot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.395', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.829');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a0902b56-b5a6-4b2b-ae28-50ea273439d1', 'In a pitcher stir together orange juice and liqueur. Fill each of 6 champagne flutes halfway with some juice mixture and top off with sparkling wine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.399', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.83');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af3d8006-5ee5-425f-a2e3-fee3ebd16d34', 'Bring ginger beer, dried fruit, and 1 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan. Reduce heat to low and simmer until liquid becomes syrupy and mixture is reduced to 1 1/2 cups, 35-40 minutes. Let cool completely. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.403', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.83');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc54eb60-fbcb-4711-987b-28587a233922', 'Heat oil in a 3- to 4-quart heavy pot over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then cook rice, stirring constantly, until it is pale golden and no longer clumps, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.406', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.831');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2d5023f-9b60-41b4-bd9b-bcab0ed75d56', 'While rice is cooking, purée onion, garlic, 1/2 cup boiling-hot water, and salt in a blender until smooth (use caution when blending hot liquids). Stir into rice and boil, uncovered, stirring, 1 minute. Stir in remaining 3 1/2 cups hot water and mint and cook, covered, over very low heat until rice is tender and water is absorbed, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.41', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.831');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9703e1ec-b6ae-487e-9ee7-91555f155a90', 'Tightly wrap beets in a double layer of foil and roast on a baking sheet in middle of oven until very tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Cool in foil package until warm (the steam makes beets easier to peel), about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.414', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.831');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2f532b52-bbd2-4de9-b7a4-d55abb8e9ab2', 'While beets are roasting, stir together vinegar, sugar, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until sugar and salt are dissolved. Cut apples into 1/4-inch dice and add to dressing along with horseradish. Toss well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.417', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('42489bd4-cd04-4494-ae7a-0589225b5bbb', 'When beets are cool enough to handle, slip off skins and remove stems. Cut beets into 1/4-inch dice and stir into apple mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.421', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('603c3a7f-6b5a-4120-8c0c-2e5471cdd4dc', 'Chill relish, covered, stirring occasionally, at least 2 hours (to allow flavors to develop) and up to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.424', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e501ae1-2645-41d7-8c4d-23656f31611c', 'Put cabbage and scallion in a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.428', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.832');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef53920b-482e-4b47-b9da-c0554e7e8168', 'Bring vinegar, ginger, sugar, and red pepper flakes (to taste) to a boil in a small saucepan over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Pour hot dressing over cabbage, tossing to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.433', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.833');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09c76398-1437-4ad2-93ab-baaf95706391', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. In a medium bowl, stir together the sugar, spices, and salt. Toast the walnuts lightly on a sheet pan in the oven, for about 4-5 minutes. While the nuts are toasting, heat the spiced sugar in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. When the sugar just begins to melt around the edges, toss in the warm nuts, straight from the oven. Shake the pan vigorously over the burner until all the nuts are coated in sugar — it will cling in somewhat uneven patches, but that is the effect I like. Pour the nuts onto a plate or baking sheet to cool — don''t be tempted to try one until they have really cooled down, since sugar at this temperature will give you a burned tongue to remember!', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.437', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.833');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('34c2e5a2-9307-4e76-bb35-768b8e04550f', 'Toss the salad greens with the spiced walnuts and the vinaigrette and top with a generous slice of ham and 1 ounce of cheese per person, according to the seasons (see Weighing Your Options).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.441', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.833');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35fade7b-5612-4d52-bfc4-ba6f1593984e', 'Spring: Grilled Asparagus with Serrano Ham and Maytag Blue Cheese (to grill asparagus, blanch the asparagus to halfway tender, brush with a little olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and grill until lightly brown)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.444', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.834');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68545333-ffca-420b-acd4-568376626aa9', 'Summer: Fresh Black Mission Figs with Smithfield Ham and Aged Goat Cheese', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.448', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.834');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('666a2186-5be3-44d2-a1be-4ac83b2afeb7', 'Fall: Lightly Roasted Seckel Pears with Pecorino Romano and Prosciutto', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.451', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.834');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c42b779-c43f-4c72-bc9a-7ade72e9a14d', 'Winter: Blood Oranges and Fennel with Feta and Prosciutto', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.455', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.835');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e860ca21-b61a-43b9-8759-d815917d7b15', 'In small bowl, whisk together sugar and 1/4 cup hot water until sugar is dissolved. Stir in lime juice and zest. Cover and refrigerate until cool, about 1 1/2 hours. (Syrup can be made ahead and chilled, covered, up to 3 days.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.459', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.835');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2278af55-63ed-4c7e-b16f-5f88e14f2ae8', 'In 1 very large or 2 medium plastic containers, combine melon wedges. Refrigerate until cold, about 1 1/2 hours. (Melons can be sliced and chilled up to 12 hours ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.463', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.836');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b1596983-82d7-4975-b925-9eef9b623f0c', 'As close to serving time as possible, stir mint into syrup and drizzle over melon wedges. Serve chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.466', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.836');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cfa26054-da6d-4aee-842f-86a03175eee2', 'In a dry heavy skillet toast anise seeds over moderate heat, shaking skillet occasionally, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Cool seeds and coarsely grind with a mortar and pestle or a cleaned electric coffee/spice grinder.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.47', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.836');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8bb369cf-190f-442d-a194-ade062f335fe', 'Peel jícama and carrots and quarter jícama. Using a mandoline or other manual slicer, cut jícama and carrots into very thin slices, about 1/16 inch. Stack slices and cut into julienne strips. With a knife cut cabbage into very thin shreds. Vegetables may be prepared 1 day ahead and chilled separately in sealable plastic bags.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.474', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.837');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bfa68a75-9bb9-44e6-a455-6c53c5231cff', 'Coarsely chop parsley. In a large bowl stir together anise, oil, lime juice, mustard, and salt. Add vegetables and parsley, tossing to coat, and season with salt and pepper. Slaw may be made 2 hours ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.477', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.837');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5fd115a-7236-4e80-960b-8562e57ddda7', 'Simmer sugar and water in a small saucepan, stirring, until sugar is dissolved, then cool syrup. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour through a fine sieve into a large glass measuring cup. Pour into molds. Freeze at least 24 hours. Add sticks when mixture is slushy, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.481', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.837');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1533cc3-36fc-4473-ae13-15f425871d7d', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Toss cauliflower and 4 tablespoons oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with salt and pepper. Roast, tossing occasionally, until tender and golden brown, 25–30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.485', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f1be4a5d-472f-45be-8b91-044a95df8ff4', 'Meanwhile, pulse parsley, lemon juice, and remaining 2 tablespoons oil in a food processor until very finely chopped; season with salt and pepper. Toss cauliflower with lemon-parsley mixture and top with lemon zest.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.488', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c47fda0-67f4-4c7b-b804-1641fb0b04cb', 'DO AHEAD: Lemon-parsley mixture can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.492', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b94b8f6-f9b2-4f10-88fb-53fca02748eb', 'Divide potatoes between 2 large sheets of foil, then lift edges of foil around potatoes to form a nest so the oil won''t leak. Divide garlic, rosemary, and oil between packages, then sprinkle each with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring edges of foil together to enclose each package, covering completely, then crimp to seal packages closed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.496', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.838');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0545e017-6ec0-4ee5-b1d3-496750e49a39', 'Prepare a grill for medium, indirect heat, preferably with hardwood or hardwood charcoal. Place foil packages near the coals and cook, moving packages around the coals occasionally for even cooking, until potatoes are tender, 30–45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.499', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e968340e-38e9-4ed7-9a32-bca72b8926c1', 'Packages can cooked and stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.503', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c39310ea-d518-4d8a-9c25-f9484957335b', 'Fry chickpeas in 2 batches until golden and crisp throughout, 5 to 10 minutes, then transfer with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.302', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a978c01-1b36-4565-bf39-39592d0d7090', 'Carefully cut out the core from each head of lettuce and separate the leaves, but keep each head of lettuce together; discard any tough outer leaves. Because each head of lettuce will be reassembled, the easiest way to work is with one head at a time. First, place the leaves in a bowl of cold water to refresh them and remove any dirt, then lift out and spin-dry in a salad spinner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.507', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.839');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e38f1eb-4a95-4124-aa0f-c005ea1804fe', 'Place the leaves from a single head of lettuce in a bowl. Sprinkle with a pinch of salt, a few grinds of pepper, 1 1/2 teaspoons of the shallots and chives, and 1 tablespoon each of the parsley, tarragon, and chervil. Then toss gently with 2 tablespoons of the vinaigrette and 1 teaspoon of lemon juice. Repeat with the remaining heads.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.84');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7d061c42-64bf-490e-8ed9-b66ac9149918', 'For each serving, arrange the outer lettuce leaves as a base on the plate and rebuild each head of lettuce, ending with the smallest, most tender leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.514', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.84');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1cf99fe6-5016-4107-8287-65c64edbd517', 'Using a paring knife, score plums all the way around, starting and ending at stem end and cutting just through the skin (you want to keep plums intact).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.518', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.841');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e2f7d5a-832d-4c3f-9705-e0d18e4df3ce', 'Bring 2 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Remove from heat, add tea bags, and let steep about 5 minutes; discard tea bags. Add sugar and bring mixture to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar. Reduce heat, add plums, cardamom, and star anise; scrape in vanilla seeds and add pod. Simmer until plums are just tender, 15-20 minutes. Remove from heat and let plums cool in poaching liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.521', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.843');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb04f8bc-4f56-42be-9ef3-2d12a146d1e7', 'Discard vanilla pod, cardamom, and star anise. Halve plums, remove pits, and return to poaching liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.525', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.845');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0640245b-cce4-4639-8de9-17f5d49a5581', 'DO AHEAD: Plums can be poached 2 days ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.529', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.845');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('201a11df-b495-4920-ac8d-f9b673e25616', 'Toast fennel seeds in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, about 3 minutes. Add lemon zest, bay leaves, olives, oil, and Aleppo pepper and cook, stirring, until just warmed through, about 3 minutes. Transfer to a serving bowl and serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.532', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.845');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('638ded36-8ae7-4df1-8790-251c553d0476', 'Purée chives, oil, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, and 1 teaspoon salt in a food processor until smooth. Strain chive vinaigrette through a fine-mesh sieve into a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.536', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.846');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa5e7092-8869-4eb2-a1ea-c7f562ed1f41', 'Cook dried sprouted legumes in a large pot of lightly salted boiling water until just tender, about 5 minutes. Cover pot; remove from heat. Let stand for 3 minutes; drain. Rinse legumes under cold water to cool; drain. Transfer to a large bowl. DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette and legumes can be made 1 day ahead. Cover separately; chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.539', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.846');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76301c87-c0d8-4279-8e95-8f6cde55182d', 'Add zucchini, rice, scallions, seeds, nuts, and chive vinaigrette to bowl with legumes; toss to combine. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.543', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.847');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('976e3b60-64dd-4759-8e7e-57070fee08f1', 'Combine peaches, sugar, vinegar, and hot pepper flakes, and briskly simmer, uncovered, until liquid thickens slightly, 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in onion and salt and simmer for 5 minutes. Relish will continue to thicken as it cools.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.546', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.847');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5397fd11-497c-4ad1-b9aa-0ee996007317', 'Combine wakame with warm water to cover by 1 inch and let stand 15 minutes, or until reconstituted. Drain in a sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.55', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.849');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47a2b83a-6f69-4059-bfd3-7dfdca2d8275', 'Stir together miso and 1/2 cup dashi in a bowl until smooth. Heat remaining dashi in a saucepan over moderately high heat until hot, then gently stir in tofu and reconstituted wakame. Simmer 1 minute and remove from heat. Immediately stir in miso mixture and scallion greens and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d585d36-efb0-41ce-ade6-d54f22ae983a', 'Whisk lemon juice, oil, and ginger in a large bowl; season with salt and pepper. Add turnips, apple, brussels sprouts, and 1 teaspoon poppy seeds and toss to coat. Serve slaw topped with more poppy seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.557', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.85');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('58df2f72-aa28-4513-aad3-a339e880c9d8', 'Peel the potatoes, with a melon-ball cutter scoop out as many balls as possible from them, and in a jelly-roll pan toss the balls with the oil and salt and pepper to taste. Roast the potatoes in the middle of a preheated 450°F. oven, turning them occasionally, for 15 minutes. Add the cauliflower, toss the mixture well, and roast it for 10 minutes, or until the cauliflower is tender and golden in spots. Toss the vegetables with the sliced chives and salt and pepper to taste and serve them garnished with the whole chives.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.561', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.851');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6427e3cb-7b28-47aa-ac42-fbd7fcfddd79', '1. Brush the tomato halves all over with olive oil. Season them generously all over with salt and pepper, then sprinkle the garlic and chopped sage over them. Press a whole sage leaf in the center of the cut side of each tomato half. Set any leftover olive oil aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.565', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.852');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51558308-459c-4a79-864d-f34529612ec3', '2. Cook the tomatoes, following the instructions below for any of the grills, until nicely browned.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.569', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.852');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79d954ce-a207-477d-b0e7-10fc860af3e2', '3. Transfer the tomatoes to a platter or plates and drizzle any remaining olive oil over them. Serve at once.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.573', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a730ecba-81ab-4836-bb25-7769e45a8a5b', '•This recipe calls for fresh sage because I like its earthy flavor and I also like the way the whole leaves look when grilled into the tomato halves. If you don''t like or can''t find sage, you can achieve a similar effect with small sprigs of fresh rosemary, tarragon, thyme, flat-leaf parsley, or another herb.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.576', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.853');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74ac9fa6-3321-4c9a-9e39-8c30bd3669f7', '• You can also grill small whole plum tomatoes this way. Skewer the sage leaves onto the tomatoes with wooden toothpicks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.58', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.854');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a96cef7-1618-4362-bef1-7ad5ed8d79c4', 'Preheat the grill; if your contact grill has a temperature control, preheat the grill to high. Place the drip pan under the front of the grill. When ready to cook, lightly oil the grill surface. Arrange the tomato halves on the hot grill, cut side up, then close the lid. The tomatoes will be done after cooking 4 to 6 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.584', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.855');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa8ba6fe-4f80-4241-8606-0c9c58a9a3dd', 'Place the grill pan on the stove and preheat it to medium-high over medium heat. When the grill pan is hot a drop of water will skitter in the pan. When ready to cook, lightly oil the ridges of the grill pan. Arrange the tomato halves, cut side down, in the hot grill pan on a diagonal to the ridges. The tomatoes will be done after cooking 4 to 6 minutes per side. Rotate the tomatoes a quarter turn after grilling 2 minutes on the first side to create a handsome crosshatch of grill marks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.587', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.856');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e6e100cd-5c24-4c98-870a-9a5715529406', 'Stir tequila mixture and spoon over pineapple. Lay a sheet of wax paper over pineapple and bake in middle of oven, basting with juices every 10 minutes, until pineapple is tender and slightly caramelized, about 50 minutes. Halve pineapple halves lengthwise and serve with any juices remaining in baking dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.737', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.882');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36b98d6b-6575-472f-914e-30b9a0a2fb80', 'Preheat the grill to high, then, if it does not have a nonstick surface, brush and oil the grill grate. Arrange the tomato halves, cut side down, on the hot grate on a diagonal to the ridges. The tomatoes will be done after cooking 4 to 6 minutes per side. Rotate the tomatoes a quarter turn after grilling 2 minutes on the first side to create a handsome crosshatch of grill marks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.591', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.857');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dbe3f296-2a47-4d5a-bd48-018969f1f43f', 'Preheat the grill to high; there''s no need to oil the grate. Arrange the tomato halves, cut side down, on the hot grate on a diagonal to the ridges. The tomatoes will be done after cooking 5 to 7 minutes per side. Rotate the tomatoes a quarter turn after grilling 2 minutes on the first side to create a handsome crosshatch of grill marks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.595', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.858');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a854c3d-8b88-4df7-889c-253d91d2ca60', 'Rake red hot embers under the gridiron and preheat it for 3 to 5 minutes; you want a hot, 2 to 3 Mississippi fire. When ready to cook, brush and oil the gridiron. Arrange the tomato halves, cut side down, on the hot grate on a diagonal to the ridges. The tomatoes will be done after cooking 4 to 6 minutes per side. Rotate the tomatoes a quarter turn after grilling 2 minutes on the first side to create a handsome crosshatch of grill marks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.599', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.86');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7efa98fd-5781-41e6-a3aa-e4ae42d379dc', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Place barley in a medium pot and add water to cover by 1 1/2". Season with salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered until barley is tender and water is absorbed, 40-45 minutes. Spread out barley on a large rimmed baking sheet; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.602', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.861');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4f0c11f3-19cb-47bd-ace5-7d9a9c1b772a', 'While barley is cooking, toss fennel slices and 2 tablespoons oil in a medium bowl to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Spread fennel slices out in a single layer on another rimmed baking sheet. Roast until fennel is crisp-tender and beginning to brown in spots, about 18 minutes. Let fennel cool on baking sheet. DO AHEAD: Barley and fennel can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.606', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.861');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcdb13de-2e0a-407f-9164-7ac57607ff25', 'Whisk orange juice, lime juice, shallot, 2 tablespoons dill, and zest in a medium bowl. Gradually whisk in remaining 1/2 cup oil; season orange vinaigrette with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.609', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.862');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0d4b944b-3e16-48a8-8909-8b63b0a257fc', 'Transfer barley to a large bowl; add roasted fennel, along with any accumulated juices on baking sheet. Add half of radishes, olives, and 1/4 cup dill sprigs. Drizzle 1/2 cup orange vinaigrette over and toss to coat; season with salt and pepper. Arrange salad on a large platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.612', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.863');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('423e2f3a-22af-4f66-a5cf-8f5285e812b7', 'Scatter remaining radishes, reserved fennel fronds, and remaining 1/4 cup dill sprigs over salad. Pass remaining orange vinaigrette alongside for drizzling over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.616', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.863');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39d64d2a-a8fc-473a-b5b8-9d94b0aaeae3', 'Put the tomatillos in a blender first, then add the remaining ingredients. Pulse a few times, then blend until the salsa is very smooth, at least 1 minute. Season to taste with additional chile and salt, and blend again.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.62', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.863');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a02e7d79-14fe-4a89-8a43-6be31ffcb3fd', 'Bring water, sugar, and anise seeds to a boil in a 2 1/2- to 3-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Remove pan from heat and stir in Pernod (if using). Cool syrup to room temperature, about 1 hour, then pour through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.623', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.864');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a09b15e9-ffd6-4b88-882c-c304ecc343b6', 'While syrup cools, cut enough pineapple into 1-inch chunks to measure 5 1/4 cups (reserve remainder for another use), then purée pineapple in 3 batches in a blender at high speed until very smooth, about 1 minute per batch. Stir purée and lemon juice into cooled syrup until combined well, then chill, covered, until very cold, about 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.627', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.865');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df9e7edd-6112-489a-879b-d3cadc4e5ae8', 'Freeze in ice cream maker, then transfer to an airtight container and put in freezer to harden, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.631', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.865');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77dd31ab-7450-49a1-b857-f3f528eb8857', 'Coarsely mash 1 1/2 cups raspberries and 2 cups blueberries with sugar and water in a 2- to 3-quart heavy saucepan using a potato masher. Bring to a boil, stirring, then boil, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes. Transfer to a blender and purée until almost smooth, about 1 minute (use caution when blending hot liquids). Pour berry mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, pressing lightly on and then discarding solids. Cool syrup, uncovered, then chill, its surface loosely covered with plastic wrap, until cold, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.634', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.866');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1a8479e-9495-40aa-aec6-3b4ac2aaa23f', 'For each serving, spoon 3 tablespoons syrup over 1 cup lightly packed shaved ice and top with 1/4 cup of remaining mixed berries. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.638', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.866');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e6d2bb9-cced-4015-a4fe-11541fb45987', 'In a small saucepan bring water to a boil and remove pan from heat. Stir in bulgur and soak 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.641', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.866');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('631ab71c-2c25-47e4-903d-9e4bedc9c106', 'While bulgur is soaking, in a bowl stir together onion, cumin, and salt and let stand 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.645', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.867');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8d24512-07ae-4b26-9c5f-fcc8d70ae532', 'Cut about 1/2-inch-thick slices from tops of tomatoes and scoop out insides to form cups. Mince parsley, mint, and garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.648', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.868');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43342e78-153e-4d81-ba93-8eb3d722e9e4', 'Shuck corn and grill on a lightly oiled rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals, turning occasionally, until browned and tender, 8 to 10 minutes. When corn is cool enough to handle, cut kernels from cobs and add to onion mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.651', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.868');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('87778dd9-2f76-4001-abd7-c68a3b7ccb95', 'Drain bulgur in a sieve, pressing hard to extract as much water as possible, and add to corn mixture with parsley, mint, and garlic. In a small bowl whisk together lemon juice, oil, and salt and pepper to taste and drizzle over tabbouleh. Toss tabbouleh well and divide among tomato cups.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.655', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.869');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa265792-4eee-42e9-ba3e-fa3e8333bdb7', 'Gently boil the lentils in a large saucepan of cold water (around 4 cups will do) and stir in the turmeric and black cardamom pods (if using)—this will add a subtle smoky flavor. Allow to cook for around 45 minutes, or until the lentils have softened and started to break down. Skim off any foam that sits on the top and give the lentils a stir every now and again in case they begin to stick on the bottom. If they boil dry, add more water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.658', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.869');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c412213-d3d9-4fae-9dc1-bbf47d32338a', 'Once the lentils have softened, turn down the heat and make the tadka. Gently heat the oil in a skillet and add the cinnamon sticks, green cardamom pods and cloves. When the cardamoms have turned white and the heads of the cloves have swollen, you are ready to stir in the mustard and cumin seeds. When they are sizzling, stir in the scallions, chiles, garlic and ginger.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.87');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4fbd109f-185b-4231-94e0-d0364a2ae24d', 'After a minute, stir through the tomatoes and turn off the heat. Pour the tadka into the dhal so that it floats on top. This is the traditional way to serve it, with the scented oil sitting on top, but I prefer to stir it through. Season with salt, sugar and lemon juice. Finally, stir through plenty of chopped cilantro and serve with some rice or fresh bread for the ultimate comfort food.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.665', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.87');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6addb13a-c3e3-45a8-bf04-4e1be71be33c', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add mustard seeds; cook until seeds darken and begin to pop, about 2 minutes. Add onion, chili and ginger; stir 1 minute. Add eggplant and zucchini slices; stir 5 minutes. Cover; cook 5 minutes. Mix in tomatoes and garlic. Reduce heat to medium. Cover; cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes. Mix in mint and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.669', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.871');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('309becbf-0695-4319-9ecc-a87e7d7918ee', 'In a 6-quart kettle bring 5 quarts salted water to a boil for linguine. In a 12-inch heavy skillet cook garlic in 3 tablespoons oil over moderate heat, stirring, until pale golden and transfer with a slotted spoon to a small bowl. To skillet add red pepper flakes, wine, and salt and boil until reduced to about 1/4 cup. Keep wine mixture warm. Boil linguine until al dente. Reserve 11/2 cups pasta water and drain linguine. Stir 1 cup reserved pasta water and parsley into wine mixture and add linguine, garlic, and remaining tablespoon oil. Toss pasta over moderate heat until combined well, about 1 minute, adding more pasta water if necessary to keep mixture moist. Serve pasta with Parmesan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.673', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.871');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cdd5be12-ab6a-4f56-abce-9e564b7ef9b1', 'In a saucepan bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes, or until slightly thickened. Let marmalade cool in a heat-proof bowl and chill, covered, until cold, about 2 hours. Marmalade keeps, covered and chilled, 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.872');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6cb0bb9-4862-4d70-afbb-fbd7fbe053fb', 'Cook squash, bell pepper, onion, and bay leaf in oil with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables begin to brown, 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.68', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.872');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59543778-fe32-4e0e-93f9-7c5346a93818', 'Add rice and stir until well coated, then add water and bring to a vigorous boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, tightly covered with lid, until vegetables and rice are tender and liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.683', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.873');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53f03fdc-cf94-4a4b-a705-8923545f0c66', '1. Carefully inspect the greens, discarding or trimming off any spoiled stems or leaves. Trim the bottom ends off and discard. Wash the greens in several changes of the coldest possible water; tepid water might cause them to wilt, and you want them to stay as alert and perky as possible before being cooked. (Note: Because bok choi and baby bok choi tend to have pockets full of sand in the nooks where the leaves meet the center stem, be certain to pull the leaves back slightly away from the stem when you''re cleaning them. There are few things worse than a mouthful of sand when you want a mouthful of greens.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.687', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.875');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e5c5968-3ce8-41ad-b9a3-a1aacc6c7483', '2. Cut the cleaned greens into pieces 2-1/2 to 3 inches long. If any of the stems are particularly wide — say, more than 1 inch — or are tough or sinewy-looking, cut them in half lengthwise. If you''re using baby bok choi or baby Shanghai choi, you can either leave the heads whole or cut them in half lengthwise — it''s up to you. Spin the greens dry in a salad dryer or set them aside to air-dry on a kitchen towel or paper towels; they needn''t be bone dry — a little dampness won''t matter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.691', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.877');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8bf6b1bd-d1c2-44cc-be19-f8cd6df173be', '3. In a wok, 12-inch skillet, Dutch oven, or soup pot (any pot large and wide enough to comfortably hold the greens will do), heat the oil over medium-high heat. When it''s hot but not smoking — it should appear shimmery — add the garlic, the salt, and, if using, the chiles. Sauté, stirring until the garlic just begins to lose its rawness, about 1 minute. (Try not to let the garlic turn golden or golden brown, which would give this dish an inappropriate roasted taste.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.694', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.877');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('32b538bc-401e-4d96-b9e8-5377aaeb9864', '4. Add the greens. Raise the heat slightly and immediately begin to vigorously stir-fry the greens around the pot. Continue to vigorously stir-fry the greens until they just begin to go limp but the leaves remain a spring-green color and the stems are still crunchy-crisp, 3 to 4 minutes, depending on the type of greens. Taste for salt, adding only a pinch more if necessary (a little salt goes a long way with greens).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.698', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.878');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca6b4a38-6bde-4424-85c2-df8852a25576', '5. Transfer the cooked greens to a large serving platter and serve promptly. Be careful not to pile the greens in a small bowl; since the greens will continue to cook for a minute or two after they''re removed from the heat, a serving bowl that crowds them may cause them to overcook and become mushy.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.702', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.879');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7279187a-2405-4fc1-a10f-e749fa15b906', '1. Place the rice, quinoa, and 3 cups water into a rice cooker and cook according to the manufacturer''s instructions. (You can also cook the rice and quinoa in 3 cups water in a pressure cooker for 15 minutes).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.705', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.879');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('373c391e-507f-47e2-afca-564e4a5ae556', '2. Bring a saucepan of water to a boil and cook the carrots until softened, about 30 seconds. Drain and rinse them under cold water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.709', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.88');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf923cea-9b13-4f79-a237-490de16e18fe', '3. Unroll a bamboo sushi mat on a work surface and put a sheet of nori on it. Wet your hands and divide the rice into 4 equal portions. Divide one portion into 4 small, firm balls and press them evenly onto the nori, covering the entire sheet with a thin layer of grains. Evenly spread one-quarter of the bean curd, one quarter of the carrots, one-quarter of the cucumbers, and one quarter of the avocado in the center of the rice. Using the mat as a guide, roll the topped nori tightly and evenly into a sushi roll, wetting the edges of the nori sheet with water if necessary, so it sticks together at the seam. Repeat three more times with the remaining nori, rice, and vegetables.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.712', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.88');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4bb061d3-71c4-466e-9417-26bb10027520', '4. Slice the rolls into 1 1/2-inch-thick pieces with a sharp, wet knife and transfer them to a serving platter. Garnish with cilantro and pickled ginger.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.715', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.88');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6b8cb173-44ab-4d04-8b19-e37bde1c638c', 'Stir together tequila, lime juice, and sugar until sugar is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.719', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.88');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33cf43d7-9ba3-411c-b4a2-a6ed80f82010', 'Peel pineapple with a large sharp knife, keeping crown of leaves attached. Trim bottom.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.722', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.881');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f725147e-b94f-46b0-a552-74d1ec62a5de', 'Remove eyes from pineapple in spiral channels with a sharp paring knife: Cut along each side of diagonal row of eyes that spirals down pineapple, forming a V-shaped channel. Cut out channel and eyes and repeat procedure with remaining rows of eyes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.726', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.881');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c89827c5-743b-449d-b247-41c6de903171', 'Lay pineapple on its side, then, beginning at base and moving upward, carefully cut pineapple lengthwise in half through leaves, keeping leaves attached. Cut out core from each half and pull out some of long innermost leaves so no leaves are longer than about 7 inches.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.881');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('43c3e043-b6ab-492d-b7a4-22c362f240b9', 'Arrange pineapple halves, flat sides down, in a glass or ceramic 13- by 9-inch baking dish, then pierce all over and all the way through with a skewer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.733', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.881');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('641c55c0-4c0a-48ed-a151-bcf4d125440d', 'Toss sweet-potato crisps, pumpkin seeds, chiles, chickpeas, and raisins with sugar, cayenne, and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.306', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8563846d-40da-4ad5-b079-227c5dccb660', 'Heat 4 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add okra and sauté until coating is golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer okra to paper towels to drain; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Wipe out skillet. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet over medium heat. Add corn, squash, and garlic; sauté 2 minutes. Add tomatoes; cover and cook until squash is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Mix in okra, cilantro, and green onions. Remove from heat. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and more cayenne, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.744', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.882');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f573e3d-4840-4f62-a17e-9936285af801', 'Put the chickpeas in a large bowl and add enough cold water to cover them by at least 2 inches. Let soak overnight, then drain. Or use canned chickpeas, drained.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.747', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.883');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abd13dcc-5be0-4269-8f95-bbdf7f654a61', 'Place the drained, uncooked chickpeas and the onions in the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade. Add the parsley, cilantro, salt, hot pepper, garlic, and cumin. Process until blended but not pureed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.751', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.883');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a8e7f558-e2cd-475c-a06a-fcc4966ade71', 'Sprinkle in the baking powder and 4 tablespoons of the flour, and pulse. You want to add enough bulgur or flour so that the dough forms a small ball and no longer sticks to your hands. Turn into a bowl and refrigerate, covered, for several hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.754', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.883');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e841257-1e81-4962-a03e-3a58da409221', 'Form the chickpea mixture into balls about the size of walnuts, or use a falafel scoop, available in Middle-Eastern markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.758', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6976bd09-7ccc-4b4a-8774-81ea24062ae8', 'Heat 3 inches of oil to 375ºF in a deep pot or wok and fry 1 ball to test. If it falls apart, add a little flour. Then fry about 6 balls at once for a few minutes on each side, or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Stuff half a pita with falafel balls, chopped tomatoes, onion, green pepper, and pickled turnips. Drizzle with tahina thinned with water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.761', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d0d4799c-6bf8-4443-9ed0-d00db34ddc5c', 'NOTE: Egyptians omit the cilantro and substitute fava beans for the chickpeas.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1011bb9a-ab69-4a97-8e7e-527ed1432e62', 'Tahina (also called tahini) is an oily paste made from ground sesame seeds. It is available in Middle Eastern markets and at www.ethnicgrocer.com.
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('920a6037-0b91-4a18-b37c-05def543de65', '1. Combine the quinoa and 1/2 cup water in a very small saucepan with a lid. Bring to a boil, cover the pot, and lower the heat to the slowest possible simmer, with a heat diffuser, if you have one, underneath. You''ll have cooked quinoa in about 20 minutes. Uncover, fluff with a fork, and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.771', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.884');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b50ca3d-c105-4872-8fcb-0eb955a4de51', '2. Meanwhile, cut the sweet potato into rounds about 1 1/2 inches thick and steam over or cook in boiling water until fork-soft, about 15 minutes. Cool until comfortable to handle. Strip off and discard the peels and transfer to a food processor.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.775', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.885');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('40495419-6122-4de5-888e-6e2478271b03', '3. Add the chickpeas, ginger, garlic, scallions, 3/4 teaspoon salt, cumin, and 2 tablespoons of the lemon juice to the sweet potato and process until reasonably blended. It doesn''t need to be completely smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.778', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.886');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b7a0c5e-8cca-48c3-865a-130d41d5bd29', '4. Transfer the mixture to a bowl, then sprinkle in the cooked quinoa and the quinoa flour. Stir until all the quinoa disappears into the mixture. Gently fold in the green peas and peanuts, if using. Taste to see if it needs more salt or lemon juice and add a few big pinches of crushed red pepper flakes to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.782', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.887');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('759c1f65-7868-4a5a-a592-e31970c083d3', '5. Place a medium skillet over medium heat for about a minute, then add a scant 1/2 tablespoon oil and swirl to coat the pan. Heat for a little longer, until the oil is hot enough to instantly sizzle a dot of the sweet potato mixture. Turn the heat to low.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.786', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.887');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f18f057-93aa-4224-a7ce-9dc28a5e33f9', '6. Use a nonstick-sprayed 1/3-cup measure to scoop-shape the batter as uniformly as possible. Carefully transfer as many burgers as will fit in a single layer to the hot, oiled pan, knocking the cup handle assertively against the side of the pan or using the back of a spoon to release the batter. Smooth the top surface with a dinner knife, so the burgers will crisp evenly, and push in the sides to help them keep their shape as they cook.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.789', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d8301e8-96c1-4438-84e8-1010419583d1', '7. Cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown on the bottom. (Longer cooking is OK—just not hotter. The sugar content of sweet potatoes causes them to burn easily at higher temperatures.) Use a small spatula with a thin blade to carefully loosen each burger and flip it over, adding more oil as needed and pushing the burgers back into shape if they slump or break.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.792', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bce055c1-351a-4fc4-ab4b-3e651517784d', '8. Cook on the second side for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the bottoms are nicely browned. Continue to cook in batches until all the batter has been used. Serve hot or warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.796', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('416ebd42-6627-4f8f-a150-8afd738f100f', 'Toasted peanuts on top * Steamed peas on top * Yogurt or Raita * Salsa Verde * A drizzle of pomegranate molasses', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.8', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.888');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1dd13207-3dce-473f-80ec-35110f297ff2', 'In a large heavy saucepan toast spices over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in eggplant, bell peppers, onion, garlic, water, lemon juice, sugar, and salt and pepper to taste and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes, or until eggplant is almost tender. Stir in zucchini and simmer uncovered, until vegetables are tender and most liquid is evaporated, about 5 minutes. Cool caponata slightly and transfer to a bowl. Chill caponata, covered, until cold, about 2 hours. Caponata may be made 3 days ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.803', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eff833ee-5cd5-40ea-b6f8-b19552a5bb47', 'Halve bread horizontally with a serrated knife and make 1 large hero with caponata and basil. Cut hero into 4 pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.806', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f2fbc9c-ccf8-435d-9ee3-75c282d892e1', 'Combine cranberries, 1 1/2 cups water, sugar, ginger, and shallot in heavy large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Cover and cook until berries burst, about 10 minutes. Stir in molasses. Season with salt. Cool. Cover and chill until cold, about 3 hours. (Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.81', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8aef3da4-28de-475d-9906-a7272f6d26c7', 'Preheat oven to 475°F. Place eggplant on a baking sheet and toss with 1/4 cup oil; season with salt and pepper. Roast until lightly charred and very tender, 20–25 minutes; let cool slightly. Chop eggplant (skin and all) until almost a paste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.813', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.889');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b702e201-e411-4e61-a87b-f22c832b2a0c', 'Mix eggplant in a medium bowl with garlic, lemon zest, lemon juice, tahini, and cumin; season with salt and pepper. Drizzle with oil and top with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.817', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.89');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('056eabdd-20f0-4a13-93c7-9e50e16446c1', 'In a large pot, heat oil over medium heat. Cook onion, stirring occasionally, until golden, 3 to 5 minutes. Add celery, carrots and garlic; cook, stirring, until vegetables soften, 3 to 5 minutes. Add wine; stir to scrape brown bits off bottom of pot. Add stock, beans, tomatoes, bay leaves and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring soup to a boil; reduce heat, cover, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until carrots are very soft, 15 to 20 minutes. In a blender, puree basil, walnuts, black pepper, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 cup water. Transfer pesto to a bowl; wash blender. Remove bay leaves from soup; discard. In blender, carefully puree half of soup; transfer to a bowl; repeat with remaining half of soup. Divide soup among 4 bowls, dollop each with 1/4 pesto, and swirl in; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.82', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.891');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a7c0258-47f6-4bd8-872d-2c03bc15418f', 'Preheat oven to 300°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.823', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.891');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82df39c7-2e59-4d5a-86fd-193caf3e2de0', 'In a large colander set over a bowl toss eggplant with salt and let stand 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.827', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.891');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('451b7d80-2db2-42b1-b846-24fff5a4ffed', 'Rinse eggplant under cold water and gently squeeze by handfuls to remove excess liquid. Transfer eggplant to a large jelly-roll and toss with 2 tablespoons oil. Roast eggplant in middle of oven, shaking pan occasionally, until tender and golden, about 45 minutes, and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.83', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.892');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0d5ace61-1ea0-49cf-b5bd-022ff3147e36', 'In a 4-quart kettle bring 2 quarts salted water to a boil for pasta.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.834', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.894');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('80f332fa-97b7-4d9d-b5eb-fa887ce3e0ff', 'In a large bowl stir together eggplant, bell peppers, pine nuts, parsley, and basil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.837', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.894');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f423f256-57c2-4548-b41d-8c2c7c51bd96', 'In a small bowl whisk together garlic, sugar, vinegar, and salt and pepper to taste. Add remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.841', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.894');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fd02348-2e97-4139-9386-b20d932112aa', 'Add pasta to boiling water and boil, stirring occasionally, until al dente. In colander drain pasta and rinse under cold water. Add pasta to eggplant mixture and drizzle with dressing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.844', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.895');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02e61ade-9536-4252-898e-305d2b8431ec', 'Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate up to 8 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.847', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.896');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f378fd2-84d0-421a-9b7b-efe0603f3409', 'Toast hazelnuts in a small shallow baking pan until golden, 4 to 5 minutes. Trim woody ends from asparagus and, if desired, peel lower 2 inches of stems with a vegetable peeler. Cook asparagus in a large saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes, and drain well in a colander. Whisk together remaining ingredients except nuts with salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.85', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.896');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0025d4b-1eae-4fdc-b146-17bf1534adf0', 'Transfer hot asparagus to plates. Spoon orange dressing over top and sprinkle with nuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.854', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.897');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60c73a22-86e1-46ea-acd6-4a4c48fd233c', '1. Cut the puckered ends off the polenta, then slice ½ inch thick. Cut each slice into 4 little wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.858', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.898');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d3d19777-2667-495e-ad27-38e1fdefdbc0', '2. Heat a wide nonstick skillet. Add a drop of the oil and spread it around with a paper towel to create a very light coat, or use cooking oil spray. Add the polenta wedges; cook in a single layer over medium heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes on each side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.861', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.898');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df6acec2-63b9-4508-80d5-94102e75bc27', '3. Transfer the polenta to a plate. Heat the oil and soy sauce slowly in the same skillet. Before they get too hot, add the seitan and stir well. Raise the heat to medium-high and sauté, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Stir in the bok choy, spinach, and scallions, then cover and cook until just wilted, 1 to 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.865', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.899');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7cf268a4-0066-436a-868a-c76bc83399d8', '4. Sprinkle in vinegar to taste. Gently fold in the polenta wedges and sun-dried tomatoes, if using, Season with salt and pepper and serve at once.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.868', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.899');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8eb81253-0c27-4db0-855e-5980f8305e4a', 'To make the crema, soak the raw cashews in room-temperature water to cover for at least 1 hour. Drain and reserve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.872', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.9');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('81c92d57-29c5-4355-aba4-20b56e7d5215', 'Toast the cumin in a small, dry, heavy skillet over medium heat for about 1 minute, until fragrant. Transfer to a spice grinder, let cool, and grind finely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.875', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10b6c623-19a9-4e01-aa45-fc410dbae0d7', 'In a blender, combine the cashews, cumin, lime juice, water, and salt. Start the blender on the lowest speed and gradually increase to the highest speed. Blend for at least 1 minute, until a creamy consistency. Pour into a serving bowl and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.879', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.901');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b89afb48-fb3a-4557-b03d-f09969492f31', 'To make the pumpkin seeds, heat the oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the pumpkin seeds and sauté for about 2 minutes, taking care that they do not burn. The seeds will begin to puff up and pop. Once they appear toasted, immediately pour them into a bowl. Toss with the cayenne and salt and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.882', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.902');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f33429a8-e8ad-4f46-894b-0bbdb1e79134', 'To make the filling, heat the oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté for about 3 minutes, until softened. Add the garlic and sauté for about 1 minute more. Add the squash and sauté for 6 to 7 minutes, just until the squash begins to soften. Season with the chile powder and salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.886', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0fd74931-a976-4d80-99d4-02a1eb48a843', 'Add the kale and cook, stirring, for about 1 minute, until it begins to wilt. Remove from the heat, taste, and adjust the seasoning with salt if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.889', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.903');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4a0a040-821c-410b-b1ee-52c4452d43bc', 'Serve with the tortillas, crema, pumpkin seeds, onion, cilantro, and salsa. To assemble each taco, invite guests to spoon about 1/2 cup of the warm filling into a tortilla and top with some crema and pumpkin seeds. If guests want more toppings, they can finish off their tacos with onion, cilantro, and salsa.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.892', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fbd5633-ff5a-464e-aa54-44d9feede6a2', 'Purée almonds, oil, salt, and 1/2 cup water in a high-powered blender on high speed until thick, light, and smooth, about 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.896', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.904');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6e3a8b5-f757-4962-a15a-6c3066774e0e', 'Aioli can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and chill. Thin with water if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.9', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.905');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6783799-e153-452e-a998-626ffd2d1195', 'Whisk lime juice and sugar in large bowl until sugar dissolves. Add watermelon and all remaining ingredients; toss gently. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.903', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.907');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7fcd2b9c-fcdd-40a4-8f57-0fafd3538285', 'Purée 1 chopped Granny Smith apple (with core and peel), 1/4 cup raw unfiltered apple cider vinegar, and 1 tablespoon fresh lime juice in a blender, occasionally scraping down sides of blender with a spatula, until smooth. Strain mixture through a finemesh sieve into a medium bowl, pressing down on solids with spatula to extract all juice; discard solids. Whisk in 1 tablespoon minced shallot and 1 teaspoon raw sugar. Whisk in 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon safflower or grapeseed oil until well blended. Season with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper. DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewhisk before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.907', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.909');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5cc0a51b-be38-49b4-9bd7-432e280b00ed', 'Place watermelon in a large resealable plastic bag. Purée rice vinegar, oil, soy sauce, lime juice, tahini, agave nectar, and plum vinegar in a blender until smooth. Pour over watermelon, seal bag, and chill at least 4 hours and up to 1 day.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.91', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.91');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37d4238e-aa80-44ff-9d4c-8d6d0a944ece', 'Heat a large skillet over medium. Remove watermelon from marinade; set marinade aside. Cook watermelon, tossing often, until lightly caramelized and dried out, 6–8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.914', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.911');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0432058e-92b3-4324-8707-caf93aecc94d', 'Meanwhile, bring reserved marinade to a boil in a small saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer until thickened to the consistency of heavy cream, 12–15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.917', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.911');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('50058af4-c7db-4882-96e7-ad40f6bc7d09', 'Chill watermelon and sauce separately at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.921', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.912');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf3d1dbc-e58e-46bf-9be2-650244047ee8', 'To serve, toss watermelon with sauce; taste and season with salt as needed. Top with scallions and cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.925', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.913');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fd79a187-64a2-4989-a5b4-8e2e3322054e', 'Watermelon and sauce can be made 12 hours ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.928', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.914');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('efe4ac7c-c400-42d6-8a8d-1bb2a442785d', 'Rinse rice in a large bowl with cool water until water runs clear. Drain rice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.932', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.915');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2eab7ed0-1710-41f7-8792-1eae2917dd9c', 'Combine rice, coconut cream, sugar, salt, and 2 cups water in a medium saucepan. Bring just to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar, then cover and reduce heat to low. (Alternatively, cook rice in an electric rice steamer.) Cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 40-45 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork; cover and let sit for 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.936', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.915');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0ae046a-5107-452f-a322-5fb4c6908ec9', 'Place sugar in small bowl. Mix in lemon juice as needed to make icing just thin enough to drip off fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.939', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.916');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('39b92074-6490-4f36-9cdb-bdc21c8cafbc', '1. In a blender, combine the lemongrass with 3 cups water and puree until mostly smooth. (Lemongrass is very fibrous, so you will not get to a completely uniform consistency; that''s okay.) Transfer the puree to a saucepan and bring to a simmer over medium heat. Remove from the heat, cover, and let the liquid infuse for 15 to 20 minutes. Strain the syrup into a bowl, pressing on the solids; discard the solids in the strainer. You should wind up with about 2 cups of strained "lemongrass tea"; be sure to measure out your final yield.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.943', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.917');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b1ebb14c-9eb9-4bb2-b36c-b3caf2d8ab2e', '2. In a medium saucepan, combine the "lemongrass tea" with the same amount (by volume) of sugar. So, if you wind up with 2 cups tea, you will add 2 cups (400 grams) sugar. Stir the mixture over medium-high heat until all the sugar has dissolved and the syrup comes to a simmer. Remove from the heat and let cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.947', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.917');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82ba1497-ea5c-439f-9587-562540d7fa0b', '3. Transfer the cooled syrup to a quart-size container and stir in the ginger juice and lime juice. Cover and refrigerate the sorbet base until completely cold, at least 3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.95', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.918');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('103cf623-492e-4c58-ac4f-dc303369a7f4', '4. Pour the chilled sorbet base into an ice cream maker and freeze according to the manufacturer''s instructions. Place the container in which you refrigerated the sorbet base in the freezer so you can use it to store the finished sorbet. Churn the sorbet until it resembles Italian ice. Transfer the sorbet to the chilled storage container and freeze until hardened to your desired consistency. The sorbet will keep, frozen, for up to 7 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.954', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.918');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f8c93d6f-871e-4048-bc1c-5c0512a11862', 'Toast coconut in a small heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, until golden-brown, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.957', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.919');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3fb96967-5e16-428c-86a6-ba5208b454f2', 'Cut pineapple crosswise into 8 slices (about 3/4 inch thick) and core slices. Stir together remaining ingredients in a shallow glass baking dish and add pineapple in 1 layer, turning to coat evenly. Marinate, turning occasionally, 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.961', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.919');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79a31910-7ed1-462a-853e-4a8b15873b7a', 'Oil grill rack. Grill pineapple (reserve marinade), covered, turning once, until grill marks appear and pineapple is heated through, about 4 minutes. Serve pineapple with marinade and sprinkle with toasted coconut.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.964', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.92');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1714756e-1157-4c24-9334-05d1839a1bd0', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Brush corn with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Grill corn until tender and brown in spots, turning occasionally, about 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Cut off corn kernels; place in large bowl. Add black beans, jicama, carrots, green onions, cilantro, and basil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.92');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad9d8e3f-1d93-49b2-b732-6e1c320dbee1', 'Whisk lime juice, orange juice, lime peel, cumin, and remaining 4 tablespoons oil in small bowl. Mix dressing into bean salad. Season generously with salt and pepper. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover; chill. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.971', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.921');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8fc30c12-2933-48ed-816d-c8ddb9fe940b', '1. Using a box grater, mandoline, or a coarse Microplane grater, grate the cabbage. In a large saucepan, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and sauté for 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.974', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.921');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04db678b-01a6-4198-be46-963e33b76a11', '2. Lower the heat to medium; add the cabbage and apples and stir to combine. Add the juniper berries, allspice berries, cloves, bay leaf, salt, pepper, jelly, vinegar, sugar, and 1/2 cup (120ml) of water and stir to combine. Turn the heat to low, cover, and cook for 40 minutes, until the cabbage is tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.978', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.923');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2a460983-a62c-4cb8-9781-43d68c9f118f', '3. Remove the juniper berries, allspice berries, cloves, and bay leaf. Serve the cabbage hot or at room temperature. Refrigerate for up to 4 days. Leftovers can also be frozen in an airtight container for up to 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.981', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.924');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f995a24b-3950-498e-812e-cd9a341703b3', 'Cook green beans in large saucepan of boiling salted water until just tender, about 5 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer beans to plate. Add orzo to same boiling water. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally; drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.986', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.925');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c8f801d5-3f25-4941-b8e5-c11c1df539c5', 'Blend dill, oil, vinegar, and lemon juice in mini processor until almost smooth. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.989', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.925');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59c38802-1e0e-427d-ae56-e85fad7854a6', 'Cut beans crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Place in large bowl. Add orzo, cucumber, and fennel; mix in dressing. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.993', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.925');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1762cf9-81db-4c65-b065-5465e8427a34', 'Bring wine to a boil with water and sugar, stirring, in a 4-quart heavy pot. Add rhubarb and cook at a bare simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until very tender and beginning to fall apart, 5 to 7 minutes. Purée in a food processor with lemon juice until smooth, then force through a coarse sieve into an 8- to 9-inch baking pan, pressing hard on solids (discard solids).', '2023-06-12 17:13:28.997', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.926');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5fe4e8a-3e51-487d-b2b4-a5a50f9ec0a5', 'Freeze, stirring and crushing lumps with a fork every 1 1/2 hours, until evenly frozen, about 8 hours total. Scrape granita with a fork to lighten texture, crushing any lumps.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.001', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.926');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('46210188-32f7-4b20-afc5-b5bb269f5ee1', 'Combine vinegar, brown sugar and ginger in small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add tomatoes with juices and cinnamon. Bring mixture to boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered until chutney is slightly thickened, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Discard cinnamon. (Chutney can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Rewarm over low heat or bring to room temperature before using.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.004', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.926');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1fed4f9-5edc-41ed-ab77-a397494e2b49', 'Combine 1 1/2 cups blueberries, sugar and 1/3 cup water in heavy small saucepan. Simmer over medium heat until berries burst, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Add remaining 1 cup berries. Cook until compote coats spoon, stirring often, about 8 minutes. (Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and chill.) Serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.008', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.927');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d09c3fba-7975-4833-8d9e-6b82934aecbe', 'Toss peaches with lemon juice in medium bowl. Add preserves, sugar, and cardamom and toss. Let stand 10 minutes to allow flavors to blend. (Can be made 4 hours ahead; cover and refrigerate.) Add raspberries and toss gently.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.012', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.929');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef3eb188-6674-4cd2-b6c9-f814edb742b4', 'For the dressing, first soak the bread in water for 5 minutes. Drain the bread, then place in a blender with the almonds, garlic, vinegar, and 1/2 cup of the olive oil. Gradually add the cold water and blend on high for 30 seconds, or until a smooth purée forms. Add salt to taste, then set aside in a bowl until serving time.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.015', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.93');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a6e87ed-d57c-4a22-9bdb-be868b5940ec', 'Preheat the oven to 350°F', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.019', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.93');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d3b32428-a12f-4ac0-a4f4-65653383e2ae', 'On the stove, heat a ridged grill pan or grill to high, until slightly smoky.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.023', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.931');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ea2c5ff-b330-4e77-a7c1-826b857633a2', 'Coat the cut sides of the zucchini pieces with 1/3 cup of the olive oil. Place them on the ridged grill pan and cook them, turning now and then, until they are branded all over. Place on a baking tray and finish in the oven for another 3–5 minutes-you want to cook them through, but leave a bit of texture and crunch to the zucchini. Once cooked, set aside and keep warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.026', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.932');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8a1ee48-124d-4945-bea8-5cb07ebf9af6', 'Place the nuts and remaining olive oil in a small saucepan over medium heat and warm through until fragrant. Transfer the nuts to a bowl, then season with the paprika and salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.932');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf87dea5-1da9-497f-acac-03c47d1e7d50', 'To assemble the dish, place the warm zucchini in a large mixing bowl, along with the herbs and nuts, and stir gently to combine. Season with salt to taste and freshly ground black pepper if needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.033', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.933');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b46ff978-352a-4352-87b2-3e03ba87a9c5', 'Dollop most of the dressing around the bottom of your serving dish, then arrange the zucchini salad on top. If desired, drizzle some more dressing on top for that creamy, nutty flavor and texture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.036', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.933');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('83d47e6d-22cf-447b-8bd0-bb22e5e26f8d', 'Pulse toasted nuts in a food processor until coarsely chopped.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.04', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.934');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6067d16f-14c3-45af-abc5-972576841224', 'Add dried fruit, zest, and spices and pulse again until chopped.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.934');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6863b241-24b9-41d6-9a7e-6ef1d1017015', 'Add Port and pulse until all ingredients are chopped and combined into a coarse paste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.048', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.935');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8aee4328-98f4-4169-940e-4c85e8994463', 'Transfer to a bowl and stir in raisins.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.051', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.935');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf57f771-7961-4892-aab5-2abf79e2efee', 'Bring beans, onion, fennel, carrot, garlic, thyme sprigs, chiles de árbol, 1/3 cup oil, and 8 cups water to a simmer in a large pot over medium. Reduce heat to bring liquid to a gentle simmer and cook until beans are creamy all the way through, 50–65 minutes. Season generously with salt. Serve beans topped with pepper and a drizzle of oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.054', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.936');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('784a4766-0492-4f80-bccf-d958fdaf0d5e', 'Beans can be cooked 3 days ahead. Let cool in cooking liquid; cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.058', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.936');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63c68042-28d2-4bf7-9c6b-6c855cbb758c', 'Cook green beans in a large pot of boiling salted water (2 Tbsp salt for 6 qt water) just until tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to an ice bath, then drain and pat dry. Add lima beans and black-eyed peas to boiling water and simmer until tender, 16 to 18 minutes. Drain and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.061', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.936');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e292d43b-c7ca-48f0-bc8e-495dc9171df3', 'While limas and peas simmer, whisk together lemon juice, 1 1/2 tsp salt, and 3/4 tsp pepper in a large bowl, then whisk in oil and scallions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.065', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.937');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('594d6fa1-1ebf-44d4-a2f8-cef72b035bbf', 'Add lima beans and black-eyed peas while still hot and toss well. Cool 15 minutes, then add green beans, tossing well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.068', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.939');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('75b92309-45cb-4466-92f5-f761e8654aa5', 'Cut peel and white pith off oranges and grapefruit. Using small knife and working over heavy small saucepan to catch juice, cut between membranes of fruit to release segments. Using slotted spoon, transfer segments to work surface and chop. Transfer segments to bowl. Scrape juice from work surface into saucepan. Squeeze any remaining jucie from citrus membranes into saucepan. Whisk curry powder into juice. Boil until reduced to 1/4 cups, about 10 minutes. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.071', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.94');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11405078-bd00-458b-86dc-76fa8552451a', 'Add avocado, onion and chives to citrus segments. Drizzle with oil and 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon reduced juice (reserve remaining juice for another use). Season with salt and white pepper. Toss gently; serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.075', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.94');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7a5d739-59a1-48ad-8caf-58ae99739be1', 'In a 10-inch non-stick skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and sauté pine nuts, stirring until golden. With a slotted spoon transfer pine nuts to paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.079', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.941');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abf34b6d-031a-4a92-a270-d5b8c34beb04', 'In a skillet cook garlic over moderate heat, stirring , until golden and with a slotted spoon discard. Add fennel to skillet and cook, stirring, until golden, about 2 minutes. Add lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste and cook until fennel is crisp-tender. Stir in radicchio and sauté mixture over moderately high heat, tossing with 2 wooden spoons, just until radicchio is wilted and tender. Add pine nuts and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.082', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.941');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('940ac7e1-c83b-4f45-88b8-e2b61f93c306', 'Rinse rice in a sieve until water runs clear and drain well. Cook cumin and mustard seeds in oil in a 2-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until mustard seeds begin to pop, about 2 minutes. Stir in garlic and rice and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add water and bring to a boil, uncovered. Cover rice and cook over very low heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Remove pan from heat and let rice stand, covered, 5 minutes. Fluff rice with a fork and stir in scallions and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.086', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.942');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b051d47b-dbdd-4b58-95e2-6db1e2f1deab', 'Pulse the celery in a food processor until coarsely chopped. Add the chickpeas, 5 tablespoons sauce, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, and salt. Pulse to create a coarse puree. Taste and add more sauce, lemon juice, and/or salt as needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.089', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.942');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b13257e7-604e-40c5-89b2-fe9bdfd1835a', 'Add olive oil and parsley to potatoes. Toss well and let marinate at least 20 minutes and up to 2 hours at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.572', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10aa0ea7-424f-4e3d-b320-2e8df8c08870', 'Puree first 7 ingredients in processor until paste forms. Cook in large pot over medium heat until aromatic, stirring often, about 10 minutes. Add tomato paste. Cook until mixture starts to darken and brown, stirring often, about 5 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.093', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.943');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('313bdaa1-ab01-4336-98d7-62c718e570c6', 'Add broth, brown sugar, lime leaves, and cardamom. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often and scraping up browned bits. DO AHEAD Can be made 2 days ahead. Cool, cover, and chill. Bring to simmer before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.097', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.944');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('110b5aca-957b-47c3-8db5-32269269a87b', 'Add sweet potatoes, russet potatoes, coconut, carrots, tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper to mixture in pot. Bring to boil, then reduce heat to medium low. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes. Add spinach, if desired, and cook until wilted, about 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Discard lime leaves and cardamom. Transfer curry to bowl; garnish with cilantro and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.1', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.944');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a94b8e58-f9f1-496d-b8f6-c7ed6b4f9bdd', 'In a bowl, combine all ingredients. Marinate olives, covered and chilled, stirring occasionally, at least 1 day and up to 3.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.104', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.945');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57458822-20b4-471b-a76d-48a9908793a7', 'Mix garlic, parsley, chives, oil, and almonds in a small bowl; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.107', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.946');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94d888e1-0fee-44df-bf87-4e7aa8c4c27d', 'DO AHEAD: Salsa verde can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.111', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.946');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dabc58ac-40c0-42f7-85a1-20f5a4536c2d', 'Heat oil in a medium skillet over medium-high. Add capers and fry, stirring occasionally, until crisp, about 2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer capers to a paper towel-lined plate to drain and season with salt. Fry basil in batches in same skillet until crisp, about 30 seconds. Transfer to paper-towel lined plate and season with salt. Let oil in pan cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.114', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.947');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f104024-135c-4ab6-8dd2-ea87104c1026', 'Toss cucumber, tomatoes, onion, vinegar, fried capers, and 1/4 cup warm caper-basil oil in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Vigorously rub one side of hot toasts with garlic, then top with tomato mixture. Top with fried basil leaves and serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.118', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.947');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('809a8a53-b784-478f-b2fd-9ba68d6888f8', 'Purée raspberries with syrup, sugar, and lemon juice in a blender or food processor. Pour mixture through a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing on solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.122', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.947');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9863bf2-a665-4c9f-b702-724824192c98', 'Combine sumac with soaking liquid, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, 2 tablespoons pomegranate molasses, garlic, 2 teaspoons vinegar, and dried mint in a small bowl. Gradually add oil, whisking constantly, until well blended. Season with salt; add more lemon juice, pomegranate molasses, and vinegar to taste, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.948');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da024975-4856-466e-950e-9796c664c266', 'Place pita pieces in a medium bowl; pour oil over and toss to coat. Season pita to taste with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.128', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.948');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('86dd58f9-8596-4476-9b43-bb6a0d44c96d', 'Mix tomatoes and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Add 3/4 of dressing; toss to coat, adding more dressing by tablespoonfuls as needed. Season with salt. Add pita; toss once. Sprinkle sumac over, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.132', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.948');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9dddbd8f-0ae5-4935-b92c-f3f6078f035d', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy pot. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer until mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes. Transfer to medium bowl. Refrigerate compote until cold. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.) Spoon into bowls. Top with sorbet and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.135', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.948');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4f21bdf2-703b-4d47-a481-8682b1403f80', '1. Wash and pat dry the eggplants. Roast them whole over an open flame on top of the stove or under the broiler, turning, until the skins are charred on all sides. (This may also be done on a grill.) Remove and let cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.139', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.948');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b9ab3b3-d122-4f79-868c-c797d2e3416b', '2. Have a large bowl with the olive oil ready. Cut the eggplants open lengthwise and remove as many of the seeds as possible. Scoop out the roasted eggplant pulp and place it in a bowl with the olive oil. Salt lightly. With a fork and knife, cut the eggplant so that it is chunky. Add the onion, garlic, capers, tomato, and parsley and mix with a fork to combine well. Add the vinegar and adjust the seasoning with additional salt, pepper, and vinegar if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.143', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.949');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79509aa9-7b25-4c4c-aed3-3eeb671d3659', 'Bring 4 cups water to boil in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add salt. Gradually whisk in semolina. Boil until thick, whisking often, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.146', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.949');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a1683d75-2c26-46e9-bdc7-4baa699b8a40', 'Heat butter in heavy medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, ginger, curry leaves, chile, mustard seeds, and cumin seeds; sauté until aromatic, about 1 minute. Add tomatoes, peas, and cashews. Sauté mixture until cashews begin to color, about 2 minutes. Stir mixture into semolina. Season with salt and pepper. Rewarm, if necessary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.15', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.949');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c4e86e3d-94c8-475d-b135-e87f9263e265', '*Semolina flour is available at some supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and Italian markets. Farina can be ordered from amazon.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.153', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.949');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6667ce7-f006-4dd9-ba9e-3629c7a3e519', '**Also known as kari patta; available at Indian markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.95');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0593535-36c9-4d5a-957a-5d517e9ac7bc', '***Sold at specialty foods stores, Indian and Asian markets, and adrianascaravan.com. If unavailable, substitute brown mustard seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.16', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.95');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef003e63-26ab-436f-b6f6-27c41ec3969b', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Brush both sides of portobello mushrooms with 1/3 cup olive oil. Place whole mushrooms and whole red bell peppers on grill rack. Grill until mushrooms are tender and bell peppers are blackened on all sides, turning occasionally, about 20 minutes for mushrooms and 25 minutes for bell peppers. Transfer mushrooms to plate. Enclose bell peppers in paper bag. Let stand 10 minutes. Peel and seed peppers. Cut into 1/2-inch-wide strips. Cut mushrooms into 1/2-inch-wide strips. Season mushrooms and peppers to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.164', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.95');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b0be353-b86c-44c9-8aaf-e8adf8c4b792', 'Combine 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar, chopped fresh rosemary and garlic clove in food processor. With machine running, gradually add remaining 1/3 cup olive oil and process until well blended. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.168', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.95');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27a45ed5-539b-4385-8148-a19d0ad26981', 'Arrange mixed baby greens on large platter. Top with portobello mushroom strips, then red bell pepper strips. Drizzle dressing over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.171', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.951');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('529732ee-aa35-439c-8b8c-6b8d49e24a73', 'Working in batches, cook greens in a large pot of boiling heavily salted water until just barely wilted, about 2 minutes. Drain; let cool, then squeeze out excess water with your hands. Coarsely chop; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.174', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.951');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e5eee52c-f867-477f-9576-063a1ef1a38e', 'Combine pears and 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons wine in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat. Cover and cook until pears are tender, about 8 minutes. Puree pear mixture and sugar in processor. Mix in 3/4 cup wine and corn syrup. Chill until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.346', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e04988cd-f30e-4fc5-8145-38faa52b1f5f', 'Heat a clean large pot over medium. Cook garlic and 1/2 cup oil, smashing down on garlic with a wooden spoon, until golden and soft, about 4 minutes. Add chiles de árbol and cook 30 seconds to infuse the oil with chile. Reduce heat to medium-low; add reserved greens. Cook, tossing and stirring occasionally, until greens are deep green and tender, 20–30 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer greens to a platter and drizzle with more oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.951');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('83557f3b-4377-4692-808a-0d3b5e7f7716', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Combine first 3 ingredients; add Asian sesame oil and toss to coat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill vegetables until tender, turning often, about 7 minutes for eggplant and mushrooms and 5 minutes for green onions. Transfer mushrooms and onions to cutting board; cool slightly. Slice mushrooms and onions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.951');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7e77912a-4b64-4d1c-9320-fba4cba8fffb', 'Meanwhile, cook noodles in large pot of boiling salted water until almost tender but still firm to bite, about 3 minutes. Add sugar snap peas to noodles; cook 1 minute longer. Drain well. Transfer noodle mixture to large serving bowl. Add grilled vegetables.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.185', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.952');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0601514-0c9c-4c60-a92f-36d768b82688', 'Whisk last 4 ingredients in small bowl to blend. Toss noodle salad with dressing; season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.189', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.952');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0a4d401-20d5-4472-ac5f-4d6d28e1bae7', 'Test Kitchen Tip: The cooking time of Japanese-style chuka soba noodles varies by a minute or two depending on the brand of noodle. Test them after three minutes to avoid overcooking.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.193', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.952');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79c95566-5df4-41bb-8ffc-f179b4781a63', 'Spray grill rack with nonstick spray. Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Whisk vinegar, sugar, 1/2 cup oil, mustard, and tarragon in medium bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.197', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.952');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65406843-29ca-4ccf-a790-7f5f03f7af86', 'Brush cabbages and green onions with oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill cabbages until dark grill marks form, 3 to 4 minutes per side. Grill green onions until charred on 1 side, 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer vegetables to work surface.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.201', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.952');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f9da8e2-6f0f-414c-bda7-1230d8d7de9f', 'Chop green onions and cabbages; place in large bowl, discarding cores. Add dressing; toss to coat. Season slaw to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.204', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.953');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a2d89f37-1a00-4eff-a8cf-a8f7a4c7633d', '1. Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.208', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.954');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70cdc66b-fb05-436f-b752-0fef1b88b4e4', '2. Add the onions, saute for 2 minutes. Add in garlic, ginger, carrots and mushrooms and saute for 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.212', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.954');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d3dcd1b-196b-4872-a40b-f973cd4b62ff', '3. Add the cabbage, kale, scallions and salt and saute an additional 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.215', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.955');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('605861c4-f051-43e2-be35-062fafafdd05', '4. In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, rice vinegar and sesame oil, and add it to the skillet. Stir to coat the veggies well. Remove from the heat and allow to cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.219', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.955');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8bf5e3b-08cc-46c5-bc27-d038d3d78731', '5. Place one spring roll wrapper on a flat surface in front of you, with a corner facing you, so it makes a diamond shape.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.222', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.955');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ab4d8f19-ff55-4769-95ff-56ad541a1c8f', '6. Place 2 tablespoons of the filling in a line in middle of the wrapper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.225', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.955');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f6850cee-d48c-4928-8244-f54606f77b79', '7. Fold the corners toward the center on top of the filling and the bottom corner over the top of the filing. Brush a little water on the top corner and roll it up like a burrito.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.229', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.956');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6542e8d-53c4-49a1-b13e-0aba79149c17', '8. Heat the remaining 3 tablespoons oil in the skillet or wok over medium heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.232', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.956');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18af8eaa-2f40-461b-8c80-26703705f9bf', '9. Place a few spring rolls in the pan, making sure you have room to roll them. Cook them on each side for 2–5 minutes, until they are golden brown on each side. Each spring roll will take about 7–10 minutes to fully cook.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.236', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.956');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('edcef764-8e22-40bc-b237-62ba69e0108e', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray 9-inch diameter cake pan with 2-inch-high sides with nonstick spray. Sift all purpose flour, sugar, whole wheat flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt into large bowl. Add 3/4 cup water, oil, juice concentrate, vanilla, and vinegar and whisk to blend. Transfer batter to prepared pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.239', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.956');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fd922383-2fee-479a-9647-faf5692e9b86', 'Bake cake until tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 35 minutes. Cool cake in pan on rack. Carefully cut around pan sides and turn out cake onto serving platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.243', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.956');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4e9dc6e-7a27-4004-80d2-ff997995cc58', 'Place chopped bittersweet chocolate in medium metal bowl. Set bowl over saucepan of barely simmering water. Stir constantly until chocolate is melted and smooth. Carefully transfer bowl to work surface. Cool melted chocolate to room temperature, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.246', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.957');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd3a54cf-6d4b-4b69-bafb-4c5e4cec239f', 'Using electric mixer, beat "butter" in large bowl until smooth. Add powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon juice concentrate, vanilla, and salt; beat until smooth. Add 2 tablespoons juice concentrate; beat until blended. Beat in agave nectar, then chocolate. Let stand 10 minutes. Frost top and sides of cake. DO AHEAD: Cake can be made up to 8 hours ahead. Cover with cake dome and store at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.249', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.957');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abce18f8-bcdc-4a24-9bd6-1500ed294821', 'Also called whole grain pastry flour; available at some supermarkets and at most natural foods stores.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.253', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.957');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6d0138e2-e73b-4e9e-82cb-34f8cdd2b468', '** A natural sweetener made from the sap of agave succulent plants; sold at some supermarkets and at natural foods stores.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.256', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.957');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d37d206-1de4-4661-a2f6-72915b6ed71c', '1. Preheat the oven to 400°F. Puncture each potato with a fork three times, sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon of the coarse sea salt, and wrap individually in foil. Bake until tender to the touch, about 40 minutes. Unwrap the potatoes and let cool; when cool enough to handle, cut each into eight wedges. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.259', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.958');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('98bb12f2-6533-4b6c-920a-bcee1a369266', '2. While the potatoes are cooling, whisk together the olive oil, 1 teaspoon of the salt, the garlic, pepper, and shallots in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.263', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.958');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f8ca941-772b-49e3-84fa-fa8fa6bf2477', '3. Place the portobello caps on a sheet pan with rimmed edges and coat them evenly on both sides with the olive oil mixture, leaving them rounded sides up. Roast until soft in the middle, 8 to 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.267', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.958');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7456dbf1-41a8-432d-85e0-2b1bd1c0fa25', '4. Transfer the portobello caps to a plate, still rounded sides up, and set aside to cool. Pour the wine, vegetable stock, and mustard onto the warm sheet pan to mix with the mushroom cooking juices. Scrape any solids off the tray, then carefully pour this mixture into a large saucepan. Heat the mixture over medium heat until reduced by half, 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.27', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.958');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04b11940-4ced-4244-a71d-c51c5904fc1b', '5. Stir the tarragon into the red wine sauce. Remove the saucepan from the heat and cover to keep warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.959');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c582a166-044f-47d4-843d-832c2bac65ba', '6. In a large sauté pan, heat the canola oil over high heat. When the oil is very hot, carefully fry a few potato wedges at a time until they turn brown on all sides, about 6 minutes. Transfer the frites as they are done to a plate lined with paper towels and sprinkle them lightly with the remaining 1 teaspoon salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.277', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.959');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3bb539b0-3501-4cdc-ba1a-d9064fbd9675', '7. Reheat the portobello caps in the oven if necessary. Serve smothered with red wine sauce and frites on the side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.28', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.959');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60f92f15-8d29-4907-819a-50c47ca47ef6', 'Oil 15x10x2-inch glass baking dish. Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 18 minutes. Drain; return to same pot. Stir over low heat to dry, about 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add 1/2 cup oil. Mash until smooth; season to taste with salt and pepper. Mix in 1 tablespoon oregano. Spread in prepared dish; smooth top. Do ahead Can be made ahead. Let stand at room temperature 2 hours or cover and refrigerate overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.284', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8019a7c7-a4fc-45f9-9a97-0285317b1301', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Bake potatoes uncovered 30 minutes. Stir to distribute any crusty parts; press again to even layer. Bake until very hot and beginning to get crusty on bottom, about 45 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.287', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ae52102c-91c3-4aff-9894-23ebe1d6ad6c', 'Remove potatoes from oven and preheat broiler. Broil potatoes until golden and crusty on top, repositioning for even cooking, about 4 minutes. Cut potato cake into 8 squares. Cut each square in half on diagonal. Transfer potato wedges to platter. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon oregano.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.291', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.96');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ec2f50e-d385-4a6b-bfca-c144f5df679f', 'In a bowl whisk together lemon juice, oil, and salt to taste. Stir in remaining ingredients, except lettuce leaves, with salt and black pepper to taste and let salad stand, stirring once or twice, 15 minutes for flavors to develop. Line 2 plates with lettuce and divide salad between them.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.294', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('67271f54-6828-4105-bad8-337ec39509ec', 'In a kettle combine the black beans with enough cold water to cover them by 2 inches, simmer them, covered, for 1 hour, or until they are tender, and drain them well. While the beans are cooking, in a large saucepan combine the barley with 4 cups boiling salted water and simmer it, covered, for 45 minutes, or until it is cooked but still al dente. Drain the barley in a colander, rinse it, and drain it well. In a small bowl whisk together the lemon juice, the mustard, and salt and pepper to taste, add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified. In a large bowl combine the black beans, the barley, and the onion, add the dressing, and toss the salad until it is combined well. The salad may be prepared up to this point 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled. In a saucepan of boiling salted water cook the green beans for 4 to 5 minutes, or until they are just tender, refresh them under cold water, and drain them well. Cut the beans crosswise into 1/4-inch pieces, add them to the salad with pine nuts and salt and pepper to taste, and toss the salad until it is combined well. Serve the salad chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.297', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('32a215a9-0a16-461a-ad8b-e5f51fe21aed', 'In a colander rinse the beans under cold water and discard any discolored ones. In a kettle combine the beans with enough cold water to cover them by 2 inches, bring the water to a boil, and boil the beans for 2 minutes. Remove the kettle from the heat and let the beans soak, covered, for 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.961');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c06b027b-2ae4-4d49-96d5-99f395aaa89a', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Mix oats, pumpkin seeds, sunflower seeds, sesame seeds, chia seeds, poppy seeds, and salt in a large bowl. Stir oil, maple syrup, and 3/4 cup room-temperature water in a medium bowl to combine. Pour liquid over oat mixture and toss until mixture is completely soaked. Let sit 10 minutes; mixture will absorb water and thicken.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.304', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.962');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5a1d45b-0b34-4ae4-a33c-909b6779fd12', 'Form oat mixture into a ball and transfer to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Press a second sheet of parchment paper directly on top and, using a rolling pin, flatten to 1/8" thick (the shape doesn’t matter). Remove top layer of parchment.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.308', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.962');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('52fb51f7-edd4-4e3c-b62c-6fe6fee91ac7', 'Bake cracker until golden brown around edges, 15–20 minutes. Remove from oven and carefully turn out, parchment side up. Place a fresh sheet of parchment on baking sheet. Remove parchment from cracker, carefully turn cracker over, and return to baking sheet. Bake until firm and golden brown around edges, 15–20 minutes. Let cool on baking sheet, then break into pieces with your hands.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.311', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.963');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59ccbc06-6f4f-4e0c-ad79-c892f54a8b93', 'Crackers can be made 1 week ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.315', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.964');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a37310c-b7ac-480a-be7c-087bc8719c8a', 'Place frozen berries in large bowl. Sprinkle sugar over berries; let stand until berries are just thawed but still cold, about 1 hour. Using fork, coarsely mash berries. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.318', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.964');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d384ace-9ca6-47de-a8ac-010641996587', 'Spoon sorbet into dessert glasses. Top with blackberry sauce and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.321', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.964');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48f1f48d-74cf-47bc-8cec-d5319ec00be9', 'Prepare a hardwood-charcoal fire in a grill. Let coals cool to medium heat (coals should be covered with ash and glowing red with no black remaining).', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.325', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.965');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fd11baf8-bb22-4591-b80b-ba1796db5e47', 'Place 2 small eggplants (about 1 pound total) directly on coals and cook, turning occasionally, until skins are blackened and flesh has collapsed, 10-15 minutes. (Alternatively, grill on the grate of a gas or charcoal grill over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, 15-20 minutes.) Transfer to a rimmed baking sheet and let cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.328', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.965');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac87e230-59ef-4018-ae35-30a07e9a48a6', 'Carefully remove skins from eggplants, leaving stems intact. Place eggplants on a wire rack set inside the same rimmed baking sheet and let stand 30 minutes to allow excess water to drain. Just before serving, split lengthwise and serve with desired sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.331', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.965');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c460ae2-eafa-4bcc-be5c-bc5991c68ef6', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook scallions, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 3 minutes. Add garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add corn, zucchini, cumin, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender, 4 to 6 minutes. Stir in cilantro and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.335', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.966');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7f9c67a-86ff-4eb5-8387-5dcf07756ea6', 'Boil 1 cup wine in heavy small saucepan until reduced to 1/4 cup, about 6 minutes. Pour into large bowl. Add grapefruit juice, sugar, corn syrup, grenadine and peel; stir until sugar dissolves. Mix in remaining 3/4 cup wine. Refrigerate until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.339', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.966');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('686fd69e-614a-40db-91c9-8a050b9b12b5', 'Cook all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat until berries pop and soften, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes. Puree in processor. Strain into bowl. Refrigerate until cold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.342', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.966');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('896fad0c-c448-4101-9421-cb86eee09d1b', 'Process each mixture separately in ice cream maker according to manufacturer''s instructions. Freeze in covered containers. (Can be made 1 week ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.35', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cddb7e46-3510-4809-9c32-df6cf4e35c10', 'Place rice in strainer. Rinse under cold water until water runs clear. Drain well. Transfer rice to heavy medium saucepan. Add 1 1/4 cups fresh cold water and kelp to pan. Cover and let soak 30 minutes. Uncover, discard kelp and bring mixture to boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until water is absorbed and rice is just tender, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand covered 15 minutes. Transfer rice to large glass bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.357', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.967');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e40a0019-a827-4502-b140-bb6fcce8e66f', 'Combine vinegar, sugar and salt in small saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Drizzle mixture over rice. Gently toss rice with vinegar mixture to coat. Cover rice with clean damp towel and cool completely at room temperature (do not refrigerate).', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.361', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.968');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('934785ba-c3c9-4c68-b9a4-0d7de5ac1a41', 'Cook garlic and red pepper flakes in oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring, until garlic is golden, about 1 minute. Add broccoli and salt and cook, breaking up frozen chunks and stirring occasionally, until broccoli is thawed and crisp-tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in chickpeas and cook until heated through.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.365', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.968');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('552bfdfe-b734-45bd-b2ba-38956ba880d4', 'Cook pasta in a 6- to 8-quart pot of boiling salted water until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain pasta in a colander. Add pasta and reserved cooking water to broccoli and chickpeas in skillet and cook over moderate heat, tossing, until combined well. Serve drizzled with additional olive oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.368', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.97');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2fb9c77b-6933-4851-b91d-e9d891928141', 'Preheat oven to 400°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.372', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.971');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('852df791-91bc-4858-9505-596bf229b7b0', 'Cut off and discard top of garlic head to expose cloves. Brush top of head with 1/2 tablespoon olive oil. Wrap garlic in foil and roast until tender, about 45 minutes. Cool to warm, then squeeze garlic cloves from skins into a small bowl, discarding skins.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.972');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abf7a3fd-5926-4baa-88db-684cdf94897d', 'Meanwhile, cut eggplant into 1/2-inch pieces and toss with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt in a large colander. Let drain 30 minutes. Squeeze eggplant in a kitchen towel to remove liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.378', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.972');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b5adbda-f869-445c-9c68-9077cd7392a3', 'Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then sauté one third of eggplant until browned and tender, about 6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl. Cook remaining eggplant in olive oil in same manner (in 2 batches), transferring to bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.382', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.973');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15e258f9-be81-4e06-a9ca-77a33018b68f', 'Add 1 cup cooked eggplant to garlic and coarsely mash together. Stir into remaining eggplant with sun-dried tomatoes (without tomato oil), parsley, basil, lemon juice, and 3/4 teaspoon pepper. Season with salt and drizzle with tomato oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.385', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.973');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10c2b91c-b03f-4c0e-885a-7f3dd855e82b', 'Artezin Mendocino
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc09251c-e1ca-48fa-b82b-8c21c05f4bb7', 'Bring sugar, water, and lemon juice to a boil, stirring occasionally until sugar is dissolved, then boil, uncovered, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in cantaloupe and raisins and simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until cantaloupe is translucent and syrup is thickened, 15 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.974');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b3088a11-4e01-4d9f-8b48-66032497ac70', 'Transfer conserve to a metal bowl, then set bowl in a larger bowl of ice and cold water to cool, stirring occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.396', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('265acf74-3caf-4b1d-9e3e-cbe09e379563', 'Combine 2 cups water, coconut milk, sugar, and salt in heavy large saucepan. Bring to simmer, then stir in rice. Cover, leaving slight opening for steam to escape. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 12 minutes. Cover tightly, remove from heat, and let stand 10 minutes. Transfer rice to bowl; sprinkle with toasted coconut.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.4', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1428d552-194f-412e-b434-047f0c521202', 'Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.404', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.976');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fec02f79-f671-434f-8dc3-3bd87b6f71bc', 'Combine spices in a small bowl and store in a cool, dark place in a tightly sealed container.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.408', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.977');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('353e2518-87b4-4d25-809f-7797ab04aa94', 'Peel zest in long strips from half of orange with a vegetable peeler and trim any white pith from zest. Cut zest into fine julienne strips. Halve orange and squeeze 1/3 cup juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.411', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.978');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f2feb18-b2e5-47a1-b022-d686212dcb98', 'Combine zest, juice, wine, sugar, and 2 cups water in a 3-quart heavy saucepan. Scrape seeds from vanilla bean with a sharp knife into wine mixture, reserving pod for another use. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then continue to boil, uncovered, until reducedto about 3 cups, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.414', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.978');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('134c7a23-33a8-49cb-9831-a3183a7b9342', 'While syrup is boiling, cut off and discard fig stems and halve figs lengthwise. Add figs to syrup and simmer, covered, until they soften, about 5 minutes. Add apricots and prunes, then simmer, covered, until plump, 8 to 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.418', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.979');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f577a4fc-60db-4252-bc57-de92f2c1fff9', 'Transfer compote to a heatproof bowl and cool to warm or room temperature, 1 to 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.421', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.979');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad0f38e9-ac9e-42ef-9f46-76a3692f14bb', 'Heat a comal or dry 12-inch heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron; not nonstick) over medium-low heat until hot.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.425', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.98');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c3d3abd-d2c0-4f77-8359-ffa77299dc29', 'Cook garlic and jalapeños, turning with tongs occasionally, until blackened in spots, about 15 minutes. Cool slightly, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.428', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.981');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('562ea6a6-d9c4-45e3-8a56-690bce13adf1', 'Combine all ingredients except parsley in a food processor and finely chop. Add parsley and pulse a few more times.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.432', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.982');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c26bec8-fd21-4221-852e-1499c09b3664', 'Bring water, sugar, and lemon thyme to a boil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Boil syrup until reduced to about 3/4 cup, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove pan from heat and steep syrup, covered, 30 minutes. Pour through a sieve into a bowl, pressing on and discarding thyme.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.435', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.982');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('604b0bd0-7a16-4c37-8c7a-a29d41b1f6ac', 'While syrup steeps, remove rind from honeydew wedges, then halve each wedge crosswise on a slight diagonal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.438', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.983');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a11b330d-9875-4f8b-be15-734c57ec9e49', 'Put melon in a shallow bowl and drizzle with syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.442', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.983');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be43ba5c-acec-41df-999d-531c0f2c7140', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Place 4 beets on a large piece of foil and rub with 1 tablespoon oil; season with salt and pepper and close up foil around beets. Place on a rimmed baking sheet and roast until tender, 30–40 minutes. Unwrap beets and let cool slightly. Peel and cut into 1/2" wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.446', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.984');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25200e62-c0c8-4cf5-bee8-203c13d347ed', 'Meanwhile, whisk miso, vinegar, remaining 2 tablespoons oil, and 3 tablespoons water in a small bowl. Set dressing aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.449', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.985');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('512a1a73-9d39-4a83-9c56-48dc4b11a36c', 'Thinly slice remaining 2 raw beets on a mandoline. Arrange watercress and roasted and raw beets on a platter and drizzle with reserved dressing; top with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.452', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.986');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cfb75db6-9af2-47c3-8bab-33f9c82de6a6', 'Bring rice, water, and 1/4 teaspoon salt to a boil in a small heavy saucepan, then reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until rice is tender and water is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 10 minutes. Spread rice evenly in a lightly oiled 4-sided sheet pan and cool completely. Coarsely smash coriander seeds with side of a large knife.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.459', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.988');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c69b4ca-0d7d-4d1d-bd73-6c399a497fd5', 'Toss rice with coriander, remaining ingredients, and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large bowl and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.463', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.99');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('60ff9ed7-ece9-4ace-bbbb-79c2821fcb77', '1. Bring the water, sugar, and salt to a boil in a small saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Reduce the heat and simmer for 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.466', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.991');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4cb5b981-b664-4b01-ba1c-ac8277929db4', '2. Transfer the sugar syrup to a small bowl and refrigerate, tightly covered, for at least 1 hour, until thoroughly chilled, or for up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.469', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.991');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f8ee1b6-f320-4c15-aa54-8a85011f4b00', '3. Whisk together the coconut milk and lychee juice in a large glass measure or bowl. Whisk in the chilled syrup and lime juice. Pour the mixture into an ice-cream maker and freeze according to the manufacturer''s instructions. Transfer to a freezer container and freeze for at least 2 hours before serving. (The sorbet is best served on the day it is made.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.473', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.992');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2128a91f-0dbb-4ca9-86c5-c3b24fa8ebc3', '4. Spoon the sorbet into serving bowls or glasses to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.476', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.992');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a1eebae-ec72-4fdc-a0e5-da194fb58aac', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. and brush a baking sheet well with oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.479', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.993');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a027699b-9b1c-4f70-b62d-792ce02a6de5', 'Peel potato and trim to form a rectangle about 3 by 1 1/2 by 1 inch. Halve rectangle through 1 -inch side to form 2 rectangles about 3 by 1 1/2 by 1/2 inches. With a mandoline or other hand-held slicing device slice potato 1/16 inch thick on the long narrow side of each rectangle to form strips about 3 by 1/2 inches. On oiled sheet arrange strips, 4 at a time, overlapping ends to form squares. Brush each square with oil and sprinkle with salt to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.483', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.993');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4caa73dd-bcdc-42d8-98fb-c4bf6541a0d1', 'Bake crisps in middle of oven 10 minutes, or until golden brown. Transfer crisps to a rack to cool. Potato crisps keep in an airtight container 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.486', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.994');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('427d5fc8-3a51-4f54-8572-198fb41771f5', 'Preheat oven to 375°F. Spray heavy baking sheet with vegetable oil spray. Heat 1 teaspoon sesame oil in heavy large nonstick wok or skillet over high heat. Add green onions, garlic and ginger; stir-fry 1 minute. Add spinach, mushrooms, zucchini and carrot; stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender and spinach wilts, about 3 minutes. Add 4 teaspoons soy sauce and stir to coat vegetables, about 30 seconds. Transfer mixture to colander and drain off liquid. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.489', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.995');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('636e88be-ed0e-426f-9c4a-40ff85455ea4', 'Place egg roll wrappers on work surface. Spoon filling in 4x2-inch rectangle in center of each wrapper, dividing equally. Fold in short sides, then roll up tightly. Arrange seam side down on prepared sheet. (Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover with plastic wrap, refrigerate. Remove plastic before continuing.) Bake until wrappers are crisp and filling is heated through, turning once about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.493', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.995');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2f792ebd-aae0-4036-9448-fcda56368408', 'Meanwhile, mix vinegar and remaining 1 Teaspoon sesame oil and 3 tablespoons soy sauce in small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.496', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.996');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df3465bc-b827-4df6-a6c7-515aad23d24c', 'Transfer rolls to plates. Serve warm with dipping sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.5', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.996');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e2841f9-b926-4b30-b343-035dcc24b64d', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. Combine onion rings, oil, and salt in medium bowl; toss to coat. Spread onion rings in single layer on rimmed baking sheet. Roast until golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. DO AHEAD Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Before using, rewarm in 350°F oven until heated through, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.503', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.997');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e99302d6-6fb9-4a31-9279-51f47e6afab4', 'Bring 3 cups water to boil. Add peas; simmer until tender, about 5 minutes. Drain. Return peas to saucepan. Mix in roasted onion rings, mint, pepper, and sugar. Transfer to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.507', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.998');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57b5c7cd-cc6f-4bc3-bc5e-f60d5a0e8d8d', '1. Make sure your kitchen is well ventilated. Put a piece of aluminum foil in a heavy sauté pan (preferably cast iron) and set it over medium-high heat. Place the whole tomatoes, chile, and garlic cloves in the pan and dry-roast them on all sides until well charred and soft. The garlic and chiles will be done quickly; the tomatoes may take 10 minutes or longer to cook.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.998');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cee1370e-7dba-4c87-8275-95af90c405c9', '2. Peel the garlic and stem the chile. Place the tomatoes, garlic, and chile in a food processor with the onion, salt, and cilantro. Pulse until the salsa is smooth and taste for seasoning. The salsa will keep, refrigerated, for several days. Reseason before use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.514', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.998');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e735540b-f67e-4c11-be12-8152f071dfdc', 'Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper and toss well. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.517', '2023-06-13 00:13:19.999');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18f5beb3-293a-4048-8f63-a56cdd2ab8c5', 'Whisk the mustard and the red wine together in a small bowl. Slowly whisk in the 3 tablespoons of oil until the mixture is thickened, then whisk in the olive oil. Taste for seasoning. To thin the vinaigrette, simply whisk in a teaspoon or two of water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.521', '2023-06-13 00:13:20');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74884bd9-d4de-4a24-a36b-aae85ae4020e', 'Combine 2 cups herbs, 1/4 cup scallions, ginger, and garlic in a mini-processor. Pulse to chop ingredients. Add 4 tablespoons oil, vinegar, and 1/4 cup water and process until a coarse purée forms. Transfer herb sauce to a bowl and stir in sesame seeds. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Herb sauce can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.524', '2023-06-13 00:13:20');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11a644d2-df87-40e8-bc20-eefe39686d8c', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large heavy skillet over medium-high heat until oil just begins to smoke. Add remaining 1/4 cup scallions and wheat berries. Stir-fry until wheat berries are golden brown and slightly crunchy, about 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Divide wheat berries among bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.527', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.001');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82a01987-f784-4963-b9d2-7d104ef3df53', 'Return skillet to medium-high heat and add remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Add vegetables, season with salt and pepper, and stir-fry until brightly colored and crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Add remaining 1 cup herbs and toss to combine. Divide vegetables over wheat berries. Drizzle with herb sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.531', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.002');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b480d0e5-ed56-41ad-9a92-b38b6a4e6483', 'Heat the oil in a heavy pot (wide enough to hold the artichokes with room to spare) over medium-high heat until it just begins to smoke. Stand the artichokes cut sides down in the oil, wait a minute, then reduce the heat to medium-low, sprinkle in the garlic and salt, and cook, without stirring, just until the garlic turns golden and smells toasty, about 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.534', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.003');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2681b25d-8d20-4bac-ac8e-81f06467f81e', 'Cut cucumbers into 1/8-inch-thick slices and in a bowl layer slices, sprinkling each layer with salt. Chill cucumbers, covered, 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.687', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.154');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6554b0a7-9b8f-4e5a-8b25-a385401148e4', 'Slowly pour in the wine, cover the pot, and cook, without stirring, at a vigorous simmer until you can insert a sharp knife into the thick artichoke bottoms with barely any resistance, about 25 minutes. Five minutes or so before they''re fully tender, remove the lid and scatter on the capers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.537', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.003');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9ce98e7-e8d1-4a43-bd6a-8e8734c3cf41', 'Raise the heat to medium-high, and bring the liquid to a boil. Cook until all the wine has evaporated (the bubbling sound will become a sizzle), about 3 minutes. Add the mint and parsley and keep cooking the artichokes in the oil (it''s OK if a few of them tip over), until the cut sides of the artichokes are deep golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Lower the heat if necessary to prevent the artichokes from getting too dark.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.541', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.004');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4414bf5-3359-46fe-9dee-29196bb5b4cb', 'Arrange the artichokes prettily on a plate, and scoop the capers, oil, and slightly crispy herbs over top. Serve straightaway or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.544', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.004');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b862075-4202-4835-9130-95cb8811a1bd', 'Stir mustard seeds in small dry skillet over medium heat until seeds darken slightly and begin to pop, about 5 minutes. Transfer seeds to heavy large saucepan. Add plums, brown sugar, vinegar, onion, cinnamon sticks, and coarse salt. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to medium-high and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until liquid is thick and syrupy and mixture is reduced to 7 cups, stirring frequently, about 55 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.547', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.005');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57ae479c-fc24-4ec4-925d-8a1b73fc69f9', 'Ladle mixture into 7 hot clean 1/2-pint glass canning jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at top of jars. Remove air bubbles. Wipe jar threads and rims with clean damp cloth. Cover with hot lids; apply screw bands. Process jars in pot of boiling water 15 minutes. Cool jars completely. Store in cool dark place up to 1 year.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.551', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.005');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68866767-02f9-4ee0-bcc0-6d24112e18bd', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add zucchini; sauté until slices are light golden and tender, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and red pepper; stir 1 minute. Season to taste with sea salt. Transfer zucchini to serving platter, sprinkle with parsley, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.006');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f82c7075-357a-45f7-ae2d-99270b0670a4', 'Preheat oven to 325 degrees.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.558', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.006');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33750ee6-8659-4384-91a1-db9799768e9e', 'In a food processor, pulse the first 6 ingredients until finely chopped (it''s ok if there are few coarsely chopped pieces).', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.561', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.007');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc4203d4-a3c4-40bf-a86f-92650ee1681e', 'Add the honey and sunflower and pulse until starting to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.565', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.007');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('478ea1c3-2558-47da-ad46-3429d2c9f225', 'Pour the mixture into a 9 x 9 inch pan, greased then line with parchment and press down into the pan until completely even.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.569', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.008');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38970ef0-f205-4c00-83b6-8f10a8a9d75a', 'Bake for 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.572', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.008');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('497d5032-bea9-4e56-8cda-457d8476d770', 'Let the bars completely cool before cutting with a serrated knife into bars.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.576', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.009');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('670806cb-2eb9-42ee-90a3-87522bf0fc52', 'Line a plate with paper towels. Pour a shallow layer of canola oil in a large sauté pan or skillet and heat over high heat until it ripples.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.579', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.009');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3aec931a-3167-4d7b-87bf-5de52bad1672', 'Fry the papadum sheets one at a time until crispy, about 30 seconds. There’s no need to flip them, as they are so thin. Transfer to the paper towel–lined plate to absorb excess oil, then cool to room temperature. Store in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.583', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.01');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('92963095-490d-4af8-95dc-a084c8b5648c', 'Heat the sunflower oil in a medium saucepan over high heat until it ripples. Add the onion, garlic, curry, cardamom, ginger, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion is translucent, about 4 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.586', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.01');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('beb0eb3c-e095-47b1-9e00-c0c6aac8835e', 'Reduce the heat to medium, add 3 cups water and the lentils, and cook, stirring occasionally, until the lentils are tender, about 15 minutes. Set aside to cool fully.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.59', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.011');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61fcfc20-21c0-43d7-a965-a10db7d33d0e', 'Transfer the lentil mixture to a blender with the remaining ingredients and blend until smooth. Serve with papadum pieces or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.593', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.011');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9850edf-d33b-48d5-bbb5-2ed559e099e2', 'In food processor, pulse onion until minced, about 10 seconds. Add tomatoes and pulse just until chunky, about 5 seconds. Add cilantro, lime juice, salt, and pepper and pulse until mixture is mixed, about 5 seconds. Transfer to covered container and refrigerate 2 hours to blend flavors. (Salsa can be made ahead and refrigerated, covered, up to 2 days.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.597', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.012');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d03ddc5-404c-480d-bf5c-2d1f5e4f6ae5', 'Cut a small X in bottom of each tomato with a sharp paring knife. Blanch tomatoes in a 3-quart saucepan of boiling water for 10 seconds, then immediately transfer with a slotted spoon to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. Drain, peel, and coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.6', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.013');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ad7493a-d800-4d0c-96a5-1200b0a4b08c', 'Cook onions and garlic in oil in a wide 5- to 6-quart heavy pot over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are softened, about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.604', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.014');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('619e8df0-7e2e-4167-90ce-40bc11cc911b', 'Add beans, water, sugar, salt, and pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to moderately low, then cover and simmer until beans are very tender, about 45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.607', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.014');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d94f020e-105a-4402-9b87-cf6ecaab08e2', 'Remove from heat and season with salt and pepper. Cool to room temperature, uncovered, about 45 minutes. Serve beans with juices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.611', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.015');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51768e7f-c8df-46d8-aca0-ec5366ed6bf2', 'Simmer mushroom in water in a small saucepan, covered, 15 minutes. Add kombu and barely simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a large glass measure, pressing on and discarding solids. Return 2 cups liquid (add water if necessary) to saucepan. Add soy sauce, mirin, ponzu, sugar, and 1/4 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Remove from heat. Stir in sesame oil, then cool in pan in a large ice bath.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.015');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b09cdf2-6ddb-4762-b4e6-7dbbbc186164', 'Blanch sugar snaps in a large pot of unsalted boiling water until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to a large colander set in ice bath to stop cooking. Lift colander to drain. Transfer sugar snaps to a bowl. Meanwhile, return water to a boil. Blanch spinach until just wilted, about 30 seconds, then cool and drain in same manner. Squeeze out excess water. Add to sugar snaps.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.618', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.016');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c8e04e1e-7f26-46c3-b095-73e03a30ac9d', 'Return water to a boil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.621', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.018');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f0688f0-c52c-45d0-bd92-f4d673170d73', 'Add noodles and cook according to package directions, stirring occasionally, until tender. Drain in colander and rinse with cold water. Cool in ice bath until very cold (add more ice to water as necessary). Drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.625', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.019');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3fbb089a-1a1c-4acb-b905-5ce88ca06dd9', 'Carefully drain tofu and pat dry. Cut into 3/4-inch cubes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.628', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.019');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('acfdae52-aba2-4519-8665-669b42449e81', 'Whisk sauce, then pour 1 1/2 cups sauce into a large bowl. Add noodles, sugar snaps, spinach, and half of scallions and toss. Serve in shallow bowls, topped with tofu, remaining scallions, and ginger. Drizzle with some of remaining sauce and serve remainder on the side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.632', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.019');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d01176aa-55ec-4120-bc1a-16b519b81afb', 'Cut bananas into 1/2" slices. Arrange in a single layer on a large plate or rimmed baking sheet. Freeze until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.635', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.02');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6dc81ef3-bc5b-4d1a-b1db-d4004abe3744', 'Purée banana slices in a food processor, scraping down bowl as needed, until mixture becomes creamy, about 3 minutes. Add peanut butter and 3 Tbsp. water; purée until smooth, about 2 minutes more. Drizzle jelly over banana mixture, then pulse a few more times to just incorporate jelly and create a speckled appearance.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.639', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.022');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79dcad97-3421-4394-b97c-eb06996bdf08', 'Divide ice cream among serving bowls and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.642', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.022');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('086ce272-683f-4289-bd8e-3ac83eca6a71', 'Banana slices can be frozen up to a day in advance.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.646', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.023');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82442754-847e-4a45-b562-7a28d4860429', 'Preheat oven to 450°F. and butter a 2-quart shallow baking dish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.649', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.023');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a78c3838-33d2-41ea-a189-58884734034d', 'Prick each potato with a fork 3 times and bake on a sheet in middle of oven about 1 hour, or until very tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.653', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.026');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c60c55c-93b9-4051-9675-c721d6931764', 'While potatoes are baking, in a bowl wash quinoa in at least 5 changes cold water, rubbing grains and letting them settle before pouring off most of water, until water runs clear and drain in a fine sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.657', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.028');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('628a4146-c173-489a-b35a-925507f13a60', 'In a saucepan combine quinoa with 2 cups salted water and bring to a boil. Simmer quinoa, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes, and remove lid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.661', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.028');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bef9417-aafc-4870-8345-c3a4a51e4b6e', 'In a skillet heat 1 tablespoon oil over moderate heat and cook bread crumbs until golden brown. Season crumbs with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.664', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.03');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e6aec740-f7bb-4ee6-9e93-b7436dac235b', 'While quinoa is cooking, finely chop reserved Swiss chard stems and coarsely chop leaves, keeping both separate. In a deep heavy 12-inch kettle heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil over moderate heat and cook stems until tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in leaves, a handful at a time, and stir in garlic, tossing. Cook leaves until just wilted, about 4 minutes. Remove kettle from heat and stir in quinoa until combined well. Season mixture with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.668', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.031');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47d63b22-3f9b-48c7-b55c-d1f31257d027', 'Reduce temperature to 350°.F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.031');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0d14720-fb33-40b7-855c-a9a03114686d', 'When potatoes are cool enough to handle, peel and mash with a fork. Season potatoes with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.675', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.032');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e208bea-66dd-405e-b510-af42ad04f5e3', 'With a large spoon drop mounds of potatoes and Swiss chard mixture in baking dish, alternating them decoratively to cover bottom, and smooth top. Top gratin with bread crumbs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.679', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.034');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a7bd4311-579e-4971-bb08-2cc745ff1481', 'Bake gratin in middle of oven about 30 minutes, or until hot. Cool gratin 5 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.682', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.035');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d73ad61-90f2-4a23-8fed-9ffcf836a9e5', 'Cut 1 medium zucchini into matchstick-size pieces. Heat 2 tablespoons toasted sesame oil in a large skillet, preferably nonstick, over medium heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, 3-4 minutes. Season with kosher salt, freshly ground black pepper, and gochugaru (coarse Korean red pepper powder).', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.685', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.035');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4bb6b2b-fa98-4163-bb00-4c464b97fbe4', 'Cook fava beans in large saucepan of boiling salted water until just tender, about 5 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer fava beans to medium bowl. Add diced carrots to same saucepan of boiling water; cook until carrots are tender, about 4 minutes. Drain and transfer carrots to small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.689', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.036');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f1871a59-b4cd-4357-b462-98c6ade07d24', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion, diced zucchini, diced bell pepper, pressed garlic cloves, and minced fresh thyme. Sauté until beginning to soften, about 3 minutes. Add corn, diced cucumber, and reserved carrots; stir 1 minute. Add beans, unsweetened coconut milk, cayenne pepper, and freshly grated nutmeg. Stir until heated through, about 1 minute. Season succotash to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.692', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.036');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9d7c7b01-89f8-4c36-a3be-316221603761', '1. In a small bowl stir together broth, rice wine, sugar, cornstarch, and salt until smooth. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.696', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.037');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5adb7b81-da70-4ffe-b457-cea054dd066d', '2. Heat a wok over high heat until hot. Add vegetable and sesame oil and heat until it just begins to smoke. Stir-fry carrots 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, cabbage, garlic, and ginger and stir-fry 2 minutes, or until carrots are crisp-tender. Add broth mixture to vegetables. Stir-fry vegetables an additional minute to coat. Add scallions and stir to combine. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.7', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.037');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9841544-6a90-4d29-8719-68972aa13826', 'Boil water, sugar, juniper berries, rosemary, and a pinch of salt in a small saucepan, stirring until sugar has dissolved, until reduced to about 3/4 cup, 10 to 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.703', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.038');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('069c827d-b963-4fca-ad1a-25f7409fbdb4', 'Put blueberries in a heatproof bowl and strain syrup through a sieve over berries. Stir in gin. Macerate until completely cooled, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.707', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.039');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2adb5ac4-9296-4fef-867b-cd5495b581b0', '1. Heat the oil in a wide skillet or stir-fry pan. Add the garlic and sauté over medium-low heat until golden.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.711', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.039');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9569bc24-2a1d-47a3-b483-b4b52a219082', '2. Add the potatoes and about 1 cup of water. Cover and bring to a simmer, then cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.715', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.04');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b641c3ec-1103-4ceb-8b58-ea200907470c', '3. Add the cauliflower, sprinkle in the ginger, garam masala, cumin, turmeric, and mustard and continue to simmer gently for 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.719', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.04');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ef4cced-8a9a-4b72-b32b-40d05dd18e9b', '4. Stir in the tofu, tomatoes, and peas, and cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Stir in the optional cilantro, season with salt, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.723', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('468e30b0-6601-410b-b145-e7d325eeb103', 'Peel and quarter potatoes. In a kettle cover potatoes with salted cold water by 2 inches and simmer until just tender, about 25 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes. Drain vegetables in a colander and transfer potatoes to a large bowl and tomatoes to a cutting board. With a potato masher mash potatoes and keep warm, covered. Cut tomatoes into thin julienne strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.726', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eb8eb897-591e-4854-8409-8192d6c2ab59', 'Using largest holes of a 4-sided grater, grate zucchini. Pit olives and cut into thin julienne strips. Mince garlic. In a large nonstick skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and sauté garlic, stirring, until golden. Add tomatoes, zucchini, olives, and salt and pepper to taste and sauté, stirring, until zucchini is just tender, about 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.041');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5abd8c32-0057-453c-a153-6ec0449a1392', 'Stir zucchini mixture into potatoes until combined well and season with salt and pepper. Potatoes may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Reheat potatoes, covered, in a 350°F. oven about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.735', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.042');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ebbf1f8d-42da-4253-bfd0-a8a70a0bfbd3', 'Prepare a grill to medium-high heat. thread garlic cloves onto a metal skewer. Put garlic skewer, tomatoes, onions, peppers, chile, and eggplant on grill rack. Grill, turning occasionally, until tender and lightly charred all over, 6-7 minutes for garlic and tomatoes; 10 minutes for eggplant; 15 minutes for peppers and chile; 20 minutes for onions. Place peppers and chile in a large bowl; cover with plastic wrap and let stand 15 minutes. Peel, seed, and coarsely chop peppers and chile. coarsely chop tomatoes and eggplant. Peel and coarsely chop onions. Pulse all vegetables in a food processor, along with oil, until puréed to desired consistency. transfer to a large bowl. season to taste with lemon juice, salt, and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.739', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.042');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f45f8c1-554c-4d5a-8f4e-8f3e2115c9e8', 'Bring a large saucepan half full of salted water to a boil over high heat. Add the snap peas and peas and cook until tender-crisp, about 1 minute. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the vegetables to a colander and rinse under cold water. Set aside. Return the saucepan to a boil, add the barley and cook until tender, about 45 minutes. Drain and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.742', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.043');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7dd9e62b-1d9d-4542-a4ae-63da1b53c43a', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the rice vinegar, soy sauce, 2 tbsp water, brown sugar, and sambal oelek until blended. In a large, heavy frying pan over high heat, warm the sesame oil. Add the green garlic, green onions, and lime leaves and stir-fry until the green onions are tender, about 30 seconds. Add the reserved snap peas, peas, and barley along with the pea shoots, and stir to coat. Pour in the soy sauce mixture and stir and toss until the peas and pea shoots are tender and the liquid is absorbed, about 4 minutes. Transfer to a warmed serving dish and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.746', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.043');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('34780259-3afc-4d61-8af3-09411c2c2333', 'Finely chop garlic in processor. Add cilantro, oil, lemon juice, ginger and cumin. Process until well blended.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.75', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.044');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('48b6c057-a4c3-4b69-99c4-0594dffe5ec7', 'Cook carrots in medium pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain. Transfer to large bowl. Add dressing and toss to coat. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. Cool to room temperature; serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.754', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.044');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d52aed0b-f143-4b15-a694-dd2acdfec115', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Place carrots on a rimmed baking sheet and onions and fennel on another rimmed baking sheet. (Make sure to give them plenty of room, which is key to roasted veggies with nicely browned edges.) Drizzle vegetables with 2 Tbsp. oil, dividing evenly; season with salt and pepper. Roast, tossing occasionally, until golden brown and tender, 20–25 minutes for carrots and 35–45 minutes for onions and fennel. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.758', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.045');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fab698e-205b-446c-aeff-e3f9a0c6be38', 'Meanwhile, cook sunflower seeds, coriander seeds, Aleppo pepper, paprika, and remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in a small skillet over medium heat, stirring often, until oil is gently bubbling around seeds and spices are fragrant (be careful not to burn), about 2 minutes. Let cool. Stir in vinegar and lemon juice; season vinaigrette with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.763', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.046');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f03bcb59-34eb-4bfc-b960-798cd24f164a', 'Combine roasted carrots, fennel, and onions onto the same baking sheet, drizzle vinaigrette over, and toss to coat well; transfer to a platter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.767', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.046');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c40eb0c-8080-49a4-8aa3-803bd3614396', 'Just before serving, re-toss vegetables to pull up any dressing that may have settled at the bottom of the platter and scatter mint over top.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.771', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.047');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8faa44ae-7095-40d8-a2af-dbfc9a4e46cd', 'Dish (without mint) can be made 3 hours ahead. Store tightly wrapped at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.775', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.048');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e5860c90-b8a3-4198-bf5e-38d1a4a3371b', '2. Trim the beets, leaving on the skin, an inch of the stem, and the wispy "tail" on the bottom of each, then scrub and drain. Place the beets in a small casserole dish just big enough to hold them. Pour the water and canola oil over the beets then cover tightly with a lid or aluminum foil and bake until tender and easily pierced with a sharp paring knife, about 1 1/2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.779', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.049');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc5b0e4f-f170-4bcb-96c3-f8a1663cfa31', '3. Remove the casserole from the oven and uncover the beets, keeping your face averted from the escaping steam. Allow the beets to cool completely in the casserole.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.783', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.049');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eef376ce-f4d4-43f3-95f8-8b70ffea8175', '4. Meanwhile, combine the vinegar, 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, the salt, and pepper in a medium-size bowl and whisk to blend. Taste and add more olive oil, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.787', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.05');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9f957538-af74-4413-9979-519ae49888e2', '5. Peel the cooled beets with the back of a paring knife and cut into 3/8-inch slices. Add to the dressing in the bowl and toss gently but thoroughly to coat. Serve immediately or marinate, in the refrigerator, for up to 24 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.79', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.05');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35d5e5a8-6b92-4f5e-9286-844e12bf1dff', 'Heat peanut oil in a wok or 12-inch heavy skillet over high heat until just beginning to smoke then stir-fry garlic and ginger with salt until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add cabbage and cook, tossing, until just beginning to wilt, about 2 minutes, then stir in chestnuts and sugar. Reduce heat to moderate and cook covered, 3 minutes, then stir in soy sauce and sesame oil. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.794', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.053');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8844dd8-33f1-4410-9069-b04c06fe96f4', 'Combine berries, sugar and juice in heavy large skillet. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Simmer over medium heat until berries burst, stirring often, about 5 minutes. Puree in processor until smooth. Strain into same skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.798', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e99720b-dd00-416d-a400-f09f71c089a2', 'Bring puree to simmer over medium heat. Add pear wedges and stir to coat. Simmer until pears are just tender, about 8 minutes. Using slotted spoon, remove pears from skillet, shaking excess puree back into skillet, and transfer pears to paper-towel-lined plate. Reserve puree. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover pears and puree separately and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.803', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce7694e4-7fd2-4c47-9f58-8961365026da', 'In a bowl let the cranberries soak in the orange juice for 30 minutes, drain them in a sieve set over a bowl, and reserve the juice. Reserve 1 large piece of the preserved ginger and in a blender or food processor purée the remaining ginger with the syrup and the reserved orange juice. In a deep 2-quart glass serving dish arrange half the cranberries, drizzle them with about 1/2 cup of the ginger mixture, and top them with the grapes. Drizzle the grapes with about 1/2 cup of the remaining ginger mixture, top them with the grapefruit, and drizzle the grapefruit with about 1/2 cup of the remaining ginger mixture. Top the grapefruit with the pineapple, drizzle it with the remaining ginger mixture, and arrange the remaining cranberries on top. Arrange the orange sections over the cranberries, chill the compote, covered, for at least 2 hours or overnight, and serve it garnished with the reserved ginger, cut into julienne strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.807', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.054');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82502c9e-5312-4854-9b9f-395f1324e652', 'Freeze ice pops 1 hour. Insert sticks and freeze until ice pops are solid, at least 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:35.86', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.733');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec343901-e98d-455f-ba03-5fe3c4b9b91d', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Toss squash, thyme, garlic, olive oil, and coconut oil in a large baking dish; season with kosher salt and pepper. Roast, tossing occasionally, until just tender, 40-45 minutes. Add dates; toss to coat. Roast until squash are very tender and dates are soft, 12-15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.811', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b309cf17-22ef-4cdd-821b-19af3e0a6c54', 'Arrange squash, dates, garlic, and thyme on a platter, spoon any oil in dish over squash, and sprinkle with sea salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.815', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6414610f-ffe6-4b25-9427-c841ef777e9e', 'Combine wine, sugar, orange peel, and lemon peel in heavy large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add rhubarb and salt and simmer until rhubarb is tender but still retains its shape, about 9 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer rhubarb to shallow dish, arranging in single layer. Boil wine syrup in saucepan until slightly thickened and reduced to 1 1/4 cups, adding any juices accumulated from rhubarb, about 5 minutes. Pour syrup over rhubarb and cool, then cover and chill until cold. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.818', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0d48d7a4-065b-467e-a88f-46b32ef3c996', 'Cook onion and fennel with raisins, fennel seeds, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in oil in a 4-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, 8 to 10 minutes. Add rice and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add water and bring to a vigorous boil. Tightly cover and cook over low heat, undisturbed, until water is absorbed, about 22 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.822', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.055');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd7c63b1-a3a2-47c8-a7c4-7cbfb4147789', 'Remove from heat. Remove lid and put a clean kitchen towel over pan, then replace lid. Let stand 10 minutes, then fluff with a fork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.825', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a089577-3d9a-43d0-bebf-426c4ce45c9d', 'In a large skillet sauté the garlic in the oil over moderately high heat, stirring, until it is golden and discard it. To the skillet add the escarole, the olives, the raisins, and salt and pepper to taste and sauté the mixture, stirring, for 1 minute. Cook the mixture, covered, over moderately low heat for 4 minutes, or until the escarole is tender, stir in the pine nuts, and boil the mixture for 1 minute, or until the liquid is evaporated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.829', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e32c3bc-bd5c-4924-87d6-0eaf2587d717', 'Boil vinegar with sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small heavy saucepan, stirring, until reduced by half, about 3 minutes. Transfer to a cup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.833', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d815ca8-8585-4622-8a0e-eea9745e37c2', 'Wash leeks and pat dry. Cook in oil with 1/4 teaspoon salt in cleaned saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.836', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.056');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('49275f49-3387-4ba1-a478-158e91fb3f17', 'Arrange frisée and pear on plates. Drizzle with hot leeks in oil, then vinegar reduction. Grind pepper over salads.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.84', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e83af38-0904-4c04-b3df-f2e7378ec45e', 'Bring salt, 1/2 cup sugar, and 2 cups water to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring to dissolve salt and sugar. Let syrup cool. Stir in rose water, if using, and pour mixture into a 13x9x2" baking pan, preferably metal.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.844', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed8f4675-d1b3-4177-96c9-3a2878b06271', 'Freeze mixture until edges begin to set, 25–30 minutes. Using a fork, scrape to break up any frozen parts, then continue to freeze, scraping and breaking up mixture every 20–30 minutes, until it resembles fluffy shaved ice, 2–3 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.847', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a76442c2-fa46-4f8f-a120-4bfeccd59ae8', 'Toss blackberries, lime juice, and remaining 2 tsp. sugar in a medium bowl. Let sit at room temperature, tossing occasionally, until berries soften slightly, 10–15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.852', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d8b87d4-cbb8-4731-abcb-3a30b14c7d31', 'Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°F. Toast almonds on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing once, until golden brown, 5–8 minutes; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.855', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.057');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dc818a75-d077-40ff-8877-8faa9b0815e0', 'Scoop granita into bowls, dividing evenly, and top with blackberries and some of their juices, toasted almonds, and mint leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.859', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cabee9d5-3f88-4eae-9b57-9a0d515cc472', 'Granita can be made 3 days ahead. Cover and keep frozen. Scrape to break up and fluff before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.863', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3218615a-a556-4b6f-a4ce-0cbc4a1531b1', 'Fill large bowl with ice and cold water. Cook beans in large pot of generously salted boiling water just until crisp-tender, 5 to 6 minutes. Drain. Place beans in bowl of ice water until cool. Drain well, then pat dry with kitchen towels. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Wrap beans in several layers of paper towels; enclose in large resealable plastic bag and chill. Bring to room temperature before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.867', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4562e6cf-6d11-4862-9bbf-b7fd956ac239', 'Combine 2 cups water, cider vinegar, and next 6 ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add onions; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until onions are wilted, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool uncovered to room temperature. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill onion mixture. Before using, drain liquid; discard thyme, cloves, and bay leaf and bring to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.871', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.058');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79c9a4c9-f225-4920-a264-a761da8bdc6a', 'Whisk oil, syrup, and chopped thyme in large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Add green beans and drained onions; toss to coat. Transfer salad to platter and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.875', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13dee948-de23-4260-ab97-410723320a7c', 'Whisk together all vinaigrette ingredients in a small bowl until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.879', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb0248b0-1442-461c-8b05-d36bc40db118', 'Bring water, vinegar, sugar, and salt to a boil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan, then add onion and simmer until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Drain and cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.883', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8979afdd-e281-4d3f-adf4-d7436b0a6f66', 'Spread romaine on a large platter and scatter with parsley, peppers, artichokes, olives, peperoncini, tomatoes, and onion. Whisk vinaigrette again and drizzle over salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.887', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.059');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6ce53614-624d-4f6a-b051-368c397e1b6a', 'Toast coriander, cumin, and caraway seeds in small skillet over medium heat until beginning to brown, about 2 minutes. Cool. Transfer to spice mill; process until finely ground. Transfer to small bowl. Add red pepper, turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.89', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ba3b0a5-9d62-4607-bbd8-a435c9977d45', 'Mix lemon slices, lemon juice, and 4 teaspoons coarse salt in small skillet. Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until lemon slices are almost tender, about 10 minutes. Cool preserved lemon. Drain and chop. DO AHEAD: Spice blend and preserved lemon can be made 1 week ahead. Store spice blend airtight at room temperature. Transfer preserved lemon to small bowl; cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.894', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e4a9bba-b026-4b5e-babf-afb88f00586c', 'Heat olive oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion; sprinkle with salt and sauté until beginning to soften, about 5 minutes. Add toasted spice blend, garlic, and tomato paste; stir 1 minute. Add carrots and celery; stir 2 minutes. Add chopped preserved lemon, 4 cups water, sweet potatoes, turnips, olives, and sun-dried tomatoes. Simmer with lid ajar until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes. Stir in parsley, cilantro, and mint. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes to allow flavors to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.897', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c72a4141-4587-4bc0-9d1b-88970008f86f', 'Spoon couscous into large bowl, spreading out to edges and leaving well in center. Spoon vegetable tagine into well in center. Sprinkle Spice-Roasted Chickpeas over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.901', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88f04657-3017-422e-9fc8-b1a9b1648fab', 'Rinse lentils; drain. Place in small bowl. Rinse rice; drain. Place in another small bowl. Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add cinnamon, cloves, and cumin; sauté about 2 minutes. Add garlic and ginger; sauté about 30 seconds. Add water, salt, sugar, and turmeric; bring to boil. Reduce heat; add lentils and cook 8 minutes. Increase heat to high. Add rice and boil 5 minutes. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until lentils and rice are tender and liquid is absorbed, about 8 minutes longer. Remove from heat; let stand covered 5 minutes. Transfer rice to large bowl. Remove cinnamon stick pieces and cloves. Mix in cilantro and lime juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.905', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.06');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2355b78d-e816-4018-aecc-3648b54b5aed', 'Basmati rice is available at Indian markets and some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.908', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.061');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2f5daa6c-4c96-41bf-a567-f38858a3b1bf', 'So long as you find the right snap peas, you''ll have a smashing salad. But I find that putting your knife to them adds even more excitement, a little textural variation and attractiveness. Accordingly, run the tip of your knife along the spine of some of the larger pods, open them like a book to expose the peas, and gently pull to separate the two sides of the pod. Slice others diagonally in half or thirds. Keep small ones whole.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.911', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.061');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f88d6356-d988-47c2-b627-3c195ceb6b46', 'Combine the peas and mint in a large bowl. Pour in the dressing and toss gently but well. Season to taste with more salt and lemon, if you''d like. Add the arugula to the bowl and toss gently to coat the leaves in the dressing without bruising them. Arrange it all prettily on a platter and serve straightaway.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.915', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.061');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5498495e-1cfc-4f1e-8ad3-462b267f6799', 'Steam potatoes in steamer basket set over boiling water in a 12-inch-wide pot, covered, until tender, 5 to 6 minutes. Transfer carefully to a platter with a wide spatula to avoid breaking sticks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.919', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.062');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('26cbeffe-331a-4922-ad53-d39be2065576', 'While potatoes steam, cook garlic and ginger in oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderately low heat, stirring, until oil begins to sizzle, about 1 minute, then add mustard seeds, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring, until garlic is pale golden, 1 to 2 minutes. Spoon hot oil mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with cilantro.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.922', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.062');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('440c47eb-9d8b-4b59-b820-f78e7607e667', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Place pine nuts on small cookie sheet. Toast until golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Cool completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.926', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.063');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a7d79b6-e732-44dd-ab64-c8c7ca1c8d32', 'Combine oil, vinegar, lemon juice, shallot and orange peel in bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in pine nuts. Transfer to cruet and seal. (Can be prepared up to 4 days ahead; refrigerate.) Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.929', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.064');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d219b49c-8d2d-4efb-ba59-d0bf3b966055', 'Place berries in large bowl. Add orange juice, sugar, and orange peel; mix gently. Let stand at least 30 minutes and up to 1 hour, tossing occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.933', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.065');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15490d84-4cf6-48ce-b568-46a34b720899', '1. Fill a large, heavy pot with apple juice. Tie the cinnamon sticks, ginger, and cloves together in a cheesecloth bag with kitchen string and add to the juice. Bring to a boil; reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer 15 minutes, partially covered, to infuse flavors.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.938', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.065');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1830f264-a18e-4ed5-8bfb-002961592227', '2. Meanwhile, squeeze the lemon into a large bowl and fill with water. Core the apples and pears from the bottom and peel them. Drop immediately into the lemon water (to prevent browning) until poaching time.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.941', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.065');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d477964b-fe24-4991-aa33-24d0097fef9a', '3. Carefully add apples to the boiling poaching liquid, reduce heat, and simmer until tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove to a bowl. Add the pears to the liquid and poach until tender, about 8 minutes. Remove to a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.945', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.066');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4ad73a0-9df6-4eb8-8c46-35138c686263', '4. Cool the poaching liquid to room temperature and discard spice bag. Return fruit to the liquid and refrigerate overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.066');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8886f274-6217-49d9-a108-f172d33f42ad', '5. To serve, place the fruit, stem-ends up, on a cake stand or platter. Strain some of the liquid over the fruit.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.068');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24f45e5f-afed-43f1-8a62-5b25db30d7d0', 'Bring 1 cup distilled white vinegar, 2 tablespoons kosher salt, 2 teaspoons sugar, up to 2 tablespoons spices (e.g., peppercorns, coriander seeds, and/or mustard seeds), and 2 cups water to a boil in a saucepan. Pour over vegetables in jars.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.955', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.068');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e687e04c-d827-48c2-9f12-a522e4e43124', 'Divide 1 1/2 pounds green beans, trimmed, 1 lemon, thinly sliced, seeds removed, 4 chiles de árbol (if desired), and 4 smashed garlic cloves between jars.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.958', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.069');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('098eb02f-609c-4ad1-bb0c-7e0e49161874', 'Dividing evenly, pour hot brine (see formula, left)—using 1 teaspoons crushed red pepper flakes for the spice—into jars and cover. Let cool, then chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.962', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.069');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd507018-0e80-45cb-ae58-67a554400606', 'Green beans can be pickled 2 months ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.965', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.07');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7041c59f-9e2b-401a-8a5a-492f4e9714ec', 'Stack half of collard leaves and roll into a cigar shape. Cut crosswise into very thin strips (1/8 inch wide) with a sharp knife. Repeat with remaining leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.07');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('795a639d-0d60-4abf-baf7-bf8c580cd6a5', 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a heavy 12-inch skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook half of collards, tossing, until just tender and bright green, about 1 minute, and transfer to a serving dish. Cook remaining collards in remaining 2 teaspoons oil in same manner, then toss all of collards with salt and pepper. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.972', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.071');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76cc9efe-c884-4969-8d2e-b84c7be15233', 'In a small bowl, combine the tomatoes, chiles, onion, cilantro, lime juice, and olive oil. Toss to combine, season to taste with salt, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.975', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.071');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dac227ac-bc70-44cd-8bc5-470221d3de53', 'Blanch carrots in a 4-quart nonreactive saucepan of boiling salted water 1 minute, then drain in a colander and rinse under cold water to stop cooking. Transfer carrots to a heatproof bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.979', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.072');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d916a607-ba92-463e-9e2a-995a87f71182', 'Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in saucepan, then reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Pour pickling liquid over carrots and cool, uncovered. Chill carrots, covered, at least 1 day for flavors to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.982', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.072');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9d447cb9-75cc-450c-9f09-92e3ceac1238', 'Peel the onions, trim the roots, but leave the root ends intact (this will keep the onions in wedges, rather than slices). Cut the onions lengthwise into 3 or 4 thick (about 1/3-inch) wedges. Slice the garlic cloves lengthwise into three or four thick slices each.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.986', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.073');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('15bc0733-d55e-4b70-99e7-9c744af284af', 'Place warm potatoes in large bowl. Stir red wine vinegar and sugar in small bowl until sugar dissolves, then drizzle over potatoes. Toss to coat. Mix in onion slices. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.568', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.138');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('712e7c51-b657-4984-b207-f840ec41ecc0', 'Toss all the ingredients in a large bowl with 2 tablespoons salt and some freshly ground black pepper. Transfer the beans to a baking sheet. Roast in the oven for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes or so, until the beans are completely wilted, shrunken, and concentrated in flavor, with a little caramelization around the edges. (You may need to stir more often toward the end, to keep the beans from browning too quickly.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.989', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.073');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('448d05b8-2a95-448c-b088-871ea4f7b63e', 'Combine all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to medium. Simmer until fruits are tender and syrup is slightly reduced, about 25 minutes. Cool compote. Cover and refrigerate until cold, at least 3 hours. (Can be prepared up to 3 days ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.993', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.074');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ab73005-9c59-49a4-9d2f-7a4372cbcf2b', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. In a medium bowl, toss potatoes with 1 tablespoon oil to coat; season generously with salt and pepper. Spread potato halves in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Roast potatoes, turning occasionally, until tender and golden brown,25-30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:29.996', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.074');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('720ccff0-6498-49fd-9a0c-0aa4548f00d4', 'Meanwhile, combine 1/2 cup chives, parsley, almonds, and garlic in a processor. Pulse until finely chopped. With machine running, gradually add remaining oil through feed tube and process until incorporated. Transfer chive pesto to a small bowl. Stir in lemon juice, then 2 tablespoons water. Season pesto with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.075');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('afa2a8fa-faa6-449b-a5c6-43c66ac565fc', 'Transfer potatoes to a platter. Drizzle with half of pesto; sprinkle with additional chopped chives. Serve with remaining pesto.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.003', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.075');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c732b699-48c0-4574-9526-49de0dfd57a3', 'Place beans, onion, carrots, and celery in a large pot and add cold water to cover by several inches. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer very gently until beans are cooked almost all the way through, about 1 1/2 hours. Season with salt and continue to cook, adding more water if needed to keep beans submerged, until tender (outside skin should still be intact), 45–60 minutes. Discard onion, carrots, and celery.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.007', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.076');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27dc9211-e617-4c64-b365-a2c99a3285df', 'Transfer beans and broth to a serving dish or a large bowl; season very generously with salt (start with 2 Tbsp.) and pepper and drizzle with oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.01', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.077');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4b039fcf-8148-4387-86fd-92232e03da69', 'Beans can be cooked and seasoned 2 days ahead. Let cool; cover and chill. Reheat gently before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.014', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.077');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('54ca85a6-053d-466e-9e86-c83f4dc85e15', 'Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add cranberries and fresh ginger; stir until cranberries begin to burst, about 3 minutes. Add wine and sugar; boil until mixture is reduced to 2 1/2 cups, about 15 minutes. Add crystallized ginger, curry powder and five-spice powder. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover; chill.) Serve sauce cold or, if desired, rewarm over low heat, stirring often.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.018', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.078');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('86253467-3fbd-4f52-8eb6-8ba604778dbf', 'Cut off and discard the stems of the artichokes with a serrated knife and rub the artichoke bottoms with some of the lemon juice. To a kettle of boiling salted water add the remaining lemon juice and the artichokes, boil the artichokes for 15 to 20 minutes, or until the bottoms are tender when pierced with a knife, and plunge them into a bowl of ice and cold water to stop the cooking. Drain the artichokes well, pull off the leaves, reserving 36 tender ones, and scrape out the chokes from the bottoms. Trim the artichoke bottoms and cut them into julienne strips.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.021', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.082');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e9544f0-589a-443c-a144-5909a083e2ff', 'In a small bowl whisk together the oil, the vinegar, the garlic paste, the pimiento, and pepper to taste, add the artichoke strips, and toss the mixture well. The artichoke mixture and leaves may be prepared 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled. Divide the artichoke mixture among 6 salad plates with a slotted spoon, arrange the reserved leaves around it, and spoon the dressing remaining in the bowl onto the leaves. Sprinkle the artichokes with the parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.025', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.082');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('86f4acd6-4716-4e19-ba03-754075c43efc', 'Bring a large pot of heavily salted water to a rapid boil over high heat. Working in 2 batches, blanch kale for 2 minutes. Drain, let cool, and squeeze out excess water with your hands. Coarsely chop; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.028', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.083');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6c947a1-e069-4c22-8425-f48f3fd4484e', 'Heat a large pot over medium heat for 2 minutes. Add 1/4 cup oil, rosemary sprig, and chile. Let sizzle, shaking pan often, for about 1 minute. Reduce heat to medium-low; add onion. Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a pinch of pepper. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring often; stir in garlic. Cook, stirring often, until onion is soft and starting to brown, 5-7 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.032', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.083');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb18c449-0a38-4bc7-988d-799995a5d14f', 'Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil and kale; stir to coat. Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt, reduce heat to medium-low, and cook, stirring often, until kale turns almost black and is slightly crisp at edges, about 30 minutes. Let cool. Discard rosemary and chile.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.036', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.084');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c80e56f9-8b05-454f-a7ca-05a36f8f4e19', 'Mix sugar, chopped mint, basil, and lime peel in medium bowl. Mash with wooden spoon until herbs turn dark green, about 3 minutes. Stir in lime juice and 1 1/4 cups water. Let stand 1 hour. Strain into large bowl, pressing on solids. Transfer 1/2 cup lime syrup to small pitcher; cover and refrigerate. Pour remaining lime syrup into 13x9x2-inch metal baking dish. Place dish in freezer. Stir syrup with fork every hour until frozen, about 4 hours. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and keep frozen.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.04', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.084');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce796aa3-d005-4b10-88f9-af12d34e3d52', 'Divide melon wedges among 8 shallow soup bowls. Drizzle melon with reserved lime syrup. Scrape granita into flakes with fork. Spoon generous 1/2 cup granita atop melon in each bowl. Sprinkle with sliced mint leaves, garnish with mint sprigs, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.085');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3894407c-901d-4433-860b-ca13c2fbb1ee', 'Trim vegetables and cut lengthwise into 116-inch-thick ribbons with a U-shaped vegetable peeler.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.048', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.085');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a841625f-d0da-4512-9caa-2146ab6ce31d', 'Have ready a bowl of ice and cold water. Cook carrots in a large pot of boiling salted water 2 minutes. Add both squashes and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender, 1 to 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.052', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.086');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b56784f7-dc88-40e7-83b0-1b1f8c201d27', 'Drain vegetables and transfer to ice water, then drain in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.056', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.087');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c8f3916-308e-4a2a-a1a1-5a0e33038b44', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook vegetables, tossing, until heated through. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.06', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.087');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a5c1824-b1f5-47bc-830a-569746732340', 'In large bowl, stir together all ingredients. Store, covered, at room temperature until ready to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.064', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.088');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a4ce0a82-305c-41b8-82dd-306955751473', 'Mince and mash garlic to a paste with a pinch of salt and transfer to a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.068', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.088');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2468e365-16ff-4b47-97be-64d549c5e910', 'Peel 1 cucumber, then halve lengthwise and seed. Coarsely grate into bowl with garlic paste. Stir in yogurt, 1/3 cup mint, and 3/4 teaspoon salt to make tsatsiki.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.072', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.089');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1c82875-d0ea-435e-a1b0-41797f5cae5c', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add onions and celery; sauté until onions are golden, about 7 minutes. Add garlic; stir 1 minute. Add broth and next 5 ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until squash is tender, about 15 minutes. Transfer 3 cups soup to blender; cool slightly, then puree until smooth. Return puree to pot with soup. Simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.086', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.09');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('304a76ac-8c46-44b9-8cdc-866f71cdf90f', 'Ladle soup into 6 bowls. Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon basil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.091', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.091');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('181f2780-9db7-4bfb-a86c-c2ff9cbb0f0c', 'Toast pumpkin seeds in a dry medium skillet over medium-low heat, tossing often, until golden, about 2 minutes. Add sesame and fennel seeds; toast, tossing often, until golden brown, about 2 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.095', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.092');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37f5b913-9034-4b6f-9c68-98ab46e74532', 'Mix in syrup; cook, tossing often, until glossy clumps form, about 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in hemp and chia seeds. Season with salt. Transfer to a parchmentlined baking sheet; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.099', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.093');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('afcf6f14-9911-405e-a8e5-9b5ae7a389e6', 'In a 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan cook pine nuts in oil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, about 2 minutes. With a slotted spoon transfer pine nuts to a bowl. Add rice to oil in pan and cook over moderately low heat, stirring, 1 minute. Add water and bring to a boil. Cover rice and cook over very low heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 18 minutes. Remove pan from heat and let rice stand, undisturbed, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.103', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.093');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('650c911e-e35c-497a-aeeb-4324b6725c56', 'Finely chop basil. Fluff rice with a fork and stir in basil, pine nuts, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.107', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.094');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c92f0ab6-5f89-496b-adbd-384fa887a99d', 'Roll up grated zucchini in large kitchen towel; press to dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.112', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.096');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10506640-23e3-4720-85a3-beef7cb3fe01', 'Heat oil in large deep skillet over high heat. Add 1 cup green onions and sauté 30 seconds. Add zucchini, carrots, and 2 tablespoons dill. Sauté until vegetables are just tender, tossing often, about 8 minutes. Mix in remaining 1/2 cup green onions and 2 tablespoons dill. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.116', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.096');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ecf1f373-902a-4a8d-b4c9-a9793e76d600', 'Combine 4 cups water and sugar in large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil 3 minutes. Stir in coffee beans; boil 2 minutes. Remove pan from heat; cover and let steep until mixture is cool, about 3 hours. Strain liquid into 13x9x2-inch glass baking dish; discard coffee beans in strainer. Add coffee liqueur to liquid in dish; stir to blend. Freeze until firm, stirring every 45 minutes, about 5 hours. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Cover and keep frozen.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.097');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0889676-a6ae-4196-acff-c5ac125bfa6a', 'Before serving, scrape surface of granita with fork until crystals form. Using ice cream scoop, scoop out granita and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.097');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('62498cb8-8c6b-4d6b-8559-320834134abe', 'Whisk together oil, vinegar, water, garlic, shallot, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper until salt has dissolved. Whisk in herbs. Let stand 20 minutes for flavors to develop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.129', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.097');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b5788802-e91a-4d3b-a4c8-a6eec2b7ec15', 'Bring all syrup ingredients to a boil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer until syrup is reduced to about 1/2 cup, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let steep, covered, 1 hour. Pour syrup through a sieve into a bowl, discarding solids.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.133', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b363d678-3ce6-4ccd-9619-6211b300bedf', 'Heat a dry heavy 10-inch skillet over moderate heat until hot, then toast pumpkin seeds, stirring constantly, until puffed and beginning to pop, 3 to 5 minutes. Transfer seeds to a plate and season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.138', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7ffbafe-48ed-41a1-a039-3c15539f770a', 'Halve, pit, and peel avocados, then thinly slice lengthwise. Gently toss slices with 2 tablespoons lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste, then gently toss with 1/4 cup syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.142', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca053f64-5889-437a-bbad-445828c92867', 'Halve pears and core, then thinly slice lengthwise. Toss pear slices with remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Stir in remaining 1/4 cup syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.147', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.098');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2f69d3b9-6f93-44b1-9b9d-9a7e45daa56c', 'Drain pears, reserving syrup, and arrange slices on 4 plates. Transfer avocado slices to plates with a slotted spoon, discarding syrup. Toss greens with reserved syrup from pears and salt and pepper to taste. Mound greens next to avocado and pear slices and sprinkle with pumpkin seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.15', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37a0433e-10df-46b8-b83d-f9b661962b55', 'In a medium stockpot, heat the oil over medium heat. Add the onion, bell pepper, and chili; cook, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Add the broth, chickpeas, tomatoes, curry powder, salt, and black pepper; bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat and simmer gently, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through, about 5 minutes. Serve warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.154', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('17e7a16e-41c2-4238-b66b-c565f4c8ec86', 'Combine shallot, lemon zest, lemon juice, and 1/4 tsp. kosher salt in a medium bowl. Let stand 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38f2fab3-7fb9-4479-8634-e9d55068339f', 'Meanwhile, toast pistachios, 1 Tbsp. olive oil, and 1 tsp. za''atar in a small skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, about 3 minutes. Season with 1/4 tsp. kosher salt. Transfer to a small bowl; let cool and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.099');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('342ec4f5-a102-4ce0-8c23-6f0b4a4ebb6c', 'Add honey and 1 tsp. za''atar to lemon mixture and whisk to combine, then whisk in 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil in a slow, steady stream.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.166', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('734e4a41-a858-401b-9dfe-94fe5b070e1d', 'Place frisée, carrots, parsley, 3/4 cup grapes, and half of the pistachios in a large bowl and drizzle with vinaigrette. Gently toss until frisée is evenly dressed; season with sea salt and pepper. Top with remaining pistachios and 3/4 cup grapes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.17', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bef053b-00e4-4dfc-9036-53548767fec7', 'Peel the bananas, cut into 1/2" thick slices and place in a large bowl. Mix the vinegar, light brown sugar, dark brown sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and mace in a large pot. Tie the cloves, cardamom, peppercorns and saffron in a cheesecloth bag and add to the pot. Bring to a rolling boil and pour over bananas. Drain off and repeat for 5 more days. On the seventh day, discard the spice bag, pour the bananas and juices into a large pot, bring to a rolling boil and ladle in sterilized jars, cover and seal .', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.174', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5cedcc8a-af1d-43e4-8afc-55231a1473a3', 'Put oven rack in upper third of oven and place a shallow baking pan on rack. Preheat oven to 475°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22fab9cc-5833-48c3-8987-d2de50d5707c', 'Toss cauliflower and potatoes together in a bowl with 3 tablespoons oil, cumin seeds, and1/4 teaspoon salt. Spread in hot baking pan and roast, stirring occasionally, until cauliflower is tender and browned in spots and potatoes are just tender, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.1');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7f343df-5096-4645-b779-b8c82b2f9602', 'While vegetables are roasting, cook onion, garlic, jalapeño, and ginger in remaining 2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until very soft and beginning to turn golden, 8 to 10 minutes. Add ground cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne, and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes. Stir in water, scraping up any brown bits from bottom of skillet, then stir in roasted vegetables. Cook, covered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.101');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d4080acf-eaf3-4b0d-b65f-560507140e17', 'Pulse 4 coarsely chopped red bell peppers and 2 coarsely chopped red chiles (such as Fresno) in a food processor until very finely chopped (be careful not to purée). Transfer to a large saucepan and add 3 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups apple cider vinegar. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until liquid is reduced by twothirds, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.191', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.101');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('50512a25-c380-4037-b8da-6991472cde1c', 'Transfer jelly to heatproof jars; cover and chill until set, about 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.195', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.101');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('625b1d77-389f-4bab-8ef6-0a3c13530166', 'Remove rinds and seeds from melons and cut fruit into 1/4-inch dice. Cut bell pepper into 1/4-inch dice. Finely chop onion and cilantro and, wearing rubber gloves, finely chop jalapeño with seeds. In a bowl toss together all ingredients and season with salt. Salsa may be made 4 hours ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.199', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.101');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bdeee02b-4a7f-4d29-9446-e8467972005a', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Toss chickpeas with oil, curry powder, and salt on a rimmed baking sheet until coated. Spread in an even layer and bake until crisp and golden brown, 35–40 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.203', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.102');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0913fb79-d920-4a29-a1a9-49ce50323ca6', 'Whisk first 5 ingredients in small bowl to blend. Season dressing very generously with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.207', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.102');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e92c50f2-e3b2-49f9-9cf2-ae3aaf8836c0', 'Cut off peel and white pith from grapefruits. Cut each grapefruit crosswise into 4 slices, then cut each slice crosswise in half. Arrange lettuce leaves on platter, tearing large ones in half. Top with grapefruit and avocado. Drizzle with dressing; sprinkle with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.102');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6901e8ef-5967-4365-a47a-ee13bb73a806', 'Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl. Season to taste with additional chile, lime juice, and salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.216', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.102');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('356d1711-15a8-43b0-b282-e28b21f0a941', 'This salsa keeps in the refrigerator for up to one day. Before you serve it, stir it well and drain any excess liquid that has accumulated in the bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.22', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('303de801-c86f-4309-81a7-d3460618859a', 'Place the sugar and 1 cup (250 ml) water in a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil, allowing the sugar to dissolve. Let simmer gently for 5 minutes, then remove from the heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.224', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a57c0ea1-9355-4130-82fb-fed0765d456d', 'Place the blueberries in a food processor and add the blue curaçao and one-third of the sugar syrup (about 5 tablespoons). Blitz until completely smooth, then pour into the bottom of four popsicle molds and place in the freezer for 1 1/2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.228', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5434299f-8f2b-4dc3-91ec-1488746e4c8e', 'Meanwhile, clean the food processor bowl and add the mango with the tequila and another one-third of the syrup. Blitz until completely smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.232', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.103');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c6017fb-4ebb-4331-aa82-8d473bd979d3', 'When the blueberry base is frozen solid, remove the molds from the freezer and pour over the mango mixture. Return the molds to the freezer and freeze for another 1 1/2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.236', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcc7aa97-ee0b-4386-b2e6-421d6e7ef5c8', 'Finally, blitz together the strawberries, rum, and remaining syrup. Pour the strawberry mixture over the mango layer once it has frozen solid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ef2f11e-dfc9-41f6-b21b-d52a0ac6105f', 'Freeze for another 1 1/2 hours, or until completely solid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.245', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d95453a8-1d76-4f5f-9b57-f5939b1fee32', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Whisk together vinegar and oil. Season with salt and pepper. Brush both sides of eggplant slices with 1/4 cup vinaigrette. Grill until cooked through, turning occasionally, about 4 minutes per side. Remove from grill; brush with 1/4 cup vinaigrette. Cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.249', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.104');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('55ca4abe-13a1-4a18-8bb8-f7b29f5a6f97', 'Grill bell peppers until blackened on all sides. Wrap in paper bad and let stand 10 minutes. Peel and seed peppers. Cut into 1/4-inch strips. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. cover; chill eggplant and bell peppers separately.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.253', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b4358f1-a938-4e49-b908-acc2e7adba72', 'Place eggplant slices on work surface. Place 4 bell pepper strips on 1 end of each eggplant slice; top with 2 to 4 arugula sprigs, allowing peppers and arugula to extend beyond both sides of eggplant. Sprinkle pine nuts atop arugula. Roll eggplant up. Place seam side down on platter. (Can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Cover.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.257', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('20f076f4-47a8-4fbd-aeae-15ccdf732a3d', 'In a small pot, combine the rhubarb and sugar with 3/4 cup water and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to moderately low and simmer until slightly thickened and bright pink in color, about 20 minutes. Let the syrup cool then pour through a fine-mesh sieve set over a bowl. Press down gently and discard the solids. DO AHEAD: The rhubarb simple syrup can be made in advance and stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.262', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8395418f-1399-41d0-82f2-aae83e8de718', 'In a cocktail shaker, combine 1 ounce of the rhubarb simple syrup with the gin and lemon juice. Fill the shaker with ice and shake vigorously until completely mixed, about 20 seconds. Strain into a highball glass and top with Champagne or soda water.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.267', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c623cbc-10da-4625-82ff-f818b002e551', 'Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Season with white pepper and salt. (Can be made 3 hours ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.271', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.105');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d9d6b4ae-e2f5-4ec0-8677-ef89e76aa9c6', 'Arrange chickpeas in 1 layer on paper towels and allow to air-dry while frying other ingredients.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f077a58-a4f2-4f5b-b07e-c30a0d0841e1', 'Heat oil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat until deep-fat thermometer registers 365°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.278', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('561404b3-1efb-4c75-b053-2fe44a81d90c', 'While oil is heating, peel sweet potato and, using peeler (preferably Y-shaped), shave enough thin strips to measure 2 cups (reserve remaining sweet potato for another use).', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.283', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1d8ebbc9-060a-456c-a67c-075e5bc06598', 'Fry sweet-potato shavings, 1/2 cup at a time, until golden and just crisp, about 1 minute, then transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Return oil to 365°F between batches.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.287', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.106');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('494d6dfc-7d9d-4fa7-9cf5-6f43e24cbcd7', 'Cool oil to 340°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.29', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7134a94-7703-4743-aeac-793d35b9c360', 'Fry pumpkin seeds in 2 batches, covered (seeds will pop and splatter), until puffed (but not brown), 30 seconds to 1 minute, then transfer with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Return oil to 340°F between batches.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.294', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c4570d9-0cb2-469a-9d3a-ba5fdffca3ee', 'Fry chiles until crisp but still red, about 1 minute, then transfer with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.298', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.107');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c21fff1-59f1-44af-a918-6edc9e671c56', 'Combine all ingredients in heavy large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until cranberries are soft and figs are plump, stirring frequently, about 15 minutes. Cool to room temperature. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Serve cold or at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.311', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b6eed40-aa87-4871-bc15-9b675adc6715', 'Mince garlic, then mash to a paste with sea salt. Whisk together garlic paste and remaining ingredients until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.344', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b76eb159-9ba3-4880-9b8e-cd9928360a07', 'Bring vinegar, brown sugar, salt, mustard powder, and 1/2 cup water to a boil in a medium pot over high heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar and salt dissolve, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.349', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('725ff899-c0ca-48ff-9f3e-2a151d9ffebc', 'Place cucumber, onion, raisins, and mustard seeds in a heatproof resealable container. Pour hot brining liquid over cucumber mixture; stir to combine. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving. Serve cool or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.354', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.108');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b8feb0a0-a5da-4359-b53d-521f435828ac', 'Finely chop pine nuts and garlic in processor. Transfer to large nonstick skillet. Add tomatoes, oil and jalapeño. Season mixture with salt and pepper. Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.358', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.109');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa7c6cc9-ce65-447f-8b1d-fc11c1b9247f', 'Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite. Reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking liquid. Drain. Add pasta and 1/4 cup cooking liquid to tomato mixture. Stir over medium-high heat until heated through, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Add arugula; toss to blend. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.362', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.109');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ba2d54a-4aa8-410d-860b-e7af0426b644', 'Whisk first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Add arugula to bowl and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.366', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.109');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('edafc567-b97e-4c42-aeec-391d7a465445', 'Melt butter in a large pan. Add mushrooms, garlic, and a pinch of salt and sauté until mushrooms are softened and excess water has cooked off, 8-10 minutes. Remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.371', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.109');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f568d6e-2792-4008-a612-4e3f354b73ac', 'Combine ground flaxseed, Parmesan, chickpeas, dates, parsley, egg, fennel seeds, tahini, tamari, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1 teaspoon pepper in a food processor. Pulse to combine well and transfer to a large mixing bowl. Once mushrooms are at room temperature, add them, along with pan juices, to the bowl along with rice and stir to combine. Cover and refrigerate for about 30 minutes or up to 1 day. If the mixture seems too wet to form into a patty, stir in 1-2 tablespoons oats.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.374', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.11');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('844ce6a7-978d-47e0-ac98-c1502fcee070', 'Preheat oven to 475° with rack in upper third.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.111');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6acdd04f-c379-4794-9951-ee0c7e42e3f9', 'Form the mixture into 6 patties, each 1" thick. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and arrange the patties with space in between. Bake until toasted, 14-18 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.383', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a6737727-864f-4bf8-83ca-c25ae08564f7', 'Warm oil in a sauté pan over medium heat. Add shallots and a pinch of salt and sauté until edges begin to brown, 5-7 minutes. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.388', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.112');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('479ab776-f7bd-458c-b6e0-b54249cdbf9c', 'After removing the patties from the oven, toast the English muffins. Put a swipe of hummus on each muffin half and assemble by layering patty, avocado, arugula, and shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.392', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.113');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('687bd813-7ae2-4b10-8b0c-cddea82c8e25', 'Pour the orange juice into a 10-ounce highball glass, add ice cubes, and fill with champagne.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.396', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.114');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bf925ad2-1737-41a4-9102-4b624c780c39', 'Blend together walnuts, roasted peppers, bread pieces, garlic paste, lemon juice, cumin, and cayenne in a food processor until as smooth as possible, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.4', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.114');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47a756c5-22ef-4880-ba1b-3a7850cc12d7', 'With motor running, add oil in a slow stream and blend until combined well. Season to taste with salt and additional lemon juice, as well as additional cayenne and minced garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.404', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.114');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a197e620-8de5-4057-bdea-440b15536fb6', 'Combine parsley, cilantro, basil and garlic in small bowl; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.408', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.115');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0b81be94-5344-499c-a38a-76edd1404f80', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Spray large baking sheet (preferably nonstick) with vegetable oil spray. Combine vegetables in large bowl. Drizzle oil over; toss to coat. Arrange vegetables in single layer on prepared baking sheet. Roast 15 minutes. Turn zucchini and yellow squash over; roast until tender and golden, about 5 minutes longer. Transfer asparagus, zucchini and yellow squash to platter; cover with foil. Turn bell pepper over; roast until slightly charred and tender, about 15 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.412', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.117');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b3b9aab5-a4c6-443f-90f9-dc31521beb89', 'Transfer pepper to platter with other vegetables. Sprinkle with herb mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Serve warm, or let stand up to 4 hours and serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.416', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.117');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e530fe33-0f05-4a58-8e78-6111384c965b', 'Halve tofu crosswise, then cut lengthwise into fourths to form 8 slices. Put tofu slices between several layers of paper towels to drain, replacing towels as needed, until ready to use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.42', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.117');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c19a81f3-7ba6-4538-9fc7-c6a41d87c42c', 'Finely chop enough shallots to measure 1/2 cup and reserve. Cut remaining shallots crosswise into 1/8-inch-thick slices and separate into rings. Heat oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron) over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then fry sliced shallots in 2 batches, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, 1 1/2 to 3 minutes per batch (watch closely, as shallots can burn easily). Quickly transfer shallots as fried with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon oil from skillet and reserve skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.425', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.118');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('465b695e-59f5-407a-a555-c195ad6c496f', 'Cook sugar in a dry 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, undisturbed, until it melts around edges and begins to turn golden, then continue to cook, stirring, until all of sugar is melted and turns a golden caramel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.429', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.119');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a094e6a8-c3bc-43e6-8640-2713f3552c99', 'Add reserved chopped shallots (use caution; caramel will bubble up and steam vigorously) and cook, stirring, until shallots shrink and are very fragrant, about 45 seconds. Add garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, 30 seconds. Stir in soy sauce, vinegar, and 1 1/3 cups water and simmer, stirring, until any hardened caramel is dissolved, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.433', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.119');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eb983503-e3e5-4c68-af19-262d546d1ba2', 'Stir together cornstarch and remaining 2 tablespoons water until smooth, then stir into sauce and simmer, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes. Remove from heat and keep warm, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.438', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.12');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b23ed3f-d83d-4f77-b4d4-c97cadb65734', 'Heat oil remaining in skillet over high heat until hot but not smoking. Meanwhile, blot any excess moisture remaining on tofu with paper towels, then add to hot oil in skillet in 1 layer. Fry tofu, turning over once, until golden and crisp, 7 to 10 minutes total. Transfer to clean paper towels to drain briefly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.442', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.12');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('53aa179d-72b2-403a-9a53-85d9e32aadb7', 'Reheat sauce, then serve tofu topped with sauce, basil, mint, and fried shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.447', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.121');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bc9817d9-52ed-4ed8-acec-28215061d9ff', 'Cook sugar in a 3-quart dry heavy saucepan over moderately low heat, stirring slowly with a fork (to help sugar melt evenly), until melted and pale golden. Cook caramel without stirring, swirling pan, until deep golden. Remove pan from heat and carefully add wine (mixture will bubble up and caramel will harden), then simmer until caramel is dissolved and syrup is reduced to about 1 1/2 cups, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.451', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.121');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1700f460-1386-4e08-9515-44f9654c7faf', 'Divide berries among 8 serving bowls, then spoon syrup over berries.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.455', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.122');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b265d7aa-16fc-428c-ade7-97561cb91e1e', 'Lightly toast cumin and coriander seeds in a small skillet over medium heat, stirring often, until fragrant, 2-3 minutes; let cool. Purée seeds with jalapeños, scallions, garlic, oil, parsley, cilantro, lemon juice, and salt in a blender or food processor until smooth. DO AHEAD: Harissa can be made 5 days ahead. Press a piece of plastic wrap directly onto surface of harissa. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.459', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.122');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13182312-42b1-4a0a-bcee-fd59af51372b', 'Bring 3 cups dried shiitake mushrooms (about 3 ounces), 1/3 cup reduced-sodium soy sauce, 1 tablespoon raw or brown sugar, and 1 cup water to a boil in a small saucepan. Cover pan; reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are softened and all liquid is absorbed, 12-15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.463', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.123');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e848836-68b0-4c27-afa7-40095633818d', 'Let mushrooms cool slightly, then thinly slice. Transfer to a small bowl, add 1/2 teaspoon toasted sesame seeds, and season with freshly ground black pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.468', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.123');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b72bed62-1e28-4ede-8e2d-fa6279c085de', '1. Cut a thin slice from the ends of each cucumber', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.472', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.124');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('446642dd-48b5-4daf-a52f-1df619cd10b4', '2. Meanwhile, combine vinegar, water, and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.476', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.125');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c3191694-0a72-4c00-bb58-f2a93fd0c9aa', '3. Remove hot jars from canner. Place 1 head fresh dill or 1 tsp (5 mL) dill seeds and 1 clove garlic into each jar; pack in cucumbers. Pour boiling vinegar mixture over cucumbers to within 1/2 inch (1 cm) of rim (head space). Process 10 minutes for pint (500 mL) jars and 15 minutes for quart (1 L) jars as directed for Longer Time Processing Procedure.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.481', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.126');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('249732ed-689d-4b20-8f1b-8bf2b332e345', 'Garlic may turn blue or green in the jar. Nothing to be alarmed about, it is only the effect of the acid on the natural pigments in the garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.486', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.127');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('959c2fc6-7bcc-4efc-891d-9b06356b5c43', 'Combine chiles, cilantro, and onion in a large bowl. Just before serving, halve and seed avocados, scoop out pulp, and mash pulp into chile mixture with a fork until just combined. Season with salt and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.49', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.128');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ecada24-00ba-4d4c-9e2a-b69c04bda112', 'Slice fennel lengthwise 1/4 inch thick. Coarsely crush almonds by firmly rolling over them with a rolling pin.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.494', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.129');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('27685905-fe1b-4ffa-951e-8ea68b753a50', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then sauté fennel with garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes. Stir in almonds, raisins, coriander, zest, juice, and saffron and sauté until raisins start to plump, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.499', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.13');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29355d5e-694d-44ce-9404-8a11dd8eef0a', 'Stir in cilantro just before serving at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.502', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.13');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1006361b-f6fb-481f-a5eb-2da09a495f76', 'Combine onion and 1/4 cup vinegar in a small bowl. Cover with plastic wrap, pressing directly onto surface. Chill until onion is uniformly pink, at least 4 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.507', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.131');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('095c00d5-ee67-4440-af5e-2e42089864b0', 'Heat a medium skillet, preferably cast iron, over medium-high. Cook tortilla and chile, turning often, until completely charred, 8-10 minutes. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.511', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.131');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3621f1b2-dc1e-491e-9bdb-a5c9c8808493', 'Blend tortilla, chile, celery, oil, lemon juice, and remaining 2 tablespoons vinegar until very smooth. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve lined with a layer of cheesecloth into a small bowl; discard solids. Add reserved palm liquid to make 1 cup; season aguachile with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.515', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.132');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('db02dc4c-043e-47cf-822b-3365832e8a77', 'Combine palm and artichoke hearts, tomatoes, and radishes in a large bowl and toss with 1/2 cup aguachile; season with salt. Let sit at least 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.52', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.132');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a6c82f9-7a98-46ef-9ef1-d4069dc3c270', 'Just before serving, drain pickled onion and add to marinated vegetables along with cilantro. Toss to combine and transfer to a platter. Pour remaining marinade over top or serve alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.524', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.133');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e138c90-48bd-487a-b8f2-ea08756d31e5', 'Do ahead: Onion can be prepared 1 day ahead; keep chilled. Aguachile can be made 1 day ahead.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.528', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.133');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1aab5ae7-20b0-4b3c-8e26-5f8e28f6ef58', 'Toss cucumber with vinegar, oil, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.532', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.134');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d7eaa42-904e-4455-b61a-95294d60e53d', 'Add frisée, watercress, spinach, and radishes and toss well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.537', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.134');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f64c78a0-2917-4a58-9464-f7cc6976012c', 'With processor running, drop garlic through feed tube and mince. Scrape down sides of work bowl. Add chick-peas, tahini and lemon juice; process until mixture is smooth. Add roasted peppers; process until peppers are finely chopped. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer hummus to small bowl. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.541', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.135');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ab5e1d6-56d7-49bf-9df5-8a9d6ad5c324', 'Bring first 5 ingredients to boil in heavy large saucepan over medium–high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to medium–low. Cover and simmer until quinces are soft, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Pour mixture into large strainer set over bowl; reserve juices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.545', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.135');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('79242328-b886-41e0-8a15-1038c0ee614c', 'Return quince mixture to same saucepan; mash with potato masher. Add cranberries; cook over medium heat until most of berries burst, stirring frequently, about 8 minutes. Stir in salt. Transfer sauce to bowl. Cover and refrigerate sauce and reserved juices separately until cold, about 3 hours. Do ahead Can be made 2 days ahead. Keep chilled. Before serving, stir enough reserved juices into sauce to thin to desired consistency. Serve sauce cold or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.55', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.136');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a312c6f8-5dbf-45ac-9c16-0d633fe74332', 'Discard tough lower third of broccoli stem. Peel remaining stem and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices. Cut broccoli into 2-inch florets. In a steamer set over boiling water steam broccoli, covered, until crisp-tender, 4 to 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.554', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.136');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3273e85f-f8f1-4e5b-b34b-14fd64941029', 'While broccoli is steaming, finely chop garlic and in a small skillet combine with oil, lemon juice, and salt and pepper to taste. Heat garlic mixture over moderate heat until garlic is fragrant. In a bowl toss broccoli with garlic mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.558', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.137');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c74a28d3-b58a-4d7b-b052-2ee8aeb8577e', 'Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 30 minutes. Drain. Cool to just warm, 10 to 15 minutes; peel potatoes. Cut each potato in half, then cut into 1/3-inch slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.563', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.137');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8a4779bb-e86b-4c28-b567-99281b854f69', 'Heat vegetable oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add ginger and stir 30 seconds. Add half of cabbage and toss until wilted, about 4 minutes. Add remaining cabbage, green onions, and sesame oil. Toss until all cabbage is crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.576', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.139');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aea83ccf-7db3-4840-a71a-1d640c0a8dc8', 'In a small heavy saucepan bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring, and skim surface. Simmer mixture, stirring and skimming foam occasionally, 15 minutes, or until thickened and translucent. Remove pan from heat and cool preserves completely. Preserves keep, covered and chilled, 1 month.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.581', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.139');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ef552a3-a217-4f8a-bc31-8de13c770132', 'Combine all the fruit in a large bowl and stir in one of the syrups. Garnish with the mint or rosemary sprigs if you''re using Herb Syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.585', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.14');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('801abe99-4999-4f89-bef6-3b360c985824', 'Finely grind star anise, clove, and cinnamon stick in spice mill or coffee grinder.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.588', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.142');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('379dd317-0184-42ad-ad0b-82333484a576', 'Combine spice mixture, vinegar, sugar, ginger, mustard seeds, and pepper in heavy large saucepan. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves and bring to boil. Add plums; reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until chutney thickens and chunky sauce forms, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes. Cool. Season to taste with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.592', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.143');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('73651ad9-404f-4287-b8c4-4284298e67b3', '*Available in the spice section of some supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and Asian markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.597', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.143');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df7c4cf3-05fb-4c41-b0d5-77cd03d343f8', 'Combine vinegar, milk and miso in a bowl. Add tofu to milk mixture. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Heat oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Combine coconut and flour and coat tofu. Place on sheet. Coat with cooking spray and bake until golden, 35 to 45 minutes, turning and coating other side after 20 minutes. Whisk tamari, sugar, ginger, pepper flakes and 1 cup hot water in a bowl. Wrap tofu, cilantro and carrots in lettuce and dip in tamari sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.602', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.144');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0264f26b-5fa8-4a55-8e71-2ef0d7ae7a17', '1. Pour 1 tablespoon peach concentrate into each glass.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.606', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.144');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1ca6cb3f-b1b3-48a2-b17e-dd32157f2cb6', '2. Fill each Champagne glass two-thirds full with sparkling cider.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.61', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.145');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e77096cb-2fff-4f7f-9675-6dd60a5526f8', '3. Drop 2 raspberries into each Champagne flute and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.145');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30964d23-ef4f-40f8-b168-3c91b3c1dc5f', 'Pulse garlic and thyme in a food processor, scraping down sides as necessary. Add oil, 2 tsp. kosher salt, and paprika and continue to pulse until a thick paste forms, about 1 minute. Transfer to a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.619', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.146');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e3e287e-92db-4b03-8aaa-5890ba94a73c', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. garlic-oil mixture in a medium pot over medium-low until beginning to brown and smells fragrant, about 30 seconds. Cook mushrooms, shallot, and bay leaves, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are tender and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes. Add broth, bring to a simmer, and cook 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.623', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.146');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f770638-f704-4a5d-b9c5-c19750c8fafa', 'Strain mushroom mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl; wipe out pot. Cook flour and remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in pot over medium heat, stirring constantly, until nutty brown and thickened, about 8 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.627', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.147');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a1efe86-ba81-482b-9590-a4399eab8a33', 'Add wine, bring to a simmer, and cook 3 minutes. Add mushroom broth, parsley, 1/4 tsp. pepper, and remaining 1/4 tsp. kosher salt, and return to a simmer. Season to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.631', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.147');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f93f16ac-9ddb-478b-9777-5cb5400d0065', 'Gravy can be made 3 days ahead; transfer to an airtight container and chill. Heat in a small pot over medium, whisking constantly and adding warm water or vegetable broth 1 Tbsp. at a time if needed, until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.636', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.148');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3702a19a-6b5d-40a4-ac0f-fe3cc7023258', 'Slit chiles open and remove seeds and veins. Heat a flat griddle or dry heavy skillet (not nonstick) over medium heat until hot, then toast the chiles, opened flat, 2 at a time, by pressing down and turning on either side with tongs, until fragrant and insides change color, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.64', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.148');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d06fecd9-e817-4b69-b362-35f16107f837', 'Put chiles in a bowl with cold water to cover and let soak until soft, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.645', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.149');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f6dfdbac-d217-4dec-9e5b-e82dbf7aff04', 'While chiles are soaking, cook onion in oil in a 5- to 6-quart heavy pot over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.649', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.149');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f4cf7ff-ad47-475a-8b93-6600fe9bec40', 'Transfer chiles with tongs to a blender (discard soaking water) and add garlic, cider vinegar, cumin, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar, cloves, and 1 cup water. Blend until smooth, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.653', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.15');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38327a3c-eeed-47ba-9ca2-088f891f31f1', 'Add chile purée to pot and cook, stirring, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.657', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.15');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd755ccb-7b80-42a9-8169-1cf5f311ce83', 'Add remaining 5 cups water, hominy, beans, zucchini, corn, and 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender, about 20 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.662', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.151');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e6b8125-2f6d-4523-813c-90834e70d0f4', 'To serve the stew, surround it with small bowls of the accompaniments and let the guests garnish their servings as they wish.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.666', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.152');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('11467d12-90ab-448a-a54c-2046ec26bf02', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and sprinkle with coarse salt. Sauté until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes. Add garlic; stir until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add tomatoes, corn, and lima beans. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until corn and lima beans are tender and tomatoes are soft, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewarm before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.67', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.152');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb021f7f-fe14-47ea-9b02-d4a75171239c', 'Stir in basil and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.674', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.153');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f1b08080-e61a-4c8b-993d-9c63835611bf', 'Place tofu in a colander; set a heavy pot on top 10 to 15 minutes to press out moisture. Halve; sprinkle soy sauce, garlic powder, then flour over halves. Heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat in a large skillet. Cook tofu until golden, 2 to 3 minutes per side. Slice; set aside. In same skillet, cook peppers and onions, covered, until peppers soften, 7 to 8 minutes. Cook noodles as directed on package. Whisk miso paste, garlic, ginger, zest, juice and remaining 1 tablespoon oil in a bowl. Add pepper mixture, noodles, corn, water chestnuts; toss. Top with tofu.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.678', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.153');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05c12a47-4db4-49d5-9cb0-58ff7083d536', 'Simmer blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar, and water in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart heavy saucepan, stirring occasionally, until blueberries burst and collapse, 3 to 5 minutes. Purée with lime juice in a blender until smooth. (Use caution when blending hot liquids.) Blend in sugar to taste. Pour into molds and freeze until slushy, about 45 minutes. Insert sticks and continue to freeze until completely hardened, at least 3 hours and up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.683', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.154');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d1bcc269-65e9-424d-93e1-263dc84030bf', 'In a colander drain cucumbers and rinse thoroughly. Drain cucumbers well and squeeze dry in handfuls. Pat cucumbers dry on towels. In a bowl stir together mustard, vinegar, and sugar and stir in cucumbers and dill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.692', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.155');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fe0741a-4947-4559-9428-143c0846d374', 'Cut baguette with a serrated knife on a long diagonal into 3/4-inch-thick slices (about 5 to 6 inches long). Cut a lengthwise slit about 3 inches long from center through edge of a slice, then cross ends, overlapping them, to form a "claw." Repeat with remaining slices. Brush both sides of slices with oil and arrange in 1 layer on a large baking sheet, then sprinkle with sea salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.696', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.155');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d0bf883e-a1e5-403d-a263-fc8f70ffbc72', 'Bake until crisp and golden, about 15 minutes. Cool on a rack.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.7', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.156');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('93d70d56-cae8-4226-ace3-3147b121b5aa', 'Wash spinach well, discarding any course stems, and drain in colander. In a 3- to 4- quart saucepan bring water to a boil. Add spinach and steam covered, 2 minutes. Drain spinach in colander, gently pressing out most of liquid. In a bowl toss spinach with oil, soy sauce, and salt and pepper to taste. Chill spinach, uncovered, for 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.704', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.156');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ad2fa5e2-e0eb-40ac-93b6-6ace2cb9c660', 'While spinach is chilling, in a dry small heavy skillet (not non-stick) toast sesame seeds over moderate heat, stirring, until golden, 3 to 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.708', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.158');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9583b336-06cd-48fa-8bb4-229232d1c1db', 'Toss spinach with sesame seeds and vinegar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.713', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.159');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed722659-576a-44f2-863d-056b238689ef', 'Combine pomegranate molasses and oil in small bowl. Using garlic press, press garlic into mixture and whisk to blend. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.717', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.159');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b079c9c0-cdb6-408c-8c56-6d9cdc31fb70', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 6 minutes. Add bulgur; stir 1 minute. Add 2 cups warm water, cover, and simmer until water is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Mix in jalapeño chiles, then black-eyed peas, basil, and green onions. Cover skillet and let stand 5 minutes. Transfer bulgur mixture to large bowl. Mix in dressing. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.721', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.159');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47f5b659-171b-401b-b075-e2739dd41059', 'Just before serving, mix tomatoes into salad and sprinkle with nuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.725', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.16');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0aef7fcc-5a27-4e2b-a547-7ede66be2a2e', 'Put oven rack in upper third of oven and preheat oven to 350°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.729', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.163');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9c856c55-c0dc-4dad-9f4c-6cb1a4df0fef', 'Put bread slices in a large shallow baking pan and brush slices with oil. Season lightly with salt and pepper, then bake until pale golden, about 10 minutes. Rub toasts with cut sides of garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.733', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('18f556f1-aa17-40b4-91de-2b171332493c', 'Combine 2 cups chopped dried apricots, 1/2 cup chopped dried tart cherries, 1/2 cup sake or dry white wine, 1/4 cup fresh orange juice, 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice, and 1 cup water in a large saucepan; let soak for 2 hours. Place 1 whole star anise, 1 small bay leaf, 1/2 cinnamon stick, and 1/2 teaspoon finely grated peeled ginger in the center of a layer of cheesecloth. Gather up edges; tie with kitchen twine to form a bundle. Add to pan. Bring to a simmer over medium heat; reduce heat to low and cook, stirring often, for 30 minutes. Stir in 1 tablespoon plus 2 teaspoons miso. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened, 5-10 minutes. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.737', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.164');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dde020a3-957c-49d1-86e7-832cc1ce805e', 'Soak noodles in a medium bowl of boiling-hot water 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.741', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.165');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee2d151e-ef6e-4921-9edd-154120e97a85', 'Meanwhile, blanch carrot in boiling water until softened, about 45 seconds. Drain. Rinse under cold water to stop cooking, then transfer to a small bowl along with cucumber, jalapeño, vinegar, sugar, 1 tablespoon lime juice, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Let stand 5 minutes. Reserve 2 tablespoons liquid and drain pickled vegetables.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.745', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.165');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ea386914-4913-456b-a4aa-de8a9222dd8a', 'Drain noodles and rinse under cold water, then drain and pat dry. Toss noodles with remaining 3/4 teaspoon lime juice and snip with kitchen shears 5 or 6 times.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.749', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.166');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ab9d79c-0ea4-4cb5-9702-88b95fd01cd2', 'Fill a shallow pan or pie plate with warm water. Soak 2 rice-paper rounds until they begin to soften, about 30 seconds, then let excess water drip off and stack soaked rounds on a work surface so that they overlap by all but 1 inch on either side. Put 2 pieces of romaine on bottom third of round. Top with one eighth of noodles (about 2 tablespoons), tofu (4 sticks), bean sprouts (about 2 tablespoons), herbs (3 tablespoons), and pickled vegetables (3 tablespoons). Roll up tightly around filling, folding in sides. Make 7 more rolls in same manner.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.753', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.166');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('07087907-1a5b-4342-ade0-4745788f3c90', 'Stir together hoisin sauce, peanut butter, water, and reserved 2 tablespoons pickling liquid. Serve rolls with dipping sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.757', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5c883651-c950-40ce-a067-369227828f66', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl. Season with salt. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.) Add avocado to salsa just before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.761', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.167');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c6b62b30-9d8e-4f33-ac56-0307a63107e3', 'Standing mango upright, cut two lengthwise slices, each about 1/2 inch thick, from a broad side of mango pit. Cut remaining broad side and remaining mangoes in same manner. (There should be a total of 12 slices, 6 of them end pieces.) Discard pits and reserve any remaining mango for another use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.765', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c39c62b-ca28-49a2-be07-bc8c084379f7', 'Working with end pieces only, score flesh in a cross-hatch pattern, being careful not to cut through skin, and grill, cut side down, on a well-oiled rack set 5 to 6 inches over glowing coals until golden brown, about 2 minutes. (Alternatively, mango may be grilled in a hot well-seasoned ridged grill pan over moderately high heat in same manner.) Transfer mango as grilled to a platter. When end pieces of mango are cool enough to handle, push from skin side to turn inside out. Grill remaining mango slices about 2 minutes on each side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.769', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.168');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('244cbf2b-5d9c-4781-a7bd-6e4d55bc6c4d', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Wrap beets tightly in foil. Place directly on oven rack. Roast until tender when pierced with knife, about 1 hour. Cool beets. Peel and quarter beets. Transfer to large bowl. Add 2 tablespoons olive oil, 2 teaspoons thyme, salt, and pepper; toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.773', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('52ada952-da19-4edf-9544-6d0dbc0bd24b', 'Spray 2 large rimmed baking sheets with nonstick spray. Divide onion wedges between prepared baking sheets. Brush onions on both sides with 2 tablespoons oil; sprinkle with 4 teaspoons thyme, salt, and pepper. Arrange onions cut side down and roast until golden brown on bottom, about 10 minutes. Turn onions over. Roast until golden brown and tender, about 10 minutes longer. Transfer to another large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.777', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.169');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c2d401f-d2a7-4d69-9dd9-b7356ac5e285', 'Whisk lemon zest, lemon juice, ginger, sugar, and 1/2 tsp. salt in a medium bowl. Whisking constantly, gradually add oil. Whisk until emulsified; season vinaigrette with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.894', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.19');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc8a6cb0-1170-4e2f-b95c-7da13769b593', 'Divide green beans between same baking sheets. Drizzle beans with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1/4 cup water, and 2 teaspoons thyme. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover tightly with foil and roast until almost crisp-tender, about 14 minutes. Uncover and continue to roast until water evaporates and beans are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Transfer to bowl with onions. (Beets, onions, and green beans can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.781', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.17');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c13236a-19c9-4015-9188-8b294e954b24', 'Drizzle onions and green beans with balsamic vinegar; toss to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Top with beets and serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.785', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.17');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('94c016cf-4315-4ffe-a4c8-a333b7a24bb2', 'Bring juice and sugar to boil in medium saucepan over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil 1 minute. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until mixture thickens and reduces to 1/4 cup, about 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat and stir in orange-flower water. Refrigerate syrup until cold, about 1 hour. (Syrup can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.789', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('31476172-6952-45d1-ba69-ed333f004ee3', 'Place pomegranate seeds in plastic bag and freeze 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.793', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.171');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05ae45f8-58c1-4c42-b2ff-0630e485def4', 'Pour 1 1/2 teaspoons syrup into each of eight 8-ounce Champagne flutes. Fill flutes with Prosecco; stir gently. Float a few frozen seeds in each glass and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.797', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.172');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a6aa2d6-e46d-42d9-86f0-36d3ca0285ae', 'Cut zucchini lengthwise into 1/8-inch-thick slices with slicer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.801', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.174');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6c50822e-33e1-4f7e-9ef5-4fb17e47bb67', 'Heat 1 Tbsp oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot, then sauté half of zucchini with 1/4 tsp each of salt and pepper, stirring and turning frequently with tongs, until just tender, about 3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and repeat with remaining oil and zucchini.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.805', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.175');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('257de44c-de38-460b-960c-1c3d68d5a1cc', 'Return first batch of zucchini to skillet. Add tarragon, lemon juice, and salt to taste and toss to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.809', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.176');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cb735207-36db-470f-939f-00c419887437', 'Rinse rice and barley in a medium-mesh sieve, then drain and transfer to a 4- to 5-quart heavy pot. Add water (31/2 cups) and bring to a rolling boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, 45 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 10 minutes, then stir from top to bottom with a rubber spatula.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.813', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.176');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cabb6116-3dc8-44cd-823f-08818515723b', 'Combine currants and vinegar in a small bowl; let sit at least 2 hours and up to 1 day.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.818', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.177');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e57cbf43-9160-4ec4-ac4f-b16ac8ce6efa', 'Cook rice in a large saucepan of boiling salted water until tender, 45-50 minutes. Drain rice, return to pot, cover, and let sit 10 minutes. Spread out on a baking sheet; let dry out overnight in an unlit oven or on countertop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.823', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.178');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('93e0749f-166e-4707-9599-9cb4ad99d1a7', 'Fit a medium saucepan with thermometer and pour in vegetable oil to measure 2". Heat over medium-high heat until thermometer registers 350°. Working in 4 batches, cook rice until golden and puffed, about 1 minute. Using a fine-mesh sieve, transfer puffed rice to paper towels to drain; season with salt and let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.827', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.179');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('56798369-d193-4c49-bf26-663c35f2ed49', 'Meanwhile, pulse cauliflower in a food processor until finely chopped. Transfer to large bowl. Working in batches, pulse kale in food processor until finely chopped (be careful not to turn into a purée), adding to cauliflower as you go. Add puffed rice, currants with soaking liquid, cucumber, scallion, olive oil, Aleppo pepper, and sumac, if using; toss to combine and season with salt, black pepper, and more vinegar, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.831', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.181');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51bbc83b-6d6e-4812-9507-46435438e41d', 'Do ahead: Rice can be fried 5 days ahead. Store airtight at room temperature', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.836', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.181');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d13ebe8-0daa-40f9-b2d6-733ad2e61b6d', 'Toss bell peppers, onion, and vinegar in a large bowl; season with salt and black pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.84', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.182');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0df6c923-027a-4a3e-b62e-1fe5f861d701', 'Let sit until bell peppers are slightly softened, 10–20 minutes. Just before serving, toss herbs and oil with bell pepper mixture.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.845', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.183');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3bdf0ab-39dd-4296-8957-4614c4b6b015', 'Blend first 7 ingredients in processor until finely chopped. With machine running, gradually add olive oil. Process until coarse puree forms. Season sauce verte to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.849', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.183');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63702ee3-0f8a-44c1-acd2-964de04bd7aa', 'Heat oil in heavy large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add vegetables; stir until coated. Sprinkle with salt and 3 tablespoons water. Cover; cook vegetables until almost crisp-tender, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes. Uncover; cook until vegetables are just tender, about 2 minutes longer. Stir in enough sauce verte to coat vegetables generously. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl. Garnish with parsley and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.853', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.184');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('367284d2-3d09-46ae-bb05-97124ba2fd6e', 'Place the strawberries and sugar in a food processor and pulse just until the mixture is finely chopped and juicy but still chunky; you don''t want a smooth purée. Transfer to a bowl and stir in the balsamic vinegar and a few grinds of pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.857', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.184');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('21c2eaa9-25f9-4645-aed9-622c29cb6adb', 'Spoon the mixture into ice pop molds and insert sticks. Freeze until firm, at least 6 hours or up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.862', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.185');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dc486f4c-0056-487a-9ca0-6ec94188115c', 'To unmold the pops, run hot water over the outsides of the molds for a few seconds, then gently pull the sticks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.866', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.185');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1248311-6733-445f-b1ba-b51c8d01fff3', 'In a small heavy saucepan cover potatoes with cold salted water by 1 inch and simmer until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.87', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.186');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4297245-b464-45a9-a54d-f0b5bcea4168', 'Transfer potatoes with a slotted spoon to a colander to drain and cool 10 minutes. Return water in pan to a boil and blanch snap peas until crisp-tender, about 1 minute. In a colander drain snap peas and refresh under cold water. Drain snap peas and pat dry with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.874', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.186');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('655aaaba-c470-423d-994b-48622672ebe0', 'Cut potatoes lengthwise into quarters. In a bowl toss together potatoes, snap peas, vinegar, oil, mint, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.878', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.187');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc1c63e5-d9e8-4213-984f-f4f96ab7f631', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in medium bowl. Add 1 teaspoon oil. Grill or toast bread. Brush with remaining 2 teaspoons oil. Season generously with pepper. Top with bell pepper mixture. Cut each into 4 pieces and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.883', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.187');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e63bdce3-e302-4887-b7fe-864f6d1af881', 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Rinse farro under cold water. Cook in a large pot of boiling salted water, skimming surface occasionally, until tender, 20–25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.887', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.188');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37c5e78a-649f-4e52-8658-e22f0285ee85', 'Meanwhile, toast pistachios on a rimmed baking sheet, tossing once, until golden brown, 8–10 minutes. Let cool, then coarsely chop.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.89', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.19');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6059c12a-d8a6-4cd1-8ab3-d60b0d4361c1', 'Toss fruit and mint with 1/4 cup syrup, or to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.335');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a60365fb-a3e6-421a-9f57-a70685cf25ae', 'Drain farro and rinse under cold water. Transfer to a large bowl and add chile, herbs, raisins, and pistachios; toss to combine. Drizzle with vinaigrette, season with salt and pepper, and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.898', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.191');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22b6414c-a761-4ce7-974f-97c8f9ca500c', 'Farro can be cooked 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.902', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.191');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4a3a2a28-30d9-4969-a54e-9192d8a3c214', 'Cut grapefruits in half and juice them (reserve juice for Daiquiri Ice Pops or drinking). Using a large spoon, scrape out pulp and flesh (it should come out easily). Peel away any residual white pith so you''re left with completely clean rinds. Fill grapefruit halves with sorbet and smooth tops flush with edges of fruit using a small flexible spatula or butter knife to make cups; freeze until ready to serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.906', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('51b0c5e4-593e-418a-9b82-73021dc2022e', 'Cut each sorbet cup in half to make quarters just before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.909', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02055ff7-6091-4632-85a0-9c7812de7df8', 'Sorbet cups can be made 1 day ahead. Cover once sorbet is solid and keep frozen.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.914', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('07f2963a-c6c6-4ebf-ab1f-57fbf21dc09f', 'Puree 1 tablespoon preserves, mustard, and vinegar in blender. With machine running, gradually add oil. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.918', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.192');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f446246-3bba-423d-bdec-58e95aeeca9d', 'Reserve 1/4 of grated apple and several walnut halves for garnish. Toss cabbage, remaining 2 tablespoons preserves, apple, and walnuts in large bowl. Toss with enough dressing to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Garnish with reserved grated apple and walnut halves and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.922', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.193');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14224bc9-97d2-4ef5-b7d5-d2d6ac32fe0c', 'In a small saucepan, bring rice, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 1/4 cups water to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover; simmer until rice is tender and absorbs the water, 30 to 35 minutes. Turn off heat; leave covered. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Cook scallion whites, chile, ginger, curry, black pepper and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, stirring, 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water and green beans; cook, stirring, until beans turn bright green, about 2 minutes. Add plums, bell pepper and coconut milk; cook and stir until colors are bright and sauce is thick, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in cashews. Divide plum-green bean mixture among 4 plates. Serve with rice; sprinkle with scallion greens before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.926', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.193');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('941019b8-346a-43a4-ade5-543ec5fc55e1', 'Stir mustard seeds in small dry skillet over medium heat until seeds begin to pop, about 3 minutes. Transfer to small bowl; cool. Add vinegar, lemon juice, and mustard to mustard seeds. Gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.931', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.193');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6d853f56-e9ca-46f7-8c77-16020a6ac167', 'Toss watercress, endive, and radishes in bowl with enough dressing to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.935', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.193');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('19cb8766-33bc-4f28-8920-671d8d0f29e6', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté onions, stirring frequently, until softened. Add bell pepper and ginger and sauté, stirring, 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.94', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.194');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df36ce89-0c04-4bd7-b258-723c0b5d10ae', 'Stir in mangoes, pineapple juice, vinegar, brown sugar, curry powder, and red pepper flakes. Simmer,stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 15 minutes. Season with salt and coarse pepper, then cool. Serve chutney at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.944', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.194');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7a7d2e63-a4c4-4bca-b6cc-069661136162', 'Heat the olive oil in a heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and sauté for 5 minutes, or until just beginning to color. Add the red, yellow, and green bell peppers and sauté for another 10 minutes, or just until the peppers soften. Stir in the olives, walnuts, parsley, and basil. When well blended, add the vinegar and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.194');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('567fd902-1e7b-4ffe-b1f6-188755987207', 'Remove from the heat and pack the mixture into the sterilized containers. Spoon 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil on the top of the mixture in each container. Cover and set aside to cool before refrigerating.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.195');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cf26463f-2220-4b3c-8535-6d3841c9d8c5', 'Combine prunes and Armagnac in an airtight container and let macerate at room temperature at least 24 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.956', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.195');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22c453f0-2cb2-49e0-b1fc-0e92a5a5738e', 'Bring sugar and 3/4 cup cold water to a boil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.96', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.196');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('90429ed3-5fb6-4753-a201-ebf2e88843d0', 'Purée prune and Armagnac mixture with sugar syrup in a food processor until very smooth, about 2 minutes. Add orange juice and remaining 1 1/4 cups cold water and pulse to combine. Force through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl and discard solids. Chill until cold, about 1 hour. Freeze in ice cream maker, then transfer to an airtight container and put in freezer to harden, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.965', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.196');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3701dcef-f432-4881-9793-6586254df077', 'Bring all ingredients to simmer in heavy medium pot over medium-high heat. Cook until sugar is dissolved and mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes. Transfer mixture to 9x13-inch metal baking pan. Place pan in freezer. Freeze for 3 hours, stirring with spoon every hour to break up ice crystals. Scoop mixture into chilled bowls and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.968', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.196');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8b78fe66-ab9e-44c8-b0f2-070d42d89d8f', 'To make the filling, in a large bowl, using an electric mixer, cream the butter with the agave nectar until smooth, about 2 minutes. Add the cinnamon and flour and mix well. Stir in the walnuts and raisins. Refrigerate to firm the mixture for a minimum of 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.972', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.197');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8dbf9fb2-ddd6-4a7e-a7b4-c6cc5d2348c3', 'Begin the dough by cooking the potato in boiling water for 25 to 30 minutes, until soft. Drain, reserving 3/4 cup of the starchy water. Mash the potato and reserved water until smooth. Set aside and cool to room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.977', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.197');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c14c63e0-a76a-4c0c-8f6c-79f1d88e7545', 'Place the yeast, warm water, and 2 tablespoons of the agave nectar in a food processor. Pulse a few times to dissolve the yeast. Let this mixture sit about 10 minutes, or until foamy. Add the cooled mashed potato, milk, the remaining ¼ cup agave nectar, the melted butter, and salt. Pulse several times to mix. Add the flour a little at a time, pulsing to blend until a soft dough forms. Transfer the dough to a lightly floured surface. Gently knead by hand for approximately 1 minute, or until smooth and elastic. Place the kneaded dough into a lightly oiled bowl. Let rest for 20 minutes. Punch down the dough and turn in the bowl to coat with oil. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and place in a draft-free area to rise. Let the dough rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.981', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.197');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be372a4e-f860-4bcb-8aff-45b39cd37310', 'While the dough is rising, prepare the glaze. Place all the glaze ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth, about 1 minute. Refrigerate until ready to use. The mixture will thicken slightly when chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.984', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.198');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8558627c-4838-4002-b30b-35c310e6ac68', 'Trim both ends off the lemon, then stand it on a cut side and use a sharp paring knife to cut off the peel, including the white pith; discard the peel. Cut the segments free from the membranes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.335');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('453bee02-b73a-4319-a96b-6cc08b5f3cf2', 'To prepare the sticky buns, line 2 rectangular jelly roll pans with parchment paper and lightly spray with canola oil spray. Gently punch the dough down. Roll out on a lightly floured work surface to form an 18- by 20-inch rectangle. (The dough will be sticky to work with.) Spread the filling mixture over the dough, leaving a 1-inch border on all sides. Beginning from a long side, carefully roll the dough up to form a long log. Slice the log into 18 equal pieces. Place the slices onto the prepared pans with the edges of the rolls lightly touching together. Fill 1 pan entirely before starting the next, so most rolls will fit snuggly together. Brush the tops with the melted butter. Cover with a damp kitchen cloth and place in a warm, draft-free area. Allow the rolls to rise for 40 to 45 minutes, until doubled in size.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.988', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.198');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2fa52a52-22a4-4c9d-94c6-20215e7cf8de', 'Preheat the oven to 375°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.992', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.198');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a71a032a-3466-4c38-9977-a18f6582ae98', 'When the rolls are fully risen, bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly golden. Let the rolls cool on the pans for 10 to 15 minutes before drizzling with the glaze. Pull apart gently to serve. Best served warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.995', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.199');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65cb1c4f-6105-49cf-abb9-095257c1ece4', 'Store the leftover rolls in the refrigerator and reheat in a 350°F oven for 10 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:30.999', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.199');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('22e045eb-6b5a-47ea-85f9-56f649ea5923', 'Combine tomatoes, red onion, parsley, olive oil, lemon juice, and serrano chiles in medium bowl. Season generously with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.003', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.199');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f9c6cf2-feaf-4577-926d-5111fd45bcfb', 'Purée frozen berries, corn syrup, rum to taste, and lime juice in a blender until slushy. Spoon into 6 (8-ounce) wineglasses or other stemmed shallow glasses and top with melon.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.007', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d6d9b90-7778-47db-8e2a-b2678b5c3d18', 'Sterilize four 8-ounce Mason-type jars.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.011', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('33c90370-b7eb-4486-afaa-4d88657bb2c8', 'Quarter and pit plums and cut into 1/4-inch pieces. In a 2-quart heavy saucepan stir together plums and remaining ingredients and bring to a boil over moderate heat. Lower heat and simmer mixture, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Pour chutney into jars. Wipe rims with a dampened cloth and seal jars with lids. Put jars in a water-bath canner or on a rack set in a deep kettle. Cover jars with hot water by 2 inches and boil, covered, 5 minutes. Transfer jars with tongs to a rack and cool completely. Store chutney in a cool, dark place.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.015', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bb82960b-2009-4408-ab95-c8c0d6e7b099', 'Purée 1/2 cup (packed) flat-leaf parsley (leaves and stems), 4 kale leaves (center ribs removed), 1 cup frozen organic berries (such as strawberries or raspberries), 1 banana (cut into pieces), 1 teaspoon ground flaxseed, and 1 cup water in a blender until smooth (add water if too thick).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.019', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.2');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2aedb3b-c3ca-4cc1-8b2e-d0f7ce922c40', 'In a medium pitcher, make a thick paste by stirring together the sugar, ginger, cardamom, lime juice, salt, and a small splash of the sparkling water. Stir until any lumps have dissolved. Add more water, a little at a time, stirring all the while. The mixture will get quite fizzy, so just take it slow. Serve as cold as possible with as many ice cubes wedged into the pitcher as possible.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.022', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.201');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f3ef251c-10f9-4a4e-b25e-1436908ec381', 'Place the chopped onion in a bowl, sprinkle with the salt, squeeze the lime juice over, and set aside for 15 to 20 minutes. Add the chopped chiles, tomatoes, corn, and cilantro to the onion mixture, and stir. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.026', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.201');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7da32e37-c3d0-406e-8077-a7b38b95420c', 'Combine rhubarb, sugar, and 1/4 cup water in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Bring to simmer, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes. Simmer gently until rhubarb is tender but not falling apart, stirring occasionally, about 7 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in strawberries. Transfer to bowl and stir in mint. Chill until cold, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.201');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('738cebae-36ab-49cf-a03b-1ca7c01ac5d7', 'In a bowl whisk together oil and vinegar and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.033', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('88a7f4cc-72a8-41f4-b23e-5b80eb6e488c', 'Discard coarse stems from arugula. Thinly slice radicchio and cut endives crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. In a large bowl toss greens with vinaigrette until coated well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.037', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e8e0e11-0d2d-4a45-9ffb-9f230aa2a071', 'Place the sugar and mint in a saucepan with 1 cup (250 ml) water and slowly bring to a boil, allowing the sugar to dissolve. Let simmer gently for 5 minutes, then remove from the heat and allow to infuse for 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.041', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('70316250-4eb6-4f60-98bf-89efe741985d', 'Place the blueberries and bourbon in a food processor or blender, and pour over the syrup, mint sprigs included. Blitz until completely smooth. Pour into six popsicle molds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.044', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.202');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7342d6ff-8f16-4571-ba3b-22b71077d1d6', 'Place the molds in the freezer. Let set for 2 hours, insert the popsicle sticks, and allow to freeze until completely solid (about 4 more hours).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.048', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.203');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d26e9597-f03b-4d09-9a0c-10593e37cca9', '1. To prepare the marinade, put all of the marinade ingredients in a blender. Blend on high speed until well combined.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.051', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.203');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7fc93fc0-918a-4563-a014-bbabf03f52b7', '2. Put 4 pieces of seitan on each of 12 metal or bamboo skewers. Place them in a large non­reactive bowl or baking dish, pour the marinade over them, and let marinate for at least 1 hour or up to overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.055', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.203');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('59b385fe-1174-4f7e-be3f-f76019789870', '3. To prepare the Chimichurri Citrus-­Herb Sauce, put all of the chimichurri ingredients in a blender. Blend on high speed until well combined. Refrigerate until ready to use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.058', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.204');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d8f2161-791c-4334-b349-dfbc9f699283', '4. Prepare a charcoal, gas, or stove-top grill. Grill the skewers over medium-­high heat until well browned, about 5 to 7 minutes per side. Serve immediately, drizzled with the Chimichurri Citrus­Herb Sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.062', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8600f26-a924-4544-9689-1675f897323d', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and 1 tablespoon parsley; stir 30 seconds. Add artichokes and stir to coat. Cover skillet; simmer until artichokes are tender, about 12 minutes. Uncover; simmer until juices thicken and coat artichokes, stirring occasionally, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl; sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.065', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f78fcf8f-3f40-46ea-8253-e2b879e3c194', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and sauté until onion softens slightly, about 5 minutes. Add green beans, tomatoes, basil leaves, and 1/2 cup water. Cook until beans are crisp-tender, stirring and tossing occasionally, about 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.069', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.205');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6fe8a4f9-02d5-439d-b774-d56c133501c0', 'Bring strawberries, water, sugar, corn syrup, and salt to boil in large saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally and adjusting heat to prevent mixture from boiling over. Add lemon juice. Strain, pressing on solids. Cover and chill syrup. DO AHEAD Can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.072', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.206');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9cf82b9f-a6ac-480e-a60e-6ce6133d83a8', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Place beets in roasting pan and toss with 1 tablespoon oil, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Add 1/4 cup water. Cover pan with foil; roast beets until knife easily pierces center, about 50 minutes. Cool. Peel beets and cut into 1/3-inch-thick wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.076', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.206');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('52b27b86-742a-485c-82f6-67a8b5e6db3b', 'Whisk orange juice, pomegranate molasses, vinegar, and remaining 2 tablespoons oil in large bowl to blend. Season vinaigrette with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.079', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.207');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('881c3d3a-21a7-4716-9e96-63d1abedf130', 'Place onion in small bowl; cover with cold water. Soak onion 1 minute, drain, and squeeze dry in kitchen towel. Add beets, onion, orange slices, and pomegranate seeds to vinaigrette in bowl; toss. Season salad with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.083', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.207');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6f2109e-a68b-4ed2-ab27-09fb60639c4e', '*A thick pomegranate syrup available at Middle Eastern markets, some supermarkets, and by mail from Adriana''s Caravan (adrianascaravan.com).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.087', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.209');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bd3e878d-1a13-49f4-85ef-01a073dc907d', 'Combine plums and raspberries in large bowl. Combine wine, 1 1/2 cups water and sugar in large saucepan. Scrape in seeds from vanilla bean; add bean. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat and boil until reduced to 2 2/3 cups, about 20 minutes. Pour hot wine mixture over plum mixture. Cool. Cover and chill overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.09', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.209');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('353497a9-41d6-45bb-a876-5297ccdc2a77', 'Spoon fruit mixture into dessert glasses or bowls. Top with cream.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.093', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.21');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dccd1221-c8c0-496d-a232-a7aa03bf56e9', 'Place bell pepper, cauliflower, jicama, and chile in medium bowl. Bring vinegar, mint, sugar, and salt to boil in heavy medium saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cool syrup completely.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.097', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.211');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d7c533b0-1662-43c6-9d72-c334b0426bb4', 'Strain syrup over vegetables. Let stand at room temperature 2 hours. Cover and chill until ready to use. (Can be made up to 1 day ahead.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.101', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.212');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('258040c0-e187-45b7-a8b2-c5be6a0dd78b', 'Soak bread in a bowl of water 30 seconds, then squeeze dry and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.104', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.212');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('442d49b4-e8a6-4747-924e-8eac2fe8df8f', 'Drop garlic into a food processor with motor running, then drop in nuts and process until finely ground. Add bread and 3 tablespoons lemon juice and process until smooth. With motor still running, add oil in a slow, steady stream until incorporated. Transfer to a bowl, then stir in salt and pepper and lemon juice to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.108', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.213');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b969fc98-db72-47d2-9573-fe6ce0b8fe07', 'Remove any leaves from cauliflower, leaving core intact. Cut cauliflower into 1/2-inch-thick slices as if it were a loaf of bread, then cut slices into 2-inch pieces (some florets will separate).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.112', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.214');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e461167b-40fd-4a58-82e2-d3ee6975c5a6', 'Bring cauliflower to a boil with enough water to cover it in a 4- to 5-quart pot, then reduce heat and simmer until just tender, 4 to 6 minutes. Drain well in a colander and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.115', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.215');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65787324-f7cb-4784-9eda-49035200803d', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté half of cauliflower, turning over occasionally, until very well browned on both sides, about 8 minutes total.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.118', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.215');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6731bd3a-e499-47d7-a263-fd8c7865a86d', 'Transfer to a platter with a slotted spatula and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.121', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.216');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec51ff53-64d3-4840-a2eb-f4d795c79d9d', 'Wipe out skillet, then sauté remaining cauliflower in remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same manner, transferring to platter and seasoning.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.216');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dba20358-0283-4e94-839e-5c183928fc2d', 'Serve cauliflower, warm or at room temperature, with sauce and celery leaves (if using).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.129', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.217');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('db0b48d3-19d8-4d84-870c-70b09e978297', '1. Place the lentils, 4 cups water, turmeric, and salt in a large pot and cook over medium-high heat until the lentils are tender, about 30 minutes, frequently skimming off any foam with a spoon.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.133', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.218');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('350005f6-6114-4f00-8021-216c1e9393cc', '2. In a heavy-bottom pot, heat the oil over medium heat and add the curry leaves, stirring until very fragrant, about 1 minute. Remove 4 leaves and reserve for the garnish. To the oil, add the mustard seeds, asafetida, ginger, and tomato and cook until the tomato begins to dry, about 3 minutes. Add the lentils, 2 1/4 cups water, the coconut milk, tamarind, and black pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for another 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.136', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.218');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2370876-7e95-4995-a3d5-a79a420a3c28', '3. Season with salt and serve hot, garnished with the fried curry leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.14', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.219');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('180b9e6c-e285-48e2-812f-a1668fee6a09', 'Place onion in large bowl. Sprinkle lightly with salt and toss to combine. Let stand 10 minutes. Mix in tomatoes, bell peppers, cucumber, parsley and mint. Drizzle olive oil and lemon juice over. Toss vegetables with dressing to coat. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.143', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.219');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f0bff40f-5e51-434f-ab60-311f506b0b7a', 'In a blender puree tomatoes, white-wine vinegar, salt, and olive oil until smooth. Pour tomato mixture through a sieve into a bowl, pressing on solids. Yellow tomato coulis keeps, covered and chilled, 2 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.147', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.22');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d07f5e0-fc94-4b1f-ab89-0a69c8cd1c3f', 'Serve yellow tomato coulis garnished with halved tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.15', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.223');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2cf72e78-8ec1-4ee0-baa8-76179ab0377e', 'Cover eggplant with water in a bowl and add 1 1/2 tablespoons salt. Soak 30 minutes. Drain eggplant and squeeze handfuls to remove excess moisture, then pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.154', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.224');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bca3c317-4be8-480c-81e8-8f7984467282', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté eggplant, stirring occasionally, until tender and browned, about 7 minutes. Cool eggplant.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.157', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.224');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('45597cba-3b0b-4700-8850-b1f724e1813a', 'Cook onions in remaining 2 tablespoons oil in a 3- to 4-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until softened. Add rice and cook, stirring, 2 minutes. Add 1 1/2 cups water, raisins, remaining 1/2 tablespoon salt, and cinnamon and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered and undisturbed, until rice is tender, about 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.161', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.225');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3bbd75c9-e598-41ba-a335-b0395dbe8648', 'Fluff rice with a fork and gently stir in tomato and eggplant. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Uncover and cool 10 minutes. Stir in dill, then transfer pilaf to a serving bowl or platter and sprinkle with pistachios.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.164', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.225');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('328fee90-16d7-48e8-87f0-5eb5e1a0034a', 'Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion; sauté until tender, about 5 minutes. Add next 4 ingredients; stir 1 minute. Add zucchini and tomatoes with juices; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until zucchini is tender, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Add garbanzos and olives; simmer 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.168', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3984e29f-6e5c-4132-90e4-97d57e0fc208', 'Feed the lemon segments, apple, celery, kale, and parsley through a juicer. Stir in the turmeric and serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.382', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.336');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d17f78c-2c10-43dc-be69-9aa50e5f5642', 'Slice zucchini very thinly with slicer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.386', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.336');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('af1927f6-b4b0-4eb2-88ec-3b92d49c7850', 'Preheat oven to 300°F. Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Working in batches, spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick spray; add 1 teaspoon oil. Heat over medium-high heat. Add potato mixture by 1/3 cupfuls, spreading each to 3-inch round. Cook until pancakes are brown, about 5 minutes per side. Transfer to baking sheet; keep warm in oven.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.171', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.226');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fe5375f2-978d-44ac-84b8-c22c05228f1a', 'Place 3 pancakes on each of 4 plates. Spoon stew over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.175', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.227');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa1f83ec-eaef-447e-9519-2df0a72a1076', 'Parboil potatoes in a large pot of boiling salted water just until a paring knife slides into the center with some resistance, 15–20 minutes. Drain; transfer to a rimmed baking sheet and chill uncovered until cold, at least 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.178', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.228');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('01fff87f-c9f5-427f-a9f2-53d6fefe47d5', 'Place racks in highest and lowest positions in oven; preheat to 425°F. Line two 8" cake pans with parchment; brush with 2 Tbsp. oil. Toss onions, vinegar, and 1 Tbsp. kosher salt in a large bowl. Let sit until onions are softened, 5–10 minutes (massage gently to speed up process).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.181', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.229');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ead03c10-b903-4a8e-ae52-f8cf1efac1bc', 'Meanwhile, grate parboiled potatoes on a box grater or in a food processor, or cut using a julienne slicer. Place prepared pans on lower rack and heat 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.185', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.229');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f46f4dc-4b2e-4c47-b9d1-d2132c3d9b7a', 'Add potatoes to onion mixture and toss to combine; season with kosher salt and pepper. Divide potato mixture between hot pans and press down as firmly as possible to compact (a thin flexible spatula works well). Place on lower rack and bake until potatoes are very brown around the edges, 45–60 minutes. Remove rösti from oven; let cool slightly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.189', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.23');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2c789a6c-8a79-4a00-8da7-5724a0e71c40', 'Heat broiler. Broil rösti on upper rack until tops are golden brown all over. Cut around sides with a small knife or offset spatula to loosen and invert rösti onto a wire rack set inside a rimmed baking sheet. Carefully remove parchment paper (if potatoes stick, let cool slightly). Brush top of rösti with more oil, sprinkle with sea salt, and broil until second side is deep golden brown.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.192', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.231');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('71da3622-995f-4d21-8634-2cf5e97e9646', 'Potatoes can be parboiled 1 day ahead; once cold, cover. rösti can be made 3 hours ahead; store uncovered at room temperature (or keep warm in a 250°F oven up to 1 hour). Reheat in a 300°F oven for 10 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.196', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.231');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6e982af-f59c-481c-8314-adf937af7276', 'In a small bowl stir together soy sauce, vinegar, gingerroot, and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Peel and finely grate carrot. Carefully drain and halve tofu. Put tofu on 2 plates and spoon sauce over it. Top tofu with carrot and scallion.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.2', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c618c2e7-f7d8-4cfb-947e-0092ea200b40', 'Cook kale in a 6-quart pot of boiling salted water , uncovered, stirring occasionally, until just tender, about 10 minutes, then drain in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.204', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.232');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('597ee65c-bd3d-431b-a3ed-071779883966', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then sauté onion, stirring occasionally, until softened, 6 to 8 minutes. Add garlic and red pepper flakes and sauté, stirring, until garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute. Reduce heat to moderate, then add kale and cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through. Remove from heat and stir in vinegar and salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.207', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eeface65-4ca4-4477-9b14-91a82fc7feb7', 'Cut 12 6-inch squares of aluminum foil and line 12 4-inch tart molds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.234');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0db45f14-403e-4f91-a1df-cd527552d966', 'Melt the chocolate in the top half of a double boiler or in a small bowl set over a saucepan of water. Place over low heat and stir often. When all the chocolate has melted, remove it from the heat and pour equal amounts into the lined molds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.215', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.235');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8f53f140-e1bd-4a46-877b-c10cf75a28f5', 'Let the chocolate cool for 5 to 10 minutes in the molds and then distribute the various nuts and raisins equally over the tops. If they sink, wait another few minutes and try again. The chocolate should be soft enough that the nuts and raisins adhere, but not so soft that they sink.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.218', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.237');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('80506f29-a518-4681-91dd-dbb8604f20bf', 'When the chocolates have hardened, lift them out of the molds and gently remove the aluminum foil. The cooling process can be speeded up by putting the candies in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.222', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.237');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('959e82e6-0cdb-4ea5-b550-16a7b6a6b5cd', 'Place the chocolates on a serving tray or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.225', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.238');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('541cd59e-fea5-4c41-9ac1-122992cdc369', 'In a blender, blend 2 cups of the cantaloupe, the sorbet, and the ice until the mixture is almost smooth. Add the remaining 2 cups cantaloupe, belnd the mixture until it is smooth, and pour into chilled glasses.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.229', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.238');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc2c9bc4-9401-4cf7-b31e-f2564cf2ad1a', 'Bring a medium pot of salted water to a boil. Cook beans until cooked through but firm, about 7 minutes; rinse with cold water. Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl; add beans and toss. Serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.232', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.239');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c4acc578-2127-4ce5-9135-b7271bda7afa', 'Bring granulated sugar, 3 cups water, and 1 tablespoon salt to a boil in a 1 1/2- to 2-quart saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then reduce heat to simmer. While water is coming to a boil, prepare chiles. Cut a slit from stem to point down 1 side of each chile with kitchen shears. (Some brands of chiles may be precut.) Add chiles to sugar water and simmer 5 minutes, then remove pan from heat and cool chiles in liquid while making escabeche and filling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.236', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.239');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('edc08aec-28ad-4c1e-a0ab-2d24a6d94a37', 'Cook carrot in 1/4 cup oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderately low heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Add allspice, thyme, marjoram, bay leaves, vinegar, piloncillo, 2 1/2 teaspoons garlic, and remaining 3/4 cup water, then bring to a simmer, stirring until piloncillo is dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt and half of onion.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.239', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.24');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b618e79b-06d5-4e5f-aca4-5e34d550d974', 'Transfer escabeche to a bowl and cool while making filling and stuffing chiles.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.243', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.241');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2556efda-d2ec-475f-b815-8c8174dea79f', 'Cut off ends of plantains, then remove and discard peel and cut plantains into 1/2-inch cubes. Cook remaining half of onion in remaining 2 tablespoons oil in cleaned skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until it begins to brown, about 4 minutes. Add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons garlic and cook, stirring, 30 seconds. Add plantains and cook, stirring occasionally and lightly mashing mixture, until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Stir in remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt and remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.246', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.263');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('80523281-e0c4-4f2d-9036-37e9bd86771c', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then fry zucchini in 3 batches, stirring occasionally, until softened and very pale golden, 3 to 4 minutes per batch. Transfer as fried with a slotted spoon to a baking pan lined with paper towels to drain. Keep zucchini warm, covered with foil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.389', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.337');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('edb04c59-f500-4ea7-aed1-ec5e22993550', 'Drain chiles in a colander. Cut off stems with kitchen shears and carefully scrape out all seeds clinging to seedpod and attached to veins with your fingers. Press 1 tablespoon plantain mixture into an egg shape, then stuff into a chile, molding chile around stuffing. (If chile is split in other places, arrange around stuffing and reshape chile.) Transfer chile, slit side down, to a shallow 2-quart glass or ceramic serving dish. Stuff remaining chiles with remaining filling, transferring to serving dish and arranging in 1 layer. Spoon escabeche over chiles and marinate, uncovered, at room temperature 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.25', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.267');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcd32777-0300-43b0-8400-dea27ea84066', 'In a large bowl combine the watermelon, the cantaloupe, the honeydew, the plums, the nectarines, and the grapes. In a small bowl stir together the sugar, the salt, and the lime juice until the sugar and salt are dissolved, drizzle the syrup over the fruit, and toss the mixture gently until it is combined well. Chill the compote, covered, stirring gently once or twice, overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.254', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9a5628e-95f1-4c6d-80eb-77b1c7f93ab1', 'Toss together strawberries, sugar, and Marsala until sugar is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.26', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('233be9c7-ded5-4e72-a950-4f089e1caab7', 'Let macerate at room temperature, tossing occasionally, 30 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.264', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.271');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c24c892-8336-4958-9ecc-9065e5f722de', 'Bring vinegar, brown sugar, cloves, star anise, salt, mustard powder, mustard seeds, peppercorns, and 2 cups water to a boil in a medium pot over high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.27', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.277');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68238398-68f5-4d4b-932b-9a0d05cdfb8e', 'Place squash in a heatproof resealable container or jar (divide among several containers if necessary). Pour hot brining liquid over squash. Let cool to room temperature, then cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.274', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.277');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cc6f6498-1443-406d-87ef-0f719982de18', 'Preheat oven to 475°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.277', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.304');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f9d82ed4-5732-457c-9b83-17d306b18c01', 'Halve lemons and scoop out flesh, keeping both flesh and peel. Cut enough peel into 1/4-inch dice to measure 1/4 cup. Put lemon flesh in a sieve set over a bowl and press with back of a spoon to extract juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.281', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.315');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f79ed49d-0397-41f0-a341-3bf73de9f2ae', 'Toss squash with 1 tablespoon oil and salt to taste in a large shallow baking pan and spread in 1 layer. Roast in upper third of oven 15 minutes, or until squash is just tender, and transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.285', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.315');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3175be2b-66bc-4319-9b78-6a0a44adaa24', 'Cook onion in 1 tablespoon oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until just beginning to turn golden. Add to squash.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.288', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.316');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('04ca8e28-8f7f-41bc-ae02-0df2b04f3dc3', 'Cook couscous with cinnamon stick in a large pot of boiling salted water 10 minutes, or until just tender, and drain in a colander (do not rinse). Add couscous to vegetables and toss with 2 tablespoon oil to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.292', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.317');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8ba7c875-3cda-4033-a7f7-5b2247885774', 'Add lemon peel and juice, parsley, nuts, raisins, ground cinnamon, and salt to taste. Toss to mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.296', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.317');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b91c50c-a6ce-4a0a-b46f-985c6e7502f4', '4 to 5 preserved lemons', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.3', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.318');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e0bf9e76-e1b1-4a59-bcf1-88853059406f', '5 lb. butternut squash, peeled and seeded', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.303', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.318');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cfd91136-56b1-44b6-aaf7-abf649e23e75', '3/4 to 1 cup olive oil', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.307', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.323');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e8cddb4d-405f-4ad5-87e0-7286fdad9ac3', '3 cups chopped onion', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.31', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.323');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4cc96f94-a9f9-4942-aa55-38c6523dd847', '7 cups Israeli couscous or acini di pepe (tiny peppercorn-shaped pasta), about 3 lb.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.314', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.324');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f4553141-9860-4be9-a286-631a90ae1457', '4 (3-inch) cinnamon sticks', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.318', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.324');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9a4b1b8a-92dc-470c-925f-754b8ae006ab', '3 cups chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.321', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.325');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e381a36f-3941-4851-8016-cc13c7fbcd07', '2 cups pine nuts, toasted', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.325', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.325');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('24acc170-5fb8-4404-a410-ae60a16b8472', '2 cups golden raisins', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.328', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.326');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12add042-4491-49f8-bedb-58a34879f69d', '1 teaspoon ground cinnamon', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.326');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da5662e4-974e-424e-87c9-dd2e460fcfa2', 'Halve lemons and scoop out flesh, keeping both flesh and peel. Cut enough peel into 1/4-inch dice to measure 1 cup. Put lemon flesh in a sieve set over a bowl and press with back of a spoon to extract juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.336', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.327');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c011fb7-0191-438a-8f9b-5695b0519d66', 'Cut enough squash into 1/4-inch dice to measure about 12 cups and toss with 1/3 cup oil and salt to taste. Roast in single layers in batches in your largest shallow baking pan in upper third of oven 15 minutes, or until just tender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.339', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.33');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d65fb0f1-7db4-4b5c-87b3-77bfe703c77c', 'Cook 1/2 of onion in 3 tablespoons oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until just beginning to turn golden. Add to squash. Repeat with remaining onion and more oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.343', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.33');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fda5548b-21a4-4eaf-9cdb-9bdfefe39d62', 'Cook couscous with cinnamon sticks in an 8-qt. pot of boiling salted water 10 minutes, or until just tender, and drain in a colander (do not rinse). Toss couscous with 3 tablespoons oil in a large bowl. Add squash, onion, lemon peel and juice, and remaining ingredients. Season with salt (you''ll need a lot) and toss to mix well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.346', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.331');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9ac9d0db-ba60-4071-818f-182593532fdc', 'Stir together all ingredients and a pinch of salt in a heavy medium saucepan and cook, covered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until plums fall apart, about 25 minutes. Discard cinnamon stick and zest. Purée in batches in a blender until very smooth (use caution when blending hot liquids). Force purée through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, discarding solids. Cool, uncovered, then chill, covered, until cold, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.35', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.331');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('57fa026b-2cf4-4fc2-9855-7878af2feedd', 'Freeze purée in ice cream maker, then transfer sorbet to an airtight container and put in freezer to harden, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.353', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.332');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a647cdb3-b403-4c4f-a59e-cd9356c1fe91', 'Preheat oven to 450°F with rack in middle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.357', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.332');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('293172f5-b675-4c3c-a041-1294da8453a3', 'Prick sweet potatoes in several places with a fork, then bake on a foil-lined baking sheet, rotating potatoes halfway through baking, until very soft, 45 minutes to 1 hour. When cool enough to handle, halve sweet potatoes and scoop flesh into a bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.361', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.333');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cfaa2aee-e127-4add-90b5-f71ae58d93e3', 'Meanwhile, bring coconut milk, brown sugar, and 1 teaspoon salt just to a simmer in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.364', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.333');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f3f9680a-8a52-44cd-af10-c0577f16e12d', 'Stir into warm sweet potatoes, then pulse in batches in a food processor until smooth. Season with salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.368', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.334');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c96c41c-a706-45ce-885e-0a163c2f0e96', 'Bring water, sugar, and ginger to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan, then stir until sugar is dissolved. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, then remove from heat and let steep 15 minutes. Pour ginger syrup through a sieve into a bowl, discarding ginger. Chill, covered, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.371', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.334');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1de7a861-290b-4808-95e6-09e9de705563', 'Add garlic to oil in skillet and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until very pale golden, about 30 seconds. Remove skillet from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.393', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.337');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2eaaef53-f8ba-46b5-b139-dbb12e400936', 'Cook pasta in a 6- to 8-quart pot of boiling salted water , uncovered, until al dente. Reserve 1 cup pasta-cooking water. Drain pasta in a colander and transfer to a large shallow bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.397', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.338');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e4e9c3a6-2a4f-4471-80cf-2d7c4fbc72b4', 'Toss pasta with garlic oil, zucchini, mint, zest, salt, and pepper. Add some of reserved cooking water to moisten if necessary.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.401', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.338');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dc9aa304-cbbf-4d0f-8210-0147381d9ee5', 'Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Season relish with salt and pepper. Let stand at least 30 minutes. (Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover and chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.405', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.339');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78ee44df-205d-45dd-9b54-ddd9e663c1d6', 'Mix 2 tablespoons toasted sesame seeds, 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt, and 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper in a small bowl; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.409', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.339');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1ca278bb-b596-4ed7-b587-604c48b301e8', 'Cook 6 cups mung bean sprouts (about 12 ounces) in a large pot of boiling salted water until soft but not mushy, 3-4 minutes. Drain well. Transfer to a medium bowl. Add 2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil; toss to coat. Season with sesame mixture and gochugaru (coarse Korean red pepper powder). (Serve remaining sesame mixture with Bibimbap .)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.412', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.34');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('96d52e21-c0de-46a9-9433-151350248c11', 'Stir together all ingredients in a heavy medium saucepan until sugar has dissolved. Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, gently stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced by half, about 25 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.416', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.34');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dedf2a80-d018-499c-aba9-6e4c901be056', 'Remove from heat and cool until barely warm or room temperature. Discard vanilla bean.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.42', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.34');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('16180081-257a-490e-a4f9-3a0bc5f18925', 'Arrange tomatoes on a lightly greased jelly-roll pan and brush with 1 tablespoon oil. Season tomatoes with salt and pepper and broil about 4 inches from heat 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.424', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.341');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('de35c8c6-c7c9-4768-97a6-921555a88163', 'In a bowl toss together corn, okra, remaining 1/2 tablespoon oil, and salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.428', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.341');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('911fdf5b-9e04-4325-bb2c-5e55de65127e', 'Spread corn and okra evenly on pan with tomatoes and broil about 4 inches from heat until tender, about 5 minutes. In a bowl toss vegetables gently with basil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.432', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.341');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e45e6043-593f-4595-a0e8-790573802271', 'Place eggplants on double thickness of paper towels. Salt generously. Let stand 1 hour. Pat dry with paper towels. Cut 2 deep incisions in each eggplant. Using tip of knife, push 1 mint leaf and 1 garlic sliver into each incision.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.436', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.342');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('283e3081-32e5-4274-97c0-0e806dd0ec1c', 'Pour 2 cups oil into heavy medium saucepan and heat to 375°F. Add eggplants in batches and fry until deep golden brown, turning occasionally, about 4 minutes. Transfer eggplants to paper towels and drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.439', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.342');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('299fc618-debe-4d3a-9147-98c7831feba9', 'Blanch tomatoes in pot of boiling water for 20 seconds. Drain. Peel tomatoes. Cut tomatoes in half; squeeze out seeds. Chop tomatoes; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.443', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.342');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0054aca8-712a-4bd4-a148-4f625264c735', 'Heat 4 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil in large pot over high heat. Add 2 flattened garlic cloves; sauté until light brown, about 3 minutes. Discard garlic. Add onion; sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add reduced to 3 cups, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.447', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.343');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef9f4a4c-9903-4550-b54a-60772949554f', 'Mix capers and 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil into sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat. Add eggplants. Simmer 5 minutes, spooning sauce over eggplants occasionally. Spoon sauce onto platter. Top with eggplants. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.45', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.343');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('377d92ee-b956-4a99-a904-323652fa32f0', 'Cut peel, including all white pith, from 2 grapefruit with a sharp knife. Cut segments free from membranes, letting them fall into a medium-mesh sieve set over a bowl. Squeeze juice from membranes into sieve, then discard membranes. Transfer grapefruit segments to a heatproof bowl and chill, uncovered, while making syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.454', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.343');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8555dfa3-eb3f-49d9-9f4e-c15398fa285a', 'Squeeze juice from remaining grapefruit through sieve into bowl. Stir together 1 cup juice (reserve remainder for another use), 2 tablespoons sugar, and a pinch of salt in a nonreactive 10-inch heavy skillet and boil over moderately high heat, swirling skillet occasionally, until reduced to about 1/2 cup, about 4 minutes. Stir in Campari and sugar to taste, then immediately pour hot syrup over chilled grapefruit. Chill, uncovered, 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.457', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.345');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89a616d1-301f-4e96-b757-7cca0085a41d', 'Place lima beans in large bowl with enough water to cover by 5 inches. Soak overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.461', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.346');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a12efa85-cde1-4b92-b6d0-57678c15ec80', 'Bring 2 cups water and dried mushrooms to boil in small saucepan. Using slotted spoon, transfer mushrooms to medium bowl; reserve liquid in saucepan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.464', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.346');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5e0c0777-4081-4836-ba68-a21fc942e724', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; sauté until onion is tender, 10 minutes. Drain beans; add to pot. Pour in mushroom liquid, leaving sediment behind. Add 6 cups water. Bring to simmer; skim foam from top. Stir in red pepper and thyme. Simmer partially covered until beans are tender, 45 minutes. Season with salt. Chop mushrooms; add to pot. Simmer uncovered over medium heat until beans and mushrooms are very tender, stirring occasionally and adding water to thin as needed, about 15 minutes longer. DO AHEAD: Can be made 3 days ahead. Cool, then cover and chill. Rewarm beans before continuing.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.468', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.346');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1aebe022-f6ea-4da9-99f4-940870ba60be', 'Add chard to beans. Cover pot; cook until chard is tender, stirring often, about 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.471', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.347');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e6bb3a6-373f-4f17-b1ed-08ff29a7620e', 'Preheat the oven to 200°F. Bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil. Using a paring knife, mark a shallow X on the bottom of each tomato. Add to the boiling water for 3 to 4 seconds. Immediately transfer to an ice bath and, once cool, remove the skins with a paring knife, being careful not to cut into the flesh. Toss the peeled tomatoes in the olive oil, salt, and sugar. Place on a rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 1 1/2 hours, until the tomatoes are slightly shriveled and about one-quarter of their original size. Cool to room temperature and refrigerate in an airtight container for up to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.482', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.347');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('888a19d5-c5f7-49bf-98ba-fe5ac59065ac', 'Stir together confectioners sugar, cornstarch, panko, and salt in a wide shallow bowl. Cut eggplant crosswise into paper-thin rounds with slicer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.488', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.347');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('85287438-371b-4af8-a353-c4a23b3cf340', 'Fill a deep 10- to 12-inch heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron) halfway with oil and heat over moderate heat until it registers 360°F on thermometer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.492', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.348');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1091e00b-4e97-4d13-a0c9-69009366bb96', 'Dredge one fourth of slices in cornstarch mixture, tossing until thoroughly coated and lightly pressing to help coating adhere, then gently shake in sieve to remove excess.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.495', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.348');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47104705-02fb-47e3-8b8f-c78f0091e676', 'Fry coated slices in oil, turning and separating with a slotted spoon, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes. Transfer eggplant chips with a wire-mesh or slotted spoon to paper towels to drain, then season lightly with salt. Coat and fry remaining slices in 3 batches in same manner, returning oil to 360°F between batches. Chips will crisp as they cool. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.499', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.348');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5249b80c-71ba-41bc-bb82-13af5e46f092', 'Gently toss together all ingredients with salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.502', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.349');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b619dbd9-7b5f-42b6-8c72-668db9a07258', 'Place asparagus in a medium bowl, add ice water to cover, and swirl asparagus with your hands. Drain through a fine-mesh sieve and return asparagus to bowl. Repeat process 2 more times (this will keep asparagus crunchy). Pat dry; wipe out bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.506', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.349');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5398357-7543-4f92-b4bf-359e800f5f0b', 'Toss asparagus, scallions, lemon zest, garlic, cilantro, vinegar, and chile in dry bowl to combine. Add salt and sugar and toss again to combine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.51', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.35');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a1a6cac-3089-436f-b4db-5bd48c13f7a8', 'In a medium saucepan over medium heat, cook the shallots and sugar, stirring constantly, until the shallots start to soften and brown, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and combine the caramelized shallots, vinegar, and oil in a blender and mix until well blended. Season with salt and pepper. Chill for at least an hour before using. Use immediately or keep for up to 2 weeks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.513', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.35');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a7c12f74-3435-47e0-a62a-1062878a5497', 'Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss chiles, bell peppers, oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar, coriander, and cumin in a large bowl. Season to taste with black pepper and toss to coat evenly. Arrange peppers in a single layer in a large roasting pan, overlapping as needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.517', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.351');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('84a8da04-c8b2-4439-bbba-05310a9912ce', 'Roast until peppers are soft and edges begin to brown, about 1 hour. Transfer to a large bowl. Halve, pit, and slice nectarines; add to warm peppers. Add lemon juice and toss to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.52', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.351');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e9c34e5d-fa71-4453-bd39-355744742953', '1. Combine the sugar and 3/4 cup (180 ml) water in a medium saucepan. Bring them to a boil, stirring often to dissolve the sugar. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cover. Simmer until the syrup is lightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove the saucepan from the heat. Stir in the mint sprigs, and let the pan stand, uncovered, until the syrup is completely cooled. Drain the syrup in a wire sieve over a bowl, squeezing the mint between your fingertips to extract the very last drops; discard the mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.523', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.352');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6192224f-2e04-41e6-9798-328da7d04ceb', '2. Purée the watermelon in a food processor or blender. (If you wish, leave some of the watermelon in tiny chunks that are small enough to fit into the mold.) Pour the purée into a bowl. Stir in enough of the mint syrup to make a very sweet mixture (see Tips). Stir in the sliced mint. Divide the purée evenly among the eight ice pop molds, leaving a little clearance at the top of each mold to allow for expansion. Cover the molds with the lids (adding wooden sticks, if needed).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.527', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.352');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3172ab92-9a72-42e5-91b8-a08f18b48d94', '3. Freeze the pops until they are solid, at least 4 hours. (The pops can be frozen for up to 1 week.) To serve, run the bottom of the molds briefly under lukewarm water and unmold.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.531', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.352');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('399fbbb4-f804-4d01-9aaf-4c1cea9b5505', 'Place raisins, cherries, and brandy in heavy small saucepan and let macerate 30 minutes. Toast mustard seeds and aniseed in small skillet over medium heat until aromatic, about 2 minutes. Add toasted seeds to dried fruit mixture. Simmer over low heat until liquid is absorbed, stirring often, about 5 minutes. Add rhubarb, sugar, and lime juice. Simmer until all liquid is absorbed and rhubarb is soft, about 7 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer chutney to bowl; cover and chill. DO AHEAD Chutney can be made 1 week ahead. Keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.535', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.353');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23bef12d-0bda-40a0-b9e2-b733ff1a8841', 'Cook green beans in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 5–7 minutes. Drain, then immediately transfer to a large bowl filled with ice water. Drain again and pat dry.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.538', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.353');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5fef4c4c-9077-4a63-9770-970230b5c350', 'Meanwhile, zest lemons to yield 1 Tbsp. zest. Juice lemons to yield 1/4 cup juice, then slice any remaining lemons into wedges. Cut leeks crosswise into 4" sections, then thinly slice lengthwise into matchsticks.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.542', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.353');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d7fcd643-4196-42ff-923c-f0b338f4dcd3', 'Heat oil in a large deep-sided skillet over medium-high until shimmering. Cook half of leeks, stirring occasionally, until lightly golden brown and crispy, about 5 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels; season with salt. Repeat with remaining leeks; reserve oil in skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.545', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.354');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d51cb41e-514b-4e3f-8204-312a7e42a695', 'Cook green beans, pepper, lemon zest, and remaining 1 tsp. salt in reserved oil over medium heat, tossing occasionally, just until warmed through, about 5 minutes. Add lemon juice and toss to coat, then transfer to a platter. Drizzle about 1/2 cup oil from pan over; reserve remaining oil for another use. Top with leeks and serve with lemon wedges alongside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.549', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.354');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('969a6a01-b503-4cc7-8d0f-6e57f299ab75', 'Green beans can be blanched 1 day ahead; let dry, then transfer to an airtight container and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.552', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.354');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dde1283a-d752-4b21-9111-26b189d844d8', 'Whisk vinegar and mustard in small bowl; gradually whisk in oil. Season dressing generously with salt and pepper. Combine cauliflower, olives, and celery in large bowl. Add 3/4 cup dressing; toss to coat. Cover salad and remaining dressing separately; chill overnight.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.556', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.355');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b065982-ffd7-4101-a0b7-f57cefa53ac9', 'Mix green onions and parsley into salad. Arrange arugula on platter; drizzle with remaining dressing. Top arugula with cauliflower mixture. Sprinkle with pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.56', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.355');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37900140-079d-4238-8520-8e86b138e38d', 'Arrange 1 rack in top third and 1 rack in bottom third of oven; preheat to 300°F. Line 2 rimmed baking sheets with parchment. Toss oats, almonds, and cinnamon in large bowl. Whisk oil, maple syrup, 1/2 cup hot water, both extracts, and sea salt in medium bowl. Drizzle over dry ingredients; toss to coat. Divide mixture between sheets, spreading in even layer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.564', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.356');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a670c189-8152-4210-9e79-b73fd0ce5792', 'Bake granola 20 minutes. Stir granola; reverse sheets and bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes longer. Transfer granola on sheets to racks. Sprinkle dried fruit over and cool completely, stirring occasionally. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 week ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.567', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.356');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0bf97340-107c-4dc9-8ab0-7d7b8f5c05cd', 'Toast almonds in a large dry skillet over medium heat, tossing occasionally, until lightly browned, 8–10 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl. Wipe out skillet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.571', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.356');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be23412d-32f5-4761-88d3-137512bef376', 'Meanwhile, working in batches if needed, pulse cauliflower in a food processor fitted with blade, or grate using the largest holes of a box grater until rice-like in texture (you should have about 4 cups).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.575', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.357');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0c9ee4ef-8648-4c53-9d78-db2f11508a32', 'Whisk broth and honey together in a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.578', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.357');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5bfc3441-80f7-4b27-90a8-89361876be88', 'Heat oil in same skillet over medium-high. Add cumin, turmeric, paprika, and cinnamon and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Immediately add cauliflower and stir to coat. Season with salt and pepper and cook, stirring, until cauliflower is softened, 3–5 minutes. Add broth mixture, currants, and apricots; stir to combine. Cover and continue to cook until just tender, 3–5 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.582', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.358');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f35bc9f5-b8bb-4cda-b12d-290c037469ca', 'Transfer cauliflower mixture to a serving platter and stir in half of almonds. Top with remaining almonds before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.585', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.358');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff31c522-c724-4b34-a130-8ad01dec0ecc', 'Put basmati and cold water in a 3-quart microwave-safe dish and cook on high, uncovered, 15 minutes, or until steam holes appear in rice. Cover dish and cook on high 5 more minutes. Let rice stand, covered, 5 minutes and fluff with a fork. You''ll note that using the microwave shaves only five minutes off the traditional stove-top method, but faster is not the issue here. Better is.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.358');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4823b8f6-61d9-49c2-9ff5-586e05a92e04', 'Place cabbage in very large bowl. Add vinegar, cilantro and oil; toss. Season with salt and pepper. Cover; chill at least 1 hour and up to 3 hours, tossing often.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.592', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.358');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3c826357-d98b-45fa-9692-17ee03117464', '*Also known as sushi vinegar; available at Asian markets and in the Asian foods section of some supermarkets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.596', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.359');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('448cd78b-1caa-427c-80ad-661f5859ae86', 'Char peppers directly over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Enclose peppers in paper bag 10 minutes. Peel and seed peppers, then cut into 1/3-inch-wide strips. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.6', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.359');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0cc7dfc3-b54f-475a-9611-0ab773e537ed', 'Working in batches, cook broccoli and broccoli rabe in large pot of boiling salted water until just crisp-tender, about 3 minutes per batch. Using large slotted spoon or strainer, transfer vegetables to bowl of ice water to cool. Drain well. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Wrap in paper towels; enclose in resealable plastic bags and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.603', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.363');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca28b76d-2232-43d6-b584-9e0bcf09364d', 'Heat olive oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic; stir until golden, about 1 minute. Add broccoli and broccoli rabe; toss until coated with oil and heated through, about 5 minutes. Add bell pepper strips; toss to blend. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to platter. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.607', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.366');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('863450c7-17ea-491b-944a-80c541e4ed88', 'Whisk vinegar and mustard in large bowl. Gradually whisk in oil, then mix in beets. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.61', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.366');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05fd74ea-c2ac-41e2-82c6-899c64a288c8', 'Whisk vinegar, soy sauce, and sugar in another large bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Mix in cabbage and mint. Season with salt and pepper. Let salads stand 30 minutes and up to 2 hours at room temperature, tossing occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.367');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9af70de6-3d03-4f28-9da3-7a44d9d7ef28', 'Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 425°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.618', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.368');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a8c23432-97c2-4bed-9811-ea4c68492e10', 'Arrange bread slices in 1 layer on a large baking sheet and brush top of each with 1 teaspoon oil. Bake until golden, about 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.621', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.369');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f0ea3d3-7af1-423b-8f0a-ce640d6664dd', 'Slip off skins from chickpeas with your fingers (discard skins). Blend chickpeas, water, oil, lemon juice, and salt in a food processor until very smooth (mixture will appear whipped).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.625', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.369');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('687a85d7-1999-4e71-93d3-37df55c51a9d', 'Spread toasts with chickpea purée and serve topped with arugula salad.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.628', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.37');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0f0075a4-b946-4485-9d9b-2058fd3c421b', 'Cook beans in large saucepan of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 4 minutes. Drain. Transfer to bowl of ice water. Drain; pat dry with paper towels.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.632', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.37');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68a61b25-0aac-4e22-ad6a-849581c2ddb8', 'Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 12 minutes. Drain; transfer to large bowl. Sprinkle vermouth over hot potatoes; toss gently and let stand 5 minutes. Whisk vinegar, shallot, and mustard in small bowl. Gradually whisk in oil. Pour over potatoes and toss to coat. Cool completely. Mix in green beans and parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.) Serve cold or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.636', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.371');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7c6dcc25-a43b-4db9-9099-b91038db822d', 'Drain olives if in brine. Combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 2 days, turning and shaking several times. Do ahead: Can be made 5 days ahead. Keep refrigerated. Transfer olive mixture to bowl and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.64', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.372');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9e070384-53e6-4a59-b7b4-3e3649f4a2e8', 'Heat oven to 350°F. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, toast 3/4 cup whole skin-on almonds until fragrant and light gold, 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool completely; transfer to a bowl. Fill a medium saucepan with 1 inch water; bring to a simmer over medium-low heat. Set a large heatproof bowl atop saucepan, making sure water doesn''t touch bottom of bowl. Place 10 ounces dark chocolate (60 percent to 70 percent cocoa) in bowl; cook, stirring, until smooth. Remove bowl from saucepan; add another 2 ounces dark chocolate and stir until smooth. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract, toasted almonds and 1/3 cup dried tart cherries, coarsely chopped. Pour onto baking sheet; spread into an even layer about 1/4 inch thick. Refrigerate until firm, 1 hour. Break into 24 pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.643', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.372');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa68a4b2-aaec-434c-8ccb-d0ee87cccaa4', 'Preheat the oven to 400°F. Cut the vegetables into 1⁄2"-wide spears and toss in a roasting pan with olive oil and herbs to coat. Keep the peels on; that''s where the vitamins are.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.647', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.373');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b385e63-83a2-422c-bd68-f94289be8de1', 'Roast for approximately 40 minutes, turning regularly until all sides have turned a golden brown and the fries are cooked straight through.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.65', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.373');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('38a5caa9-ea09-409d-858d-18eece3751f3', 'Heat 1/3 cup of the coconut milk in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and salt and cook while stirring until onion is softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the ginger, curry paste, and garlic and cook while stirring until well combined and fragrant, about 1 minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.654', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.374');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8d35f04e-9403-4e24-97b0-7b455ff42c5f', 'Add the carrots, 2 3/4 cups of broth, the lime juice, the 15 large cilantro sprigs, and the remaining coconut milk and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, until the carrots are very tender, about 30 minutes. Remove the cilantro sprigs and puree soup in batches in a blender, using the hot fill line as a guide.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.657', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.375');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e267636-dd31-4db8-a4ab-6c842e043f8d', 'Transfer the pureed soup to a clean saucepan and place over low heat. Stir in 1/4 cup of the chia seeds and simmer uncovered until chia seeds are fully hydrated and soup reaches desired consistency, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. (Note: If soup becomes thicker than you desire, stir in additional vegetable broth by the tablespoon to reach ideal consistency.) Taste and adjust seasonings, garnish with the remaining 1 teaspoon of chia seeds and small cilantro sprigs, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.661', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.375');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4e090e4e-b1f3-4a71-b855-093bf2b15975', 'Just before serving, dip molds briefly into hot water to release.', '2023-06-12 17:13:35.864', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.733');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c22d2b51-ad77-47ff-8ce1-3f3231921224', 'Whisk together oil, zests, juices, a rounded 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a large bowl until salt has dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.665', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.381');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c210a21-bbea-4fdc-b875-c47854f2c8f6', 'Add lettuce and radishes and toss. Serve topped with pine nuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.669', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.382');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2654ca37-2d1d-4d55-91e2-2b9f713a3138', '1. Combine the lime juice, garlic, agave or sugar, and salt in a large bowl and whisk to blend. Keep whisking as you drizzle in the oil until it is completely incorporated; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.672', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.383');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0aa3e35-d3d3-4c70-9ac3-187791805149', '2. Place a colander on a plate next to the stove and have a pair of tongs or a spider skimmer handy.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.676', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.384');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6e20932c-a895-4117-a02f-ea3e9141ec24', '3. Combine the coconut milk and water in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil. Add the noodles and cook for exactly 3 minutes (best to use a timer). Use the skimmer or tongs to lift them out (leaving the pot on the heat) and transfer them to the colander. (They will be noticeably al dente.) Shake the colander over the plate to drain and dry the noodles, then transfer them directly to the marinade in the bowl. Turn and lift with tongs and/or a fork to get them coated.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.68', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.384');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2dbcf470-a9b7-4869-9420-c1100a213754', '4. Return the colander to the plate (emptied of any water) near the stove. Add the green beans to the simmering water-coconut milk mixture. Cook them for about 5 minutes, or until just tender. Use the skimmer or tongs to lift them into the colander to drain. You can save the coconut broth to make a little soup snack for yourself.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.684', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.385');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b6dacbf8-36fa-4dca-ac53-8a5b565c028b', '5. Add the green beans (it''s OK if they''re still hot) along with the Pickled Red Onions to the noodle mixture, mixing gently until combined. (Use a fork to grab the onions, leaving their liquid behind.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.687', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.386');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e7a9b86d-586c-44cf-a59d-ace5020611e6', '6. Let the salad cool to room temperature, then add the cucumber and carrot. Cover and chill until serving time; the optimal marinating-chilling time is about 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.69', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.386');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f5b858b-939a-4a5c-a3ef-f47f7948ff89', '7. Stir in the mango, mint, and most of the cashews shortly before serving. Serve topped with the remaining cashews and any combination of the Enhancements.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.694', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.387');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1db76347-c4d8-49b4-9fa4-ab607f02df72', 'Minced jalapeño scattered through * Touch of lime zest mixed in to give it more zing * Lime wedges * Toasted unsweetened coconut on top * Minced fresh basil (regular or Thai) and/or cilantro on top * Chili paste or Sriracha on the side', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.698', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.387');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7ba40564-e11d-4570-90f5-2ee3e5b0b637', '1. Dissolve the salt in the water, and add the coriander, fennel, and dill. Set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.701', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.388');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('409dd888-cc67-42c0-9417-5acd0a659ee2', '2. Scrub the cucumbers well, rubbing off any spines. Cut away a thin round from the stem and blossom ends, and slice lengthwise into quarters. Put the spears in a large bowl, and cover with the brine. Weight the cucumbers with a plate, cover the bowl with a kitchen towel, and set aside for 24 hours. If the bowl won''t fit in your refrigerator, it''s fine to leave it out at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.705', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.388');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ce92820e-30da-49d2-9444-9eab0b801a2f', '3. The next day, pack the cucumber spears into two scalded quart jars, saving the brine. Measure out 2 cups of the brine and reserve. Strain the remaining brine through a fine sieve to capture the aromatics, and divide them between the jars. Tuck a dill head and two cloves of garlic into each jar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.708', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.388');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('65b5d851-4075-4ea8-8086-c0c3a08a3be3', '4. Mix the vinegar and the 2 cups reserved brine, and bring to a boil. Pour it over the pickles to cover. Seal the jars, and store in the refrigerator for a week before using. For long-term shelf storage, leave 1/2 inch headspace when filling the jars, then seal. Process in a boiling-water bath for 10 minutes, or in a hot-water bath, between 180 and 185 degrees, for 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.712', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.389');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3696e330-d302-4707-b7ff-b88131e787b3', 'Whisk together scallions, chile, juice, oil, and vinegar in a large bowl and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.716', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.39');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcb2bd6d-5d78-4671-8307-4e010a5f5944', 'Cut chayote halves lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick slices and arrange in 1 layer in two thirds of a lightly oiled shallow baking pan. Put bell pepper quarters, skin sides up, in other third of pan. Roast in middle of oven, uncovered, until chayote is browned in spots and bell pepper skins are blistered, about 30 minutes. Immediately add chayote to dressing and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.719', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.39');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1fba033c-8354-4bf7-a0d0-5d5b2dbe0d50', 'Transfer hot bell peppers to a small bowl. Cover and let stand 10 minutes, then peel. Cut bell peppers into 1/4-inch-thick strips and add to chayote with any pepper juices accumulated in bowl. Add lettuce and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.723', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.391');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e58a0ae0-8ab5-4c61-87fe-e6259d80c8ad', 'Cook spaghetti in a 6- to 8-quart pot of boiling salted water until al dente. Drain in a colander, then rinse well under cold water and transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.726', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.392');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5d9f8cda-40f1-4d1c-959f-c72818affdc1', 'Heat vegetable oil with red pepper flakes in a small saucepan over moderate heat until hot, then whisk in coriander, ginger, soy sauce, and salt (sauce will sizzle). Add sauce to spaghetti along with remaining ingredients and toss until combined well. Serve at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.73', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.394');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5551a251-79e8-4e4a-b107-443451a679c2', 'Bring sugar, water, and dried apricots to a boil in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and let stand until apricots are softened, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.733', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.395');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d481d8b4-89c5-4213-aca7-02e8ead9910a', 'While dried apricots are standing, roast whole fresh apricots in a small roasting pan in middle of oven until soft, about 1 hour. Cool in pan, then peel and pit when cool enough to handle.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.737', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.396');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dfc9300d-6bc6-41ed-9940-efeb64db440a', 'Purée dried apricot mixture, roasted apricots, lemon juice, and almond extract in a blender until very smooth, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Force purée through a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing hard on solids and then discarding them. Chill purée, covered, until cold, at least 2 hours.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.74', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.397');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a5fc4624-5470-4f8b-96e0-b7c144c1ceae', 'Freeze in ice cream maker, then transfer to an airtight container and put in freezer to harden.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.744', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.398');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6491fc1-de6c-477b-9d38-df84c5c21ac0', 'In a large deep skillet of boiling salted water cook the asparagus for 3 to 7 minutes, or until the stalks are tender but not limp, drain it well, and return it to the skillet. In a bowl whisk together the vinegar, the sugar, the oils, the chives, and salt and pepper to taste. Pour the dressing over the asparagus, shaking the skillet to coat the asparagus with it, and sprinkle the asparagus with the coarse salt.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.748', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.398');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6a8496d6-e4c3-42f1-8f20-774afe30bfb4', 'Place the sugar and water in a pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer gently until the sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes. Cool syrup to room temperature. Use immediately or refrigerate indefinitely in a covered container until needed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.752', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.398');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2bd583af-5ced-4665-8f4e-1fdf08aa8e2d', 'Ice pops can be made 2 weeks ahead. Keep frozen.', '2023-06-12 17:13:35.868', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.733');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8839ada1-dd73-40df-98de-5dcf1e33c4a9', 'Stir sugar and wine in heavy deep medium saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Boil over medium-high heat until syrup is reduced to 3/4 cup, about 8 minutes. Add cranberries; boil until berries begin to pop, about 5 minutes. Stir in pomegranate molasses and basil. Cool completely. do ahead Can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.756', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.398');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('16d02cc1-1a1f-41af-86fe-ffa982a12258', 'Stir in chopped cilantro and sliced mint. DO AHEAD: Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.76', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.399');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e82914a7-0bd1-43d3-a82f-768805dae199', 'A thick pomegranate syrup; available at some supermarkets, at Middle Eastern markets, and from adrianascaravan.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.764', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.399');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5eb0b741-4c97-4dba-ac8d-d601dfaa71f7', 'Place racks in top and bottom thirds of oven; preheat to 400°F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil. Toss squash with 2 tablespoons olive oil in a medium bowl; season to taste with salt and pepper. Spread out squash on prepared sheet and roast, turning occasionally, until tender and golden in spots, 18-20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.768', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.399');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('824088a0-29ff-4105-b4c9-904b50e7f7c1', 'Meanwhile, spread out hazelnuts on a small rimmed baking sheet and toast in oven until beginning to turn golden brown, 8-10 minutes. Let cool on sheet.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.771', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.4');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('874225b1-8c0a-464e-a2e4-03ce8e2036ce', 'Chop hazelnuts; place in a small bowl. Whisk in remaining 1/3 cup olive oil, hazelnut oil, vinegar, and sugar. Season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.775', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.4');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0e65556b-8e50-445e-8b92-a78ec5a62095', 'Place roasted squash and mustard greens in a large bowl; toss to combine. Drizzle vinaigrette over and season with salt and pepper; toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.779', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.4');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('40a3228c-e8d3-4eff-9270-b9851528711a', 'Chop tomatoes and in a food processor purée with vinegar, sugar, and lemon juice until smooth. Pour purée through a sieve into a bowl, pressing hard on solids. Discard solids. Stir in ice water and salt and pepper to taste. Soup may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Reseason soup before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.782', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.401');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5a56f602-0dd6-4c43-8ae8-36810ef7f866', 'Stir tarragon into soup and thinly slice cherry tomatoes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.786', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.402');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3588c681-f903-4d85-8708-0c2a735d861b', 'Serve soup sprinkled with tomatoes, zucchini, and onion, and with toasts on the side.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.79', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.403');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a54aa910-e8a7-48ad-b69e-7835f46e1691', 'In a large skillet, heat the olive oil. Add the onions, season lightly with salt and pepper and cook over moderate heat until they start to soften, about 5 minutes. Add the rosemary and continue cooking the onions until very soft and just starting to brown, about 10 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.793', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.404');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('960fde0d-8e02-4037-ada1-3a3546e1b96f', 'Add the balsamic vinegar and soy sauce and cook just until the liquid is mostly evaporated, about 1 minute. Remove the rosemary sprig and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.797', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.404');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f231bd70-1e26-4e46-af7f-b3398a3e38da', 'In a bowl stir together the plums, the onion, the coriander, the mint, the jalapeño, the lime juice, the sugar, some of the reserved marinade to taste, salt and pepper to taste.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.802', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.404');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2d5e39a-c397-4625-8982-df06fa21871d', 'In a cocktail shaker, muddle the cucumber until slightly broken up, about 20 seconds. Add the absinthe and let macerate for about 30 seconds. Add the gin, lemon juice, and simple syrup, then fill the shaker with ice and shake vigorously until completely mixed, about 20 seconds. Strain into a Collins glass (or any tall glass tumbler), top with tonic, and garnish with a cucumber slice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.806', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.404');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('efda4a00-6bc2-4754-882f-da3aa947d967', 'In a medium saucepan, bring the sugar, water, and red wine to a boil and let boil for 1 minute, stirring to dissolve the sugar. Remove from the heat and add the raspberries. Cover and let steep for 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.81', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.404');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('135df8e3-e598-47a0-a787-d76acbfee1ab', 'To purée the berries and remove the seeds, using a rubber spatula, press the mixture through a mesh strainer set over a medium bowl or pass it through a food mill fitted with a fine disk into a medium bowl. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.814', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.405');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91a397a9-71d8-4ddd-b33c-984daa3f6aeb', 'Freeze in an ice cream machine according to the manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.818', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.405');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ceb50008-2047-4aa5-abb4-04d83bdae016', 'For a lighter-tasting sorbet, use rosé in place of the red wine.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.821', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.405');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6df5c56d-a973-45f8-8ef4-e579e02f70ed', 'Start by making the curried cauliflower. Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C/gas mark 7). In a bowl, toss the cauliflower with the spices, thyme leaves and olive oil, mixing well. Transfer to an ovenproof dish and roast in the oven for 10-15 minutes, until lightly brown on top. Remove from the oven and set aside to cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.825', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.405');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aaae5215-02ef-4640-a278-ddd2e8b310e9', 'Place all the hummus ingredients into a food processor or use a handheld blender to process until smooth. If necessary, use a little of the reserved chickpea liquid to thin the mixture to a smooth purée. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.829', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.406');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('35950aa6-f94b-41a8-9faf-79af8b6171ec', 'To serve, spread the hummus on the bread and top with the curried cauliflower. Sprinkle the scallion (spring onion) on top and drizzle with the olive oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.832', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.406');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1e931f56-1e57-47cb-9260-dabebaa1abf1', 'Combine all ingredients for basic cranberry sauce in heavy medium saucepan. Add cinnamon, allspice, cloves, and nutmeg. Cook as directed for basic cranberry sauce . Cool to room temperature. Stir in ginger. Cover and store mixture as directed for basic cranberry sauce.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.836', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.406');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6254e2b2-688b-4002-83a5-c6cebb53de96', 'Put rice in a 3- to 4-quart heavy saucepan and, using your fingers as a rake, rinse under cold running water. Drain rice in a colander.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.84', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.406');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('90ad4c3e-65a4-484b-b41c-abd3aa6b5cb9', 'In pan bring water (4 cups for white rice and 5 cups for brown) to a boil with rice. Simmer rice, covered, over moderately low to low heat until steam holes appear on surface and water is absorbed, about 16 minutes for white rice and 35 to 40 minutes for brown. With a fork fluff rice and spread in a shallow baking pan. Cool rice completely. Chill rice, covered with plastic wrap, at least 12 hours. Rice may be made 2 days ahead and chilled in a sealable plastic bag.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.844', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.407');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a51e240c-efe4-4500-89fb-9319ed95adfb', 'Combine apples, blackberries and water in heavy large pot or Dutch oven. Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Cover, reduce heat to medium and simmer until fruit is tender, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Transfer to sieve set over large bowl. Press to force through as much fruit and liquid as possible. Discard solids in sieve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.848', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.408');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4ba394c2-7f26-486f-aa9a-8802c9dc9c22', 'Return puree to same pot. Add sugar and corn syrup. Stir over low heat just until sugar dissolves. Spoon puree into 13x9x2-inch glass dish. Freeze until almost solid, about 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.852', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.409');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2be332f2-a382-4642-8009-1455bf141d0b', 'Break up frozen puree into chunks. Place in processor; puree. Return to same dish; cover and freeze until firm enough to hold shape in spoon, at least 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.856', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.409');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('10308f97-b876-4f1e-8da7-b3fa058744bf', 'In a small bowl whisk together the vinegar and salt and black pepper to taste, add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified. In a large bowl combine the lettuce, the arugula, the carrot, and the bell pepper, drizzle the dressing over the salad, and toss the salad until it is combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.86', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.409');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('87fa2fb7-d1f2-4871-a86d-14bf43f2eca9', 'Toss celery, furikake, sesame oil, and soy sauce in a small bowl to coat. Chill uncovered 30 minutes to let flavors meld. Serve topped with sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.864', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.41');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('272b8618-057c-43d2-9771-09eacd084dd9', 'Preheat oven to 425°F. Spray large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick spray. Combine fennel, olive oil, garlic, thyme, and crushed red pepper in large bowl; toss to coat. Spread fennel out on baking sheet; sprinkle with coarse kosher salt and pepper. Roast fennel 15 minutes. Using tongs, turn wedges over. Continue to roast until tender, turning 1 more time, about 20 minutes. Sprinkle olives over fennel. Roast until fennel begins to brown at edges, about 8 minutes longer. Season fennel with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl and serve. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.868', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.41');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('25c79cda-5d54-48ec-80a7-012a651a5160', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.872', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.411');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c1681b76-7864-4345-b958-dc0c22d9ab8e', 'Soak noodles in a bowl of warm water to cover until softened, about 10 minutes, then drain in a colander. Cook noodles in a 3- to 4-quart pot of boiling water until tender, about 2 minutes, then drain in a colander and rinse under cold water until cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.876', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.412');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9f6ea2ff-032d-4dc7-9705-5cd1fb53206e', 'Blend tamari, sesame oil, sugar, and garlic in a blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.881', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.412');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec2c48a4-e3d9-4ea4-87e3-d93ac83d9597', 'Heat safflower oil in a deep 12-inch heavy skillet over high heat until it just begins to smoke, then stir-fry onion and carrots until onion is softened, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and stir-fry until softened, about 3 minutes. Add spinach and stir-fry 30 seconds, then add noodles and tamari mixture and toss to coat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid is absorbed, 3 to 5 minutes. Transfer to a shallow serving dish and serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.885', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.415');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6af69cfc-6a8a-4595-9a2a-b19ee85f3019', 'Whisk together mustard, shallot, sugar, salt, pepper, and vinegar in a small bowl, then add oil in a slow stream, whisking until emulsified.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.889', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.415');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa74b569-e03b-42b0-8cd5-a8ae6de59f36', 'Just before serving, toss salad ingredients with just enough vinaigrette to coat and season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.893', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.415');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3de934e0-78df-46c2-912a-119a8f6599cc', 'Combine sugar and 3 cups water in a 3- to 4-quart saucepan. Halve vanilla bean lengthwise with a paring knife and scrape seeds into pan, then add pod. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally until sugar is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.897', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.416');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b5883df-6f18-4416-8a36-e22671ac8b98', 'Add plums and simmer, uncovered, 3 minutes. Add apricots and tea bags and return to a simmer. Cook fruit, gently stirring once or twice, 5 minutes, then remove from heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.901', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.416');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('be3b0834-3a72-454e-acda-df9fa8a7da87', 'Allow tea bags to steep with fruit in syrup 15 minutes (fruit will continue to soften as it steeps), then remove bags, gently squeezing liquid from them into syrup. Transfer compote to a bowl or jar and cool, gently stirring occasionally.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.905', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.417');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('161d2c2f-baef-4244-851e-e83f039710ae', '*Available at nutsonline.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.909', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.418');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c9de3aff-09b8-4f68-8115-695a86bafae6', '**Available at apricot-farm.com.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.913', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.42');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8251927-d178-4c4c-b0fe-a93d9afed5a9', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add fennel, leek, bell pepper, capers and olives. Sauté until fennel is crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add arugula and sauté 1 minute. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.917', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.421');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29386d75-1f2c-4468-b07b-f44831f23bf5', 'Cut broccoli into 1-inch flowerets. Trim and peel stems and cut into 1/4-inch slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.921', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.421');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8863d3a4-d765-4523-8e02-78cf91aea97a', 'In a 10-inch heavy skillet heat oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking and cook gingerroot and garlic, swirling skillet occasionally, until just golden. With a slotted spoon transfer gingerroot and garlic to paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.925', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.422');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2e78d781-aeff-4075-bdbb-255b50fe2dc1', 'Add broccoli to skillet and cook, stirring frequently, until browned well, about 5 minutes. In a small bowl stir together water, soy sauce, and vinegar. Add mixture to skillet and cook until most liquid is evaporated, about 1 minute. Serve broccoli sprinkled with gingerroot and garlic.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.929', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.424');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dcc8ec13-9e86-4f0e-8012-2b410e7e9ba7', 'Cut each cantaloupe half lengthwise into 3 wedges (6 total). Shave thin slices from seeded side of a melon wedge with vegetable peeler (first slice may be irregular), stopping when you get close to rind. Arrange slices, overlapping slightly, on 1 plate. Repeat with remaining cantaloupe, putting slices from each wedge on a separate plate.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.933', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.425');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('063c575a-4607-4ce2-931e-bd464a465ac1', 'Drizzle each serving with 1/4 teaspoon lime juice and 1/2 teaspoon oil, then scatter 10 tarragon leaves on top. Season with sea salt and pepper and serve with lime wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.936', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.425');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff90a6a8-722f-46a0-b078-fa2f8de7128a', 'Cut off and discard top third of tomatoes and scoop out insides (leave shells intact for stuffing), transferring to a sieve set over a bowl to drain excess liquid. Coarsely chop tomato from sieve and reserve for making braised eggplant .', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.94', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.426');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5632951-1e34-4d52-9fe5-8a1fe6d569ff', 'Sprinkle insides of tomato shells with 1/2 teaspoon salt and drain upside down on a rack set in a pan while preparing filling.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.944', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.426');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('757bbe70-754b-41ec-a4fb-08fbd7a8a793', 'Simmer lentils in 1/2 cup water in a small saucepan until just tender, 18 to 20 minutes. Drain in a sieve, then rinse under cold water and drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.948', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.427');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d660898f-8983-44af-87f5-8266b9d92e9f', 'Heat oil in a 5-quart heavy pot over moderate heat until hot, then cook pine nuts, stirring, until golden, about 2 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.952', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.428');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('89594809-f8e6-4e39-add6-f88027ce1f65', 'Cook onion in oil remaining in pot over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until softened but not browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Add bulgur, chard, remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt, and pepper and cook, stirring, until greens are wilted, about 2 minutes. Add remaining cup water, then remove from heat and let stand, covered, until bulgur is tender, about 30 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.956', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.429');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('644cbbf1-6a24-4b88-ae9f-7592eb5f30e3', 'Stir in pine nuts, currants, parsley, dill, lemon juice, lentils, and salt and pepper to taste. Spoon filling into tomato shells.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.961', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.429');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d2b58f8a-7c75-405a-ba23-701c128e0a0f', 'Preheat oven to 250°F. Lightly oil a large sheet of foil on a baking sheet, then warm in oven.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.965', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.43');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('86a54ba8-1edf-4677-96cb-599b7c847aa2', 'Shake nuts in a coarse sieve to remove any nut powder (this will create a clearer brittle).', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.97', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.43');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d8ef00bc-39fc-4700-9611-a8c48cc24bee', 'Cook sugar and water in a deep 2-quart heavy saucepan over moderately low heat, stirring slowly with a fork, until melted and pale golden. Cook caramel without stirring, swirling pan, until golden. Immediately stir in red pepper flakes and nuts and cook, stirring, until nuts are golden, about 1 minute. Quickly pour onto foil, tilting baking sheet to spread brittle evenly before it hardens. (If caramel hardens too fast, put in a 400°F oven until warm enough to spread, 1 to 2 minutes.) Cool brittle on baking sheet on a rack until completely hardened, then break into large pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.973', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.431');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b195f275-2972-4ec0-86c2-df51136c5897', 'Combine 3 cups water and sugar in heavy large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add mixed dried fruits, white wine, orange, lemon, raisins, dried cherries, cloves and cinnamon sticks. Simmer compote until fruits are tender and liquid is reduced to syrup, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Mix in grapes. Cool compote to room temperature; cover tightly and refrigerate. (Can be prepared up to 3 days ahead. Keep refrigerated.) Spoon compote into stemmed goblets and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.977', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.432');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e3bb81da-0411-451b-a94a-c7117bc036a0', 'Puree 1 pound strawberries in processor. Transfer puree to heavy large saucepan. Mix in sugar, Vin Santo, vanilla extract and grated lemon peel. Simmer over medium-low heat until sauce is reduced to 2 cups, stirring often, about 15 minutes. Cool. (Sauce can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.981', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e1cc3a4e-fa68-49d3-aa94-e1bc58518da2', '*Vin Santo is an Italian dessert wine sold at some liquor stores and some specialty foods stores.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.985', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.433');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('45fa519f-fbc3-4d71-b904-96d3cdc095e4', '1. In a sauce pan over medium high heat, sauté onion, garlic and salt in olive oil under tender and transparent, about 5 minutes', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.989', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ffc66bb8-d7a5-493a-b5c1-a9e8c72674d4', '2. Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, olives and capers. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer for 10–15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.992', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.434');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0943bef1-5b27-4520-a9fb-9828adfdc01d', 'Crush 2 tablespoons hazelnuts; place in a small bowl. Whisk in orange and lemon juice, vegetable oil, and hazelnut oil. Season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:31.996', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.435');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fa58340b-b676-4f00-b88c-4633a65a3b7d', 'Thinly slice beets, turnip, carrot, and radishes using a mandoline or V-slicer. Place red beet slices in another small bowl and remaining vegetables and parsley in a medium bowl. Spoon 3 tablespoons vinaigrette over red beets; pour remaining vinaigrette over vegetables in medium bowl. Toss each to coat. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.435');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b7188364-d1de-4a3c-a7e6-ad3ba0b8d687', 'Arrange red beets on a platter; spoon over any vinaigrette from bowl. Top red beets with remaining vegetables. Drizzle salad with any remaining vinaigrette; garnish with remaining 2 tablespoons hazelnuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.004', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.436');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('30ee19a0-2626-4e89-b8d3-f3f2fff910e7', 'Combine rice, ginger, and 2 1/2 cups water in heavy large saucepan; sprinkle generously with salt. Bring to boil over high heat, stirring once. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 15 to 18 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.007', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.436');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a437217-c95c-40f8-a0a3-02990112156e', 'Meanwhile, heat peanut oil and sesame oil in heavy medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add green onions and sauté until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.011', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.437');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c6632e5b-efd7-4ec6-99ba-c37087bfaa34', 'Remove ginger from rice. Season rice to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Spoon rice into bowl. Sprinkle rice with cilantro and sesame seeds, then green onions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.015', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.437');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3a320a0a-e17d-4ee1-bdec-abfbd7dea650', 'Simmer chile in 2 cups water in a 1- to 2-quart saucepan, uncovered, turning over once or twice, until softened, 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer chile to a cutting board and discard cooking liquid.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.019', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.438');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0b19b48-4b5e-459d-88ba-870de6df83ad', 'When cool enough to handle, stem and seed chile, then carefully peel off skin in large pieces and reserve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.022', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.44');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b0948492-e53c-4025-b8b1-11121f3a8f46', 'Transfer chile pulp to cleaned saucepan and add sugar, 1/2 cup raspberries, a pinch of salt, and remaining cup water. Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.027', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.442');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bac379fe-4da7-4a1c-9b37-53ecb326f196', 'Remove syrup from heat and cover pan with lid, then let steep, covered, 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.03', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.442');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('992d06f4-0728-4b60-9dc6-9ea8bffcf986', 'While syrup is steeping, pat chile skin dry and cut skin into very fine threads with a sharp knife.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.034', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.443');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ebdac5b-a074-454c-83e2-570fa67f33ce', 'Pour syrup through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, pressing gently on solids (do not push solids through), then discard solids. Stir lemon juice into syrup.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.037', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.443');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('77c9efea-b47f-4970-a24f-d991f45be29b', 'Halve peaches lengthwise, pit, and cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Divide, along with remaining cup raspberries, among 4 shallow bowls and spoon syrup over fruit. Sprinkle with some chile threads.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.041', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.443');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1688e275-19f5-42d3-aa3e-e3f52da35c15', 'Preheat the oven to 350°F. Wrap the beets tightly in foil and roast them in the middle of the oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until they are tender. Unwrap the beets carefully and let them cool until they can be handled. Peel the beets, grate them coarse into a bowl, and stir in the apricots, the molasses, the onion, the oil to taste, and salt to taste. Serve the relish with pot roast or pork.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.045', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.444');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0ecd339a-0735-40b9-99ce-8bfe505c14e4', 'Warm vinegar, sugar, and salt in small saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves, about 1 minute. Stir in garlic and jalapeño. Cool. Mix in lime juice, sesame oil, and lime peel.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.049', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.444');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14d1a780-c16b-4d0f-b6c5-7bb2a3b9041a', 'Cook noodles in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain well. Rinse under cold water; drain again. Transfer noodles to dish-towel-lined platter to drain. Transfer noodles to large bowl. Add dressing and toss to coat. (Can be prepared 6 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.052', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.444');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c6696262-8701-483d-af5a-2c39bd549113', 'Add cucumber, mango, basil, and mint to noodles and toss gently. Arrange salad on platter. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Garnish with lime wedges. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and let stand at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.056', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.445');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3d9694e4-7fd2-4915-b4d1-ce7b2c591846', 'Trim green tops from beets, leaving 1 inch of stems attached (do not trim root end). Place beets in a large pot. Add water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until beets are tender, about 1 hour. Drain and rinse under cold water to cool. Peel and trim beets. Cut into quarters. Pack into a clean, hot 1-quart jar.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.059', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.445');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b53e4d66-13a7-434e-afb2-fa1ac089fef3', 'Meanwhile, bring vinegar and remaining ingredients to a boil in a small saucepan over high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat, cover, and let syrup steep for 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.063', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.445');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('50b9f344-f4e7-4d8a-b5e0-e9d9ef449873', 'Whisk together vinegar, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until salt is dissolved, then add oil, whisking until combined well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:33.768', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.615');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df655d47-8f74-46c8-9ee9-86f595ef8471', 'Remove star anise from syrup and return to a boil over high heat. Pour syrup over beets, leaving 1/2 inch space on top. Shake to dislodge any air pockets. Wipe rim, seal, and process jar in a boiling water bath for 30 minutes. Allow at least a week to pickle before eating.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.067', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.446');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1b38dca8-80c0-467c-9922-f7f6a9b47c5a', '1. Pick clean and wash the beans. Put them in a bowl and add water to cover by at least 2 inches, and let them soak for 8 hours. Drain and rinse the beans.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.07', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.446');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1208ccd1-8da6-49bd-a00d-e0809b7fc066', '2. Add the beans and 1 1/3 cups water to the container of a food processor or blender and puree them. The puree should be extremely smooth, light, and fluffy. Transfer to a large bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.073', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.447');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f5fabca0-9f8b-494a-8ee1-28a58c4f34db', '3. Line a sieve with a double layer of cheesecloth and put the cream of rice cereal in it. Hold the sieve under cold running water right in the kitchen sink. Rinse the cereal until no clinging starch is remaining and the water begins to run clear through the cheesecloth. Squeeze the rice cereal thoroughly of all moisture and add it to the bean paste. Beat the bean and rice mixture thoroughly. Add salt if desired. Cover the bowl with a kitchen towel or plastic wrap and place it in a warm place for 8 to 12 hours to ferment the batter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.077', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.447');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8934ad49-df05-4e11-9649-de7dbf517f16', '4. When you are ready to make the dumplings, stir the baking soda gently into the batter, using a rubber spatula. (Do not overblend as the batter must remain foamy and airy for the dumplings to come out light.) Let the batter rest for 4 to 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.08', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.447');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b764f2e3-3a74-4357-8f18-c64a44959357', '5. While the batter is resting, cut pieces of cheesecloth into neat rounds or squares to fit the depressions of the idlee dumpling racks. Each piece of cheesecloth lining can be used twice. Therefore you will need half as many pieces for lining as the number of dumplings. The cheesecloth pieces should be slightly larger than the depressions so that they overhang by about 1/3 inch.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.084', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.447');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ca8eedf9-2320-46d8-87ba-dee7372b4982', '6. Line the dumpling racks with the pieces of cheesecloth. Brush them lightly with oil. Bring water to a boil in the idlee steamer, a pressure cooker, or a 6- to 8-quart sauce pot in which the idlee racks fit.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.087', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ec9c0cdd-db12-4a7c-904d-2b5de078dc27', '7. Spoon about 1/4 to 1/3 cup batter into each lined depression of the rack. Attach the racks and place in the steamer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.091', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c82c6c0-6478-4404-87e7-577fc97b55f1', '8. Steam the dumplings for 12 to 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into them comes out clean. Remove the racks from the steamer apparatus and separate the dumpling racks. Pick up each dumpling with the cloth and gently peel away the cheesecloth. Place the steamed dumplings in another steamer or a covered dish to keep them warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.094', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('df335897-4aa9-443f-83fd-1374d01a9637', '9. Turn the cheesecloth pieces over and line the racks with the smooth reverse side up. Brush lightly with oil. Proceed with the remaining batter the same way.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.098', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.448');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a9286039-3585-4599-8b6e-c57462173413', 'To serve, place the dumplings (2 per person) in a rimmed soup plate or a shallow bowl about 5 inches in diameter. Make an indentation in the center of the dumpling with your index finger or with the back of a wooden spoon. Pour about 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons sesame oil in the depression and over the dumplings.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.101', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f03d3381-ac95-4973-a002-357c1c6495ab', '1. Pick through, clean, and wash the split peas. Put in a large saucepan. Add the turmeric and water and bring to a boil. Lower the heat and cook, partially covered, for 40 minutes at a low boil. Stir occasionally to make sure the peas don''t burn; when the peas are very soft, turn off the heat. Beat with a whisk for a minute to puree the peas. In a separate bowl, measure the puree and add enough water to make 6 cups of brothy puree. Return the puree to the pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.105', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2d81affe-7ed3-4cc1-9662-76bb9632455e', '2. Measure out the spices and place them right next to the stove in separate piles. Turn on the burner and bring the puree to a boil. Add the sambaar powder, the coriander, and the garlic and continue to boil the puree, partially covered, over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes. Add the onions, radishes, tomatoes, fenugreek leaves (if you are using ground fenugreek seeds, do not add them now), and salt, and continue cooking at a low boil for an additional 10 minutes. Turn off the heat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.108', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9bfee0d5-b8a6-459f-ae8d-62d131f692e3', '3. Heat the oil in a small frying pan over medium heat. When it is hot, add the chili pods and fry until they turn dark (about 15-20 seconds). Lift the pan off the heat, add the mustard powder and fenugreek powder if you are using it, and immediately pour the contents of the pan over the sambaar (the split pea mixture). Stir to mix. Cover and let the dish rest a few minutes so all the flavors will have time to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.112', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.449');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('47d11244-b3ac-455c-a40b-bcd91e250969', 'To serve, bring the sambaar to a vigorous boil, stir in the lemon juice, and pour it into a soup tureen or serve individually in katoori (small bowls). Serve the dumplings, idlee, 2 per person, in soup plates. Spoon sambaar over the dumplings as desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.115', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.45');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d3976c39-6f7d-4a81-aeeb-dccbe18ffb54', 'Measure the cold soy milk in a quart-size pitcher and season it with the mirin and soy sauce. Add the nigari mixture and stir gently to combine. Try not to create any foam as you stir.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.118', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.45');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9b154aab-e195-47bb-a0e1-072e66423dda', 'Choose between the autumn version and the spring version, then divide the mushrooms or the bamboo shoots and asparagus stalk among 4 to 6 heatproof 1-cup cups. Gently pour all but about 1 tablespoon of the soy-milk mixture into the cups, dividing it evenly. Leave the 1 tablespoon in the pitcher. Do not worry if some of the vegetables float to the surface, but do be careful not to incorporate air as you pour. Air bubbles will mar the final appearance of the dish, so bubbles on the surface of the soy milk should be lanced or dragged to the sides with the tip of a toothpick and removed.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.122', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.45');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f32acd17-d9d4-48c1-85df-dd7834a88ec7', 'Add the chopped mitsuba or sliced asparagus tip to the soy milk reserved in the measuring pitcher and set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.125', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.45');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('37ca7ef1-3fe8-41c1-9195-b8608dd94e3f', 'Place the filled cups in a flat-bottomed lidded steamer fitted with a cloth-protected lid. Set the steamer over medium heat. Once you hear the water boiling, turn down the heat to maintain a very fine flow of steam. Steam undisturbed for 8 to 12 minutes (the longer time for diced bamboo shoots or deeper cups). Carefully slide the lid to one side to check on progress. A bit of clear liquid should have formed at the edge of each cup. If there is none, insert a toothpick into the center of a custard. If the toothpick shows signs of loose soy milk residue, recover the steamer and cook for another 2 minutes. If it comes out clean, continue to the next step.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.128', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.451');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('eefcd05a-2ba9-40db-84ba-c21a3d506f7c', 'Transfer mixture to a large bowl and gently mix in millet, 1/4 cup basil, 3/4 tsp. salt, 3/4 tsp. pepper, and the remaining beans and corn until well combined. Form mixture into 4 (1"-thick) patties. Cover with plastic and freeze 20 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.294', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4722a130-7f05-4316-bde0-dd221754273c', 'Carefully arrange the soy milk-drenched mitsuba leaves or asparagus tips on the top of each custard. If you are skilled in using long chopsticks, this step will be easy to do and you will limit your exposure to the burning steam. If not, use tongs held with a pot holder to avoid burning your hands. Re-cover the steamer and steam for 2 to 3 minutes longer.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.132', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.451');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fc204ded-afd1-4be6-86a6-1dd42934c4c9', 'Turn off the heat (if using an electric range, remove the steamer from the stove) and allow the custards to settle undisturbed for 2 to 3 minutes. Use caution when removing the lid of the steamer to avoid burns from trapped steam. Retrieve the custards with pot holders and/or tongs.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.135', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.451');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9fad6a36-3272-4fba-9a0c-06c547649575', 'If you have lids for the individual cups, cover the custards as you remove them from the steamer. If you do not have lids and need to hold the custards hot for a few minutes, set a piece of parchment paper over each custard, being careful to balance it on the rim of the cup, and then anchor it with a saucer or other small, flat plate. Using foil to keep the cups warm is not recommended, because condensation easily forms on the underside and drips onto the custards, pockmarking them. Serve as quickly as possible, with spoons.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.138', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.451');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('397c31dd-aac3-4f48-bfca-47eb43dc56a1', 'As you remove the cups, set them on a rack to cool, uncovered. When steam is no longer visible, use strips of paper towel or cotton-tipped sticks to blot up any liquid that may have pooled on the surface. Cover the custards snugly with clear plastic wrap, place in the refrigerator, and chill for at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours. When ready to serve, remove the plastic wrap and serve with spoons.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.142', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.452');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8e20ffed-6002-4d41-a32b-7b7da308cde3', 'Combine all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan and bring to boil. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand until cranberries have absorbed liquid but are still slightly chewy, about 1 hour. Refrigerate until cold. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Keep refrigerated.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.145', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.452');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6b88fc3-0e37-4c49-988c-c99adfa1b02b', 'Stir first 5 ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add remaining ingredients; simmer until fruit is tender, about 15 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer fruit to bowl. Boil syrup in pan until reduced to 1/2 cup, about 7 minutes. Pour over fruit. Cool. Cover; chill until cold, about 3 hours. (Can be made 3 days ahead. Keep chilled.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.149', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.452');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('72786cb4-8c1c-48e6-a488-009aa11297f7', 'Char bell peppers over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Enclose in paper bag. Let stand 10 minutes. Peel, seed, and slice peppers.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.152', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.453');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('68d61e4e-82e1-4d7d-8aec-1146a7126edc', 'Toast coriander and cumin seeds in small skillet over medium heat until aromatic, about 2 minutes. Cool; grind seeds finely in spice mill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.156', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.453');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d89ec068-2244-4b35-903b-f3ea1f0574c9', 'Blend walnuts, oil, cilantro, chiles, bell peppers, and ground seeds in processor until just smooth. Season relish with salt and pepper. Chill up to 1 day.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.159', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.453');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('82747cf6-43af-4262-8a3c-ca4cb0fc69f2', 'Pulse first 8 ingredients in a food processor until very finely chopped. With motor running, slowly add oil; process until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Romesco can be made 1 week ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.163', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.454');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e302f187-3700-43a1-9fec-6203e125c629', 'Combine walnuts, 1 tablespoon water, sugar, cayenne, and kosher salt in small nonstick skillet. Stir over medium heat until water evaporates and nuts are dry and golden, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat; cool. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Store airtight at room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.167', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.455');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c3fbc64a-723e-4744-a1f3-bac83cf953ba', 'Whisk olive oil, vegetable oil, and vinegar in small bowl to blend. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper. Combine watercress, endive, and pear in large bowl. Add dressing and toss to coat. Sprinkle with nuts.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.17', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.455');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('598da249-9c2d-474b-9463-1fa53e455c85', 'Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.174', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.456');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('da520885-dfd8-4c48-bd2b-971ade671249', 'If using a flax "eggs," in a clean coffee or spice grinder, process the flaxseeds to a fine powder. In a small bowl, whisk together the flax powder and water. Set aside to thicken for 10 minutes, whisking occasionally; it should be thick and viscous and the consistency of a beaten egg.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.177', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.456');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bab57048-921c-40d7-bc66-c48ec9f5c7c6', 'In the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade, process 3/4 cup of the oats to a flour (a few tweedy bits here and there, without any whole oats in the mix, are fine). Transfer the oat flour to a large bowl. To the bowl, add the remaining oats, coconut, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, and baking soda. Whisk to blend.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.182', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.457');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8c577845-4d58-46ed-a314-58b34fc1cef2', 'In the food processor, combine the date paste, oil, maple syrup, and vanilla extract. Add the flax "egg" (or whole egg, if using) to the processor and blend until slightly aerated, 1 full minute.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.186', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.457');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f95fa817-c119-466a-b470-e5abfd82c9d8', 'Scrape the wet ingredients into the bowl with the dry ingredients and stir until the dough is evenly moistened. Fold in the dried fruit. Let the dough rest for 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.19', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.458');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2da64e5-5f29-4f0e-bc08-4cdedc3fdc30', 'Using a standard ice cream scoop, drop 9 quarter cupfuls of the dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them evenly. Use your fingertips to flatten each cookie to a 1/2-inch thickness-the cookies will not spread much during baking. Bake until golden, about 30 minutes. You''ll know they''re done when their fragrance fills the kitchen, and the cookies are set enough that you can lift one off the sheet to make sure the bottom is a deep golden color, though the centers will still be soft.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.194', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.46');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3391bdba-48a0-40e9-abe4-be0d5323d4a2', 'Cool the cookies on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Store in an airtight container for up to 3 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.197', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.46');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e40de916-76d1-4de1-912c-dfcb16e3d149', 'Preheat oven to 400°. Bring vinegar, 1/4 cup salt, and 4 quarts water to a boil in a large pot. Add potatoes and cook until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes; drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.201', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.46');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e2ec1842-3768-4b4f-92aa-7c40d1d2db61', 'Transfer potatoes to a large rimmed baking sheet and toss with garlic, rosemary, wine, and oil; season with salt and pepper. Roast potatoes, tossing occasionally, until completely tender and just beginning to brown, 35-45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.204', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.461');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2ae9d72b-1c1b-4dbd-bf72-523619961211', 'Peel, quarter, and core pears. Chop pears coarse and in a bowl toss with lemon juice.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.208', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.462');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('943ab5ce-c568-4482-b0c8-38864b56b0ec', 'Meanwhile, combine mayonnaise, lime zest, lime juice, and remaining 1/4 cup basil in a small bowl; set aside.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.298', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.481');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1a5db341-a831-48d7-957c-800343dbe7e3', 'Prepare a grill for medium-high heat or heat a grill pan or cast-iron skillet over medium-high; oil grate or pan. Toss reserved onion rings with 1 Tbsp. oil and remaining 1/4 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper. Cook onion rings until softened and lightly charred, about 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.301', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.481');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3e2552de-5873-4669-ba9a-1e145c538cb9', 'In a dry 3 1/2- to 4-quart heavy saucepan cook 1/3 cup sugar over moderate heat, stirring with a fork, until melted and cook, without stirring, swirling pan, until a golden caramel. Remove pan from heat and carefully add water down side of pan (caramel will steam and harden). Return pan to heat and simmer mixture, stirring, until caramel is dissolved. Add pears, remaining 1/3 cup sugar, cherries, raisins, spices, and salt and simmer, stirring occasionally at beginning of cooking and frequently toward end to prevent sticking, until thickened, about 50 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.211', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.463');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3276bfa9-bc15-42c5-9113-48af922874fc', 'Stir in walnuts and brandy and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Cool mincemeat. Mincemeat may be used immediately but will improve in flavor if kept, covered and chilled, at least 1 day and up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.215', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.463');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('cde6b40a-cef5-4eff-85a5-40591e0be346', 'In a saucepan combine the plums, the lemon juice, and 1/4 cup water and cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes, or until the plums are soft. While the plums are cooking, in a small saucepan combine the sugar and 3/4 cup water, cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved, stir in the kirsch. In a blender or food processor purée the plums with the kirsch syrup. Strain the purée through a fine sieve into a bowl, let it cool, and freeze it in an ice-cream freezer according to the manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.218', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.464');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b485fd08-b704-49cb-aec0-57b551d5558f', '1. In a medium saucepan, combine the strawberries, sugar, and lemon juice. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Transfer to a blender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.222', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.465');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a061ebdd-0a36-41cf-8a3c-c2140699b652', '2. Purée until smooth, strain, and set aside. Store in a sealed container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.225', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.465');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8803e18c-37ec-47a3-af3f-0eaba312bba2', 'Boil chickpeas in water to cover by 2 inches in a 3-quart saucepan, covered, 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let chickpeas stand, covered, 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.23', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.466');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c5de3840-5f92-4748-90fd-8de9e5be354c', 'Drain chickpeas and return to pan. Add water to cover by 4 inches, onion, and thyme and simmer, uncovered, until chickpeas are tender, about 1 1/4 hours, adding salt during last 10 minutes of cooking.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.233', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.467');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ef4618f-032f-49e9-bed5-22f24d6db8e7', 'Drain chickpeas and transfer to a bowl of cold water. Slip skins from chickpeas by rubbing them with your fingers, then drain well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.237', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.467');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f6900e6f-26fa-40e1-9333-a7da96a7e44b', 'Using smoothie or ice crush setting, purée avocado, kale, pineapple, coconut meat, coconut water, lemon juice, matcha, agave, salt, and 1/2 cup ice in a blender until smooth.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.241', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.468');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('19506fa3-a9a9-42d0-9c77-de6d82715157', 'Place the strawberries and the sugar in a large, stainless steel kettle. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Shake the pan to blend the ingredients, reduce the heat so the mixture simmers merrily, and continue cooking until the jam jells medium-firm, shaking the pan occasionally, about 40 minutes.Remove from the heat and sterilize according to jar manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.244', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.468');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f8a5f55-750c-429b-8074-1dee46d24755', 'Cook corn in large pot with boiling salted water until just tender, about 5 minutes. Drain; cool to room temperature. Cut corn kernels from cobs. Transfer corn to large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; toss to blend. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.248', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.469');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d6d7a873-01a3-4e85-8e49-efe7643cb403', 'Cook all beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain; rinse with cold water and drain well. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Pat dry, then wrap in paper towels. Enclose in plastic bag and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.251', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.469');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('36ba9d9b-f165-42a0-a5bd-9f8b4bc49a63', 'Combine beans, tomatoes, onion and basil in serving bowl. Whisk oil, vinegar and sugar in small bowl to blend. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Add dressing to vegetables; toss to coat. Cover; chill at least 1 hour and up to 4 hours, tossing occasionally. Serve salad cold or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.254', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.472');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa2505e7-7c9e-490c-a2e4-cc030dfd07ea', 'Finely chop two thirds of nuts. Coarsely grate celery root in a food processor fitted with medium shredding disk.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.258', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.474');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('29618608-176d-483e-adf8-7cecae39277c', 'Stir together vinegar, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until salt is dissolved, then add celery root, chopped nuts, parsley, and shallot and toss well. Drizzle salad with oil and toss again. Serve sprinkled with remaining pecans.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.261', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.474');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ed3bfe71-5758-4284-b052-c0aff8d8683e', 'Remove leaves and trim stem end of cauliflower, leaving core intact. Place cauliflower core side down on a work surface. Using a large knife, slice cauliflower into four 1/2" "steaks" from center of cauliflower (some florets will break loose; reserve). Finely chop enough loose florets to measure 1/2 cup. Transfer chopped florets to a small bowl and mix with olives, sun-dried tomatoes, 1 tablespoon oil, parsley, and lemon juice. Season relish with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.265', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.475');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6156c753-626d-4735-ad85-936eebcc4a2e', 'Preheat oven to 400°. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large heavy ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Working in 2 batches, cook cauliflower steaks until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side, adding tablespoon oil to pan between batches. Transfer steaks to a large rimmed baking sheet. Reserve skillet. Roast cauliflower until tender, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.269', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.475');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f5b8356-b69e-45c9-b702-8ce5699b4956', 'Meanwhile, return skillet to medium-high heat and add garlic cloves and tomatoes, one cut side down. Cook until tomatoes are browned; turn tomatoes over and transfer skillet to oven with cauliflower. Roast garlic and tomatoes until tender, about 12 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.272', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.476');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('23770524-06da-4fb8-9900-1c57f7eec0fd', 'Transfer garlic, tomatoes, and 1/2 tablespoon oil to a blender; purée until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Divide tomato sauce among plates. Place 1 cauliflower steak on each plate; spoon relish over. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.276', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.477');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ff5aaa1a-42e7-4639-b544-dce7800f8ebc', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.28', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.478');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b197475-8cd6-4d0e-a427-1630f3a98187', 'Place 2 banana pieces in each of 4 dishes. Top with 1 scoop of each sorbet. Spoon over fruit and juices. Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.284', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.479');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('b377e76a-f551-476b-ae35-6974a7914837', 'Cut onion in half crosswise. Slice one-half into 1/4" rings; set aside. Finely chop remaining onion. Pulse chopped onion, garlic, cornmeal, 3/4 cup zucchini, 2 Tbsp. beans, and 2 Tbsp. corn in a food processor until finely chopped, 30–45 seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.287', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e1773b6f-8989-4260-8fac-21b605534d0d', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a large skillet over medium. Add chopped onion mixture and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to soften and thicken, 3–4 minutes. Add remaining 3/4 cup zucchini and cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini begins to soften and become translucent, 3–4 minutes more.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.291', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.48');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('34b2fb32-7bc4-4038-8d08-11a69b922bfc', 'Brush patties all over with oil. Cook, flipping once, until medium brown and toasted, about 7 minutes on each side; add 1 slice cheese to each during last 3 minutes of cooking. Transfer onions and burgers to a plate. Toast buns until golden brown, about 30 seconds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.305', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.482');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c74cabb0-102d-4f3a-a1eb-4650133d311d', 'Place 1 piece lettuce on each bottom bun and top with a burger. Top with onions. Spread 1 Tbsp. basil mayonnaise on each top bun, add smashed avocado, and close sandwiches.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.309', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.482');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b20f26e-e1b5-48bc-bd82-f4eecafce06f', 'Put oven racks in upper and lower thirds of oven and preheat oven to 450F. Halve squash lengthwise, then cut off and discard stem ends. Scoop out seeds and cut squash lengthwise into 3/4-inch-wide wedges. Toss squash with black pepper, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and 2 tablespoons oil in a bowl, then arrange, cut sides down, in 2 large shallow baking pans. Roast squash, switching position of pans halfway through roasting, until squash is tender and undersides of wedges are golden brown, 25 to 35 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.313', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.483');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('235b7029-ed51-44c7-8944-ba3a2f923bb7', 'While squash roasts, mince garlic and mash to a paste with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt. Transfer paste to a small bowl and whisk in lime juice, chile (to taste), cilantro, and remaining 1/4 cup oil until combined. Transfer squash, browned sides up, to a platter and drizzle with vinaigrette.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.316', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.484');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('78644f44-3710-4358-bf93-2e47450cf315', 'In a bowl wash the bulgur in several changes of cold water, letting it settle to the bottom before pouring off most of the water, until the water is clear and drain it in a large fine sieve. Return the bulgur to the bowl, add enough cold water to cover it by 1 inch, and let the bulgur soak for 1 hour.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.32', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.484');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f7aaee79-21c7-4ce8-b4db-11c822aeae04', 'While the bulgur is soaking, in a large bowl stir together the onion, the salt and the allspice and let the mixture stand for 30 minutes. Drain the bulgur in the sieve, pressing hard to extract as much water as possible, add it to the onion mixture with the herbs, the scallion, the lemon juice, the oil, the cucumber, the tomato, and salt and pepper to taste, and toss the salad well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.323', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.485');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7558fd83-9f5e-4bff-baeb-ea2657ec7727', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil until cranberries pop, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Cool. Mix in crystallized ginger. (Can be prepared 3 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.327', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.487');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2b918173-4d2a-4522-a5c6-af7a137d44d8', 'Cook rice according to package directions. Spread out on a rimmed baking sheet; let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.332', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.487');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('85cf864a-5711-452f-903b-a44ea08467ce', 'Meanwhile, toss fennel and onion with 2 tablespoons lime juice in a large bowl and let sit, tossing occasionally, until lime juice is almost entirely absorbed, 10-15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.336', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.488');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fcaf0acf-e1a1-4bb5-a6a7-995a9ba41227', 'Coarsely chop 1/3 cup pecans; finely chop remaining nuts. Cook in olive oil in a small saucepan over medium-low until golden brown, 5-10 minutes. Let cool.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.339', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.489');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5f4a5964-5b4e-4282-bdc7-a9c743df7824', 'Add rice and pecans to fennel mixture along with remaining 1 tablespoon lime juice and toss to combine. Gently fold in cilantro; season with salt and pepper. Serve drizzled with pistachio oil, if desired.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.344', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.49');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb18a2b2-b6ef-4d7c-ac11-e0a54302b766', 'Do ahead: Rice salad (without cilantro) can be chilled up to 1 day. Bring to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.348', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.491');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aea67b54-c02e-40fe-a37c-5cb20d1ec6b4', 'Put the rice and all the vegetables in a large bowl. Drizzle with vinaigrette and use two big forks to combine, fluffing the rice and tossing gently to separate the grains.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.351', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.491');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9786e63c-b585-46c7-b6b4-134fe5815c63', 'Stir in the parsley, taste, and adjust the seasoning or moisten with a little more dressing. Serve at room temperature or refrigerate for up to a day, bringing the salad back to room temperature before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.356', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.492');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ef0c25cd-0121-4b2e-a231-1edc5e77de33', 'Rice Salad, Japanese Style: Use brown or white short-grain rice. Halve the amount of celery and carrot and finely chop them or shred them on a grater. Add 1 cup cubed firm tofu (preferably baked). Instead of the vinaigrette, toss with 1/4 cup or so of Simple Miso Dipping Sauce (made by whisking together 6 tablespoons miso paste, 3/4 cup warm water or sake, 1 teaspoon sugar, 1 tablespoon mirin or honey, 1 tablespoon rice vinegar plus more to taste, and salt to taste). Instead of the parsley, crumble 2 sheets of nori over the rice salad and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons black or white sesame seeds.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.36', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.492');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('103a6288-4779-4053-9bf5-9d5e7acd3986', 'Rice Salad, Mexican Style: Long-grain or medium-grain, white or brown, all work well here. When blending the vinaigrette, add 1 tablespoon chili powder and 2 tablespoons Mexican crema or mayonnaise. Instead of celery and carrot, add 1 cup chopped fresh tomato. Substitute chopped fresh cilantro for the parsley and, at the same time, add 2 chopped hard-cooked eggs and chopped jalapeño chiles if you like. Serve with lime wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.364', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('958fec05-abcf-4614-96c7-9d47580cd36b', 'Rice Salad, Indian Style: Use brown or white basmati rice. When making the vinaigrette, use rice wine vinegar, replace the oil with coconut milk, and add 1 tablespoon curry powder, or more to taste. Instead of the bell pepper, celery, and carrot, add 1/2 cup each cubed cooked potato, cooked cauliflower florets, and green peas (cooked frozen are fine). Substitute cilantro for the parsley.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.368', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.493');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dc11702a-935b-4470-b70f-df0a238b446d', 'Citrus Rice Salad: Use any rice. Instead of red wine vinegar, make the vinaigrette with freshly squeezed citrus juice—choose from lemon, lime, orange, blood orange, tangerine, pink grapefruit, or a combination. Whatever you use, add 2 tablespoons of the grated zest and 1 tablespoon of sugar or honey to the blender. Do not include the scallion or the vegetables. (You might want to use a little less dressing.) Instead of the parsley, use mint if you like. A handful of chopped almonds or pecans make a nice addition.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.372', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8aa6932b-4d13-456f-8ee8-a010fe8f121b', 'Tomato Rice Salad: Use any kind of brown or white rice. When making the vinaigrette, eliminate the vinegar and add 1 medium tomato to the blender. Instead of the scallion and other vegetables, add 2 cups chopped fresh tomato (a mixture of heirloom varieties is nice).Instead of the parsley, use chopped fresh basil or mint, or 1/4 cup chopped fresh chives, chervil, dill, or about a tablespoon of fresh thyme leaves.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.375', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.494');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee7602db-ec2c-4d49-9f7e-22823c6ce4ed', 'Cook wild rice in medium saucepan of boiling salted water 25 minutes. Add white rice to saucepan; cook until all rice is tender, about 15 minutes longer. Drain.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.379', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('02a28148-a731-441b-b216-f2d5d243d4a9', 'Place tea bags in medium bowl. Add 1/2 cup boiling water. Let steep 4 minutes. Discard tea bags. Place mint sprigs in large pitcher; mash with muddler or handle of wooden spoon until slightly bruised. Pour in tea, lemonade, and vodka. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.462', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.502');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('093049c1-9ed1-4c8b-8a43-01bfbde75f77', 'Fill 8 highball glasses with ice. Divide sweet tea among glasses. Garnish with lemon slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.465', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9703b112-047d-40d1-ae6a-769761e2fc25', 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium heat. Add onion, carrot and parsnip; sauté until tender, about 8 minutes. Add mushrooms; sauté until brown, adding 2 to 3 tablespoons water if mixture is dry, about 15 minutes. Stir in apple, raisins, cinnamon stick and orange peel; sauté 5 minutes. Mix in apple juice and cooked rice. Season to taste with salt and pepper. If using as stuffing, spoon mixture loosely into poultry. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead if serving as side dish. Cover and refrigerate. Spoon into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish sprayed with nonstick vegetable oil spray, cover with foil and rewarm in 350°F. oven about 25 minutes.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.383', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7b9bbd2d-1e43-445f-bb10-8a9a8177a707', 'Position rack in top third of oven and preheat to 450°F. Spray large heavy baking sheet with nonstick vegetable oil spray. Combine eggplant, peppers, garlic and oil in large bowl. Toss well. Transfer to prepared sheet. Bake until eggplant is brown and vegetables are tender, stirring every 10 minutes, about 50 minutes. Remove garlic and reserve. Scrape vegetables and all pan juices into bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.387', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.495');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('f458a406-95ad-4035-96d5-3f94b9636b72', 'Combine vinegar, cumin, salt, pepper and cayenne in processor. Peel roasted garlic; add to processor. Puree until smooth. Toss vegetable mixture with 1/4 cup garlic dressing. Cool, tossing occasionally. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill vegetables and remaining dressing separately. Bring to room temperature.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.391', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('001cb41e-2925-4f7c-bdb0-a20668d3f268', 'Mound salad in center of large platter. Surround with pita wedges. Serve, passing remaining dressing and Sesame Spread separately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.395', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d5e345f4-c068-4ac6-90b1-114926905406', 'Beat margarine, sesame seeds and salt to blend in small bowl. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.4', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('674a7afc-6f6f-4766-8493-7088345f18d7', 'Whisk first four ingredients in a large bowl. Add vegetables; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.403', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.496');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('aa174b2f-32f8-437b-b5cd-88e2a8aad281', 'Cook noodles in a large pot of boiling salted water, stirring occasionally, until al dente; drain. Run noodles under cold water to cool them; drain well and add to bowl with vegetables. Add cilantro and scallions; season to taste with salt and pepper. Sprinkle sesame seeds over and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.407', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8078499c-1221-4427-a2cc-b44f439589cc', 'Finely chop 1/2 cup parsley with 1 garlic clove; set parsley mixture aside. Finely chop remaining 2 garlic cloves. Whisk chopped garlic, 4 tablespoons oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt in large bowl to blend. Add mushrooms and toss to coat.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.411', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.497');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4c19c6ed-2e79-44c2-8086-e1febd4962c5', 'Heat remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil in heavy large skillet over high heat. Add mushroom mixture and saut INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('8362ebcb-6062-4d79-bced-e48cffe841ab', 'In a saucepan combine the wine, the sugar, and 1 cup water and bring the mixture to a boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Simmer the syrup for 5 minutes and let it cool. In a blender or food processor purée the grapes with the syrup and strain the purée through a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing hard on the solids. Stir in 1 cup cold water and the lemon juice and chill the mixture, covered, until it is cold. Stir the mixture, transfer it to 2 metal ice cube trays without dividers or a shallow metal bowl, and freeze it, stirring with a fork every 20 to 30 minutes and crushing the large frozen clumps, for 2 to 3 hours, or until it is firm but not frozen solid. Scrape the granita with a fork to lighten the texture and serve it in chilled bowls.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.419', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.498');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('74af9cb5-ff4f-46a3-a266-41f9fb1db5fe', 'Preheat the oven to 450°F.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.423', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.498');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('14431b30-5600-45dd-8a29-f029168bb4a8', 'Toss baby red potatoes with olive oil and kosher salt on large rimmed baking sheet. Place rosemary sprigs alongside the potatoes. Roast until the potatoes are tender and beginning to brown in spots, about 45 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.427', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.498');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ba964202-3412-4bf3-a685-78880c611846', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Place potatoes in 13x9x2-inch baking dish. Add 1/4 cup oil, chopped fresh rosemary, brown sugar, garlic powder, and cayenne pepper to potatoes. Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Brush grill lightly with oil. Place potatoes on grill, spacing about 1 inch apart. Grill until potatoes are tender and slightly charred, turning occasionally, about 10 minutes total. Transfer potatoes to bowl, season to taste with salt and pepper, and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.431', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.499');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ac3678ce-c7af-4afa-892d-17a14096664c', 'Preheat broiler and lightly oil a baking pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.435', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.499');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('db4f9233-0f54-47e0-ab5a-27c06d725c28', 'Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Chop cilantro and in a bowl stir together with remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste. Brush cilantro mixture on both sides of eggplant slices and transfer to baking pan. Broil eggplant 5 to 6 inches from heat until golden and cooked through, about 10 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.438', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.499');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('184c4976-812b-42af-b0cf-ec0d8fc38239', 'Wrap the beets together tightly in foil in 2 batches and roast them in the middle of a preheated 350°F. oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until they are tender. The beets may be roasted 2 days in advance and kept covered and chilled. Unwrap the beets carefully and let them cool until they can be handled. Slip the skins off the beets, cut off the stems, and cut the beets into 1/4-inch pieces. In a large bowl whisk together the vinegars, the sugar, and salt to taste, add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the dressing until it is emulsified. Add the beets to the bowl with two thirds of the mint and toss the salad until it is combined well. Line 4 plates with the lettuce leaves, divide the beet mixture among them, and sprinkle each salad with some of the remaining mint.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.442', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.499');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6b70516a-8ab6-4c99-8d70-186179ecd6ca', 'In a 10- to 12-inch skillet cook celery in oil over moderate heat, stirring, until softened. Add garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.446', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('0a5f3040-62db-4edc-8664-bbcd7489fe93', 'Remove skillet from heat and stir in beans. Mash about one fourth of beans with back of a large spoon and stir in remaining ingredients except topping. Season mixture with salt and pepper. Transfer bean mixture to a 2- to 2 1/2-quart gratin dish or other shallow baking dish and smooth top with a rubber spatula. Gratin may be prepared up to this point 4 hours ahead and chilled, covered.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.45', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('185b8ade-cb17-41d9-a940-001f34301e17', 'In a small bowl with a fork stir together topping ingredients until crumbs are evenly moistened.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.454', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.5');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('9fa25a22-1db4-4e92-ac51-ff9244afb7ec', 'Sprinkle topping over bean mixture and bake in middle of oven 45 minutes, or until bubbling and top is golden brown. Cool gratin 5 minutes before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.458', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.501');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2d29de29-6a89-44cb-8e1c-a6b907014c45', 'Whisk first 3 ingredients in small bowl. Add oil and whisk until well blended. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.786', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.543');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('abf7e373-25f4-47db-b869-49e2ced1c206', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, ginger and garlic and sauté 1 minute. Add all mushrooms and sauté until brown and tender, adding 2 to 3 tablespoons water if mixture is dry, about 10 minutes. Add spinach and green onions and stir until spinach wilts, about 2 minutes. Stir in soy sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl. Serve, passing lemon wedges to squeeze over.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.469', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('a53b1f4f-9333-4515-a40c-fc71cb2fdbc8', 'Whisk vinegar and garlic in small bowl. Gradually whisk in olive oil. Season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.473', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.503');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5aca5907-e2e9-4a3a-bfe3-0059408aa14c', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Place corn, chiles, and bell peppers on grill. Cover and grill until corn kernels are tender and chiles and bell peppers are blackened on all sides, turning frequently, about 5 minutes for corn and 12 minutes for chiles and bell peppers. Transfer vegetables to 2 baking pans. Cover chiles and bell peppers; let stand until cool. Cut corn kernels off cobs; transfer to medium bowl. Peel, seed, and coarsely chop chiles and bell peppers; add to bowl with corn. DO AHEAD: Vinaigrette and vegetables can be made 1 day ahead. Cover separately; chill. Bring vinaigrette to room temperature and rewhisk before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.476', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('599ddeba-c871-41e6-84b6-e7728cb03f95', 'Stir cumin seeds in small dry skillet over medium heat until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Transfer to small bowl; set aside. Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water just until tender when pierced with knife, about 20 minutes. Drain. Rinse under cold water. Drain and cool slightly. Cut potatoes into 1/3- to 1/2-inch-thick slices. Transfer to large bowl. Add grilled vegetables and vinaigrette; toss to coat. Add cumin seeds, green onions, and cilantro and toss. Season generously with salt and pepper. Cover; chill at least 2 hours. DO AHEAD: Can be made 8 hours ahead. Keep refrigerated. Serve chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.48', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12a414f8-7f8f-4b8c-9242-6e6b7162444d', '* Sold at some supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and Latin markets.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.484', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.506');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2de5511f-a88e-4516-82f3-0b0e1c58f590', 'Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain. Refresh under cold water; drain well. Transfer to large bowl. Combine mustard and vinegar in small bowl. Gradually whisk oil. Mix in shallots. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover beans and dressing separately. Refrigerate beans; let dressing stand at room temperature.) Mix dressing and tomatoes into beans. Season to taste with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.488', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('80beb7a5-eb0a-46a2-97db-0acd25c72a7a', 'Whisk first 3 ingredients and 1 cup water in a small bowl until sugar and salt dissolve. Place onion in a jar; pour vinegar mixture over. Let sit at room temperature for 1 hour. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 weeks ahead. Cover and chill. Drain onions before using.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.491', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.507');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3af77ed8-af6e-4bc8-81fe-9487318a249e', 'Pulse two 12-ounce bags fresh (or frozen, thawed) cranberries in a food processor until coarsely chopped. Transfer to a large bowl. Finely grate 2 teaspoons orange zest from 1 of 4 navel oranges; set aside. Using a sharp paring knife, remove peel and white pith from oranges. Working over a medium bowl, cut between membranes to release orange segments. Coarsely chop segments; add to cranberries. Stir 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup minced red onion, 1/4 cup chopped fresh mint, 1 tablespoon minced peeled ginger, and reserved zest into cranberry mixture. Cover; let stand at room temperature for 2 hours. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.494', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.508');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c7a7a23c-aef8-4358-aeff-b0c3dfbb0552', 'Combine all ingredients in processor. Puree until very smooth. Divide mixture among 8 ice pop molds (each about 1/4 to 1/3 cup capacity). Cover and freeze until firm, at least 4 hours and up to 5 days.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.498', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2491a9a7-58a9-4b83-a6aa-4d724a0cce40', 'Heat the grill to medium-high.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.502', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('05821da4-e9ae-429c-b763-0f6f85837b95', 'In a large bowl, toss the string beans with the olive oil and garlic. Let the beans rest for 10 minutes or so, then place the beans on a large square of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Fold the foil over the beans and fold down the ends of the foil twice. Place the foil packet on the grill, seam side up, and grill for 25 to 30 minutes. Let the beans cool for a few minutes, then combine them in a roomy bowl with the arugula, lemon zest, and salt and pepper to taste, tossing until the arugula is wilted, 2 to 3 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.505', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.509');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('c252943c-a3e0-4474-84eb-737f269e932d', 'In a high-speed blender, combine the almond milk, sweet potato, orange, date, vanilla, salt, and cinnamon and blend until smooth. Adjust the sweetness to your desired taste by adding honey or more Medjool dates. Blend in about 1/2 cup ice to chill before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.509', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.51');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('76ad0d2f-6e87-4de9-a8a9-cba2161b40de', 'Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover; chill.)', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.513', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.511');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('61556de6-ed02-48da-9752-5011fc6bd811', 'Simmer potatoes in salted cold water to cover by 1 inch in a saucepan until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. When cool enough to handle, cut each potato into eighths.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.517', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.512');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('192c5466-9dc3-4e8b-af5f-9d9796dfa6a6', 'While potatoes are cooking, trim fennel stalks flush with bulb, discarding stalks, and chop enough fronds to measure 2 tablespoons. Core bulb and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.52', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.512');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('e1d97974-02bc-4eec-a419-670359f04d22', 'Whisk together vinegar, oil, and salt and pepper to taste in a large bowl. Add warm potatoes, fennel bulb and fronds, and bell pepper, then toss well. Season with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.524', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.513');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b0c6a43-b355-470d-a423-5187b5ce0f92', 'Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart heavy saucepan and simmer, covered, over moderately high heat until fruit is tender, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.527', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.514');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('63fa5770-b5c1-4ffe-9e82-ebe8c2af51f4', 'Transfer to a bowl and cool, about 15 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.53', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.514');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('12972f52-ff10-4513-8f85-66c7b8043f0c', 'Combine spinach leaves, endive and radishes in large bowl. Place vinegar in small bowl. Gradually mix in oil. Add sugar and orange peel. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour dressing over salad and toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.534', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.515');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('759fac41-a350-40f0-9a3a-8eb57b666cc7', 'Mound salad on large platter. Top with orange and avocados slices.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.537', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.515');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('439239bd-ad81-4e1c-b4a8-840f112a0225', 'In a saucepan bring 2 cups water to a boil with the sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved, add tea bags, and let steep, covered for 15 minutes. Discard tea bags.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.541', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('fb7e12ed-60ec-4fd5-a498-83d29b876d45', 'With an ice pick or a skewer, test the three eyes of the coconut to find the weakest one and pierce it to make a hole. Drain the liquid and reserve it. Bake the coconut in a preheated 400°F. oven for 15 minutes, break it with a hammer, and remove the flesh from the shell, levering it out carefully with the point of a strong knife. Cut the coconut meat into small pieces and in a blender grind it in small batches, transferring it as it is ground to a bowl. Return the ground coconut to the blender.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.545', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.516');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09178e49-7299-4c5c-a4c0-042c2b3e14e4', 'Strain the reserved coconut liquid through a fine sieve into a large measure and add enough water to measure 2 cups liquid. In a saucepan bring the liquid to a boil, add it to the ground coconut, and blend the mixture for 1 minute. Let the coconut mixture cool, strain it through a large sieve lined with a double thickness of cheesecloth into a bowl, pressing hard on the solids, and squeeze the coconut in the cheesecloth to extract as much of the milk as possible.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.548', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.519');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('344fe8bb-c43b-4e87-89c7-ce8b41f13e0a', 'Stir the tea into the coconut milk with the food coloring, if using, and chill the mixture, covered until it is cold. Freeze the mixture in an ice cream freezer according the manufacturer''s instructions and store the sorbet in freezer containers. The sorbet may be made 5 days in advance and kept frozen, covered. let sorbet stand in the refrigerator for 30 minutes or microwave it at 30% power for 1 minute to soften slightly before serving.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.552', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.519');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ee06b232-03b6-42e3-8e32-a8410c80772e', 'In a small bowl, whisk together vinegars, soy sauce, garlic, ginger root, and sesame oil. Add canola or vegetable oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk until emulsified. Season dressing with salt and pepper.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.556', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.52');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3b9e7509-0209-469a-a5fe-90c2b2770393', 'In a small dry skillet toast sesame seeds over moderate heat, stirring, until golden and transfer to a small bowl.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.56', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.52');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('844cc5b7-97c3-4fa5-9ea0-9dce1fd7a52e', 'In a large saucepan of boiling salted water, cook beans until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Transfer beans to a colander and rinse under cold water. Drain beans well.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.563', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.521');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6af07e30-ba89-4dc6-9285-f93fd7884478', 'In a large bowl, combine beans, scallions, sesame seeds, and dressing and toss well. Serve salad chilled or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.567', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.521');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4d60566a-4d72-43b2-8f2c-44184be73f20', 'Pour grapefruit juice, vodka, and grenadine into tall glass; stir to blend. Fill with ice. Garnish with twist and serve.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.57', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.522');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('4221a8f5-5511-4d5a-8e35-88c6aa12d5e4', 'Heat a dry small heavy skillet over moderately low heat until hot, about 3 minutes, then toast fennel seeds, stirring constantly, until lightly browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer seeds to a work surface and cool 10 minutes. Coarsely crush seeds using bottom of skillet, then stir together with salt and sprinkle over watermelon. Serve with lime wedges.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.574', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.522');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('d105c86e-99b4-46c7-a9fd-e08be3c67a28', 'Heat oil in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until it shimmers, then cook cumin, coriander, ginger, red-pepper flakes, and cinnamon stick, stirring constantly, until fragrant and a shade darker, about 2 minutes.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.578', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.523');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('796e9c62-7f13-4c75-b06b-2c72905c8071', 'Add tomatoes with juices, breaking up tomatoes with a spoon, then add chickpeas. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes. Discard cinnamon stick.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.581', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.523');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('607a479a-fd5b-4b0b-a93b-ce88cd7d15c8', 'Stir in parsley and mint. Serve warm or at room temperature.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.585', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.524');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('6f921535-bef3-4d73-8849-ec10e8c31ee9', 'In a small saucepan boil the water with the sugar, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved, simmer the mixture for 5 minutes, and remove the pan from the heat. Let the syrup cool to room temperature and chill it, covered, until it is cold. In a blender purée the mango with the pineapple juice, the cream of coconut, the lime juice, the zest, and the syrup until the mixture is smooth. Freeze the mixture in an ice-cream freezer according to the manufacturer''s instructions.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.589', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.524');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('dd98b48e-eb7d-4da1-a67c-2c50496fb945', 'Heat oil in a 1-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then fry shallots in 3 batches, stirring frequently and being careful not to burn, until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer shallots as browned with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain. (Shallots will crisp as they cool.) Transfer 3 tablespoons shallot oil from pan to a cup for dressing and reserve remainder for another use.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.593', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.525');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('09c2bba3-2e66-474e-971f-775a4790ca19', 'Whisk together lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a large bowl, then add shallot oil in a slow stream, whisking until combined. Add prunes, escarole, half of shallots, and salt to taste, then toss well to coat. Sprinkle with remaining shallots.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.596', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.525');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('2839d80f-9135-4fb0-971c-01539b4f400a', 'Combine first 8 ingredients. Whisk pomegranate molasses and oil in small bowl. Season with salt and pepper; toss.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.6', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.526');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5ea7026d-ae32-48cb-8286-acadac372a89', 'Toss together all ingredients in a serving bowl. Serve immediately.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.603', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.526');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('7f7275dc-ea81-4b2c-977d-264dad6396e4', 'Depending upon seasonal availability, choose to make either the winter pancakes or the summer pancakes: To make the winter pancakes, place the red onion in a bowl. With a pastry brush, dust the slices thoroughly with some of the cornstarch. Pull gently to separate the crescent shapes, dusting again with a bit more cornstarch. Add the carrot and sweet potato peels to the bowl and dust with the remaining cornstarch. Toss to distribute the vegetables evenly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.607', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.527');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('253904ca-2dcd-4010-875e-1117bfdbfd56', 'To make the summer pancakes, with a pastry brush, dust the bitter melon slices thoroughly with some of the cornstarch, then place them in a bowl. Dust the zucchini slices and kabocha peels in a similar manner and add them to the bowl; toss to distribute evenly. Dust the shredded shiso leaves and chives with cornstarch and add them to the bowl; toss again to distribute evenly.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.611', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.527');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('316c08aa-9fc7-41a2-bfcf-ba10b7f6aac3', 'Make the batter just before frying: Place the ice cubes in a small bowl with half of the water. Sift the cake flour over the water and stir to mix slightly; there should still be lumps. If needed, add water, a few drops at a time, until the batter is the consistency of a thin pancake batter.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.614', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.528');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('13c5f138-4bf7-4e37-8977-cb2dcff1b6fd', 'Pour the vegetable oil to a depth of 1 1/2 inches into a small wok or small, deep skillet. Add the sesame oil and heat slowly. Check the temperature with an unvarnished long wooden chopstick (or a bamboo skewer). Small bubbles will form around the tip when the oil is about 350°F. Wait for about 45 seconds longer to allow the temperature to rise a bit more—to about 370°F—and then test the oil temperature with a few drops of batter. If they sink slightly, then rise to the surface and puff quickly but do not color, the oil is ready. You may need to fry the pancakes in batches to avoid crowding them in the pan. Preheat the oven to 200°F for keeping the cooked pancakes warm.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.618', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.528');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('1f7627a5-095e-44c8-9cbc-4aea36ced602', 'Spoon a bit of the batter over the cornstarch-dusted vegetables and toss lightly to coat the vegetables with the batter. Dip a large spoon or ladle into the hot oil. Place one-eighth of the vegetable mixture in the bowl of the oil-dipped spoon. Carefully tilt the spoon to slide the pancake into the hot oil, aiming to make a disk about 2 inches in diameter. The batter and cornstarch act as "glue" to keep the vegetable slivers together. Repeat to make more pancakes, being careful not to crowd the pan.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.621', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.529');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('ecfdceaa-6dfe-4488-b08e-b68dbd4f0033', 'DO AHEAD: Nuts can be soaked 2 days ahead; cover. Nut milk can be made 3 days ahead; keep chilled.', '2023-06-12 17:13:36.34', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.766');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('3f800191-b66e-4f7c-b483-0b1f5dac02c2', 'Most important, refrain from touching the pancakes for a full 30 seconds after you place them in the oil. It will seem like an eternity, but gaman will yield the best results. If wayward bits are strewn at the edges of your pan, carefully pick them up and place them on top of the still-moist pancake batter in the center. (Skill with long chopsticks will be well rewarded, though a long-handled fine-mesh skimmer can scoop beneath as well.) If the center of the pancake is very dry, dip the wayward bits in some fresh batter before "gluing" them in place. When the batter in the center of the disk seems barely moist, carefully invert the pancake.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.625', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.53');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('bca8ef63-b4cb-4702-b935-3a53837eecdc', 'After flipping, allow the pancakes to fry undisturbed for about 1 minute, or until crisp. Using cooking chopsticks or a skimmer, remove the pancakes from the oil and place them on a rack set over a baking sheet to drain. If frying in batches, place the baking sheet in the oven to keep the fried pancakes warm. Use the skimmer to clear the oil of batter bits between batches.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.629', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.53');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('91051f51-4792-4e42-8453-085d5d162f72', 'When all of the pancakes are fried, transfer them to paper towels to absorb any additional surface oil.', '2023-06-12 17:13:32.633', '2023-06-13 00:13:20.531');
INSERT INTO "Direction" ("id", "name", "createdAt", "updatedAt") VALUES ('5b5f0fca-97b4-4fa7-b16b-ed063fe073c8', 'Grease four (5-inch) individual, loose-bottomed,
